review_text: Amazing oysters! Super fresh and juicy, probably the best I ve had in Vancouver. The staff were friendly and gave good recommendations on food and drinks, definitely would come again.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: As a Chef, I must say this is the best place for oysters and seafood in Vancouver, no comparison. Best Happy Hour in Vancouver Freshest Oysters from their own company Amazing staff and fun atmosphere There is a reason everyone suggests this place

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: My first time here tonight and I must say awesome oysters pkace, even better than Rodney s actually. Service was great and the guy - Andrew at the bar shucking all the oysters were such a pro. Andrew was awesome with his service, friendliness and we also had great conversations! Will be back for happy hour some time!

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Special thanks to Hanna and Andrew for the excellent service. PLUS all the staff are very helpful and professional ! We enjoyed very much !

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Service was slightly lacking but the food made up for it! Visited as part of an epic holiday celebration with my friend! Had the lobster, ciopinni, Cesar salad, one of each type of oyster, geoduck and uni sashimi, as well as the seared scallops and pork belly ! Lobster was doused in buttery garlicky decadence    ciopinni had tons of seafood and wonderful grilled sourdough      geoduck and uni sashimi were transcendent (first time I ve ever seen sashimi sharing the same menu as Pacific Northwest dishes   Salad has a great anchovy flavour in the dressing   oysters tasted briny and very fresh    seared scallops and pork belly were a little on the sweet side but paired well with the bitter radicchio and roasted cauliflower Looking forward to including this restaurant as part of my yearly epic seafood dinner celebration with my friend!

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Oysters are delicious. Service is really good. Truffle fries are lack of truffe flavour tho.....

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Great service, fresh seafood. We enjoyed their happy hour (1.75 per shuck for featured) fresh oysters, paella, steamed mussels&clam. I couldnt drink that day, so I must come back to enjoy the oysters with some sparkling rose. Bar seats werent bad!

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: My family ate here on 28 May. Service was first class. Food was wonderfully good. Tall tables and chairs. My wife and I were not young. So we had a bit of difficulty getting up and down the bar height chairs. But it was ok. A great experience. Ambience was nice but affected by a customer on another table who kept coughing throughout his stay. Hope he recovered well.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Recommended by a friend who is a regular. All the dishes were superb. Couldn t stop slurping on the oysters. The fish taco and the chowder were delish. All the staff were friendly and responsive.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Great service and really good oysters! Came with a friend who comes here often and can say hands down the best most freshest oysters I ve ever had.  Must try is the oyster shooter with the gold flake. Very good. Aside from that their regular menu/cooked food was very good as well.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Happily ran into this place and got in at the beginning of happy hour 3pm-6pm (if you do try to go, try to get here before 3 as a line starts to form). Although we tried the oysters which were good, we had never had them before and discovered we aren t oyster fans lol! After that we ordered the fish tacos, muscles and clams and the pork belly with scallops   so good highly recommend you try any of those dishes and pair it with a white wine

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Happy hours from 2 to 6pm. Good variety of items to eat and drink, fair price. Oysters are fresh and delicious. We had good service.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Amazing oyster shop. I come here often :)

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: It is rare that my family 100% agreed this restaurant worth out 5 stars vote! Warn & friendly service makes east coast folks like us feel right at home. We arrived in time for happy hours.. Boss Gibson, Olympia & Kusshi are on special, while all of them are fresh, Kusshi was really the one that shines, with delicates & clean flavour.. we had to order a second round. Kids enjoy great fish & chips as well as a fresh Geoduck, Prawn & Octopus pokebowl.. I also had an amazing crab cake to round out the night. Great to be in Vancouver

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: We were a group of 5 and it was our first visit. Everyone enjoyed their meals very much. Mussels were amazing. Oysters in the half shell were delicious. Scallops & Pork Belly was perfect. Side of potatoes with roe on top was very tasty. And you must get the bread. Service was great, very attentive.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Started lining up at 2:50 in time for the 3pm happy hour and there was quite a long line after us. The servers were very friendly and food came fairly quickly. The sablefish collars was my absolute favourite. The paella wasnt as good as the reviews made it out to be sadly but still good. Overall definitely would come back again and Im not normally a huge seafood lover!

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: This is a great place for happy hour, which is currently from 12pm-6pm I believe!!! They have $1.5 oysters, which is definitely worth it not to mention a good variety of items to choose for. In terms of value and quality, this is one of my favourite happy hour joints! This is worth the drive for all your seafood lovers, looking for a good deal! I d say must haves are oysters, sablefish kama, parm fries and fish tacos. Only thing I didn t like were the cocktail prawns... to small and wasn t as fresh as I d like them to be.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Really had a great happy hour meal. Got there for 3pm and there was plenty of space but still pretty busy for a 3pm restaurant. The Fanny bay oysters were beautifully served and I would recommend having it with the lemon, tabasco and migonette together. The tuna tartar was absolutely amazing, the tuna, cucumber and avocado work so well together and are perfectly serve on the crisp.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Good variety of oysters. Their truffle fries are supreme, even their steak is done properly. Clam chowder was thick and creamy with chunky ingredients every spoonful. Will be back for more!

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Really nice bar, close to our hotel and the Whitecap stadium. Past by on numerous walks, had to give it a try. Food was outstanding, cocktails were spot on. It you dont eat raw oysters, why would go (idiots at the table next to us!). We did a plate of oysters and the Sablefish Collars. These deserve a Michelin rating.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Quick service with amazing foods and pricing during happy hour. The lobster roll was fresh and delicious. The oysters were delicious

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: The best seafood platter Ive ever eaten in quite sometime. The food, service and atmosphere were terrific!!!

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: My mom and I never eat seafood but we ended up ordering 2 dozen oysters and the fried chili oysters twice and the brussle sprouts   she absolutely loved it and said we wanted to come back here tomorrow. This place has the best staff and a really cool marble tabletop by the shucking bar where my mom entertained herself the whole time. Everything was so fresh and tasty. I m sure everyone would have a good time here! I think my mom has now been converted into a seafood fan

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Awesome oysters and great, friendly service! Nice hangout place with good food and drinks! Good happy hour! Theyre specialty Oyster is the best that we tried! Also, our server Alexa was awesome! I was a newbie at oysters and she helped explain everything and made the experience so much better! The bartender guy was so sweet as well! We ordered the crab legs and those were to die for!

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: My second time trying oysters, not a bad experience but still not used to the texture yet. But they were fresh, I like them better with the limon juice and horseradish. The clam chowder was good but not the best Ive tasted. The surf & turf were my favourite and can be shared. Service was good. We will definitely fine here again.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: I had a blessed enjoying the seasonal prawn, raw oysters, clam and mussels. Highly recommend this place.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Fantastic seafood. Lots of Oysters to choose from. Very fresh. Super friendly wait staff. Every entree was very well done. The mussels and fish were very fresh and flavourful. Not rubbery at all. The prices were fair for the quality of food being offered. Well worth the price.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Great place with the freshest seafood and focused on oysters. The service was outstanding.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Excellent. I highly recommend. Crab cake excellent. Grilled oysters were wicked good, so good I ordered a second round of them. Fanny Bay raw oysters were good. Brussel sprouts were very good. Beer/wine excellent. Services was friendly/quick/excellent. Reserved a table on  open table  and we were seated right away when we arrived.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Every time I come here the food never disappoints. The mussels are so big and so fresh, oysters are amazing, and best of all the staff are so friendly. A must come to place if your in Vancouver.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: I love coming here for happy hour. The fish tacos are delicious and they have a good selection of oysters and happy hour oysters do not disappoint. The service here is wonderful as staff let keep you updated with a last call during happy hour. They made a mistake with my oyster order but just ended up not charging me for the extras I didnt order. I come here every time I visit Vancouver!

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: It s a nice restaurant, since it s in the city you need to pay for street parking. We went specifically for the happy hour oysters. We recommend just getting the regular oysters and not the premium because they weren t that sweet. Also got the lobster roll which was good but I thought I was getting 2 buns but instead got 2 half buns. The service was so fast we were only there for 30 minutes since seating to paying! Parking: There s only metered street parking.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Came for a friends birthday dinner. Service was AMAZING. Hands down never experienced better service anywhere in Vancouver. The food was great. Its so insane that this place didnt get an actual michlin star. Those guys are dropping the ball. To those who might be scared to get raw oysters-- Im someone extremely sensitive to any contamination to the extent that the same oysters that gives my friends mild stomach discomfort would land me a fever for a week. I ate 1.5 dozen here and absolutely nothing happened. Can vouch with 300% confidence   I hope to be back soon!

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: It is located near bc place. People who want to try different kind of oysters or shells I highly recommend this place. They serve not only oysters but also crabs, lobsters and pasta. However, from 5:00 p.m the restaurant can be easily full of people so visitors would better to book before they visit. People who want to save money, better to visit in HAPPY HOUR time.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Friendly upscale seafood, bar/restaurant with lots of variety. Good for a date night or special occasion. The food was above average, and so was the service and atmosphere.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Fantastic value! Went at happy hour and devoured the fresh oysters, and the fried oysters were amazing! The clams were so flavourful, hubby drank up the whole bowl of sauce lol! Service was incredible too, great experience and will be back for more!

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Oh yay! Everything was sooooo fresh and delicious. Great cocktails and excellent service

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: This restaurant is not too far from JW Marriot Hotel, where we have stayed a  few days in Vancouver. This is not a big restaurant, so we have made an advance booking. When we arrived, many people were waiting to be seated. We ordered one dozen oysters with 3 different sizes and tastes, and then followed with another dozen. We also ordered other seafood dishes and wines. Oysters were reasonably priced with $3.50 each and extremely fresh. All the dishes were very delicious. The restaurant was fully packed with customers and gave an exciting atmosphere.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Great oyster bar with a lot of happy hour specials. Make sure you check the time because the value is pretty decent. It s not a super high-end place but more of a casual drinking/oyster bar. There was a small shop inside where you can buy some of the products and cans or also in the freezer.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Yum! Was my first time here for happy hour and was pleasantly surprised. Got here around 2:40 and got a spot for 4. Ordered a round of drinks (I got the spicy Paloma, it had a delicious salt rim) and ordered our happy hour noms! The sun seeker oysters were super fresh and delicious with hot sauce. The tuna tartare was beautifully presented with 8 chips. We enjoyed the mixed mussels and clams in white wine broth. The bread was a little hard to cut and break up though  still delicious since we wanted to soak up the sauce. The brussel sprouts were perfectly seasoned, and the truffle fries were great as well. Will definitely go again!

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: We had a fabulous experience here. Everything is fresh, tasty and seasonal. We arrived around 7pm on a Sunday and it wasnt too busy and service was attentive. An hour later every table was filled. Book a reservation to avoid disappointment. Worth a visit.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: You wont find better oysters anywhere else in Vancouver unless you are farming them yourself. Our oysters were expertly shucked by Hana and they came with all the proper accoutrements. We also had a smoked salmon carapaccio with pickled kelp that I still dream of to this day.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Happy Hour Oysters were $1.75, service was great, had to wait for 45 mins, but the host was really nice. Loves their Truffled fries, you can add this on to the Clams and Mussels. Would def go back again.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Always a good time. Love coming here for oysters of course. Seems like all employees are friendly. It is busy and loud all the time but I think it adds to the atmosphere. Lobster rolls were good too :))

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Came here for happy hour. Easy to make a reservation! They have many different kinds of oysters but only one is available for the happy hour special. Still delicious nonetheless. Oyster shooters were delicious as well. Service was great and accommodating.

place_name: Fanny Bay Oyster Bar & Shellfish Market
review_text: Absolutely loved this place. As soon as we walked in Saturday morning we were greeted by an easy going young guy that had the right combination of service and entertainment, with a laid back casualness that you never get in Toronto; it was refreshing. His oyster recommendations were as spot-on as the food. I was reluctant to try oysters again at first because I got food poisoning last time I had them in Toronto. Im happy I tried them here because I was absolutely blown away. The scallops were beyond incredible, as were the home cut fries and the oyster po boy sandwich-best po boy Ive had yet! I will definitely be coming back here every time I am in Vancouver.

Came here for my birthday. Everything s perfect. Our server Emily was incredibly nice and attentive. She offered a complimentary dessert for my birthday which was unexpected. I d highly recommend anyone come here for special occasions or just about any occasion. You ll enjoy the atmosphere and food and more!

The best alaskan king crab I ve ever had. Quite expensive but worth every dollar. Other members of my party got the salmon and the Shrimp and lobster roll, which were both amazing as well. Outdoor seating was accompanied by a great view of the harbour, and some nice heaters for a chilly day. Would 100% recommend.
First time here and really enjoyed it. The room is gorgeous and the staff couldn t be any more friendly or responsive. That would be enough but then roll in excellent food and this is a 5 out of 5!!

First time at this place, came here for dinner before the improv show was on. We only had about 45 minutes. Ordered a whole meal and good appys with drinks and our waitress made sure we would be out of there before the show! Loved the patio and fish n chips was very good!  Oysters, and mussels also yummy.

Great spot in the heart of Island! Oysters on happy hours were really good, service was great and everyone was friendly. The prawn shrimp cocktail was a big no, they really need to get rid of that dish and figure something else out. We didnt order anything after that one but beer and oysters during happy hour Cant go wrong.

Decided to spend the day in Granville Island, lots to see, eat and do here. It was around 4pm and we were down for Happy Hour, walked past this place earlier in the day and noticed their menu! We were promptly greeted by 2 hostess and asked if we preferred in or out, well it was a beautiful day in Vancouver so we wanted out, plus the view of the harbor was quite beautiful. Here s the HH Menu 3-5pm Sips House wine red/white Draught Beer Highballs Bites Oysters Prawns Mussels Halibut bites Prawn Cocktail Caesar Salad Mains Wild Salmon Seafood Linguini Striploin We were still full from lunch so we opted for the Oysters and Mussels both absolutely delicious the mussels were Salt Spring Island mussels served with chorizo and creamed leeks all this needed was a beautiful piece of crusty bread to soak everything up! Oysters was refreshing, light briny taste with a hint sweetness!

Great atmosphere, really good service, and delicious food! Happy hour ends at 5pm. Really enjoyed their mussels, and seafood linguini. However, the chowder was okay. Finally, our waiter Ryan did a great job.

Nice place great food with original ideas + great execution. Once 1st order was taken there was prompt service aswell with a nice taster prawn treat for all of us. Drinks then appys & kids meals then a little break no wait the dinners.       Thx ! Kid friendly if there good at sittn down.

Great atmosphere and views from the restaurant. Super nice service and environment overall. Food was amazing and presented gorgeously, and no wait time to be seated without a reservation, even on a Friday night!

Really good food and not super busy! (Tuesday at 4pm) I ordered the garlic bread as an appetizer and you get 4 long pieces. Then I ordered the Salmon from the happy hour menu with cooked prawns on the side. Not the biggest fan of the sauce they used (I typically like my fish a bit more plain), but it was not poured heavily and soaked into the Salmon which I appreciated, was just a bit on top of the Salmon and on the bottom of the dish (as seen in the photo) . You are able to order a side of Salmon here as an addition to your meal which a different restaurant said was not possible. I like that the option is available here. Presentation was excellent and friendly staff members. Bathroom is a bit small. I would definitely come back!

Came during happy hour. Happy hour has decent/fresh menu selections for food, and the drink selection is okay. This, coupled with a relaxed and friendly atmosphere, passes the vibe check.  Great place for food and drink(s) after a hard days work.
Great atmosphere sitting outside on a nice sunny summer day at Granville Island, food is reasonably priced for a hang out spot for locals and tourists. Perfect spot to chill at anytime of the day.
Celebrated my last two birthdays here! Well worth the drive from Surrey; free parking after 8pm!

The food was fresh and delicious. The ingredients choices compliment each other. I ordered the scallops. The candied bacon really enhanced the flavor of the scallops. The presentation was excellent and big thanks to my waitress whose name I had forgotten for providing an excellent service and for letting me and my friend meet the owner, Steve. I gave her a max tip for that reason.

Had an outstanding meal there this past Friday for 4 of us.  We met the owner earlier and he suggested we check it out and he was bang on!  The location, food and hospitality were second to none.  We had their seafood and tomahawk platter, which easily fed all of us.  The maple walnut prawns were amazing to start as was the wine list and desserts.  Thanks to the team for making it a special night, we will be back when in Vancouver next. Dietary restrictions: They were excellent in recommending gluten free options as well

First time with my family and was greeted with a friendly smile. Our waiter David was very friendly, polite, well mannered and has this genuine feeling he is very attentive and He made us feel welcome. The place has a very nice atmosphere. Washroom is very clean. Our food was good, we ordered fish and chips and lobster roll. The clam chowder was just Ok and the garlic bread. OVER ALL VERY GOOD EXPERIENCE BECAUSE OF DAVID.
Spectacular views while sipping local lager and enjoying halibut fish and chips. Marty our server was very nice and efficient. We sat on the porch and enjoyed the afternoon!

Wonderful place on the Granville Island. Our server was a kind, friendly and very helpful person, helped us pick the wonderful option for dinner. Delicious Oysters, the west coast oysters are creamier than the east coast s. We also ordered Wild Halibut and Tuna Poke Bowl, both were absolutely delicious. Do recommend this place.

Very attentive service and knowledgeable. We were a little unfamiliar with the oysters and ordered a set which the first one may have been off so didn t want to eat the rest but it may just have been a stronger flavour than Australian Oysters but the owner was happy to not charge. Food came out quickly and apart from the one off oyster issue was great.
David was far and away the best server we had in Vancouver. Fish and chips were perfect as was the setting. Was hesitant of being a tourist trap but it defied expectations
Good food, love the patio area, they have heating which is really good especially if youre a cold person but still want to enjoy sitting in the patio. Highly recommend, food was great too.

If youre looking for a great happy hour in Vancouver, head over to Granville Island and check this place out! Their all day menu looks awesome, but their happy hour menu is top notch.  Service is amazing, and the food is incredible! Its definitely an upscale restaurant, but worth every penny.
Perfect place to enjoy fresh oysters and good wine...Thanks Ben for the great service!

Delicious food , great service, best view. We ordered fish & chips. The fish was fresh & perfectly cooked and fries were fresh out of fryier. Heylie( if not mistaken) was our server She was super friendly and made sure all our needs met. Definetely visit again this place!

Loved the location of the restaurant. Great ambiance and natural lighting. Our waitress, Carolyne, was really pleasant with a very calming personality. Everything tasted great especially the salmon! Highly recommend this restaurant.
Six people, overlooking the marina and boats on a sunny evening. We all had a different dish and we were all so happy! Excellent food, service and atmosphere!

Amazing food, even the potatoes were well cooked. Also the staffs here are pretty friendly, came to check if anything good regularly. The staff also is knowledgeable about the place, such as parking, new events. I will definitely recommend friends to come here.

Love this spot. David is my favourite server and honestly he never steers me wrong. The halibut and chips is amazing. If you re going to eat fried food like that, better make sure it s top notch. Shout out to Hubert on the bar, he s also a great dude and very very entertaining.

My family and I came here last Sunday for the first time. I think this has become our favorite restaurant in Granville Island! The food, ambiance, and service was phenomenal. David was our server. He is one of the best servers Ive had at any restaurant weve been to. He is very knowledgeable about the menu, very helpful, very patient with my two young kids, and hilarious! Definitely coming back again to see David & enjoy the amazing food! Also, the view is spectacular. The rest of the servers were all very friendly as well :) Awesome experience definitely coming back!!!

4.5 stars! Great service and food. Really enjoyed the seafood hot pot and halibut cake from the dine out menu. Presentation of the halibut cake was ok but it tastes fabulous. The tartar sauce was just right not too sweet to help compliment the savoury cake. The seafood hot pot has a tad of spiciness to it and gave it an extra kick. The seafood chowder and seafood linguine from the all day menu were also very palatable. The seafood chowder is also slightly spicy which I thoroughly enjoyed but it might not be for everyone, especially those who do not enjoy spicy food. Only the cheesecake dessert from the dine out menu was a let down. Cheesecake itself is already quite heavy and combining with a thick chocolate fudge topping is over the top. *Been back here a few times already. We would go to adventure with kids and come over for lunch. Kid friendly restaurant with family washroom. Hailbut fish and chips is one of our favourites. The kids love the chicken steps and cod bites.

This was our first time and we can t wait to go back. The prawn appy was unique and delicious. Incredible fish and chips with tarragon tartar sauce. Fries  crispy and flavourful! The service was excellent- doting, but professional.
Great seafood restaurants Prices of the foods are relatively high The quality is nice I suggest fish and chips meal The waiters are friendly The atmosphere is very nice and friendly

Great spot for happy hour! The happy hour prices are pretty good, otherwise its definitely on the spendy side. The staff was very friendly. We came 15 minutes before the end of happy hour and they seated us and took our order quickly so we could still get the great deal. The outdoor seating was right by the water, which was fantastic! I had the clam chowder, which was just ok.

I LOVE THEIR HAPPY HOUR! The seafood was soooo fresh and we ordered ROUNDS of oysters, mussels and cocktail shrimps! Highly recommend dropping by here if you re in Granville during their happy hour! Not only do you beat their dinner rush but you get to enjoy their fresh seafood at a discounted price!!

Delicious and fresh food with great outdoor seating. I stumbled upon this gem when I was wandering around Granville Island and decided to stop for appetizers and drinks. I m sure glad we decided to stop because the seafood was fresh, the service was quick, and the harbor views were a nice touch to a relaxing Sunday morning.

1. Great server. Theyre very helpful! 2. Great shipyard view when you sit outside. 3. I ordered lobster and it was very good quality (and sweet). My wife and I totally satisfied. 4. The fish and chips as a side dish are pretty good too. Salty and tender. 5. There is bike rack, so its cyclist friendly! Parking: They have bike rack.

I am not alone in loving happy hour. The smaller portions are just right. The maple prawns are such an interesting blend of sweet, spicy and nutty. The lingcod is deep fried but not greasy and so moist. Can t go wrong. Wore warm clothes so I could sit outside and enjoy the view. Each table has ceiling heater. Attentive server, will definitely return

Absolutely fantastic food, the Halibut and fries are among the best fish and chips that I have had. The burgers are fantastic too. Nice atmosphere and the staff are very friendly. Definitely worth a visit.

It was a scorching day in Vancouver and all the predictable beer and burger places around Granville Market were packed. We managed to find Vancouver Fish Company at a lunchtime lull- lucky us! First, there were perfect refreshments for such a hot day, like the Pear-ple Rain, with Empress gin, pear, elderberry, and bubbly. The best riff on a French 75 ever! My favorite was the Jeffrey, though, which was kind of like an extra juicy Pimms cup and I had several to verify that it was indeed my favorite. The Smokin Dobbs is a delicious mezcal Old Fashioned and definitely worth a try if you like mezcal. We started with a shared plate of the crab and shrimp fritters which were very nicely done without too much seasoning or breading to let the seafood really shine. Yum! I had scallops that came with polenta and kale, this amazing pancetta reduction, and topped with a little pecorino. I savored every delicious bite! My husbands salmon with Israeli couscous was equally well-prepared and disappeared quickly! Our waiter was super- he was funny and even though he was busy, he never seemed rushed or in a hurry and was always right there when we needed him, like magic.

Spent happy hour at the bar with Chris and it was a great call. Solid chowder, fish & chips and oysters. But more importantly he was so attentive and helpful. We re visiting for a few days and he gave so many great tips and suggestions. He was even so gracious to let us use his zoom pass for the Richmond night market. We re visiting for a special occasion and Chris really started our time in Vancouver on the right foot

We thoroughly enjoyed the signature fish and chips and also the chef recommended lobster bacon sandwich. They were to die for! The attentive and friendly waiter was a big plus for this famous eatery, he even recommended us some other much try restaurants. Thumbs up to the chef and the waiter , we appreciate the food and the dinning experience!

With a Halal food preference for our entire group, I was really happy that Pierre was able to suggest and help us with menu choices and also worked with the kitchen to ensure our dishes were in line with our requirements. Excellent service and great ambiance on the quayside covered patio complete with heaters. Went there on a rainy day and was warm and cozy out on the patio. Excellent selection of prawns, lobsters and my personal favourite mussels. Will keep coming back!

Delicious meal! Great menu and compliments to the chef because our meal was fantastic. Pierre was a great server and we really enjoyed speaking with him. He was funny, kind and took care of anything we needed. Great anniversary dinner! Hope to be back soon.

Great lunch yesterday!! We put our trust in our server who  started us off with Maple Walnut Prawns and a bottle of Chardonnay. The yuzu mayo on the prawns was incredible. Course two consisted of Halibut and Chips and a Tuna Poke Bowl. The tuna melted in my mouth and the halibut was perfectly cooked with fresh, beautifully seasoned fries. Finished off with a delicious Rhubarb and Apple Crumble that was crunchy and not too sweet. All in all, a wonderful experience!!
We ate there twice during our trip in Canada and everything was perfect! Everyone was nice and kind the whole time and the food was simply delicious! 10 out of 10!

Shout out to Kayley and Caroline for making our short visit here so memorable. Just stayed for a couple glasses of wine and a beer, but the atmosphere was lovely overlooking the marina. What made it stand out was the service though. Kayley took special care to seat us where we wanted to be, even though the area wasnt technically open and Caroline was an absolute professional waiting on us; charming, friendly and very knowledgeable to boot. Great place.

The service was great, and the food was very good. Drinks were also very good and our seating was also very enjoyable. We sat by the docks, looking at the boats and water. It was very good price for the food you get. Great place to take your date with someone special. Id recommend this place and like to thank the server, and the chef.

Great place to have dinner! It was definitely worth what we paid. Service was good, Cole was great! My friends and I shared oysters. Usually I dont order them but they were super fresh. got fish and chips and they were the biggest Ive seen. So good. My friends had the seafood linguine and the trio. We were sat on the padio and  enjoyed the sun. Would definitely come here again to try everything else.

Fantastic fin ng experience, the food quality is above the par, fine dining environment, friendly service and reasonable pricing. The scallop is fresh, well seared, and very juicy inside.  Vegetable are well cooked as well. The brunch menu is pretty solid as well. Good amount of choices and affordable. Will come back again.
First time visiting, the happy hour menu was pretty good! Had the salad and fish, service was fast and interior very spacious with a great view. Would definitely drop by again

The ambiance, service, and food are 10/10! I ordered the fish (haddock) and chips, so delicious! The fish was moist and fresh. It was as if they somehow steamed the haddock and then wrapped it in fried batter, lol. Glad I came during my short time in Vancouver!
One of the best restaurants in and around Vancouver. Great atmosphere, amazing food, great service. The owner is very helpful and friendly. Compared to downtown the prices are very competitive.
Great environment. Garlic bread was bomb. I ordered the scallops and risotto and it was pretty mid. My date ordered seafood linguini and she said it was really good.
Nice place to have quick bite. Service was fast and fish and chips was tasty with cold beer.

A little pricey. But, honestly, seemed worth it. Did not expect that much garlic bread! Which was awesome. The Bison Tartare was delicious, especially with the mustard on the side. Fresh oysters were wonderful and FAT. I had the Salmon which was tasty as you might expect a salmon to be. My partner had the burger and it also tasted fine. Fries may have been better with an aioli rather than just ketchup. The service was exceptional. It seemed every table had their own server which I feel made it more personable rather than subtly noticing your server giving another table a different experience. Great choice in that strategy! It was noticed and appreciated. The white house wine is delicious. Like crisp apple. Loved it! And, location right on the pier to smell the water outside. Lovely decor and lighting. Also a bar counter seating section was available which was nice to see for those stopping for a quick drink. Thanks for the experience!!
The lobster here was the best I ve ever had and I ve had a few. Lol Nicely done!! I highly recommend this place to eat here..
Food was delicious and happy hour prices were definitely worth it! Oysters were very fresh and the mussels were very good. Would come again next time Im in Vancouver!
Definitely a favourite. Good value for money. Best oysters in town. Must try their lobster sandwich. They offer 50% Off for bottled wine on Tuesday & Wednesday
Good food and great atmosphere. Lovely view.
We can recommend the mussles from the Happy Hour menu between 3-5 pm. Also, beer   is $5 at that time.
Absolutely love their happy hour! It s a great place to stop and have a snack while you re exploring Granville Island.

The restaurant is at a great location with great food!  Theres a large patio area that overlooks the harbour and great to people-watch too.  The waiter we had was very attentive and friendly - is that too much to ask? I had the seafood platter with the shrimp, salmon & scallops grilled to perfection.  The tuna & the crab legs were both tender and the veggies were a nice bonus.  We were there in the late afternoon with the setting sun so the atmosphere was very memorable.  Id definitely come back again.

We visited the Fish Co on Saturday evening. We didnt have a reservation, but they made sure we had a great booth. We ordered the spot prawn special, and one of the seafood platters to share. Everything was fresh, delicious, and beautifully prepared. Hubert went above and beyond. He was helpful, friendly and hilarious, and made such a special night for us on the last night of our trip before we had to head back east.

Lovely patient server. I havent had fish and chips that good since I was a child; wed go to Lumbermans Arch back in the 60s and have them there. The batter was not heavy, nor greasy, nice, and light, done right   Fries nice salted and crispy Wheelchair accessibility: Double doors and wide paths through dining room.
Great service, awesome view and amazing food. Definitely recommend getting a spot on the patio and trying the food out. Will definitely come back when I am in Vancouver again.

We came all the way from Regina and were so excited to try some delicious seafood in Vancouver. The Vancouver Fish Company did not disappoint! The have amazing happy hour deals (the Maple Walnut Prawns were amazing)! There is a beautiful view from the deck and if you have kids, there are non fish options for them aswell! Highly recommend! Kid-friendliness: Kids menu with non fish options!
Cole was absolutely outstanding... best server I have ever experienced. 10 Stars. We closed it down and he recommended The Marquis....perfect The 204 Boys

David was one of the most remarkable servers I have ever experienced. We had a celebration of life lunch and David was so thoughtful and sensitive to my families needs. He gave us space, made us laugh, and made our experience incredibly memorable. The food was delicious and Oceanwise! We will be back to see David and Mark, the GM. Thank you so much for your kindness and empathy.
We came to this place for the oysters and other small snacks. Oysters were phenomenal. The ambience was on the fancier side. Great place for a date!

The seafood eater in our group, who is landlocked for 50 weeks each year, felt like hed gone to nirvana. Shrimp cocktail with nice size shrimp. West coast oysters a bit on small side, but he suckedem down lickety splickety. Bowl of clam chowder -- same. But please dont bring it all out at the same time. It was clearly for one person, and I confirmed this. If soup is served hot, it must be eaten first.  Make two trips to the table so the diner isnt sitting with 3 plates of food in front of them. (That said, our server was friendly and efficient.) Another in our party ordered the lobster and grilled cheese and pronounced it delicious. Another ordered the fish and chips. Excellent beer battered. You can get 1 or 2 fish. Get 2 if youre really hungry. We washed this all down with a refreshing pitcher of white sangria. And the view! Lovely, right on dock looking at the boats. Fun place.
Excellent service, fantastic food and great selection of beer. Atmosphere is great, wide open and comfortable. Will be a return customer, if youre on Granville Island, be sure to visit!

Delicious food and a great location.  The waiter also gave us tips on other not to miss Vancouver food. This was our first dinner of our trip and a great introduction to Vancouver. Beautiful restaurant with great food too.
the food was alright, they could definitely do better with the ingredients they have available, the service was good and attentive, the location is great just wish they made better food

Great place, delicious fish and chips and great waiters. Ours, Courtney, was awesome. She really went above and beyond. She was quick, but also took the time to chat with us. I really enjoyed the view on the patio. Will be back!

Awesome food, liked the French fries very much. I ate the burger, beef and fillers was nice, the bread was a little too dry for me.  I like it soft, perhaps for others, it would be great.  Overall ambience was great especially sitting at the deck.  You should visit soon.
Lovely, lovely little spot with a great menu, good food and friendly staff. Go for Happy Hour.

When looking for some good fish and chips in the area I stumbled upon Vancouver Fish Company.  This place was quite busy even for a late lunch. The staff was very friendly and helped me choose something out of my wheelhouse.  I was torn between the scallops and the sablefish as Ive never tried that fish before but I was quite pleased with my order!!   Sourced locally off of one of the indigenous islands, Haida Gwaii, this fish was an absolute treat to eat.  And to top it off it was served on a wonderful display of, to put it in non foodie cuisine lingo, potato leek soup. For those not so adventurous, the halibut fish and chips that my wife ordered was some of the best Ive ever eaten as well as the cod bites that my 5 year old loved! The tartar sauce was the best tartar sauce Ive ever had to the point where I asked the waitress for the recipe, to which she was able to give me the ingredients and I still swear theres a hint of coconut somewhere in the recipe.   If you have the opportunity, dont hesitate to stop in.  It wasnt the least expensive meal but it was well worth the treat!

What an amazing, memorable place to meet an old friend after many years! This place was recommended to me by my friend and I  am thankful that he did. Sitting out on the expansive deck with all of the sailboats in the harbor is the perfect setting to enjoy reconnecting with a friend. The heaters ensure that you wont get cold and being in the open space reduces the chances of Covid19. The oysters are perfectly shucked and served with lemon, vinaigrette and Tabasco. Ordering a dozen for two people is a must! Believe me they go down so easily. The Hangover Poutine was just the right size for one person and had the perfect mix of pan cooked gravy with cheese and meat! The service here was prompt,  knowledgeable and friendly. I highly recommend this place and look forward to coming back. If you agree with me, like this review.

The service is fast, the staff are friendly and the food is good. I really enjoyed their fish and chips. The only thing is the foods are pricy. Other than that, its a nice place to eat with a view of the water.

Wow! My girlfriend and I were blown away by the mussels and fish n chips. The food was delicious but our meal was made by our funny and charismatic server, David. He had us laughing for our whole meal and really made the experience stand out. Would come back!
This place had delicious happy hours. Go here during happy hours and have some oysters and walk around to check out the gift shops - best way to spend a weekend!
Food was very delicious and service was quite good as well.  The setting was a bit noisy, but partitions have been put up between booths and tables to minimize risk of exposure to coronavirus.
My favourite place for happy hour. Food is really good and very good deals on beer. Service is great. The restaurant is very nice located in Granville Island. the views are fantastic.
We had mussels, shrimp pasta and seafood bowl. All were very tasty! Highly recommended when you visit Granville Island

Spent the night for my birthday here, and I was absolutely blown away by the attentiveness of our server Ryan. The food was incredible, from the appetizers to our dessert selection we had. The meal flowed beautifully and really showcased the talent of the chefs they have here. I most definitely would recommend coming here for the food, wine selection, and experience. Hats off to all the staff here who made my experience and birthday one I ll remember for years to come. Thank you!!!
Great place for drinks & fresh seafood. Staff is friendly and courteous. Great vibe and bartender Rohat who came new from Turkey is a great guy. Made us some amazing custom drinks.

It is a higher end place, so the prices reflect that. I ordered the wild salmon and was extremely happy with it. I ordered the fish off the kids menu, which is well priced for children, for my son and he enjoyed it thoroughly. The last two things I ordered was the garlic bread which was a high quality bread, though I wish it had more garlic flavour, and the truffle fries off the happy hour menu which were great. I highly recommend this place.

Great food selection and good service too, price on a higher side but it is worth it. Service was great too, although some new staffs perhaps need some additional trainings but senior staffs are doing fantastic jobs.
The food and service here it s awesome.
Get the mussels, theyre the best. Overall a great place to dine! I would totally come back again.
Excellent fish and chips halibut

Fabulous menu and reasonable prices for a huge serving. My photos do not do justice as we were almost halfway thru when I remembered to take pictures. As soon as the food were served, we dove into it! We had the Seafood Linguini (not in photo as it was gone in a heartbeat), Salmon and Halibut Fish  n  Chips and the Salmon Club. It was a hot day and we were starving that we opted to dine inside rather than wait for a seating to be available on their patio. Nevertheless, the food was scrumptious!! Staff are friendly and seems to be enjoying what they do, fast service, and amazing experience. Will definitely be back here. Highly recommended when in Granville Island!
Delicious and tasty food, friendly staff, good vibe and one of epic restaurant that everyone should try. Highly recommended.
Very good food and our waiter was excellent. The outdoor dining has a view of the harbor and boat slips. It is a little pricy though.
A treat to be sure given location, ingredients and service! Every item we had was great! If you have your mind on your wallet, look for their travel zoo promotion!

I attended a dinner event here last night and everything was exceptional. The environment is warm and welcoming, with moody ambiance. The service is spectacular, and the food was delicious. I will definitely be back. Every server is well versed with the menu and has extensive wine knowledge. This location is beautiful as it s right on the water. Highly recommend!!

Dave is awesome. Great genuine service and advice. Nice location on Granville Island with a good liquor selection. Oysters were great, Halibut perfectly cooked. So many other menu items to try for a future visit. Presentation of those left wanting more. See you guys again, thanks!

My boyfriend and I had a delicious dinner at Vancouver Fish Company for my birthday. The service was excellent, the food delicious, and the view from the patio the cherry on top. The restaurant is a pricy one, so I would mainly recommend it for special occasions. We will come again!
Great restaurant in a great place. The view is amazing. Peaceful. The staffs are very friendly and nice. Services are fast. And the seafood is goooood !!

Had a delicious dinner the other evening. Daniella, our waitress, was so lovely! The fish and chips were fantastic and the Alaskan king crab legs were delicious and huge (obviously haha). The accompaniments to the crab were a bit lacklustre but we were too busy enjoying the crab and fish! Garlic bread and red wine sangria were also great. We sat out on the patio with the sun setting - it was a great atmosphere with the twinkle lights etc. I would recommend to anyone visiting from out of town looking for some fresh and delicious seafood.

First time coming here for dim sum. We came at 10:30 to avoid the crowds. Service was excellent. Our teapot was topped up multiple times and finished dishes were cleared away  throughout the meal. Very good quality food. Underground parking is a bonus.

Very tasty dimsum. Highly recommend the sticky rice wrapped in lotus leaf- the best I ve ever had of this kind. The rice roll with chinese donuts, shumai, shrimp dumplings were all yummy. Pricey though, even with the lunch menu. The staff was friendly and the space was clean.
Wow! What a tasty dining experience. The service was friendly and fast, and the food was amazing. We will definitely be back here.

One of the best dim sum I had in Vancouver. You cant go wrong with most of the dishes of dim sum. It gets busy on weekend so you better reserve ahead to guarantee your spot. Overall I definitely recommend.
Good food and very good/friendly service. Bathrooms are even decently clean. Would definitely go there again.

Food came out quick.. definitely over ordered as it was just me and my wife but we wanted to try everything.  The snow pea tips were amazing!! The dim sum was really good.  Only thing we didnt like was the shrimp egg roll and shrimp wonton (forgot the actual name on the menu).  The mango pudding was ok... Lacked mango flavor.  Would recommend

A trusted and classic place for dim sum! They have a wide range of food and they are great for all sorts of family gatherings. If you re looking for unique dishes, order the giant sesame ball dessert before your visit!
Amazing dim sum.  The best radish cakes and barbeque buns Ive had outside of Taiwan and Hong Kong.   The corn-shaped mango pudding was unique.

Best dimsum.   amazing options for food. The place is packed with Asians/ Chinese people, that explains the quality. Hopefully some western guests find this little charm near Chinatown area. We ordered a big meal but we finished them all... they all tasted very delicious

Sun Sui Wah is a popular dim sum spot in  Vancouver, BC that has been frequented by @sethrogen & @davidchang. After eating here, it s easy to see why this place is so loved. It was probably one of the best dim sum meals I ve had outside of Asia @eatswithedith on IG Ordered: 1. Shrimp rice noodle roll 2. Beef rice noodle roll 3. Radish cake 4. Siu mai ( 5. Tofu skin roll ( 6. Steamed short ribs (     ) 7. Chicken feet (    ) 8. Sticky rice (   ) not pictured Every dish was so authentic and delicious, it brought me back to my travels in Hong Kong   I absolutely loved everything we ordered (maybe except the chicken feet but that s my personal preference  ). The stand out dish was the radish cake because the texture was perfection.. I usually order egg tarts & other sweet treats at the end but I was so full from the other dishes that I didn t have space for it :( Tips: -call in early in the morning to make a reservation, they pick up the phone! -portion sizes are largeee -get the sweet soy sauce as it adds so much flavor to the dishes -add hot sauce & Chinese mustard on the side, they are the perfect dipping sauces! -go with a group of friends so you can try everything Price: $120 CAD/meal for group of 3

First time here, was a bit confused where it was but found it when asked a store nearby but service was fast and the people working was so nice too, busy but clean. The food was sooo good, favourite was the sesame balls, shrimp dumpling and the rice rolls, I m not sure if they do it with everyone but got a coupon too which was nice and unexpected and will come back. 10/10 will come back
Very good seafood restaurant.  One of the servers was a bit rude but you have to take whomever you get in this economy, plus she was Asian

I would give 10 stars if I could.  Not only did I receive fantastic dim sum, one of the servers managed to reconnect me with my long lost sister.  I had no idea I had one.  Now I am eternally grateful.

We had a great experience here! Mistakenly, we didn t make a reservation but they managed to squeeze us in! Because it is seafood specialized we opted to get a lot of shrimp dishes which were so delicious. Another favourite was the BBQ pork buns. We would come back!
My favourite dim sum in Vancouver, always so fresh and delicious. Staff was friendly and our food was quick to the table! Weekends are very busy, make sure to leave time before lunch closes at 3pm.
Great place for Dim Sum on Main Street.  The food is good and typical HK style food and  Service . Highly recommended to reserve your seat before going.  Walk in diner in sounds bad choice.
I had not been for many years but this place did not disappoint in any way.  Superlative service. Delightful food.  A lively atmosphere.  Go. Have fun and great food.

Went for takeout dimsum today. Pick up procedure organized. Temperature check done before walking into the back area to make payment by card. Then ushered back to the entrance to wait until food was brought back. The restaurant was fairly busy but definitely adjusted to accommodate for social distancing. Servers were wearing shields mostly. Overall quality is very good. Most items come in 4 which is nice as some restaurants will sometimes have items in 3 which makes it difficult to share. With the high turnover rate of food everything that was ordered was clearly newly made and fresh. Things that were expected to be crunchy was crunchy, nothing soggy.
Been here twice now and the food has been great! Their menu has pictures of dishes that help you decide what to order.

Some of the best dimsum Ive had in the West! We ordered almost everything on the dim sum menu and our favorites were the chicken feet, shrimp spring rolls, and the bbq was quite good too! Great service and atmosphere on top of the delicious food. Check it out if youre in the neighborhood! Located on the 2nd floor and they have parking in the basement Parking: Free parking in the basement

I dont give 5 Stars easily, but this was a good one.  Parking was great, but its in the back, so drive around.   Elevator comes right to their entrance.  I usually go to the Richmond location but this time I stayed in Vancouver so had to check this one out.  It was a bit empty, but also a weekday.  They have a large screen TV just like the Richmond location.   Wife and I actually like the Richmond location layout better and we sort of made up our mind that the Richmond location was better until the food came.  Staff was friendly right as we were sitting down, but then got a bit slow until ordering. We got our standard order of king crab and this one was just a little over 9lb.  Kids dont eat seafood so we had to order them the sizzling beef which they loved.  The crab was cooked in two ways and we ordered the same styles as the other location for a true comparison.   Last time was 8lb, but this one extra lb made a huge difference in the legs.  We didnt get the fried rice as we could never finish with it.  Got a bottle of white wine as usual.   But its a bit expensive comparing to if you were to buy it at a store direct. The entire meal was most excellent and we couldnt finish the body, but also expected for the size.  We actually finished everything else.  Also gave the corn juice a try.  It was interesting, thats all Ill say about that.  Both style of the crab was cooked perfectly and seasoning did not take away the crab meat natural flavor.  This is now new spot for king crab when visiting for sure!
Dim sum is expensive, but dinner is very reasonable. The food is tasty, there is a small parking lot downstairs, if you are early, otherwise, street parking.

We celebrated my mother s 75th birthday here with a large group, and Wallace was such a pleasure to work with to get that set up! He and his team were so easy to work with and accommodated all of our requests throughout the planning and execution of the 10-course dinner. Upon Wallace s recommendation, we also switched up a fish dish in the 10-course meal for two dishes of ling cod done two ways, and they were both very delicious! We were so impressed how all the vegetables were cooked to perfection in each dish as sometimes they can be too chewy or underdone. He also brought out an entire set of kid s dinnerwear for our toddler to be able to enjoy the dinner. Big thanks to Wallace and his team for all of their hard work and pleasant service! We d definitely plan another dinner here again in the future.

The food here is great! I love their durian rice balls, that are very well made. The best thing about this place is the high ceilings, that absorb all the sound from the guests, so it doesnt feel crowded here, and is not noisy.

This place is very creative with their dishes, food tasted good, but what impressed me the most was the service; incredible attentive and professional; they looked very experienced and worked like a clock, so smoothly. Very polite, wishing this restaurant many more years of success.
Delicious food and attentive staff!
Slightly pricier but the food and staffs are nice! Definitely make a reservation for this place!
One of the best dim sum restaurants in town! Everything tasted very good. A bit pricy, rather higher end place  usually reserved for special occasions.

An extremely popular restaurant in Vancouver east. Chicly decorated - spot and colour changing lights, huge decorative circle on central ceiling, pretty patterned carpet, and wine adorned walls. Courteous servers, including captain and manager; and attentive service. Food is fantastic, especially the deep fried baby pigeon which is widely recognized as the best of town - tender, juicy, and tasty. We come to this restaurant from time to time as it continually creates novel delicacies and offers delicious complimentary dessert after dinner. To know it better, welcome to watch my video entitled  Sun Sui Wah Seafood Restaurant  under my name  Cindy Amimer .
First time at Sun Sui Wah, and it was a good experience. Everything tasted very good except the taro squares. Service was good and everything was clean and neat.

Couple of new dishes such as the Lychee flavored stuffed shrimp. A globule of cheese in maybe canned lychee and wrapped in shrimp meat. Food colouring soaker in the bread makes it look like lychees. However the shrimp filled crab claws are far better. It is difficult to find Tofu Dessert from a restaurant since I usually got to Go Yuen Kee. Due to Covid, it hasnt been available. Every time I go to Sun Sui Wah, I miss out somehow; except this time.

Probably one of the most memorable experiences at a din sum restaurant simply because they did one thing for me: They refilled my ice water without me asking them to. No dim sum restaurant has ever done that for me Food was great, quick service and you never  had to wait long to get someone to attend to your needs. Every single dish tasted amazing. A little pricer compared to other dim sun places, but oh well :P
Nice food, reasonable price and good service. Special price for soft shell small crabs and some other special dishes.
Busy but not super crowded, takes reservations. Great quality food. Bonus underground parking.

One of the best places to get dim sum. Super efficient service and the place is always packed so if youre going during peak hours, its best to make a reservation or you could be waiting for up to an hour sometimes. Wheelchair accessibility: Elevator access from the street and from the underground parking

Great food, service and the price is just right. We usually order Siu Mai, Lo Mai Gai, Chinese doughnut and spareibs.The ambiance, design and layout is wow. This is also my first time having a Chinese doughnut with sweet soy and the portions are bigger than what I am used to see, and I highly recommend it. I will come back for more.
Delicious food with excellent service!

This place is phenomenal!! The food is absolutely delightful and the service leaves nothing to be desired, literally being at your beck and call for anything you need. Super friendly staff and gorgeous atmosphere. One of the best places Ive visited in Vancouver! I also highly recommend the delicious sparkly and sweet drinks made of either strawberry, orange, lime or kiwi! (At the awesome price of 2.95)

Excellent. Ordered through UberEats. We had the pan fried crispy noodles with seafood/pork as well as the beef with black bean sauce. Both dishes are enough to make two people full and both were good options off the dinner menu.
Typical Hong Kong style Tim Sum. Inexpensive and delicious!
Foods are very good and peoples are very nice there! Highly recommended!
Nice place for weekend brunch, tea and dim sum are always best choices. Will try dinner later
Always a great experience at SSW.
I ve been to a lot of dim sum places and this is by far the best. Everything here is SO GOOD. I have no desire to go to any other dim sum place again.
Sun Sui Wah is consistently the best dim sum in Vancouver. We come at least once or twice a month and bring our out of town guests. The experience is always great and service is super fast.
Our server Betty was excellent! So was the food! Make a reservation if you don t want to wait!

Tried dim sum here for the first time & was very happy with all the dishes. Our favorites were the Rice rolls with Chinese donut & pork floss, which were freshly fried & crispy and the Steamed egg yolk buns which were not too sweet & runny on the inside. The least favorite was the famous deep fried squid...the batter was weirdly sweet. Its a bit on the expensive side but worth it! Also make a booking ahead.
Price is appropriate for the quality of food and service.
My family s Top 1 dim sum and seafood restaurant in Vancouver, we comes 2-3 times per week on average! Recommend!
Awesome. You can order Peking duck on food delivery services, no pre-ordering required. My dinner was cooked within 30 minutes, tasty as expected
An oldie but goodie - one of the best dim sum places in BC. Tip: come early to avoid long wait.
LOVE IT!! my to go dimsum place. Have to try their honey garlic short rib!
Fabulous Dim Sum, ordered Peking duck as well; terrific service.. very, very busy on Sundays.. but well worth the effort

There was a bit of a wait to be seated (18 min) even though we had a reservation. However, the food more than made up for it, as it was probably the best-tasting dim sum weve had. The first dish that arrived, sesame balls, was the best weve ever had, and several other dishes followed that pattern. You cant go wrong here! Wheelchair accessibility: There is a wheelchair-accessible entrance and an elevator.
Best Dim-sum

This is a solid Dim Sum place. Quality ingredients and great flavor. They don t serve dim sum at night so be sure to come for lunch. Service is nice and fast. Yes, you ll need to wave them down and yes, they might not give you a service with a smile, but that s normal, they re just busy with stuff.

The absolute best Chinese restaurant for dim sum, dinner and celebrations. My family has been coming here on a weekly basis and celebrated every big milestone for the last 20+ years. Service is top  and even when my grandparents were in their last months, we continued to order take out so they could still enjoy their favourite restaurant from home.
Best dim sum place weve been in. We had to wait 30 minutes to get seated. Definitely worth the wait. Everything was delicious!

Some of the better dim sum Ive had, although I dont have a lot of experience. Great service. Very clean. A little pricey but worth it. They have free parking underground, you can access via the back alley.
Amazing & tentative staffs.  Food came out quickly & delicious.  Highly recommend making reservation.
Delicious food, great service and great price.
Quick service. Good food. Portion is big! Ordered 2 bowls of the hot and sour soup and didn t expect it to be more than enough for 4ppl.
Delicious! Great service, beautiful room. Amazing food and drinks.
Delicious and fresh Chinese seafood restaurant. Re commended for locals and travelers.  Reservation recommended.
The service and the dim sum we had were incredible.
Excellent service  comfortable environment , food is tasty and fresh! absolutely my best choice!
Great food, always a great experience. Arrive early if you dont want to wait on line.

Service was great! did not get any chicken feet nor tendon this time as we had people in from out of the country who might not have appreciated the food but great selection and they had a sesame bubble which looked like a very impressive desert.  will be back soon but always a mainstay when out of towners are looking for asian food.
Great dim sum, freshly squeezed orange juice was very good. Their mango dessert tasted great and I really liked the artistic shape.

Excellent food and service, long term customer over 20years, my favorite dim sum is still the traditional dishes. I have a hard time choosing a favorite dish, stewed beef tendon & tripe is a comfort food. My usual bill is large. Thanks to Seth Rogen & David Chang boost the restaurant business 3x busier after airing on Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner.
Ive only been here for Dim Sum, but it was first rate.

Excellent Dim Sum. Good selection and reasonable price. Manager Wallace and a few long time captains with exceptional good service. Dinner dishes is good but a bit over priced. We love this restaurant and will highest recommended

Had my first dim sum experience here and it set my standards very high    I love their steamed egg yolk buns and deep fried shrimp wrapped in sea weed. Everything tasted so good! Will definitely return when I m in the area
Good spot for dim sum - make sure you make a reservation! It s busy!
One of the best Dim Sums I ve ever eaten. I ve gone here like 30-40 times now haha

A large Chinese restaurant that has its own parking garage underground. My first time here today and I was part of a 7-person table for dim sum. We ordered dishes we wanted and they are made fresh to order. Everything was delicious! Its no wonder they are so popular and there is a constant queue at the door! Wheelchair accessibility: Theres an elevator access
Food was amazing.  Theres always a wait for dim sum but it was well worth it.  Will try their other location in Richmond next time.
The food was fresh and delicious. Service was okay.

Ive not been there for a while. Their food always have been great and consistent. They are not the fanciest Chinese restaurant but the decor is up to date.  Bright and roomy. Good service too. Now the most important part of a restaurant, food. They serve the traditional Cantonese fare. I grew up with it and I would say it is pretty good. It doesnt have any fancy dishes. If you are new to Chinese cuisine, it will be an excellent point to start.
Food was great and portions were pretty big! You should consider sharing one meal with two people! Was was open after hours so that s a plus !
Best dim sum in Vancouver for seafood lovers! This place is a must try.
A private room definitely brings in the best of the service and food. Our group totally enjoyed it.
Great dim sum and dinner! Family comes here regularly. Large restaurant and fast service.

if you love dim sum this is the place to go.  I ate at Sun Sui Wah when the owner opened his restaurant just up the street at a smaller venue.  i then went to Richmond when he opened the restaurant there and finally now on this main street location. The dim sum is always great for lunch, they are very busy so reservations is a must.  If you do not like making reservation then earlier the better or expect a very long wait time. I love their duck in noodle soup for dim sum, their deep fried shrimp rolls, their dim sum menu is extensive so I recommend a good look through and I am sure you will find something you will enjoy. Their dinners are generally very expensive so be prepared for that.  However their quality of food for dinner is well worth it.
Happy thanksgiving
Seafood galore! No complaints here, preparation and taste is top-notch.
A good spot to eat! Super busy at times though, so make a reservation in advance.
Their chowmein is really good. Dim sum is a must! Food
Went with a big group, ordered half the menu, everything was great.
Very delicious! I always have a great experience at dim sum here at Sun Sui Wah.
Best make reservations on weekends! It was packed! Probably 1 of our top 5 places to go only for Dim Sum.
Always the best Peking duck and lobster steamed rice

I revisit this restaurant after 1 year and 10 moths. They tweet that renew their dim sum menu. so I want to visit after I vaxxed. ordered around $200. and it was perfect. we were about 7 people. it was enough volume for table. and they also changed the cook style for some dim sum. and of course, it was much better.  Hope you guys can try again. they do check body temperature and limited per table. you must let them know how many of you guys. and you need to call back about extra member so they can book you for bigger or smaller table. happy dim sum.
Lobster at this place. Was here for a birthday dinner food was decent
The service was good on Sunday noon, and it wasnt overly busy.
Really good dim sum. The service was pretty good for a Chinese restaurant.

All right. Why 5? I havent lived in Van for over 10 years now so having a get together with friends and their kids, we needed to both fill our food cravings and have a place large enough to seat so many. We were seated in a room with other small tables. Thank goodness so the kiddies could run around a bit, but hopefully it wasnt too bad of an experience for others there (were pretty sure there were a few dates that Saturday morning). The server was always pleasant, and was quick and attentive. Honestly, he probably made the experience a 5, as often, the service in Chinese restaurants are sub par from Western culture but almost expected. He was really ok it! And the food. Oh, man, the food. We over ordered, of course, but every single dish was just delicious. Dumplings were plump and full, came in a timely manner, fresh veggies....it was just a great experience for me coming back so I had to give them a 5. Recommend!
Good food, great atmosphere, and kids friendly Parking: Free parking in their parking garage Food : 5/5 |
review_translated_text: Food

review_text: Great Guangdong style restaurant, but little bit pricey
One of the best dimsum restaurants in BC. Truffle dumplings are awesome! Waiting time is long though, but worth the wait. Definitely come back!!

Hands down, best fish and chips Ive ever had in my life. We got the halibut and chips - fish tasted so fresh, was flaky in the inside and had a great exterior crunch. I must say though, the chips (i.e. fries), was the star of the dish for me - they were cooked to perfection. Crunchy on the outside and fluffy on the inside, every single one of them. Service was quick and the patio atmosphere with a good view just makes this place that much better. Its about a 5min walk from Granville Island. 10000000% would recommend this place to anyone that loves good food.

The tuna sandwich was okay, but the Halibut and Chips were amazing!! Meaty with light crispy batter that melts in your mouth.. Highly recommend the fish & chips!! Nice small outdoor spot by the docks across from Granville Island. Sandwich was a 3/5 Halibut was 7/5

To be concise.. yes, I would recommend. Pro: delicious. Good portions. Very friendly staff (exceptional customer service) Con: parking is difficult. No indoor or covered seating. We tried the Cod fish and chips. Excellent batter and the fries were delicious. Tatar sauce was rich and satisfying. Coleslaw was underwhelming and slightly boring. We also had the Oyster  Po Boy  sandwich. The flavour was amazing and unique. Highly recommend. Overall, great service and exciting sandwich menu. Fish and chips were above par. I wished there were some covered seating as you re completely exposed to the elements. Of note: walking distance to Granville Island! Also, expect to wait to be served during peak hours.

Amazing!!! Wanted fish and chips and I could not have been more pleased. Best I ve ever had. Staff was great and you can see them cutting up the fish to order so couldn t be fresher. Do not hesitate to visit.

Spectacular fish and chips and other delicacies (fish tacos and burgers) at this modest shack near Granville Island. The cod is fresh and super tasty, perfectly cooked! The chips (French fries) are excellent, the tuna taco is worth a trip. With CAD 10 per person you eat like a king. Best food in a long time! The service is super friendly. The accommodation is a bit rustic but hey  you can take the goodies out and eat it in your own castle!

Super tasty Fish & Chips! I went a couple of times and it was  amazing, the Halibut and the Salmon were delicious  . I also tried the Tuna Sandwich, super tasty with the wasabi mayo. The only downside was, that in one of my visits they made a mistake on my order and instead of trying to fix it they were really rude.

The perfect way to end your day visiting Granville Island. This fish and chips shack is worth the walk over from the main market area. The staff here is super friendly and the food is cooked to order. We got the cod fish and chips basket, and it tasted so fresh and high quality! The portions here are huge so honestly one plate is big enough to share between two people. The dish also comes with an amazing sesame tasting slaw on the side. Don t skip this place!

The captain of our zodiac boat trip recommended Go Fish! for lunch and told us that it was one of the best places to get fish and chips. He was right. Its basically a shack that you walk up to and put in your order. Nothing fancy. Simple and really good. We found a table by the side of the restaurant so we could  look over the bay.

This is the legit place for fish and chips. Fresh line-caught fish and amazing flavour at a fair price in a great location. My partner got their grilled salmon sandwich and it was epic, just the right seasoning and sauce. My fried halibut was a good portion and perfectly battered. The fries were incredible, but I into the age-old problem of my girlfriend stealing half of them. Last but not least, the staff were all amazing! The cashier and cooks were the nicest people. Their quality of work proves they care, and I loved their taste in music.

Outside seating only with a great view of the bay, fishing boats and the Vancouver skyline. Gets very busy during lunch hours. However the fish and chips are great, very crispy. I ordered 2 piece cod and chips and it was enough for my partner and I. For fish and chip places in metro vancouver, this is one of the better places.
Great food, spectacular view, lovely girl taking the orders. The service is alright. I got the halibut and chips which was delicious and the portion was quite large. Food
Fish batter could have used a little more seasoning, but this was a great place to grab fish and chips and hang out by the water. The salmon tacos were good too.

BEST fish and chips Ive ever had in my life! We waited a full hour in the sun and got heat stroke (wish they had more shaded areas available for the queue / lineup folks or folks waiting to get their food) but it was worth it!!!!
Best of the best with amazing view of Granville Island and Burrard Bridge. Seating is outdoors or take back to your car, so dress appropriately!

go fish is my favorite fish and chip place. The place is small but nice, besides that it is in a very quiet and beautiful location where you can go for a walk. The amount is big for the price that you pay. I highly recommend it.
Great shack on False Creek beside Granville Island serving excellent fish and chips.  Our group had both cod and halibut.  The fries were also great.

This food stand near Fishermens Wharf has standard fish and chips with 3 fish options and other seafood creations like sandwiches and tacones. I had never tried oysters before but was feeling adventurous when I came and ordered the oyster po boy. I obviously wouldnt have known what oysters are supposed to be like, but I thought these were really good, and the sandwich as a whole was awesome. The grilled onions and chipotle sauce were really tasty with the oysters. The side of coleslaw was nice and crisp, and I always love coleslaw so I was happy this was included. The prices have gone up since the most recent menu pictures were uploaded online, but theyre still pretty reasonable for the times. My sandwich was $16. Theres a small, partially covered seating area to enjoy your food. It was raining while I was there and everyone was packing in to stay dry, but it wasnt unpleasant - it kind of added to the experience. Even in the rain, the setting by the water and fish market is perfect - this is how seafood is meant to be eaten! And although service may not be the most important thing at a counter-service place like this, the person who took my order was pleasant and made me feel welcome even with our short exchange. Vegetarian options: Everything contains seafood. Nothing vegetarian.

Expect a line up at this spot upon opening till closing - line does go by relatively quick. Limited seating on the patio but they have some expanded shared picnic tables near the parking area. Food here is great - from portions, quality of taste/fish, fresh fry to the coleslaw. The ratio of batter to fish is dominated by the meaty fish but the thin crisp outer layer works well in taste balance. Meals start from $11-> $24 depending on portion and which fish choice. Must go when in the area. Parking: Very limited parking
If you like fish and chips, ya gotta try Go Fish. The fish was fresh, not greasy, flavorful.  Just go do it.

From the first moment, i got there, I loved everything about that place. From the fries to the fish everything was delicious, even the coleslaw. Honestly, the beer bather around the fish (cod in my case) was good and light. When I said I loved everything, I meant it. Their fires are astonishing, crispy and homestyle like.

This place is well worth the walk. We were waiting in line in the Market and a local told us about this place. So we decided to head over and it was worth the 5 minute walk. Everyone will tell you this is the best fish and chips and they are right. I will go further to tell you that the Curry soup, is to die for. It s incredible, and has fresh fish in it. The salad, is made with a homemade vinaigrette and was also simple and wonderful. This little food stand is a gem, and the folks who know.. know. This is it.

Fish and chips were perfect. We got the Cod (they were out of Halibut at 2pm) and it tasted very fresh! Were planning to go again next time to try the Halibut hopefully. We waited for about 1h, including time for our food to get ready.

Delicious, seafood dishes. We got the salmon sandwich and the cod fish and chips. It was a 15 minute line to order and then a 30 minute wait for the food.
