But when the food came it was very fresh and hot. The salmon was a great sandwich with just a little bit of char to let you know that it was just cooked. The fish and chips where regular fish and chips but the fish (cod) was extremely flaky which made it so soft to eat. I would definitely get the fish and chips as the value of this dish is better than the salmon sandwich.

Always the BEST I always take my Mom here, delicious. Only reason I didnt give it 5 stars is I got an overdone piece of cod and it was chewy. By time I examined it, we were off to the side facing water and didnt feel like taking back, which Im sure they would have replaced piece. Great staff. Sometimes a long lineup Its $20. For 2piece cod and chips. Up quite a bit since pandemic.

One of the best place for fish and chips!! Highly recommended this place. Place is next to seawall and has such a great view if its a good weather. The batter tasted phenomenal. It has such a great crunch. One of the best price for fish and chips. Hopefully price won t go up due to inflation. Must try if you love fish and chips

The kitchen music can be loud and metal, the staff can seem overwhelmed and have a hard time hearing over the music, the picnic tables can be full, the lineup can be long and everything can be a little wet from a recent rain ... This is still *by far* the best place to go for halibut and chips in Vancouver. Its a pilgrimage for us ... The beginning of summer, the end of summer, the first really glorious day of spring ... Its a Go Fish celebration. Two pieces of halibut and chips with a soda and tip costs close to $40, but it feeds two easily.

Still my favorite fish n chips shack.  We miss the scallop burgers but the oyster burgers were just as good.  They were out of halibut but the cod was a great alternative.  Great portions.   We really enjoyed the tacones as well.  No sheltered seating and the area lacks parking.

One of the best fish and chips we ve had! The fish is of good quality and the serving sizes are great! Tried the cod, halibut and a tuna sandwich. Both fish were cooked well - moist, crunchy and light batter, not too oily and well-seasoned. The fries are crispy and they use good quality potatoes too. The sandwich was delicious but I would rather order fish and chips! Great for a day out to Granville island and making the walk to this location is definitely worth it!

Amazing fish and chips the best I have had in decades. Just a little shack with some tables and the wharf but oh boy it was amazing. Well priced about $21 to $28 for 2 pieces with chips. So good the wife and I went back and ordered a 3rd order to split between us.

EVERYTIME I come to Vancouver I HAVE TO COME HERE. I don t care if it s raining cats and dogs outside. Hurricane Katrina could be going on and I wouldn t even notice cause I would be too engulfed in my delicious fish & chips and curry soup. The staff are SO friendly, and hilarious! The food is amazing, consistent, and delightful. The Halibut is to die for, and the chips are fried to perfection. The oyster Po boy is also amazing! Honestly, I ve never had anything from here that didn t make me melt in my seat from sheer joy and sensory overload.

Absolutely great fish and chips, comfortable quiet place with great dockside seating, and man do the staff have character! Laughing, joking, singing, it definitely makes you feel good because when the staff put their heart into a place, you can count on great food.

Someone recommended this place as a must visit at Granville Island. And it didn t disappoint us and a quite popular spot I must say. It was a 15-minute line to order and then a 30-minute wait for the food during the lunch time in the mid-September. But when the food came it was very fresh, crispy & soft inside. One of the best places for fish and chips within reasonable price, situated next to seawall and has such a great view if it s a good weather

AMAZING Fish n Chips in an awesome setting. Came from Edmonton to check out Vancouver and wanted to checkout some great food places that wont break the bank. Go Fish is one of them and my oh my does it impress! It is quite a popular spot, so the wait time can take anywhere from 10-20 minutes during the lunch hour. But its worth it. Food came out fresh & crispy, the price was VERY reasonable and you have great views of the harbor & Vancouver. HIGHLY recommend it for anyone visiting or is from the local area.

Hands down, best fish and chips Ive had in Canada (so far).  We ordered the halibut.  The batter was very flavourful, and the fish was still moist on the inside.  The fries were also very good, and tasted like it came from a big french fry chain.  The fish overall did not feel too heavy, and did not feel too salty.  Definitely worth the 30 minute wait.
The oyster burger is light, yet meaty and I prefer their fish and oyster sandwiches instead of fish and chips (Personal preference). Great fresh seafood overall!

Its more like a food truck with an open space in front of it where they put some tables and chairs. Awesome for a sunny day. But when its raining you should grab your food and go. The food is so yummy. Fish and chips and salmon sandwich were both very tasty.
Their fish and chips are amazing, worth many visits again and again. The best thing to do is order some foods and spend your time sitting there and enjoying the scenery by the water.

Nice little hidden gem.  We got there about 2 pm and they were starting to sell out of items.  But the food was worth the wait and scenery made the wait worthwhile.  Fish batter wasnt too heavy or super thick, the chips were crispy and can tell they take care of the oil. I suggest getting there early to beat the rush. But definitely worth the wait.
We tried one of each fish and honestly the oyster burger was the best Ive ever had.

Wow Amazing. What a treat, first impressions first of all I love that its outsider it was my first time coming here today and I love the fish the service was very good people are friendly and the FISH was amazing I got the halibut and the cod with chips and cola with coleslaw on the side and tarter sauce with another spicy dipping sauce. The fish is deep fried but it was not heavy at all. When I was finished I was totally satisfied and I felt great, I didnt want to fall asleep or anything it gave me power and energy for my day. Cant wait to come back again. Thank you GoFish

Really good fish and chips! Halibut was too thick though, tasted like fillet. Very generous but would be better if the halibut was thinner. Cod piece was good. The proportion of batter and fish was perfect. Fries were good too!

Totally worth the 45-minute wait: and the small upside was they told us it would be about 45/60mins wait when we ordered. Cod and Halibut were perfectly cooked, flakey and moist. Batter was seasoned, thick enough to hold vinegar but somehow not stodgy or greasy. To top it off, chips literally could not have been crispier. Only thing I would change: ask for more ketchup next time for chip dipping! Definitely will be back for my next serve of fish and chips.

I have to say I finally had best fish and chips. It s always long line up but it s really worth it and please go there before 1pm because they might sold out halibuts. I was lucky that I had last two of them. One thing I really happy about my meal was not so greasy and halibuts were so fresh. Also the seats were enough amount for everyone no one was eating without seat.

A great experience! We had 1 piece salmon and chips and 1 piece cod and chips. OMG! There was actually fish in the fish and chip ( unlike at Vancouver Fish Company!) The portions were very generous, too. (Unlike at the Vancouver Fish Company.) Tasted great, price was very reasonable and the staff were super friendly. A very pleasant experience. Will definitely be taking ALL my out of town visitors here.
Love the Po Boy burgers. Worth a visit on a sunny warm day. Check if they are opened before visiting to avoid disappointment. You can walk to Granville island from here. Highly recommended.

This place is highly rated, and deservedly so. We re here Sunday at 12:10, about 10 minutes after they open.  There is a 20 min wait in line to order already, and by the time we ordered, the wait for the food is about 20 min.  The folks working there were friendly, and shouted out the long wait time to everyone so they know what to expect.  Didn t see anyone leave though. Very simple Menu, Cod, Salmon, or Halibut and Chips, along with a Salmon  Taco  or wrap.  The daily special was a Tuna wrap, along with a red curry soup. We ordered a bit of everything, and everything was good!  The fried cod and Salmon had a crunchy batter, and the fish was very fresh.  The fish was served on a bamboo basket filled with fresh fries that were crunchy, and a really big serving.  The tar tar sauce and the slaw was very good too, but the cod was really good with ketchup as well. The tuna wrap was tasty, the flavors were very balanced, and enhanced the freshness and sweetness of the tuna. All in all, we ate too much, but we will be going back.  The long lines were longer when we were done, but folks were waiting patiently for it.

This is a tiny take out fish and chip place. It packs a punch with your tastebuds though. The fish, chips, coleslaw and tartar sauce were so delicious! Good prices and large portions. A definite must try for anyone. Two thumbs up

Really tasty fish and chips super close to granville island. I like taking mine on my walk with me along the seawall and snacking the whole walk. I ordered three pieces of cod with fries, and I find thats a good amount for two people.

Great dockside fish n chip spot just off the beaten path of Granville island. Food was great! Watching the boats, and the city skyline are great views and the guys in the kitchen are friendly. Don t expect table service, but that s what makes this place authentic. Also beware of seagulls!

My teenager and I shared one plate of two pieces, plus fries. It was plenty as a snack. It was delicious and the prices are reasonable. Also, the view is fantastic and Granville Island market is within five minutes walk. The staff are friendly, plenty of seats. Free parking just a few feet away. Yaaay! You have to go there and have some fresh fish...they have tacos as well...Will have that next time. Im so lucky, I just need to cross the Burrard bridge and bingo! This is my new favorite fish and chips. Go Fish!

Great location. Chips and fish was excellent taste. Special is sauces. I really had a good time there. At the weekend is too busy and crowded here. We just ordered and take away. I sure will be back to try another type of food

By far the best fish Ive ever had. Im a tourist from Toronto so I wanted some local fish n chips and this place far exceeded my expectations.  friendly staff and out of this world fish and tar tar sauce (make sure you by extra, I could drink the stuff) made my first local fish experience one I wont soon forget.
The best fish and chips I have ever had. The batter is so thin and not greasy whatsoever. The fries are fresh cut. I highly recommend Go Fish. Get there early, there will be a line up.
Amazing Fish and Chips place! The Halibut was crazy good! Very good food! The ocean and Granville island view is amazing! The service was so fast! Staff are so nice and friendly! Highly recommended!
This is a great place to stop for fish n chips while walking or biking.  Just be aware the portions are quite generous. I only finished half of my chips.

Wow! This was a fantastic experience. First off it is right on the harbor. The fish is tender and fresh. We both had fish and chips. It was the best fish and chips I have very had. Other patrons tried the sandwich and tacos options which also looked good. Its a small menu which I like. It takes about 20 minutes for the food to be ready as it is fresh made to order. This place is worth the wait in line.

Their salmon burger is absolutely amazing, I inhale every bite of it every time. The staff are fun and friendly and even though the line ups are long, their food tell you why. Its great to grab a bite and sit outside in the park to enjoy the view of the bridge and pier. Awesome place.
Fresh and delicious. Definitely check this place out.

The halibut fish and chips were the best Ive had in Canada, hands down. Stayed crispy and cooked to perfection. The staff were also incredibly friendly; the young lady working the till in particular should be commended.

We got the halibut and chips. Cost for this was $19  which honestly seems like an excellent price considering serving size and quality. The halibut was thick and well-cooked. The batter was perfect as well. It was pouring rain when we went. A server pulled out the canopy and wiped down all the benches and tables for us, which was very courteous. We would definitely recommend this place!!
Had a halibut with chips and tuna salad, both were so yummy! The wait was a bit longer just because they were so busy! Strongly recommended!!!
Lucky for us, we meet a New York and recommend us this place! We had a really good lunch and honestly it was very fresh, and tasty highly recommend tuna grill sandwich and fries! Food : 5/5

we ordered two of the fish and chips; one with salmon and the other was halibut (i think) but, it doesnt matter because both orders of fish were delicious! the view was top notch and its a short walk from Granville which was enjoyable. the only downfall was that the fries were extremely salty we left some behind. although, besides that the staff is a bunch of young guys which is a nice atmosphere and funny when you hear them talking to each other and working
Great fish! We shared halibut x2 and a piece of cod with fries. They even gave us each a serving of coleslaw! Good price, batter was delicious and fries were decent!

Unbelievably good!  It was a must stop every time we came to Vancouver and literally a notable point when considering moving to Van.  Now that we live here we go all the time and easily the second best fish and chips I ve ever had.  Wait times can be long but I do it every time and no regrets.  Halibut fish and chips is worth the extra price.
One of the best thing you can do it in Vancouver if you want real street fish and chips! Excellent in all senses, seriously! Great quality-price. 10/10.

This place is a container. Converted into sort of like a food truck,but no truck... Beware there is no indoor seating. The place is open 12 months of the year. And it s interesting to go eat there in the winter and eat outside in the chilli brisk cool ocean air. You cannot beat the view with a backdrop of the city Granville Island and all the fishing boats. The food is fresh and at times in limited quantities. This place serves exactly what you would expect battered cod or salmon or any of the other seafood they sell to be. The service can be a little annoying only because there s so many tourists in front of you who don t know how to read a menu. Or ask to many questions And delay the line. Outdoor seating is probably for 50. But you can easily sit on the seawall and enjoy your snack. Beware of the birds they might steal your meal when you re not looking. My photos of the fish tacos. They were pretty good. Not enough for an entire meal. But a great snack while walking along the seawall.

The very best halibut - and honestly best fish and chips - Ive ever had. Crispy amd creamy and fresh and delightful. Coleslaw and tartar sauce are great. Patio has heaters and is warm and covered during the rain. So rain or shine, go. Go fish.
Best fish and chips I ve ever had. Cods were THICC BOIS and the fries were crisp and well seasoned. Bit of a wait but definitely worth it
Very nice place on the side of the pier. Staff is very friendly, and the food is so so good!!
Went right when it opened and there still was a line! But well worth the wait - I can definitely see what all the hype is about. The crunch on their batter and fries were 10/10!!!

A local favourite for fish and chips. I always think of this place when Im craving fish and chips. Its just a pain to get here by car, much easier if you bike. The fish and fries they serve is piping hot. The ratio of batter to fish is perfect. We biked go a park close by to enjoy our crispy fish and chips.

Great fish and chips! And Im from the UK, so I know what Im talking about.   Youll be sat outside in the sun/rain/whatever and I didnt spy any restrooms but its the best fish Ive had in 8 years in Canada. Wheelchair accessibility: There is a step up to get to the window to order and I didnt see any accommodations for wheelchairs to be able to access the platform.

Delicious fish and chips at affordable prices. I got a piece cod fish with chips at about $13. It has a small outdoor seating area that s not heated so it got quite cold on a cold windy day. The person giving us the food was absolutely funny and energetic! And that made the experience even better.

Truly amazing fish and chips! My boyfriend and I shared an order of 2 pc cod + chips. Fish done perfectly (fluffy and almost creamy texture) with a great batter, and fries are also just an amazing crisp and you can just tell that they use quality potatoes! Amazing service! The cashier was outstandingly friendly! Theyre doing takeout only (patio closed) because of COVID, but there are plenty of places nearby to chow down Im definitely going to come back to this place and tell all my friends about it. I heard that theres usually a wait, but we were lucky to beat the line at about 5:45pm on a Wednesday A true 10/10 experience
Some of the freshest and best fish and chips I  ever had! It was so so so good. Would definitely come back here if I ever come back to Vancouver!
My favourite fish n chips to date. Crispy, fresh, and flavourful. I recommend going early, and be prepared for long wait times as it is a very popular place
Simply delicious! Fantastically fresh fish, perfectly fried. Loved the Asian spin on the coleslaw with sesame oil. Refreshing.
Excellent fish and chips, best in the city. Great professional staff. Wait times can be long as it is such a popular spot, it is worth the wait.
Be prepared to wait if you come on a weekend. Wish there were more tables.

I m soooo picky about fish. But this place is wonderful!!! All I can say is free a time to stop by and grab some fish and chips. No dine-in due to COVID. So, be prepared for a place to enjoy your lunch.

From out of province and I absolutely loved this place the first time I tried it. When I returned I planned to go here, and when I returned this place was on the top of my life (literally dreaming of the fish and chips for the past 3 years) but when I arrived on a Monday afternoon, it was closed, despite Google telling me that it opened today at 11:30. So sad because I leave tomorrow and won t be able to get it now. A whole trip planned around a fish and chips establishment that I didn t even get to enjoy, but 5 stars because it would have been worth it (based on my experience 3 years ago)

best fish and chips that I ever had this is not just a hype. fish was soft and tasty covered in crunchy batter. Line up starts before they open make sure to be there early. definitely a must go when you visit Granville Island.
All the staff were super kind and the fish and chips we had was PERFECT!
Halibut was nice and thick.  Wish they included more tartar sauce. If the gates (near the dock) are closed, you will have to go around to get to the restaurant.
Best place for fish and chips as well as other options too. The foods are very fresh and tasty

The halibut was really fresh. The tartar sauce is not a conventional dill flavour, but is very thick and creamy. I think it s tarragon instead- really good. The coleslaw is also unconventional, it s Asian inspired. Personally I like it a bit more zingy but it was a really solid fish and chip platter.
Solid food and chill workers! The fish tacos were spectacular! Definitely a must try.
The fish and chips was good but even if it wasn t good I still would ve giving 5 stars because of the girl that took my order. She was very sweet

Fish was nice and crispy on the outside, flakey on the inside. Very fresh! Fries were seasoned well and you can really distinctly taste the dill in the tartar sauce. Just sucks that we couldnt eat it within the premises but its COVID season so understandable.
What a gem! Had the albacore tuna sandwich and it was a 10/10! The staff are super friendly and obviously do a fantastic job. Will be back for sure!
Top notch fish and chips, very friendly staff. 100% recommend.
We had the greatest food at this cute little shop while visiting Canada. Highly recommended. We had halibut fish and chips, and the salmon sandwich. Amazing!!

Probably the best fish and chips I have had so far. One of the local favorites around the area. They have an amazing fried Oyster sandwich but sold out when we went. We usually order the halibut fish with extra tartar sauce. The line up and wait time is usually 30 to 45 mins but if you go between lunch and dinner hour might be less. This is a must try if you visit grandville Island. Will definitely go back, they never disappoint.
Great fish and chips, happy service and a waterfront location and view of Granville Island. Simple, outdoor bench seating or takeaway.

Fresh and tasty! Amazing people! Small business making great impact. Go Fish was recommended by my colleague, and yes, Go Fish ticked all the boxes! Clean and lovely environment. I love it! I will sure go back anytime I visit Vancouver again.
Went here on a recommendation from our walking tour guide. Great location and excellent food, Id go every week if I lived in Vancouver
The best fish n chips place in Vancouver! The fish was fresh and fries were fried to perfection! Its worth paying more for the halibut fillet.

(IG: KEVIFONG) The best Fish n Chips stall in Vancouver. Its located along the ocean side of Granville Island. Their ingredients are always fresh. I usually order the Halibut Fish n Chips, it is fried in a light batter that is served with fries/coleslaw then beautifully plated onto a Bamboo Steamer. I also recommend the Oyster Po-boy Sandwich.

Fantastic fish and chips. This place is a hidden gem near Granville island. Really small and often busy  shack .  Usually a line up but worth the wait. Located on the waters edge it serves some incredibly delicious seafood and chips. Worth a trip to get some. I highly recommend stopping by.

Simply THE BEST Oyster House in town. Awesome  happy hour  deal, the atmosphere is always amazing, AND great food qualities! My wife and I enjoyed every visit, I am pretty sure you will and can find your  oyster  here! Oh, yeah, don t forget their soup, mussel & clams, and drinks! And and their spicy sauce selection! Spicy Caesar, my favorite~

By far one of my favourite place to go in Vancouver! Every time we go to Vancouver we make sure we stop by the Rodney oyster s house in Yaletown. From fresh oysters to one of the best service I ve had in a restaurant, this is definitely a place you need to try. Every single plate was perfect and came super fast, we got the crab cakes, garlic shrimps, shrimp cocktail, clams, mussels and obviously oysters. Everything was so fresh and the oysters come with a lot of different choices of sauces for you to choose from. Very clean restaurant and very cute ambiance for a date, a dinner with friends or even to just go by yourself ! The staff working there has one of the best service I ve seen in years, they are really on point and so friendly and nice, this is one of the reasons we always go back there, we just love the ambiance and service so much, a lot of place should take exemple of this place ! We ve been served by Mackenzie and sadly I don t forget the name of the other employees that took care of us but it isn t the last time they will see us in the establishment! IF YOU LOVE SEAFOOD AND GOOD VIBES YOU NEED TO TRY THIS PLACE !

Great establishment.    If you plan to visit, try to make reservations.  Its not a large restaurant, and spaces fill up quickly.  I would definitely recommend the raw oysters, calamari, and fish dip.  Our group enjoyed EVERYTHING that came to our table.

I tried oysters for the first time at Rodneys and Ive been hooked ever since! Cant go wrong with seafood anywhere on the the west coast but Rodneys is extra special. I was at the location during a work trip and the staff made sure we were served on time so we can get back to work on time. The chef also came and said hello - super nice. Loved the decor as well!

Highly recommend making a reservation for some delish eats at Rodney s. We went last Saturday, sat at the bar where Mehdi delivered both great service and entertainment as he worked the soups and steamers. The atmosphere is FUN. Go hungry. It s not cheap - but you get VALUE for the food.

Im very impressed with the quality of Rodneys Oyster House. Great food and service, a fun place to be in, top class all around. We found that it is important to reserve a table, even in the middle of the week (it was summer, too, so that might add a bit). The waiter was great, the hot sauce defection was wonderful, and the choices in oyster types was unexpected and fantastic to have. We dove right in, so if you see the picture I took you can tell that a lot of the oysters had already been eaten by the time I got my camera out. You know, you go away from raw oysters for a while and you start thinking, Im kind of ok without them, or Did I really eat those things? But then you get taken to Rodneys and you relearn that oysters are amazing things to eat.

Its one of the original fun oyster bars in Vancouver.  A variety of oyster and fresh seafood choices to pick from.  A favorite is the steamed chowder made in front of you and poured into a bowl for you to enjoy.  Fun lively staff keep the energy high and enjoyable banter Parking: Yaletown is often a challenge to find parking due to the popularity of the area and limited street parking.

An amazing seafood restaurant! Great food, service and atmosphere! Highly recommend this hidden gem if you are wanting an excellent seafood experience :) Kid-friendliness: Saw some families with kids and they seem to have a good time :)
Loved the food and experience, one of the servers taught me to eat raw oyesters since I had never tried them before. Was way more expensive than I was expecting, went for a lunch by myself.
If you are a oyster lover, I suggest getting the BC oyster selection. It was amazing and tasted so good. Would definitely come again!

I liked the lively atmosphere of the restaurant. I got lobster poutine and salmon salad. Both tasted great! I sat at the bar, and the bartender was kind to the customers. I recommend this place for a good, filling dinner.

Absolutely amazing service and the guys behind the bar are so fun and helpful. Medhi, our server was fun and extremely knowledgeable on suggestions on the menu. We ended up eating a dozen oysters, also had  the muscles which are absolutely out of this world and the shrimp and lobster roll was very good as well. I cant recommend this place enough, the place is  fun,  fabulous and some of the best food in town.

I had 12 assorted oysters and my wife had mini lobsters & shrimp sliders, both delicious! Service is very good; reservation advised. Parking: Usually full, have to park far away. I recommend Canada Line. Kid-friendliness: Not at all for kids; it is a Bar.

The hospitality here is unmatched, it s unlike anywhere I ve ever been in the best way possible. I spent 6 hours from opening to closing sitting at the bar getting to know the staff (they were all too lovely to leave), and had the time of my life! Great food, great music, and even better conversation with every staff member that took time out of their night to get to know me. All around a wonderful place to be! :)

Great vibes and service in this joint. Casual and fancy at the same time (wine is served in rock glasses haha). The oyster platter recommended was really yummy - appreciated our server giving tips on how to have them (only with horseradish and a smidge of vinaigrette!) Mussels were great, especially with the bread to soak up the sauce. Lobster is divine with a great sauce that went well with all the accompanying sides, and clarified butter - only acceptable dipping sauce for lobster. No mayo or anything that outshines this tasty crustacean!

10/10 for service and food. Our server was Micheal and his attitude was great when he was efficient and going around vibing with the music. But just not the service was great. The food was on par too. We had -Lobster Poutine which I definitely recommend everyone try as it s super rich in flavour and the serving size was more then enough for 2 people. -12 oysters(6 from the west coast, 6 from PEI)these were definitely fresh and two different flavours. The one being from the west coast looking more of a deep shell and darker meat. Being sweet and more flavourful. Compared to the ones from PEI being a more shallow shell and lighter meat. Concluding to a more salty flavour. Ended up grabbing 2 more of the west coast because being so fresh and delicious. -New England Clam Chowder was another good choice if you want a classic clam chowder. Will come back again in the future or recommend anyone that comes to Vancouver for a visit

A great seafood restaurant with a cozy environment, fresh crab and lobster and oysters and delicious muscles. All the food on their menu tastes great. But my favorite is the Lobster rolls and the Halibut. The lobster rolls are not kn the menu so you should ask the waiters for it. The staff are super friendly and very professional. They brought the food in an order that we had food all the time and they didnt bring all the food at the same time. The environment is also clean and cozy and the kitchen is clean.

Great place to go for seafood! Really enjoyed eating the full crab, calamari, oysters, mussels and who can forget the famous clam chowder soup with crackers.   Hubby and I enjoyed our date night here! Will be back again soon

The food and service was amazing. I really loved the way of presenting this restaurant. Food was fresh and delicious. Service very prompt and friendly. The ambiance very unique. I went in for a happy hour evening was perfect. Thank you We will be back.

A must go vancouver oyster house ! Very fresh oysters and great ambiance. 2 locations to choose one in gas town and the other in yaletown but always preferred the original yaletown location. Must order : oysters, New England clam chowder, shrimp cocktail and Bloody Mary! Manhattan clam chowder not as good but can try. Crab cake not bad and portion not so big. Very friendly service overall!

I had a great time at Rodneys. The service was amazing. Super friendly and helpful crew.   The food was absolutely delicious. All the ingredients are so fresh. I will definitely come back for more.   Highly recommended!

We got to sit at the back of the restaurant and it was nice and quiet. The happy hour oysters paired well with all the different sauces available. Id recommend coming before the peak hours to avoid the noise and the crowd. If you happen to order the dip, do not be afraid to ask for more bread if you run out too!

If you come to Vancouver and do not visit this place, then you are missing some truly great seafood. From the garlic prawns to the strawberry shortcake, every single dish was a treat. The fresh oysters were fresh indeed. The meal could not have been better. A must visit and recommend when visiting vancity!

Another nice visit to Rodney s Ouster House and it did not disappoint. We ordered 2 dozen shucked oysters New England chowder Manhattan chowder Clams Seafood pasta 2lb steamed lobster And key lime pie to top it off Amazing food and service. Originally booked for 7 but arrived late, they were able to accommodate us within 10 minutes with great seats.  Staff are super friendly and quick to help. Food is delicious and not over seasoned. Highly recommended

This place has the best seafood. We had the west coast oysters and they were fantastic. Then seafood pasta and the halibut. Both excellent. The food was a bit slow in coming; the waiter said they only had one person shucking that night, but he topped up our wine and all was forgiven. Definitely recommend.

This place draws you in from the outside the smell of butter and seafood. We came for happy hour one day and the food was incredible. Service was friendly and we had the fried oysters, mussels, garlic prawns, and raw oysters along with a couple beers and drinks. The mussels came with quite a bit of sauce that was quickly lapped up with all of the bread. Would definitely stop back as I m eager to try out some of the entrees.

These are the best oysters Ive ever had! We ordered 18 and they were so clean, not a single grain of sand present. Beer was ice cold, clam chowder was delicious, and lobster poutine was incredible. Great service too. I highly recommend!

Wow the server was so entertaining, he made our experience so unforgettable. Very generous pour with the chardonnay it almost spilled over. I loved the large selection of seafood and of course the oysters. Was impressed by the portion sizes and the presentation was decent. Prices were reasonable. It was a little loud in the restaurant and it didn t have much capacity even with a second floor / loft. Parking is always challenging in Yaletown so if you want to head out here, take transit. It s very close to the station.

Huge tasty oysters! Pricey dishes but very delicious. Blown away with each dish. The clam chowder was probably the best clam chowder I ve ever had, the bread it was fresh and delicious. The scallop linguine was phenomenal, and the crabcake dish balanced so well with the salad it came with. An 11 out of 10 experience, really high end ingredients prepared perfectly. Absolutely would recommend, and even worth the high price.

Crab was excellent (the melted butter tasted funny for the crab), the asparagus & potatoes were amazing (perfect amount of spicy). Oysters were amazing, I LOVED 1 of the sauces (the dark purple vinaigrette one). The butter that was for the bread was the best butter Ive tasted (homemade old fashioned vibes, favorite kind) loved it. Service of getting my 1st (and only) drink took a very long time (asked for easy spice .. and it came spicy af w/alot of horseradish) .. I couldnt finish my drink, I think I drank a few inches. Oh well ... they were busy.

This was my first time at Rodneys. I visited this place on a Sat night and it was a great experience. To start with the services were fantastic and staff was super friendly. I was recommended a few dishes as a first timer at this place. I tried Oysters, Garlic Prawns and Atlantic Lobster Poutine. Starting with Oysters, as they were just amazing. Then we got Garlic Prawns, which were served with a bit of garlic soup and bread on the side. This was my first ever time trying the dish and I just couldnt stop myself once I tasted it. It was fabulous. Lastly the lobster poutine which was equally delicious and filling. I will definitely recommend Rodneys to all my friends and family. Cheers!! Parking: Usually available in front of the restaurant. Wheelchair accessibility: There are 2 floors but only floor 1 is accessible to wheelchair

Fabulous service and a great way to spend a Monday night. Recommendations from the staff were great - the  Oyster Guy  was a wealth of information. And   the carrot cake for dessert was perfect. Will go back again soon!

This is a great oyster bar in Yaletown. Their seafood is always fresh and the service is friendly. It can get very busy here so you way want to call ahead. They have really good clam chowder (both New England and Manhattan style). Their Caesar is a great cocktail to order. It is worth a visit if you are close by.

We had an amazing experience today at Rodney s!! A huge shout out to Mackenzie who took excellent care of us. Best server ever!! Great conversationalist, explained the ins and outs of oysters, rang the bell for the  oyster virgins  and was just a super genuine guy! Make sure you sit at the bar!!!

Awesome spot! Great food, I had lobster poutine and it was delicious. Apples were good too. Our waitress Andrea made the visit a lot of fun, as well as the other server and kitchen staff! Dudes! Who ordered the chow chow! Delicious.

Stopped by for  low tide  and had a fabulous meal. Everything was delicious and fairly priced. The beverages were perfect and the service was on point. Highly recommended, especially if you re a seafood fan!
Such a great restaurant for oysters and other seafood. Its cozy and I like the atmosphere very much. Friendly stuff and good quality food. I really liked it here and we had a great time.

It was suggested that I try Rodney s for oysters and it did not disappoint. The atmosphere was fun and unpretentious, oysters were great, service was great and the staff was exceptional! All around great fun time!

Take advantage of their low tide menu (happy hour). I do believe it starts from 3 pm to 6 pm if I am not mistakened.  Dont forget to ask for extra bread, youll be needing those for your steamed shellfish.  I give them 5 stars- 4 for food and ambiance + 1 star for their GQ servers  .

Pretty Awesome Spot for Lobster and Oysters.  Had a Few Items which were  Really Good.  I just wasnt a Fan of the Poutine, Lobster was good but very Heavy Tasting Fries and Gravy.  Maybe another day I should give it a Try.  Oysters Were Awesome Had 10!  Lobster Rolls were Fresh and Delicious.  Would Come Back Again.
Fantastic genuine service. Great food too of course - we had the steamed clams, halibut hits, and crab dip during their happy hour.

I loved this place! Even though it is super pricy. We paid around $130 for 12 oysters each and for 4 beers. The atmosphere and the design makes you feel that you are just next to the ocean at a local bar or pub. The service is very friendly and the staff is rather easy-going than too serious.

Whoa, I had an amazing time here on a Friday post-work outing. Servers were so fun and social with the customers, and the food was awesome. Oysters and Mussels were good, but my favourite was the ****Garlic Shrimp****. Highly recommend checking this place out. First-timers, brace yourselves for delight.

The best spot in Yaletown for a laid-back beverage at the bar chased by oysters. The bar staff are the friendliest around and always make you feel welcome, whether its your first or tenth time there. Highly recommend the lobster and shrimp sliders. The horseradish is the freshest around and enhances these fresh oysters.
Great place. Good food.  Excellent music. Drinking with Dhillon. Food
Amazing food! One of my favourite restaurants in town! The staff here are very friendly and very efficient. Definitely worth a try!!

My friends and I have been here a few times now, and always have so much fun! The crew / staff are super friendly and charismatic. The oysters & lobster shrimp sliders are yummy. So many great seafood options to try

Great place for some great seafood! Quite busy, so book a table. Staff is awesome and like I said before the food is awesome! The dessert options, cheesecake and chocolate mouse were both to die for. Definitely would come back.
Took my lady for a belated birthday dinner and had a great experience from entry to exit and all in between. Definitely a must stop in Yaletown
Super fun experience and super fresh oysters. I have never had this many in one go but definitely a place for a fun time with friends. The staff are the best and so friendly as well!
Fun & Delicious : the place to be in Vancouver!!! Enjoy over two floors seafood specialities, oysters and handmade pasta Service is friendly
Some of the best oysters I have ever had. Freshly shucked when you order. They have a lot of sauces but really would have like to try basic cocktail Sauce.
I love Rodney s, and if you love oysters, you will love Rodney s too. It s that simple. Though, at about $4 each, its not a cheap feed...

This was my first visit to Rodneys   . What can I say....from the moment we entered it was high energy, exceptional customer service  and positive vibes all around. The gents serving our table were all super friendly and had the best sense of humor. A member of the upper management team even came over and chatted with us to ensure we were well taken care of. Without a doubt- this place SHOULD be on everyones go to list. You cant help but leave feeling amazing .....just from the positive energy floating around. Cant wait to go back.

This is an excellent place for couples, or parties it brings an upbeat vibe with an old school feeling, Michael was absolutely fabulous! Very friendly, charismatic, and knowledgeable, and was an absolute delight ! Will definitely be returning!
Great oyster selection, loved the candied salmon salad, and the service was excellent.  It s cozy but modern inside with good music and an overall great vibe.
The restaurant is clean and organized. Oysters are fresh and perfectly chewy with a variety of choices of sauce. Overall a 5 star place for seafood. Would definitely come back again!
Nice, fresh food, especially the Oysters!! If tou can eat more, Id like to recommend banana cremble. And also great staffs are in there. Dont be hesitate to go there.
So friendly and nice Delicious food Food
Absolutely live this place. The quality of the the Nd staff is excellent.  Highly recommended.  Good wine choice too.
We had oysters and shared the pasta. Both delicious. I liked the different sauces for oysters.

Very friendly service. Tried their grilled halibut at the staffs recommendation - it was grilled to perfection and beautifully presented too. Also tried 3 kinds of oysters. The server explained the dishes very patiently. The restaurant is in a loft building. The lower level seats more people and the upper one was less noisy the night I was there. Its a bar and restaurant, Noisy is normal. Booking in advance is recommended, they do get very busy. Overall  it was a very happy dining experience and I would like to come back there in the future.
Decided to try this place out for my birthday, we had an amazing time. The staff was wonderful, the seafood fresh, the drinks tasty. No complains, everything was perfect. Thanks for making my day!
My friends always come here for happy hour oysters. Im not raw oyster person but i love everything cooked here. Crazy line up but cozy place, friendly staff too.

Delicious oysters, friendly staffs, and toddler friendly - they made a lot of food adjustments for our two-year-old - and generally everything was delicious. Was quite impressed with their classic Caesar - I d come back again for their oyster + Caesar.
Amazing place for seafood.  Really great variety of oysters.  Lobster poutine is good too
Great atmosphere in a trendy pert of town! Knowledgeable staff. Everything we had tasted great. If you like ceasers then you need to try theirs.
Always, consistently, phenomenal service and food! I wish I lived closer!
We all had different dishes and everything was excellent. The servers were fast and friendly and the place has a great atmosphere.
This place is unreal. Beats every oyster place in Miami that I ve ever been to (where I live). Oysters are perfect. Clam chowder the best I ve ever had.  Great service and vibe too.

I loved the vibe. The service was great. The waiters were all so cool. Loved the food. Best seafood Ive tried in Vancouver Vegetarian options: You can choose to have the Pasta without any meat, fish but this restaurant is a seafood restaurant. You should try their seafood dishes if you go.
Fresh and tasty oysters, mussels and clams. We also got there during happy hour, great timing.
The food was great, service was great (thanks Jeff!). If you want to eat reasonably priced seafood, this place is a must :)

Summer isnt the same without Rodneys low tide happy hour. Theres a reason why I keep coming back so Ill keep this review short as anyone you ask where to go for oysters will tell you to come to here. Not to mention their lobster mac n cheese and their lousiana hot crab dip are bomb. They have 2 locations, Gastown and Yaletown. Keep in mind there are no reservations so come early. All the staff are friendly and outgoing. Great place to grab a bite, take a date or catch up with friends. Hands down, best oysters locally! If you find a place better, please let me know because I havent found one so far..

Oysters are fresh, mussels are great, clam chowder is tasty, bread is also good.   Ok the lobster roll I couldnt really taste much lobster meat and for 30$ the 3 little buns felt overpriced,  the brioche bun is maybe abit too oily, thats one dish I might not order again. Service is good. Food

Loved the easy going atmosphere here.  Great staff, great food. Loved the fresh oysters, and clam chowder.  The guys work hard here, and hustle like they are owners. Seems like a great place to work, and it shows. This really was the highlight of my 22 hour layover in Vancouver!  Awesome experience.
Pretty ambient environment. Food is good and service is excellent. Would recommend to anyone who wants to try out their famous lobster poutine.
Seafood stew and lobster poutine were excellent. Our server was fantastic. We also had oyster and they were super delicious. Highly recommended.

this place is great. had an awesome dinner with friends tonight, with equally awesome service. staff are super attentive and have great personalities. we asked the staff their opinions on Chewbaccas member and were not disappointed. 10/10 would talk about genitalia again
Great price! Top notch quality paired with a fun atmosphere. You can tell they take pride in what they serve.
Bring back the 1.50$ oysters !!
One of the staff name is AJ, He was really kind and professional. He explained us whatever we asked. Being kind is a second nature to him. Food was great as well. :)
Tastes like its fresh out of the ocean. Excellent service... make sure to save your pennies because this place isnt cheap. Well with it though.
Legendary! Vancouvers finest oyster bar!
Always fun - great selection of oysters. First time I tried spot prawns and the broth they came with was simply delicious. Great Service as well.

Definitely one of the best oyster house. Always with the fresh ones. Knowledgeable servers that can recommend from different choices. Lots of other seafood options if you are not into osyters. Definitely take advantage of their happy hour if you can. Lots of drink options too. Perfect place for a date or a couple of friends hanging out.
Great vibe on a Saturday happy hour.  Service was excellent and friendly and the oysters were awesome.
The steamed mussels were so buttery and smooth. The waiters were really friendly and helpful to make recommendations to out of town guests.
the most immaculate vibes in vancouver, if not the planet. love this place and cant wait to go back. get the crab dip, you wont regret it

This has been one of my favouite spots to dine in since about 1996! The atmosphere here is magic and thats due to an amazing staff and great food.  Best chowder in the city. Currently serving, the New England and Manhattan versions. Two of my favourites are on covid-19 holiday, the Corn Chowder and my personal favourite The Slap Jack (leek and fresh poached oysters)! I look forward to their return. Happy Hour is called Low Tide and is the best spot in town for happy hour food and drinks. Wine is poured into a 5.5 oz glass filled to the top so be prepared to sip, in place, from the table. Lastly, a shout out, the music play list is awesome! You cant go wrong at Rodneys Oyster House in Yaletown. There is a location in Gastown that is awesome but the atmosphere in Yaletown is magical!
Great service! Staff are chill and welcoming. Food was awesome! Had a great time
Great selection of food and everything was delicious!  Lobster poutine, mini lobster rolls, and raw oysters.  Awesome!
Nice vibe. Tasty food. Quick service. Enjoyed our family dinner there.

We are here two days in a row. All of the oysters were fresh and chilled to perfection. The lobster and crab rolls are delicious. We finished with the fried oysters which served as dessert. Bonus are all the sauces they have to dress your oysters.

Great vibes, good food, large portions, excellent service. Only small gripe was that food took a bit longer to leave the kitchen but the overall atmosphere made up for it. Our order: - Oyster sampler (dozen per order, so good we had two orders) - Lobster Poutine - House Salad (dressing low key tasted like Big Mac sauce) - New England Clam Chowder

I went with my friend to this restaurant pretty spontaneously for lunch and all I can say is the moment I stepped inside I knew it was going to be a good time. The interior is so cosy and the festive ambiance is very cute. The service was very polite, efficient and courteous. The food   was delicious. I really enjoyed the meals we got and I totally recommend the Oyster Po boy and obviously the oysters. Great selections of sauce to accompany the oysters ~ Overall lovely time, great food and service. Now you just need to enjoy it yourself by going as well :-) Cheers~
Very casual place. The food is exceptional! Oysters from west and east coast, so good! Lively crowd, good music.

Amazing, delicious and wonderful service! Came here as a party of three, ordered two dozen oysters as a part of happy hour. Also ordered three entrees to share amongst the three of us. Each entree was well received. Will definitely come back again in the near future!

A really fun place in Yaletown.  We got there at Low Tide (Happy Hour) and had the fresh oysters on the half-shell which were delicious with the wide array of sauces provided. The clam chowder and the hot crab dip were also excellent.
Delicious Fresh tasty oysters! Prices are decent, various beverage option and great sides. Be sure to get low tide prices to get the best deal! Friendly customer service.

Brian is the MAN!!!!! The service is out of this world! Super friendly and knows the menu inside and out. This was our first time here so we didnt know what to order, Brian spend his time with us and was very patient. Was he ever was right about the suggestions, the best seafood I ever had, did I mention they would come by and take the empties right away and refill everything right away. Had a blast of the night, will be back super soon. 10 stars, thank you Brian.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for sharing your feedback with us. We are delighted to know that you had a great experience with us. Look forward to your future visit!

review_text: Celebrated a birthday and wanted a whole lobster. So we ordered the Pirates Feast. Oh boy, what a feast! The Captains Boil sauce is soooo finger-licking good (a tad too salty but still yummy nonetheless) and all the seafood we selected were fresh and cooked just nice. Besides the corn being too soggy to our liking, everything else was on point. Obviously the two of us could only manage half of the feast and had to pack the rest home. Its our first time here and we were guided by the nice servers how to order. Will be back for sure.

review_text: Very tasty food, as soon as you enter the cafe you immediately feel the aroma of delicious food! We were there for the first time, we were recommended by friends. I havent eaten such delicious food at a reasonable price for a long time. Thank you guys for a great evening, high-quality service and care. We were lucky and the team took care of us)) Brian, Alexandra, Evan and Nicholas, thank you for the evening, you are super!!!

review_text: My experience there was amazing. When i entered, i got seated quickly. I am amazed by the customer service. The staff there were very kind and patient. I was there as a hangout with family and everyone enjoyed their food. My favourite dishes there has to be the fried rice and chicken wings. The portion sizes for the price were very reasonable and pretty good. 10/10 would recommend to everyone and will definitely go again.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for sharing your feedback with us. We are delighted to know that you had a positive experience with us. Look forward to your future visit!

review_text: It was good experience to get together with your friends and eat here in lunch time.food is fresh and warm to serve. There is no plastic bib now but they still have plastic gloves. We celebrate my Birthday here and the service is good,they let us barrow a plate for a cake that we bring it there. We are 8 people dine in here and tell me I need to pay additional 15% gratitude as we have exceed people to sit in,which is understandable. Over all we defineitly come back here agakn Parking: Parking is in the sidewalk with pay or back parking which is limited but free.

review_text: The place is small but the important part is the food! I met a friend there and we both were satisfied with the service and the food. I wish there were drinks like lemonade or mocktails. We were satisfied and will go back with my family.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for sharing your feedback with us. We appreciate your feedback and will take it into consideration as we continuously strive to enhance our offerings and ensure better value for our customers. Look forward to your future visit!

review_text: Had a blast, definitely worth the experience. Heard about it on ads for the longest time then finally made it there last night. A little overpriced but everything was absolutely delicious and so much fun eating with your hands and just throwing it on the table. Everyone should experience this at least once, but we will be back!

I love the Cajun spiced mussels! So big and juicey. You come to this place for the fun experience and yummy food. I love the seafood fried rice! The staff was amazing and I would definitely go back. This is not an experience for someone who doesnt like to get a bit messy!

Try this captain s boil in kingsway ,service crew is nice   , i recommend to get the PIRATE, its worth 129 dollars with lobster, i think but we did not try it you add 15 dollars and get king crab feet its also good for 5-6 person. Maybe will try that next time   .

INCREDIBLE!! Fresh, plentiful Seafood! Very good prices! This location is just as good as the Richmond one. Food came right away. Great service! Can t wait to come back! Make sure you get the Captain s Boil sauce on everything!!

Me and my family went there for lunch and it was splendid. The staff were so nice and the food was great! The place felt really lively and it was a delightful experience. I will definitely come back soon!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for sharing your feedback. We are delighted to know that you had a great experience with us. Look forward to your future visit!

review_text: Id never been to a Captains Boil before but I will definitely go again! I loved it. Crazy messy, very important to wear the gloves and bib provided   Our waitress was delightful and very helpful in explaining how the food was presented, (in a boiled bag!), and how to eat it, (just use the table). She checked back regularly but not so often we couldnt enjoy a conversation. I cant wait to go back and try a different bag - o - boiled seafood.
Love this place. Definitely dont suggest wearing white but they got bibs. I love eating with my hands. Only thing I would change is maybe an option for smaller gloves for the kids
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your review. We are happy to hear that we were able to provide you with an enjoyable dining experience.

review_text: Relatively new Western style seafood place. Unlike some popular names in tourist destinations which usually taste awful and overpriced, the food here is actually tasty. Got the combo which wasnt cheap but worth a try. Would go again.

Took my family for a nice seafood dinner.  This was beyond my expectation; staff are friendly, the restaurant is clean. The food was amazing!! The portions are BIG, the flavor is spectacular.  Loved the lobster, mussels, shrimp, veggies, rice, chicken, fries. The energy was fun - music playing, guests enjoying their food. After we finished our seafood feast we were already planning our next visit. Definitely going back.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for your five-star review. We are delighted to hear that you had a positive experience with us at The Captains Boil. We hope you ll visit us again soon.

review_text: This restaurant is Amazing!! First time I ever ate a this type of eatery and will definitely go back. Fresh seafood right off the table getting messy and sucking up prawn brains. Good porting, selection and great flavours. N.B. Dont wear your Sunday clothes.
Went before the rush, staff was a little slow on certain things but overall the food was really good. Kind of expensive, but it is seafood.

First time there and we LOVED it!!  The Captains Boil blend of flavors was delicious.  We got a seafood fried rice and ordered a second, it was so good!  Definitely left with insanely full, happy bellies!!

Incredible is the simple way to describe it. Delicious, incredible portions, mouthwatering flavors. A liter of beer? What more can you ask for? We got shrimp (more like jumbo prawn) with Captains boil sauce, and another order with Cajun sauce. One came with potato and sausage, the other with potato and corn. Also an extra side order of fries. It was the perfect feast, and Ill definitely be back!
I love this place, the experience and itself is so unique. Its definitely expensive and a seafood isnt the freshest but its really good, the sauces are lovely and the dungeness and shrimp are local
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for sharing your feedback with us. We are delighted to know that you had a positive experience with us. Look forward to your future visit!

review_text: Real nice place to have party with friends! Thank to Evan for great service! My next party with friends gonna to be here! Highly recommended! Food : 5/5 |

review_text: I really enjoyed the food.  We had the garlic flavoring and everything was delicious.  The fish was super crispy and the fries were amazing hot.  We would definitely come back again.

Captain Boil is a big franchise seafood restaurant. It has more than 30 restaurants across Canada in different cities. There are five locations in the Great Vancouver area. I have been to the two locations before: one is on Robson St. Downtown and another one is on Kingsway Vancouver. Both of the locations served quite delicious seafood. Very enjoy eating at Captain Boil. Captain Boil Kingsway Location is at 3309 Kingsway, Vancouver, BC V5R 5K6. The same as Robson St. location, is a super busy street in Vancouver. Many restaurants are on the street. Such a great location to open a restaurant on this street. I have been to this location twice with my friends and fiances. The first time was all you can eat Mussels night. The second time was lunch combo. For all you can eat Mussels dinner, three of us had 2lbs mussels each plus fries. It was awesome. The big plastics bags were full of fresh seafood. Yummy! Captain Boil s Lunch combo is another great combination. Fish or Chicken Teriyaki with rice with Seafood Assortments (2 Crawfish, 2 Mussels, 2 Shrimps, and 2 Clams). The total is only $13, which is such a great deal. Super hot rice with teriyaki sauce on top is super delicious. Definitely, we should go back to Captain Boil again.
Fish and chips are really good, paired with spicy cajun fries. The dungeness crab is pricey but portion is big. Choose the captains boil sauce.
Had a real good time with family Default seasoning is great Excellent lobster and dungeoness crab Food : 5/5
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for leaving us a review. We appreciate your feedback and will address it with the team to ensure a better experience in the future. We hope to have the pleasure of welcoming you back in the future.

review_text: First time eatting at Captains Boil, with 2 others. We ordered Captains platter #3 (cant remember the name, because I wasnt the one paying the bill!), 2 lbs of crayfish, okra, fish & chips, and platter comes with Cajun seafood fried rice. Each protein with different sauces. Everything is delicious, even the Cajun fries!! I like the garlic sauce the best. THE CAJUN SEAFOOD FRIED RICE have SCALLOPS too and not mentioned on the menu!!!! The scallops were not added to the fried rice after telling our server about fatal allergy to scallops, so everyone can eat enjoy the fried rice drizzled with the yummy sauces. Will definitely eat at Captains Boil again!!!

Ill certainly come back, not too many options for kids though. Delicious prawns served in a very unique and messy way - do not come here with nice clothes on or for a first date, you will leave covered in sauce

review_text: First time at this restaurant and loved it. Different kind of dining experience,  where your food comes in a bag cooked and you have to eat with your hands. Food was awesome. Service was prompt and delightful.

review_text: Some special style seafood! If you are not too specific or picky about your sauce, their Captains boil sauce is recommended.
Awesome dinning experience, great food and friendly and helpful staff. Will certainly revisit.

review_text: Although it s a bit pricey the food never disappoints. I ve yet to try the all you can eat because the different crab options are too good to pass but I shall try it one day.

review_text: My family and I are always going to this location for a special occasion or if we are craving for some good seafood! We always order pounds of shrimp, the captain boil fried rice, and the Cajun fries. Great place to share seafood and eat with your hands with family and friends :)
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for your five-star review. We are delighted to hear that you had a positive experience with us at The Captains Boil. We hope you ll visit us again soon.

review_text: Really good food. Not too happy about using so much plastic though

review_text: The captains boil was so fun and had a cool vibe. They gave us gloves and had the most useful sizzers so you didnt have to work super hard for your crab. The captains choice seasoning was really good.  I also would have really liked to try the garlic. This is the first place we have eaten in Vancouver and they set the standard way high.  Also thanks for all of the recomendations.
Best seafood ever!! I love eating there and get messy   haven t been there for a while because it s quite expensive but it s worth it.
Food was out to us quickly,  great service.  Loved the lights and rest of the decor
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for taking a moment to share your experience at The Captains Boil. We are so pleased to hear you found your experience your liking. We look forward to welcoming you back again soon.

review_text: The food was so awesome and the staff afe so friendly. Be back again
The captains boil in kingsway is the way to go they have their own specials
My favorite place for seafood. Been going for few years and never had a problem with my food or service.
Absolutely love this place from customer service to food fantastic. The various options they have and talk about the best seafood I have ever had. Amazing delicious cant wait to return.

response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for sharing your feedback with us. We are delighted to know that you had a great experience with us. Look forward to your future visit!

review_text: First time here, great food, cooked perfectly, interesting way to eat.

What is not to love about fresh seafood.! I drive from surrey to come here. The food is always steaming hot. The servers are very sweet. I always get mild because got is really spicy but mild lets you enjoy the flavours. I really missed this place during the pandemic and Im happy they still stayed in business!
Very cool and romantic.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the review. Hope to see you again soon!

review_text: Great place to eat seafood. Reasonable prices and very nice staff!

Unique dine in experience compared to most of the local restaurants, great hospitality, good portions, variety of options to pick from. They also have customer parking at the rear which is a plus on a busy evening, which is usually the case. I would recommend this place to anyone who hasnt tried it yet.
Awesome place to dine with family. Wonderful food and service.
response_from_owner_text: Angelo, Thank you so much for your five-star review. We are delighted to hear that you had a positive experience with us at The Captains Boil. We hope you ll visit us again soon.

review_text: Best sea food in Vancouver! Always love bringmy friends and family over for a nice feast! Love the shrimp fired rice, dont you dare to get rid of it! Food
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your review. We are happy to hear that we were able to provide you with an enjoyable dining experience.

review_text: That was a great place to have some seafood and drinks!

I love the different experience to eat directly from a bag full of amazing and yummy options. The price is good and the shrimp is really delicious. The idea of the cool bib is incredible. When I said that my meal was too spicy - even asking no spice - they gave me another one, promptly. Moms Day - it was really crowded but worth it.
Was very good everything tasted great and the staff was great too definitely will be back again
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for taking a moment to share your experience at The Captains Boil. We are so pleased to hear you found your experience your liking. We look forward to welcoming you back again soon.

review_text: You couldnt go wrong with this place. Tasty, good serving size and a good price. Very friendly and polite staff. I love seafood, I can be here every weekend.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for the kind words. We look forward to serving you again soon!

review_text: A must see in Vancouver! Great food, service n vibe!

So much fun to eat with your hands! Great flavors, and excellent lunch prices of you prefer before 4pm. The only recommendation I have is to dim the lights slightly after 6pm. Best for well suited couples and NOT A FIRST DATE   SO MESSY! and so much fun.
I m seafood lover, Alaskan king crab was the best crab ever I had, the cajun flavour was so good, for sure will come back. Their portions are very generous.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Karwan, that s wonderful to hear. Thanks so much for leaving us a review. We look forward to seeing you again soon!

review_text: Great food & service!  Highly recommend!  Our group went for the share platter option. (Pirates Feast) Good value and very tasty!  With the 3 lbs of shrimp you can ask for 3 different flavors for each 1 lb.  (Captains Boil flavor was my fav)
One of my all time favorite places to have crab.  Its messy and unconventional but oh so delicious!!

Sooo delicious! Just went for the first time, ordered king crab legs with captains boil seasoning & medium heat with sausage and corn as sides. Also ordered Cajun fries and 1 lobster tail (not yet on the menu, but available if you ask) We are super impressed and will be back again soon :)
Great flavor, fun  to  eat,  many options, great packages  and good  beer! Sometimes  waiting time can be long , other  than that is  great  :) Wish their  spicy option was really spicy... Food
response_from_owner_text: We appreciate the positive feedback. It means a lot. See you next time!

review_text: Yamyamyam I want to go there soon! The fried rice is my favorite.

Great experience! We were seated quickly on a Thursday evening. Server was polite and friendly and the food we ordered took under 10 minutes to get to our table after ordering. You are given a plastic bib and gloves to start and everything is brought fresh.
My family loves the food here. Our go-to dishes on special occasions are the snow crab, shrimp fried rice and shrimp basket.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your review. We are happy to hear that we were able to provide you with an enjoyable dining experience.

review_text: Been here twice now both times was good. Got the gold and planium set dinner. Crab had firm and sweet tasting so I know it is fresh, not the frozen ones. Other items like the snow crab, clam, and shrimp are good as well. Only complain was all four sauces has some spice so unless your kids can take a tiny/mild spice, they wont like it much. My kid like the flavour but cant take the slight heat.
Food is absolutely delicious, but they really need to get the air vent/ AC upgraded. Every guest seated for dine in was sweating buckets.
response_from_owner_text: We appreciate the review. Thanks for taking the time. Have a great day!

review_text: This is a great place if you are really wanting some good ole fashioned seafood in a truly maritime fashion.  Be prepared to get your hands dirty.  The food was great if not a little salty but it was fun.  Everything you order comes out in plastic bags and is just plopped down in front of you.  You have plastic gloves on so that you can minimize the amount of sauce that you get on your hands.  The only thing that I might be concerned about is the large amount of plastic bags that they go through before every group.  Definitely not an environmental friendly place. Maybe they use bags that are biodegradable.  If they do, they should really market that better.
Service was good and fast. Will def come back again.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for sharing your feedback with us. We are delighted to know that you had a great experience with us. Look forward to your future visit!

review_text: This place is now my favorite restaurant Im gonna come here on my birthday on my girlfriends birthday and Im bringing my grandma here on her birthday cause the service is amazing and the food is so good, My favorite part of all those you eat with your hands and that makes you feel like a kid a gun great for children and just a fun meal highly recommend.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for taking time out of your day to review us. Hope you have an amazing day!

review_text: was so good... staff were friendly.... food was served fast. we had one of the FEASTS and it was so much food for 2 people but made for great bed snacks later :)
response_from_owner_text: So glad you had a great experience, Tyler. Have a wonderful day!

review_text: Really tasty unique food. Just be prepared to make a mess and be advised its quite expensive. Bring an appetite.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for your five-star review. We are delighted to hear that you had a positive experience with us at The Captains Boil. We hope you ll visit us again soon.

review_text: The restaurant was amazing. We came there last week and ordered various seafood, fry and oyster. food was so tasty and especially their Dungeness crab was awesome. fresh and a lot of meat. Fresh seafood, tasty sauce, cheerful servers. for sure I will go again with my family!
Amazing food Great prices Food
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for sharing your feedback with us. We are delighted to know that you had a great experience with us. Look forward to your future visit!

review_text: Very interesting place to experience something different with various seafood. They are way more organized with decent service than before and we did not have to wait for a table no longer than 20min. They do take reservations, and they know what they are doing.  : ) I would definitely come back again.  Good job, crew!

Theres this place in California called Boiling Crab where waiting times are often 45+ minutes. At the time, when I used to live around the area for several years, my family and I thought the food was legendary and we would eat there at least once a month. However, when my family and I moved to Canada and discovered this place, we were blown away at how much more delicious the food was. When we vacationed at California and tried out the Boiling Crab restaurant, there was a sharp difference in quality. Captains Boil truly is amazing. Their food is beyond legendary.

The best place to get down & dirty with your food!  Had so much fun & the food was awesome. Its definitely a great place to go with friends & enjoy seafood that is fresh & very tasty. We loved it & well be back soon!

Strongly suggest to try their fried rice and seafood. It feels relax I can grab the food by hand and eat without any cutlery. The spicy level is really mild, so the spicy lover prob need to ask making the food extra extra spicy

The location is very easy to find, its between Joyce & Kingsway. The prices are considered cheap compare to other seafood restaurants. Orders comes in lbs and I say a pound of shrimps is good for two people sharing as their servings are quite large. And also, the sauce is more spicy than expected. You should try the captains boil sauce, its superb!   And lastly, make sure to make reservations, theres a crowd!

Amazing service, very attentive and charming. Food was amazing, and the customizations are endless. Portion size is generous and the sauces are delicious ; not to mention that th seafood is fresh and tasty. The experience is worth the cost. Would definitely come again.

Definitely one of my new favourite places! Fresh and extremely tasty food, very friendly and helpful staff, great prices, fun atmosphere and decor, good for large groups or small intimate meals. If youve never been, theres no cutlery or dishware, food arrives bagged and everything is an amazing hands on experience. They provide bibs and gloves if youre concerned about splatters etc, and snips and claw crackers to break open the legs and claws. The Captains Boil flavour is the best, and omg the Cajun fries. Havent had a Dungeness crab in years, but I devoured every tasty morsel with a huge grin on my face, wrist deep in sauce, and licking them clean every chance I got. Definitely worth a try if youve never been and love seafood!

Came here for the annual ayce shrimp with the family. Service was great, our server suggested items suitable for the kids and she modified them to be non spicy. There were a lot of options to choose from and our server took her time to get everything right.

Good experience to eat . Our first time and we like the food. Messy when we grind but we are the warriors doesnt matter. . Lil bit hight pricey  but I dont if I got a discount when I come back . 5 start for me for my first time.
Tastey seafood, superb menu and fantastic friendly staff. Highly recommend    Keep up the good work and  hope to see  more  the Captains Boil restaurants. Surrey would love a yummy addition
I visited to buy 2boils event, but it was only used for store meals, so I bought the basic menu and picked it up. It was good and I think Ill use it again next time
response_from_owner_text: Glad to learn your experience was a positive one. See you next time!

review_text: As it was Eid yesterday, i wanted try some sea food. Hence, ordered Mix and Match from Ubereats. It was amazing. The gravy in this dish was awesome and spice level was up to the mark.

Was our first time eating at The Captains Boil and it was so good! The service was pretty good and the food was bomb. One of our new favorite places... Just make sure you wash up before you leave lol I walked around the grocery store after with sauce all over my face after.

Sea foods at its best. Eating the king crabs,  shrimps and squid with your hands makes it more comfy and tastier. But you are provided with an apron and plastic gloves in order not to smell after. We went to Kingsway branch and service and food was great!
Decent prices and good food. Dont come wearing fancy clothes and be prepared to make a mess
The food is beyond amazing.. absolutely delicious and I totally recommend this place
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your review. We are happy to hear that we were able to provide you with an enjoyable dining experience.

review_text: Foods delicious and service is awesome

Totally amazing assault on your taste buds. Very clever unforgettable food presentation which is unique and the sauces adapted to suit your taste and mood. Ideal for sharing. Sincerely hope to be back one day.

Incredible seafood, always tastes fresh, and the prices are very good. Its the excellent sauces, and the atmosphere, great visual style, and novel, messy, eat with your hands experience that really make it special though.

Amazingly delicious seafood thats fresh and well seasoned. We had the Dungeness crab at market price, which I thought was expensive but it was definitely worth it, was at least 2 lbs as described and it was a super meaty and delicious crab!

Their shrimp is probably my favorite food in the world. Lots of garlic, so much shrimp meat. Order a cup of rice, squeeze some lime on it, put lots of the sauce they season the shrimp with, and eat away. You will not regret it. Its a bit expensive but...
Seafood lovers rejoice. This is the place you want to be. The place is packed during dining hours. Reserve in advance for a big group. Be prepared to use your hands. Parking is a challenge as well.

Gloriously messy. The tables are covered in butcher paper, you eat with plastic gloves and a bib, and theres a dedicated sink by the front desk for patrons to wash up after dinner. Recommended for first dates and business meetings, to weed out the overly-dainty.

The best seafood that I ever taste in my lifespan! This place is awesome with very eficient and kind service all the time. It fills all your expectations and you will completly in love of this restaurant!
Tasty seafood with the unforgettable sauce(the captain s boil) !
Had a wonderful experience there with food and environment. The staff is very quick. The food is so unbelievably good . I will surly go there again and suggest everyone to give it a visit.
Amazing! We were here for my father in laws birthday and well definitely be coming back
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your review. We are happy to hear that we were able to provide you with an enjoyable dining experience.

review_text: Awesome food!
response_from_owner_text: Glad to learn your experience was a positive one. Hope you have an amazing day!

review_text: My husband and I spent a weekend in Seattle and then traveled by train to Vancouver. We went straight from the train station to the restaurant and had the best meal of our trip so far. The crab baguette was fantastic. Crusty yet soft baguette with an explosion of flavors. The fennel slaw added an amazing crunch and flavor. We also had the salmonito wrap. Fresh and fantastic - the salmon was cut right then and there to make our wrap. The fries were excellent too and we dipped them in the housemade tartar sauce. The staff was incredible and made sure we were happy with our food. I don t often leave reviews but this was too good not to note. Take the time to visit this slightly out of the way spot. You won t be disappointed. I m hoping my first visit to Vancouver won t be my last because I ll be dreaming of this food for awhile.

After a long and rewarding stroll from downtown to the Bloedel conservatory, I enjoyed one of the best , if not the best, fish and chips of my life. I was recommended to try the halibut and, oh boy! Heavenly, not oily at all, crispy and light, seasoned to perfection. A generous serving of fish on a bed of fantastic fries, coleslaw and tartar dip.
