Super friendly staff, cool and laidback interior, with some seating by the window. Really really recommended, as they focus on local, seasonal and sustainable seafood. Really awesome!

Really enjoyed the cod fish and chips. Loved that their fries are fresh handcut fries. The fish was very fresh - looking forward to trying other fish types and items. We ate on the bench outside with our dog and it was the perfect casual dinner.

Its usually halibut, salmon, or cod managed to veer off my typical menu choices and explore the Arctic Char for my Fish and Chips order. From the onset, the service representative demonstrated a commendable level of hospitality and eagerness to cater to this unique request since it was not on the menu that was very nice of them. Now, onto the main event - the Arctic Char Fish and Chips. To say it was superb would be an understatement. The perfectly fried Arctic Char exceeded all my expectations. It was succulent and full of flavour, pairing harmoniously with the crispy chips. This dish struck a perfect balance between the delicate fish and the satisfyingly crunchy chips. Its like a perfect balance between trout and salmon in taste. This was, without a doubt, the best Arctic Char Fish and Chips I have ever had in Canada. Their tartar sauce is also to die for they now sell it in mason jars great choice. Rating: 5/5 Stars

Got the Halibut fish and chips. The halibut was so tender and moist and fresh and the batter wasnt too heavy, perfectly crisp with a delicious tartar sauce. The atmosphere was charming and the employees were friendly.
Delicious crispy fresh food with lots of options to being home too. Definitely on my list to return to next time Im in Vancouver!

A very cool local spot with gluten free fish and chips!!! So amazing. Fries and halibut chips were outstanding and cooked in a separate safe frier. Worth the trek. Also got the dairy free clam chowder!

I got the halibut fish and chips and clam chowder. The fish was fluffy, not greasy and best fish from fish n chips that I ve tasted. The service was really attentive and nice! Clam chowder was different wasn t creamy was more like a stew. They sell some sauces, seafood on the side. A few spots to sit inside and at the counter. They have glasses for water as you eat. :)
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much Annie, we really try our best and this review is amazing for us to read. The team and I really appreciate the great review. It means a lot.

review_text: I recently had the pleasure of dining at Fish Counter, and I must say, it was a truly delightful experience from start to finish. As a seafood enthusiast, I am always looking for the perfect fish and chips, and I can confidently say that I found it here. When I walked in, I was greeted by a warm and friendly staff that made me feel right at home. The restaurants ambiance is charming, with a nautical theme that adds to the overall dining experience. The batter was perfectly crispy, providing that satisfying crunch with every bite. The fish itself was incredibly fresh, flaky, and full of flavor. It was clear that only the highest quality ingredients were used. I cant wait to return and indulge in another round of their mouthwatering fish and chips.

Halibut & chips and fried oysters have a nice light batter. Very fresh from the sea. The halibut was cooked perfectly maintaining its texture with a lightness to it. Absolutely delicious. The fries were also very good, tasted freshly cut and fried, somewhat like NY Fries. We got takeout so the oysters were a bit overcooked and cold by the time we got home. But when eating at the counter, very nice! This time, disappointed with the size. I ordered four oysters, and at $3.99 each, I expected them to be bigger. Here you can see that they are the size of a tablespoon. Aside from the size of the oysters, I give this place 5 stars for the quality and taste.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Kathy, Thank you for taking the time to write a review, Im happy to see that you enjoyed your experience here. Apologies about the oyster size they have been a little small lately maybe due to weather? Weve informed our chef to put extra oysters in orders. Hopefully next time you visit we will have our 3 inch oysters back.

review_text: We are repeat customers!  This is the best fish and chips shop in the city and I am very sure it is not close. Loved it all today!  And a big fan of the new scallop bites.  Fun!

The blazing heat of a summer day found us here. We had crispy cod tacos, Salmonito, crab and shrimp baguette, and clam chowder. The clam chowder wowed us with its satiny texture and the tortillas in the tacos were super soft. The crispy fried fish was packed full of flavor!We sat inside, eating and watching the world go by. The place is very cozy with its wooden beams and sells pickles and other tangy condiments.  Definitely going back!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much Bartika, we are very glad we made your experience one to remember and hope to see you soon.

review_text: Super friendly staff, and delicious fish & chips, fish  tacos and more. Fast service and super fresh. They also sell their homemade tartar sauce, and several other local products. We stopped here during a flight layover (30 minutes from the airport via the Canada line/walking), and it definitely hit the spot. Would recommend and will come back next time we are in town!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much Kim, I hope you had a nice flight and cant wait to have you guys visit again!

review_text: I recently had the pleasure of indulging in a plate of fish and chips at a local eatery, and I must say, it was a delightful experience that took me on a nostalgic culinary journey. The star of the dish, undoubtedly, is the fish. The fillet was tender and flaky inside, with a satisfyingly crisp and golden-brown batter on the outside. It was clear that the fish had been freshly prepared, contributing to its succulent texture. The tartar sauce, on the other hand, was tangy and creamy, complementing the dish well. Considering the generous portion size and the quality of the ingredients, the dish offered good value for money.

They nailed both the fish and chips! The halibut wasnt oily and had the perfect crispiness. It had the right seasoning and texture, and it was amazing with the tartar sauce. The crab and shrimp sandwiches were also amazing. Overall its an amazing place and Ill definitely come back for the oyster sandwiches some day!
response_from_owner_text: Come before the summer! The colder the weather the better the oysters! Thank you for your review Alistair the team did a great job and Im happy you enjoyed your food.

review_text: Freshly battered and fragrant fish and chips! Ordered the cod fish and it was really fresh and smooth inside with the crispy batter outside. Breaded oysters was surprising good too. Very delicious and will definitely go back again.
response_from_owner_text: Oh YEAAHHHHHHHH. Thank you. See you soon.

review_text: UPDATE2023-went back here last week. HOLY SCHITZU! THEY STILL ROCK! FAST and plentiful. Both my Cod F&C and my wifes Fish Ts were awesome. Thanks again you guys..The Gfree Fish tastes amazing..greatly appreciated! Dont waste your money anywhere else..this is THE PLACE! The front end staff also..super friendly and helpful while you wait! **OLD REVIEW** BEST We had 4 fish fish tacos (cod) and two piece GlutenFree Fishnchips (cod).  Well I will tell ya..the fish tacos...are true to form what a fish taco should be..generous and delicious! Plentiful helpings! The GlutenFree breading on the Fishnchips? Take it from a certified Celiac..truely beautiful! You guys showed me I can still have real fish n chips that tastes EFFIN amazing too! Thank you. Officially TheFishCounter is our GoTo fish taco and fishnchip place from now on. Dont waste yr money anywhere else! This place rocks! And the polite fast service just made it refreshing after our crazy covid days! Thanks you guys..keep it up!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much, I m glad your able to enjoy our Fish and Chips gluten free. Our partners with the batter have done a great job working with us and we are really happy you enjoyed everything. See you in the near future!

review_text: This is a small little spot with some delicious food. The cook (who I think was the owner) was very friendly to everyone who came in. The fish and chips is very tasty!

Halibut & chips and fried oysters were delicious. They have a nice light batter too. Found their dishes so fresh and was cooked perfect. The texture and flavor absolutely perfect. The fries were freshly cut and fried. I give this place 5 stars for their quality food and taste.

Parking: We had lunch at 130 on a Monday and there were several street parking available. Ambience: fast pace Service: The service was very welcoming and they offered many great recommendations Food: I ordered the Oyster Poboy which was ok to me. Halibut fish and chips which i would have to say is the best fish & chips I ve had, and the tasty crab & shrimp baguette. Overall: Everything was great. I will definitely be returning.

Best gluten-free fish and chips I ever had anywhere in the world. (~$15) Its hard to find a place that does gluten free batter and also have a seperate fryer for that. Cod was very fresh, the batter is crispy, yet light and not oily. The one piece portion is actually quite filling even it looks small in the picture. (Also comes with alot of fries). Good condiments: A slice of fresh lemon, container of gourmet tartar sauce (likely made inhouse?), and things you can request like ketchup, hot sauce, malt vinegar.  Hot sauce seems homemade too. Chips are more like north american style fries, the shoestring kind. I would be having a thicker cut if I had fish and chips where its a native dish (UK/NZ/OZ), so the chips here were so-so for me, but still warm and fresh... Just feels greasier because of this cut. Luckily theres some very refreshing coleslaw on the side and I really enjoyed that. I think it had cabbage and kale in it. I also tried their clam chowder, also gluten free. It was very hearty and you could tell there are wasnt any artificial flavouring, the flavour was just powered by alot of clams and celery/carrot/potato base.  The portion is quite small but it was a nice side to have (~$7).  Its not cream based, just very tender potatoes that are driving the thickness. There is a counter for buying fresh fish and fish patties, and local artisanal condiments.  The people working are very friendly.  Highly recommended for a quick bite, its about 7 mins wait only.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for the positive and detailed review, it really helps us. Yes we do make our tartar sauce in house and we are really happy you enjoyed it. Hope to see you soon!

review_text: Incredible Gluten free Halibut and chips. Was so happy to hear there have a separate dedicated fryer. Staff are friendly and knowledgeable about allergens for gluten. Fish was crispy and fries were hot a delicious. Will definitely be back.

Ordered crab and shrimp baguette for me and crab and shrimp sandwich for my daughter. Both were phenomenal.  They were fresh and delicious. Along side we ordered chips that were freshly cut and fried. Prices are fair and worth it. We enjoyed there atmosphere too. Would love to drop in again. Big thumbs up!! Food

The fish here was fresh and delicious- we had the gluten-free fish and chips and the salmon tacos- all tasted great. The service was also really good - especially for a counter-style restaurant. The gentleman cooking was helpful and kind. Overall this place went above and beyond our expectations!

The fish counter is an awesome place to eat and chill. I visited here with my friends and tried few of their dishes. Tacos, Oyster PO boy, fish and chips, halibut and clam chowder. Everything was freshly made. All were damn delicious. We enjoyed their food and great service, would love to come again for sure:)

They use top-notch ingredients, and you can truly taste the difference. The fish is always fresh and perfectly cooked, resulting in a delightful crispy batter and tender, flaky cod. Its pure seafood perfection! The portion sizes at The Fish Counter are very generous. I typically opt for the 2 piece pacific cod, and its more than enough to satisfy two hungry individuals. The staff at The Fish Counter create a warm and welcoming atmosphere, making us feel appreciated. Its no surprise that The Fish Counter often has a lineup. Trust me, the wait is absolutely worth it. If you happen to be in the area, I highly recommend checking them out.

I just love the ambience of the Fish Counter. The staff is super friendly and fast. I dropped in on the way to my office to grab my breakfast. I bought Oyster PO boy sandwich and cod tacos. They were absolutely fresh and yummy. I really wanted to give them a big thumbs up. So sending them 5 stars

I have been wanting to eat at the Fish Cafe for a very long time.  It was always closed lunch times when I went.  Fortunately, this Friday it was opened to my delight.  The waitress said it is sometimes closed during lunch times.  She didnt give a reason why.  I ordered the blackened steelhead and rice.  It was served in a frying pan.  The fish was tender and moist.  It melted in my mouth.  The yellow rice was good.  It came with lemon caper sauce.  It was the first time I tried steelhead and blackened cooking method.  I was impressed with my meal.  I intend to come back and try the arctic char.  First time that I heard of this fish.

This is the place to come for fish and chips in Vancouver. Fish was delicious and the batter was cohesive. The only downside is the fries were just barely acceptable. They were over fried, short, and quite dry. The two piece portion is very large
response_from_owner_text: Hi Andrew, Thank you for the kind review. We are actively looking for a solution for the small potatoes we are getting which turns into small and unwanted fries. I am happy to say a few of our ideas are about to become reality! One of which is turning the smaller potatoes into meals that me can hand to the homeless/turning them into potato chips. We should be up and running in a few weeks with this program! Not only will this result in larger potatoes for our fries, but our smaller ones dont go to waste! Thank you for your continued support!

review_text: After hearing a couple of friends rave about this place on Main Street, and their fish & chips in particular, I decided to give it a try. Came inside on Saturday afternoon (face mask required) and was immediately greeted by an employee, super friendly and efficient, he took our orders: Two piece halibut, and 2 piece salmon, and we picked up a couple of beverages from a well-stocked fridge on the side. The restaurant side is relatively small, with sitting available for 6 people, but we were lucky and found ourselves a couple of seats. After about 10 minutes our order was brought to us, it was amazing! I opened my compostable container and found 2 huge pieces of halibut in a bed of french fries and a scoop of cold slaw. The fish was thick and tasty, the batter gold and crispy, deep fried to perfection... fries cut small, perfect size... cold slaw tangy and super fresh. Order came with a container with tartar sauce and catsup. After the halibut, I tried a piece of salmon, presented exactly as the first, and equally tasty and crispy! Now its my turn to recommenf this place to others, check them out! They have take-out as an option, if you prefer. To round this establishment out, they have a fresh fish section inside as well, with a very nice selection of seafood to bring back home.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Octavia, this review really means a lot. Thank you very much.

review_text: Always a great place for seafood fare! I brought out of town visitors for fish and chips and then time by the ocean. Great! Gluten-free options available. Highly recommended Dietary restrictions: Great! Gluten-free options including gluten-free, fish and chips

Such a perfect spot for Fish and Chips! I recently shifted to Vancouver and heard many are talking about this place. I found their service was so fast. Food was fresh and well cooked. They have Gluten Free options available. I tried their Oyster PO boy Sandwich and Halibut fish N chips. Great taste. Theres something special about their sauces and batters. They are just perfectly blend with dishes. This place has become my favorite restaurant in Vancouver already. Waiting to try their other dishes too.

I really enjoyed their seafood chowder , Cod fish and chips. The food was so fresh and delicious. I love this little Fish n Chips place. They have the perfect choices suitable for anyone. Would love to try their other dishes too.

Small and very busy place for Fish and chips . The Clam chowder soup on its own is very filling . Its a great tasting soup. The 2 piece cod was excellent as well . It is lighty breaded so it is definitely more fish than breading . Very reasonable pricing , it is a little difficult getting a seat to enjoy but definitely pn my repeatable list .
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much Jason, we are currently working on adding some more seats for our great customers. Hopefully we have it set up before your next visit for you to enjoy. Many thanks, it means a lot.

review_text: Super awesome place for some freshly made fish and chips.  The Fish Counter, as the name implies, is where the purchases are made at the counter.  Seating is very causal, with a few tables and benches.  The pacific cod and chips combo, fish taco, mushy peas, crispy oysters and clam chowder were all amazing.  The fish is perfectly made with a thin coat of batter thats fried with a balance of crispiness and soft texture.  The tasty batter does not soak up too much oil, thus it isnt too greasy.  Highly recommended!
Small little space but with best fish and chips I think i ve had in quite a while. Fish was fresh and delicious. Definitely going back again! Dietary restrictions: They have gluten free options!
Currently closed for restoration after a fire! Nov 2023 Great food, efficient and friendly staff, good amount of seating. Would definitely recommend coming when they are open again.
Best fish and chips in town! Food was great, we had the salmon, cod in both regular and gluten free batter.
Our team visited today, unfortunately the fire that occurred has The Fish Counter closed for restoration for a few weeks. Cant wait to have the fish n chips again!

Consistently superior to any other F&C place in town. Great service but it s all about the food. I like the cod and have heard their gluten free batter is very good. The bouillabaisse is chock full of seafood, veggies and very rich. Be mindful of the days/hours so as not to be disappointed. You won t be disappointed.
response_from_owner_text: Wow! Thank you so much Doug this review really means a lot to us! We try our best to keep a great service while also really focusing on the food that goes out. Again, thank you very much and we hope to see you in the future Doug.

review_text: Definitely some of the best halibut fish and chips I ve had.  A little oily but still incredible.   The tartar sauce was better than most I ve had.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much J, I ll let the chef know right away that the halibut was a little oily,  it I m happy that didn t ruin your experience with us. We hope to see you in the near future. Thanks again!

review_text: All I can say is yum. By far the best fish and chips in Vancouver. Made to order, fresh, delicious and crisp. They have gluten free batter (YAY) and some amazing soups too. Theres always a lineup which is no surprise because the quality is superb.
Awesome service and friendly staff. Large portions and big pieces. Quality and cooked to order. Delicious is youre in for fish sandwiches like oyster poboy or crab shrimp sandwich.

The best fish and chips youll ever eat! The place is small, you might not get a place to seat, but it is not necessary because when something is THAT good, you dont need to sit down to enjoy it. The pieces are so big, plenty of fries, great coleslaw, speedy service and if you want to buy some raw fish to take home, you certainly can! Not to mention other fish and seafood products, as well as condiments. I am going back and very soon!

A cool place and the staff is super friendly and accommodating. Had fish and chips with fresh halibut and black cod (black cod wins - buttery, juicy with the perfected coating of the crispy beer batter and was melting in my mouth!!). Greatly recommend this place!

Hands down the best fish tacos I had in my life. 4 for $20 but you can feel that these are not your average lightweight tacos that you get at a bar or wherever else you get them. Crispy fried fish with fresh salad -none of that soggy week-old one. If I was living in Vancouver, I d come here every other week. Hats off!

A really great spot on Main Street to relax with some comfort food. The fish tacos are spot on with flavor and a good selection of house made sauces if you need an extra punch. If you need ingredients for dinner check out the display past the register.
Very good fish and chips and crab baguette.  The tacos were a little bland and lacked something but the prices were so good for the portions. Definitely coming back.

The food is amazing, the staff makes you feel welcomed, but the best thing is the vibe, having a delicious halibut fish and chips, while watching people and cars passing on Main Street thats what makes you feel you belong. Overall I was a great experience. Food
Got the halibut and clam chowder. The fish is very tender on the inside and crispy on the outside. Chowder is tasty too. Would come again and try the fried oysters next time

The Fish Counter is my favourite place for fish and chips! They use quality ingredients and you can really taste the difference. They also have the best tartar sauce (I always order extra!). I order the 2 piece pacific cod and its enough for 2 people. The portion sizes are generous. I also give them bonus points for using compostable takeaway containers. The staff are very friendly and incredibly efficient. Kudos to them for making their customers feel welcome and appreciated. This place is lined up for good reason. If youre in the area, definitely check them out. Its worth the wait!
Best fish and chips in the city. Dairy free clam chowder also delish. Buy a jar of their tartar sauce for home Dietary restrictions: Dairy free

The fresh and frozen fish is always delicious and fairly priced. Its one of the only fish markets in the area so its our go to. The selection isnt massive, but we kind of like that since were never overwhelmed by options. The fish and chips are also delicious (but pricey). The tartar sauce is great.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much, We are more then happy to be your neighborhood fish market. If you need any type of fish that we might be carrying in the case let us know and we can bring it in the next day! Thank you so much, see you soon Jake.

review_text: This place is great -- people come here for the fish and chips and their different selections of fish they offer for that, but I feel like the fish and chips is the weakest thing on the menu.  The crab and shrimp baguette and salmonito are phenomenal.  It also doubles as a store for fresh seafood.  The only downside I would say is it is a tad bit expensive, but its worth it.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Sunil, Im so happy to hear you like the crab & shrimp baguette and the salmonito. Thank you and take care.

review_text: Such a nice spot for a late lunch. We ordered the fish and chips and one of the sandwiches and quickly grabbed a couple of the few spots to sit near the window. Order came up quick  and the only regret we had was that we didnt try more items.

If you are feeling like fish and youre around the area, Id suggest coming here. Small operation with big taste. Had myself the lingcod tacos, and oh man was it good! My coworker had the halibut fish and chips, and was very satisfied, as was I! Recommended! Gilad and Amy were wonderful to us!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Joe, we hope to see you soon!

review_text: Fish was great, fries were good, price was not too bad for the quality. Only rating 4 stars as they offer indoor dining but have a bathroom that is  out of service  which I m pretty sure is against a few health codes (not to mention its a pandemic and not being able to wash your hands before eating seems problematic)
Very delicious food!!! One of the best in town. Not too many seats in the shop though

My husband and I hit this place every time we are in Vancouver. You get big portions and they are worth every penny. The gluten free fish and chips are awesome. Things to note - I dont think there are bathrooms and there are not a lot spaces to sit. So I recommend going when its not busy if you want to sit.

Fresh and good. Friendly, efficient service. Clean. Limited seating or stand up counter to eat your food but most people get it to go. Today I had the cod and chips, looking to try there fish tacos next. Recycling responsible establishment.
The Salmonito Burrito is my favorite go to lunch for a healthy delicious and affordable meal. Highly recommended if you want something light!
This place is just fantastic! Amazing fish and chips and they offer gluten-free, non-alcoholic options. The serving is generous. You can t go wrong here
Excellent fish n chips, great staff and atmosphere. I m celiac and they have gluten free fish n chips at no extra charge!!!! My wife said they taste even better than regular ones!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Amir, Im happy you enjoyed your halibut & chips. Always a pleasure having you in the store. Merci

review_text: Great local joint based from sustainable sources! First time here I got the oyster po boy. Loved the crispy batter on the big fresh oysters and the light slaw (I hate creamy coleslaw so this was perfect for me). The best part was the soft warm toasted bun with the perfect thickness. Theres no formal seating (benches and standing tables) and half of the shop is a store with fresh as well as prepared seafood
Best place in Vancouver for Fish and Chips. I always take my dinner on Fridays from Fish Counter. It has become my go to food store now. Fresh and Yummy!

Delicious. Although they made me question humanity when the cashier asked if I wanted tartar sauce with my fish and chips which implies there s people that don t want tartar. Who are these people that eat deep fried fish and potatoes but say no to tartar sauce? I want to be friends with them so I can have their share. The po boy is yummy and so is their clam chowder. I think you can skip Steveston altogether and just come here. The only negative is the seating and no water view. There s not much seating and if you re sitting outside you re awkwardly facing someone that s inside on the counter side.
Great place for fish and chips. The fish are a good size but they give a LOT of fries. I personally like the cod and chips, with a few oysters!

This place was great :) delicious food and nice people. My 9 year old son had been craving fish n chips for a while so we stopped in on a whim. He said it was his favorite hes had. I loved the oyster po boy and will be coming back for more.

Great food, but limited seating. They really want you to dine in for eco reasons but there isnt a lot of space. Love that they have a gluten free fryer! Very knowledgeable and aware staff for celiac. Dietary restrictions: Gluten free fryer and options
Visited for fish and chips and was thoroughly impressed. The staffs friendliness added to the enjoyable experience. Highly recommended!
Best fresh Oyster , and fish snadwitches. I would say the prices for the ready made food , is a little high. Rather than that, amazing place. My favourite, all year long.
The best fish and chips ever! They serve fresh fish! Tartar sauce is very good!
First time here today. Really liked the fish here. Ordered the Wild Salmon and the Lingcod. The Lingcod fish was nice and flaky. Inside was nice and moist also. Will be back

This a great place for gluten-free,  nut-free, egg-free fish and chips.  Cod, halibut and salmon were in the menu, and we ordered the cod, which is substantiallyless expensive than the other two.  The cod was flakes and fresh, and the crust is amazingly crunchy. Staff and customers are friendly and accommodating, and need to be as the indoor dining area can only accommodate about 10 people at a time.  8am Parking: No dedicated lot.  There is a pay lot about 2 blocks away. Street parking can be found a few blocks walk from the restaurant as the immediate streets are restricted to residents.
I had the Cod. The one-piece was definitely enough for me. Fries are good, and not too hard. Sauce is yummy, and I ran out of it too quickly.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for this great review Lio, we are really happy you enjoyed everything. Next time we will give you some extra sauce no problem :)

review_text: Amazing, amazing customer service. And for my fellow gluten free eaters, yes, you can eat here. (Yay, right?!) They have awesome GF fish and chips. Like, so good, guys. I trekked all the way across town just to try this place and it was worth it. GO HERE.
This place gets a lot of props for being the best fish and chips in Van city and honestly I think its pretty deserved. Definitely not a huge seating space but fresh and yummy seafood.
My first time trying fish and chips   and it s good! Portion is huge, and food is fresh, crispy
Best fish and chips in Vancouver. The dudes working are super friendly. GF batter is like no other.

Ive been meaning to try The Fish Counter for months now after great recommendations from a few friends and they definitely delivered! Crunchy flavourful fish and crispy fries that you can continuously keep munching on. I suggest calling in your order ahead of time for there is always a wait.
response_from_owner_text: Hi KP, smart to call ahead of time, especially if you are looking to pick your food up after 5. Thank you for finally coming to The Fish Counter.

review_text: Best fish and chips in Vancouver! We go here any excuse we get. A great one is to bring any GF friends out, as they have a DEDICATED gluten-free fryer. Be prepared for a wait of about 20 minutes. Always good. Lots of fries, shoestring type. Great tartar, generous portion. Coleslaw is light on mayo.
One of the best fish & chip joints in town. If only the had more seating available. Also difficult to find parking.
Amazing little fish n Chips shop. Love that I can have delicious gluten free fish and chips! Super nice  shop, feels like a homey little place
response_from_owner_text: Hi Elizabeth, Thank you for leaving a kind review, Im happy to hear you enjoyed the GF cod you ordered and the halibut. Thank you again, we hope to be your neighborhood fish store!

review_text: Wow. Just wow. Unfortunately I have only been lucky enough to try their fish tacos. They were really yummy, the fish is just so fresh and delicious and made to perfection. Im really excited to come back and try some of the sandwiches I saw on the menu.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Patrick, like Valerie said we got the best poboy in town. Try it out and let me know!

review_text: Had to go into the city yesterday and thought we d find an interesting place for lunch. We had our grandson with us who is gluten-free and we re so was so happy to find this fish and chip shop that offered gluten-free fish and chips as well. The fish was fresh and delicious. Thanks so much for how you consider the eating needs of others we would definitely come here again.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Leslie, Thank you so much for the kind words and I m happy to see you enjoyed your stay. Gluten free and dairy free products are very important to us here and I m glad you enjoyed everything. Thank you again

review_text: The gluten free fish and chips were crunchy and tasty, my daughter loves them... Ordering ahead worked out perfectly... Will be regulars!

Had the most delicious experience today at The Fish Counter. Locally sourced fish freshly made and great recipes. The Chowder was fresh creamy and rich without being heavy. The fish and Chips were crispy and just the right amount of flavour - never oily.... and the Tartar Sauce is to die fo! Traditional TarTar sauce is like nothing you have had before. And did you know that fish stay fresher longer when on bamboo boards as opposed to plastic? Check this out as your next grab and go good food stop.
Great place for fish and chips (and chowder). The seafood is fresh and the food is delicious. Great service. Highly recommended but seating is limited.
Great place that has a good variety of fish n chips and other seafood dishes. Good for quick eats or take out.

Every month I should have at least 2 meals at this awesome place. This fish and chips restaurant never disappoints in providing the best fried fish in town. Their portion size is extremely good and it is always fresh.
Always fresh and delicious! Had the Shrimp and Crab Baguette this time. The Po Boy is also brilliant. Is buy their slaw in jars if they sold it too.

Took out their dairy free clam chowder and loved it! Its potato based and chock full of celery, carrots and onions. There could be more clams within the chowder (perhaps its dependent on the scoop you get), but it was still hearty. Hopefully they add other dairy free soup varieties in the future! Would love to see a fish chowder, and try their GF fish and chips.
I tried all of the fish and Chips, and they were all excellent. Fresh fish cooked to ferfection
A great selection of sustainably caught seafood and their menu is very reasonably priced.  Portion sizes are plentiful and the staff are always warm and friendly with fast and efficient service.

I ve been going here for many years and the fish quality is the best in the city that I ve seen. It s fresh and the service is second to none. I wanted to point out that Armand greets me by name every time and is by far one of the nicest guys on all of Main Street. I think the owner needs to acknowledge that he s an outstanding manager and he makes the experience of shopping there very desirable each and every time. Thanks to Armand and the team for your exceptional service and genuine style of taking good care of your customers. Highly recommended!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much Ron, Its been our pleasure to serve you and your family for almost 2 years now. This review and your support of our family business really means a lot. Thank you again.

review_text: The best halibut and chips in town! It s always generous portions and perfectly cooked. I love the open set up inside with bar seating and all of the air circulation. They also have a good selection of NA drinks. 100% recommend.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much Christopher, this means a lot!

review_text: Just the best fish and chips in town. Not to be missed if youre a fish and chip person

Good food and always excellent service.  Halibut cakes are so good!  An easy dinner to take home.  Make sure you get their tartar sauce to go with them!  Of course you can t go wrong with the fish n chips and the heaping portion of fries.  Chowder is also delicious.  I don t have anything bad to say!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for the kind review, I just told the staff and everyone s very happy. It s always nice to see hard work pay off! Thank you again.

review_text: Love fish counter!  Awesome fish and chips and other yummy food!
The good is awesome.   Especially, the fish are not oily even it is cold.  LOVE IT
Oysters were best Ive had, fantastic clams, and great service overall. Highly recommended
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Thomas, Love to hear this. Thank you for the review and recommendation.

review_text: We had a fabulous time here! The staff is so friendly and welcoming. The oysters are incredibly fresh and good quality. They also pour the wine to the very top of the glass, which is fun!
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Alisha, We are so happy to hear you had fun! Thank you so much for the review.

review_text: This place is a  must ! Here, one can find delicious oysters, and the happiest Happy-Hour (complete with generous pours of wine)! All service members took excellent care of us, and the delightful conversation they fostered made us feel truly welcome.   My only regret was that my Husband & I didn t visit again for a full meal while on vacation in Vancouver.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Kimberly, Thank you for the fabulous review. We are so happy you enjoyed your time with us!

review_text: Top notch oyster joint! Super friendly and attentive staff. The oysters were amazing and I tried the scallops. Probably the best scallops Ive ever had out.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Morvis, We love to hear this.  Thank you so much for the positive review!

review_text: We have been to Rodneys more than once ...(we are not from Vancouver) the service is always great along with the food..
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Asap Jun, Great to hear this! Thank you for the review.

review_text: Charlie, Bobby and Chris made our bar experience phenomenal! The food and drinks were great and the interactions with staff were next level! Amazing experience!
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Bronwen, Thank you for the awesome review! So happy you enjoyed your experience with us.

review_text: Delicious food and super friendly and knowledgeable servers! Will definitely be back!
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Daria, Thank you for the positive review. See you again soon!

review_text: We didnt even notice how Rodneys Gastown location turned in one of our favorites in town. Before, we mainly went to Fanny Bay to feed the craving for oysters but decided to try Rodneys one day, and theres no coming back. Upon our first arrival, the place was bustling, and we were seated at the bar, which was something new for us at an oyster joint. Jumping ahead, I can tell that the bar seating is the only one we accept visiting Rodneys since then. At first, I was a bit irritated with the service but turned out we came there right at the change of shifts, and everything was fixed pretty quickly. Ive heard from many people that they dont like the atmosphere here because the staff reminds them of a fraternity. I have to disagree with that. I think that the mood created by the team with their witty behavior and high energy creates one of a kind experience no one else can offer. Thats why seating at the bar is the best spot available if you ask me. After all, I dont find oysters to be fancy food like many dining places trying to make it, so I think that a more straightforward and friendlier atmosphere suits it much better. The variety of oysters is pretty amazing, and its always the freshest and best product out there. And its hard to beat their Low Tide deals for oysters and drinks. I encourage people to try Rodneys because this place is absolutely spectacular.

Amazing food and oysters.  Our host even walked me through the process of shucking.  Had a great wine and dinner with friends. Great recommendations for continuing the evenings shenanigans.  Amazing evening!
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Gabriel, Thank you for the awesome review. So happy you had a great time!

review_text: Great place. Casual vibe. Fantastic oysters. The host, Miguel, accomodated 10 of us with only a last minute reservation (by phone   don t use the app). Mina was the best waitress ever. Efficient, good recommendations, very nice. Our group had a great evening.
Great food and great service.  Very fresh oysters but also try their Manhattan Claim Chowder and Seafood Salad.

Excellent service and outstanding oysters. We asked for West coast oysters and enjoyed trying the different options while taking with the guys behind the bar. The staff take pride in their jobs and enjoyed discussing shucking, different types of oysters, and even how the chowder pots work. Prices are in-line for high quality seafood. Its a lively, noisy restaurant, but we didnt have trouble hearing each other over the music and other customers. It is a relatively small restaurant, so reservations are probably a good idea. We sat at the bar without a reservation on a Saturday afternoon, but even that filled up quickly while we were there.

5 stars are not enough. Great staff (positive-meniscus-Bobby and positive-energy-Amanda), and a buzzy vibe. Oysters, oysters and more oysters, natural and as shots (so delicious!). The most fun. Thank you! #willbeback
Came in for drinks and appies and was immediately greeted by Chris who was awesome from start to finish. Oysters fresh and drinks prompt! A must-visit in gastown.

I dont know where to start! The Oysters were amazing and their wide variety of sauces were amazing! We ordered the Lobster Poutine and the New England Clam chowder and wish we wouldve ordered more! it was so delicious!

what can i say! really fresh oysters with a wide variety of sauces to choose from! the staff was patient and kind enough to tell us where each oysters are from and gave some good recommendations. We also tried the clam soup(both red&white) and they were amazing as well! overall sucha great experience, great time, great staff

Very fresh oysters and delicious new england clam soup. The tomato clam soup is okay but a bit too herbalic for my taste. The service is fast and helpful. It was our first time so I asked them for suggestion on the oysters like how many is ideal and which types etc. and he was professional from beginning to end.

Best oysters, amazing steamed mussels, strong wine pours and hilariously entertaining bar staff. I highly recommend Rodneys and I suggest you grab a seat at the bar. Delicious dinner, fresh seafood and good company.
Always a good time. Finally got to use my gift card. Sad my gift card is maxed out but looking forward to returning sometime soon
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Donna, Thank you so much for the review. Can t wait to see you again soon!

review_text: Was a super fun night. Food was great. Servers were awesome. I was hoping to have a lobster night with the boys but they only had one lobster available. Made the best of it though, and ordered a few steaks to go with the one lobster. They put it all on a cool platter and everyone loved it. We had lots of appetizers so we were all full by the end.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Graham! I m so sorry about the lack of lobsters! I wasn t there when you guys came in but I heard all about it. Next time let me know and I ll ENSURE there s enough for you all. Glad you had a nice time regardless! Thanks for coming in :) ~Lou

review_text: Fresh Oysters and seafood in town ! Although the oyster is a bit small but it is very creamy and sweet ! Soup is nice, mussels are nice, the only down side is the scallops linguini is too soaked. Lovely service !

I love this spot! Bobby, Charlie and Chris are exceptional. They always greet you and check in throughout the experience. Exceptional service every time. The kitchen create amazing dishes that you find yourself ordering way more than one item on the menu. Great value. A destination spot for any Vancouver foodie. Cheers friends.
We had an awesome experience at Rodneys! Oysters were perfect, great vibe, our waiter Michael was super friendly and funny. Recommend 150%! Enjoy
Weordered Oyster & Lobster +Shrimp sliders. Very delicious
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Parisa, So happy you enjoyed the tasty fare. Thank you for the wonderful review.

review_text: The lobster roll is bar none the best thing Ive ever eaten in the entire world. I cant even begin to describe it. If it ever leaves the menu I will host a funeral. If each roll took a year off my life and they had a cocktail menu I would die by the end of the week.

Wow! Can I move this place with me to Scotland?! I wish I could. The food was exceptional,  the quality of oysters was excellent, and the service, including the knowledge and passion of the staff, is very visible. Atmosphere is electric! I also tried my first cesars here. I loved it. Thanks for fabulous time!
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Peter, Thank you for the wonderful review! We love to hear this. So happy you had a great time with us.

review_text: The food was incredible only to be out shined by the service. Huge raves to Jordan and Peter
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Liz, Fantastic to hear such kind words about the crew and fare!

review_text: My boyfriend and I had a really great time in Rodneys oyster house, good service and amazing food, oyster is pretty fresh! We had a good experience here, we will differently come again :)

One of the best oyster house in town. Fresh! Cheerful atmosphere. Service was outstanding. Well worth the wait. Bring a partner and just share time in line. One of you can gamble while the other holds your spot in line. Definitely best seafood and oysters! Can t wait to go back!

Wow!  What a fabulous place!  I loved the atmosphere and the friendly staff. I came here at 9:30 on a Saturday night and sat at the bar. I had a great time chatting with the staff and they recommended oysters and wine for me. Lovely experience I will gladly be back.
Sat at the bar with Mckenzie yesterday for some wine and oysters! We had such a fun time and the environment was great ! The oysters were out of this world but the service is what we really loved !
Sat at the bar and had a great time with the staff. They made sure we were taken care of and gave fantastic recommendations for dinner and what to do next with our night.
Never been here before so I cant vouch for the food or atmosphere but my friend had a great experience here.

Recommend by the Airbnb super host so decided to give it a try. You immediately feel welcomed by the staff and everyone working there was friendly. Alex, helped me choose my dish, fish and oysters and it was definitely a memorable time. Highly recommend it!
yum!!! Best spot for oysters. Also super fun that they put wine in a normal glass. They have lots of home made sauces to add to the oysters, hope you like spicy!! Get the Solomol oysters!
Had a great time here the other night.  Nate did a fantastic job in taking care of us.  Cant wait to go back again.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Ivan Thank you for the fabulous review. We look forward to seeing you soon!

review_text: My sister and I took a girls trip to Vancouver and found ourselves at Rodney s Oyster House. The vibe was awesome, staff friendly and very helpful as we had never had fresh oysters! All around a very cool experience!

It was great experience. Even I cant eat oyster, there prawn menu fresh and good taste. Potion is bit small though. But there staffs are super friendly, cute and make me feel so comfortable. High recommend!
Warm, energetic atmosphere. Ordered oysters, scallop pasta and shrimp curry. All were delicious and the service was quick. Especially like the half portion option so we had room for more choices.

Not a single bad word to say about the experience eating at Rodney s. The food was amazing, super fresh and full of flavour. The service was great with a knowledgeable waitress explaining the origins of their oysters and how it affects their flavour, making a small platter of different oysters for us to try. The special scallop starter was one of the nicest things I ve ever tasted, prices are reasonable considering the quality of the food and service. I highly recommend!
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Joe, We are so happy to hear this! Thank you for the review and recommendation.

review_text: Great place,fast service,amazing customer service,food was delicious.very busy and is loud so if you are looking for calm romantic corner,is not for you.we really enjoyed our evening though
High quality oysters and funny servers. Love this hidden place in gas town
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Leo, Thank you for the positive feedback! We look forward to hosting you again soon, Fair sails

review_text: We sat at the Bar tonight and Chris (or Kris) is so awesome! Phenomenal service, tasty food and lovely atmosphere.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Amanda, Thank you so much for the amazing review. We can t wait to have you back!

review_text: Amazing service, amazing food. Staff were above and beyond on hospitality and the menu offerings were delicious! Well done to the kitchen! Great server as well and took excellent care of our table!
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Kris, Thank you for the positive review.  We are so happy you enjoyed our hospitality and menu.

review_text: I had an amazing experience at this location tonight.  The staff is amazing and accommodating.  I love the Rodneys Pour for wine! This is by far the best location for staff accommodation,  the best oyters, and by far the best atmosphere.  The manager Chris made sure that our table was taken care of our entire time. We will definitely be back to this location, a great experience.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Racheal, Thank you so much for the review!  We can t wait to host you again soon.

review_text: Great staff and atmosphere! Their in-house hot sauce selection is awesome, and their Low Tide (happy hour) menu is fantastic - $1.50 oysters were really fresh.
Friendly staff and great deals. We enjoyed oysters during low tide hours with beers and ceasars.

The food was amazing, the service was also professional and friendly. Especially shout out to Peter who was our lovely server, thanks a lot for being so nice guys. (thanks for letting us dance with our turkish song as well!) Go go go everyone and enjoy your day in peace
Great food Low tide price friendly staff (ordered 3 glasses of house wine and got the whole bottle!) Coconut shrimp is a must try!
Freshness counts, atmosphere counts with service and a smile. Great food gets me all the time.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Andy, Thank you for the kind words!

review_text: Our server was the best! Top notch experience Food was absolutely delicious Food
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Anastasiia, Thank you so much for the review.

review_text: We loved everything about the place. The staff was exceptional!! They were a really fun bunch of guys that made us feel so welcomed. Excellent oysters along with the ambiance. We are going back one more time before we leave to go home.
Went for the low tide happy hour and was great. The oysters were amazing and the staff were super nice.

One of the best meals we ve had in a long time. Scallop pasta was so good, I ordered another plate of just scallops, which they happily accommodated. The garlic prawns were amazing, especially the broth they come in which they give you bread to soak up with. Service was great, and the  low tide  happy hour on the oysters was a pleasant surprise as they were relatively inexpensive for tasty oysters.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Tanner, Thank you so much for the kind words. Very happy that you enjoyed your time at Rodney s. See you next time, fair sails!

review_text: Absolutely worth the nearly 200$ we spent here. The super tall gentleman serving us was lovely! Food was fresh, tasty, and beautifully presented. Loved the ambience and totally would come back/recommend to others. 10/10! We got fresh oysters, crab cakes, jalapeno shrimp, bam bam shrimp, crab legs, and lobster rolls.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Lacky, Great to hear you loved it! Thank you

review_text: Our server, Charlie, was really great. Food was fresh and tasty. We had the crab cakes, shrimp cocktail and calamari to start and then scallop pasta, clams, lobster poutine and the lobster shrimp rolls for round two. Sprinkled in a dozen oysters throughout the evening as well. No complaints about anything. Music was awesome, we were checked on by other staff members as well. We can t wait to go back and try more.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Melissa, Thank you so much for the positive feedback! We look forward to hosting you again soon.

review_text: Top notch service, food and music from Mina and crew at Rodneys! Great food and music. Kudos to Mina for the stellar accomodation!
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Kris, Thank you for the awesome Review!

review_text: My favourite restaurant whilst visiting Vancouver for 4 days. We had some oysters, clam chowder. seafood linguine and halibut. All delicious! And to finish their cinnamon bun cheesecake was incredible too. Great service and super friendly atmosphere. Definitely recommend a visit!
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Ciska, We are so happy you enjoyed your time with us! See you again soon

review_text: 100% must visit if you like a fun crew and delicious food!!
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Janet, We love hearing this. Thank you so much!

review_text: Cool and quirky setting, casual atmosphere. Our table was ready within a few minutes. We had BC oysters to start and they were amazing. The kitchen was missing a cook, orders were backed-up and hot food took longer to come out. However, our server Fox, and Manager Lou  came by and made sure were were kept informed, and made us feel so well taken care of we did not mind the wait. They knew how to recover the situation and turned what could have been a long wait into a very positive experience. They were fun, positive, and very professional. And when we did get our pan fried oysters, they were more than worth the wait! Chef came by and we had nothing but compliments for him. A most pleasant experience, will be back next time we are in Vancouver!
response_from_owner_text: So great to see you two again on Friday! Thanks again for stopping in and being SUCH lovely guests. See you next time you re in town!

review_text: Excellent waiter!  Excellent food!!  We would come again in a heart beat!
Food is fresh and delicious! The place is cozy and service is good.
Love their food! Awesome atmosphere and service.
Great conversation with the guys at the oyster bar, very cool experience and the oysters are great! Also try the clam chowder!
Casual atmosphere, lovely food, ordered a Chef Favourite :Lobster pasta which is lovely Friendly service and the restaurant is packed Strongly recommended.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Trent. Thank you for the positive review. We hope to see you again soon!

review_text: Absolutely outstanding! We ordered the clams, and the wait staff accidentally brought out mussels. Without is even mentioning anything, our waiter realized and calmly put the mussels on the house while fixing up our original order. Both dishes were great (though the free mussels were far superior). The seafood linguine was still the highlight of the night! All the food arrived very very quickly, and everything was delicious!
I can sum up the experience in five succinct but eloquent points: 1. Crab 2. Crab 3. Crab 4. Crab 5. Crab Also Bobby and Chris were okay I guess.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Don, Thank you for the eloquent review! Hope to see you again soon!

review_text: Perfect place for girls night out. Make sure you sit on the bars. It s really fun and they have the best oyster. Make sure you order dozens of oyster and pasta with scallops. And again thank you for make my night wonderful.
Excellent food, very friendly staff and cosy atmosphere.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy CB Thank you for the review. Look forward to seeing you again!

review_text: Delicious food and a great atmosphere. Tons of different stuff to try and decent beer specials too. Try the lobster poutine.

Excellent! Fresh oysters, delicious clam chowder, crab cakes, fish and chips. Interesting beers. Great cheesecake. Above all   very good service and great prices. Highly recommend. Might want to make reservations or go there for early dinner.

I am a big fan of Rodneys Yaletown and was excited to check out Rodneys Gastown on my latest visit to Vancouver. They did not disappoint. I was in for Low Tide and enjoyed some oysters and a yummy new shrimp appetizer they had just introduced (it wasnt on the menu yet). The service was excellent.

This was absolutely wonderful.  Had a large group and we all had such an amazing time.  Food was amazing, services was top notch. If your a person who loves seafood and a good night out you don t have to look any further. If you have the chance to have Mike as your server, sit back and enjoy! We will all be back again.
Been in Canada for 3 weeks for vacation and this was the best meal of the trip. Calamari, steamed clams, and seafood pasta were all top notch. Get here before 6pm for oysters at  low-tide  prices.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Min, Thank you for the positive feedback on your Rodney s experience. We look forward to seeing you again soon. Fair sails

review_text: Great atmosphere, great food and love both oysters & the manhattan clams!

My cousins and I went her a couple weeks ago and I just have to say best service, best food, and great environment! Are serve Mina was very kind, did not hesitate to answer any questions and overall made our experience there amazing. Will definitely be returning and recommend others as well!

Crisp pints.  Excellent chowder.  An institution with a worthy reputation. The team here really knows how to run the operation and every visit feels special. Kitchen has high standards; every time I eat here the food is on point. Great time.  10/10 recommend.  They wont leave you disappointed.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Jason, happy to hear about your positive experience. Hope to see you again soon! Fair Winds!

review_text: Excellent service here. The staff was very accommodating even though we had two small children who didnt know how to behave. They definitely knew their oysters and had a variety of sauces to try. I would definitely come here again. However if you are not here during happy hour, the oysters are quite expensive.
Went for the first time last night and was extremely impressed! We sat at the bar and the staff were absolutely amazing! Oysters were fresh and super good! So much fun! 10/10 recommend

Good Seafood. Clam chowder lunch special, so good. Friendly staff provide a good atmosphere. I was taking friends engagement photos outside their door and they invited us in and got her to try oysters for the first time, on the house. It was really fun. Always a good experience.

Theyve managed to recreate the same atmosphere as their Yaletown shop, which is great. I always enjoy my visits to either Rodneys. The staff are friendly and the food and drink are good. Try make a reservation before you go though, it fills up fast especially at the weekends.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Will. Thank you for the positive review. We look forward to hosting you again!

review_text: Highly recommend the lobster poutine! We had it, plus a huge plate off muscles, and oysters. All was very good. No drinks, but we had cheesecake as well - super good! With tip came to $75 for two. Service was excellent and great atmosphere. Food is good and good portions. We had to wait 45 minutes for a table, but just got a drink somewhere else in Gastown for that time and they called us, so good location generally for before/after drinks as well. We were able to find parking relatively easily less than 2 minutes away and it was also inexpensive. Would return!
We had a great time here tonight - the hostess had great energy and we enjoyed the service! The food was well presented and delicious too.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Natalya, We are so glad you enjoyed your night with us. Thank you for the review!

review_text: $1.50 oysters during happy hours. 3pm to 5pm.
Greta food for a reasonable price. All the food is amazing!

Happy hour specials are the time to go! Good price for oysters and appies. Have had birthday parties there and service has been good even for larger groups. A must try is their deep fried oysters. Their Caesar s are also top notch.

Great happy hour, attentive service. will definitely be back update: came back, had another amazing experience! our server, Nathan, was funny, attentive and personable and even recommended a cool Speakeasy as our next place. 10/10 will come again
Fresh oysters and good variety of seafood dishes. Very welcoming and friendly staff!

Excellent service. Excellent food. Oysters were great, as was the seafood clubhouse. Great selection of hot sauces. Desserts were amazing as well. Overall a great experience. Will definitely be going back next time were in Vancouver.

Staff are amazing and hilarious. Very accommodating and great service. Pan-fried oysters are very good and the selection of raw oysters is quite good. 80s music played throughout 90% chance the servers and you will have a good time when in the air tonight by Phil Collins comes on. Definitely recommend coming out here.

The absolute best place for fresh oysters, hands down! The staff are so great and it is such a light, fun and welcoming environment to sit with friends or family. Top recommendation goes to this restaurant!

Amazing place with amazing seafood dishes. Oyster selection was great and fresh and had me dying for more. The ambience is great as well with awesome servers with great personality. I will definitely return once I save up my pennies.

One of the best places to shell out money. The staff is fun and full of spunk, the raw food is excellent. Cooked food isnt great, this isnt where you go for cooked food. Beer and drinks are great. The Rodneys Gas Town experience is one of my favorites and this is definitely my favorite Rodneys location.

Rodneys had such a great atmosphere, the food was fresh and delicious, and the service couldnt have been better! All the servers are engaging and energetic, browsing across the room you could see surprise and delights and smiles all around from happy customers - I highly recommend grabbing a bite and enjoying the company! Special shout out and thank you to our waiter Sherman! If you are reading this - yes, Global Entry grants you Nexus access - just need the physical card on hand! (Now I know for next time)

The food and servers were amazing here. They constantly checked on us and were great with our babies being there. I would recommend this place to everyone. The only downside is that you have to find parking on the street and Gastown can be a bit of a nightmare right now.
Good

Absolutely awesome. It was probably one of the best meals my wife and I have ever had; the food, the atmosphere, the banter from the servers - we absolutely loved every minute. We shared as many dishes as many dishes as we could manage, including desert and it was all just brilliant. One day when were back in BC, well 100% be back here.

Had a short wait (not a problem, we didnt have a reservation) Waiter and server were attentive and thorough. Coco Shrimp Curry and the Garlic Shrimp were very good. The restaurant was a little noisy as it was full and everyone seemed to be enjoying themselves - the music could have been turned down a bit. We would definitely return!
The oysters are so good and fresh!!! High recommend this place.
response_from_owner_text: Ahoy Arya! Thank you for dining with us! Fair Sails

review_text: Great food and personalised service!

My partner suggested this spot after reading some reviews online, it s a small family friendly joint! The restaurant gets quite busy during lunch, I would suggest plan accordingly and come after the lunch rush. The restaurant holds about 20 people or less, the ambiance is that of a fish spot with seafood art on the walls. Since this was our first stop in Granville Island and wanted to try and see everything, we decided to share the clam chowder and the infamous fish and Chips! Great customer service, daughter was our server, mother washing dishes very humble people. If you are in a hurry, I wouldn t suggest coming here, everything is made fresh to order so it ll take a min. The food was hot and absolutely delicious, one of the best fish and chips around!

I absolutely love a good fish & chips, and Tonys cod fish was delightful, especially when dipped in the creamy tar tar sauce.   Chill atmosphere, great service, and fresh seafood. Cant quite ask for more. After your meal, hop on over to the brewery across the street.

Ducked into this little spot for lunch, best fish & chips (halibut)! The service was excellent and personal, inquiring about our visit to Vancouver. Great lunch experience and well worth the short wait for a table!

The freshest, biggest and absolutely delicious Oysters I have ever had! The front of house staff greet you warmly every time and we were able to be sat immediately. Not long after ordering they bring out their incredible Oysters. We went to Tonys for quick oysters before dinner, after dinner and then another day before lunch! You GOT to come here if you are seeking incredible Oysters.

We wanted to try fish and chips in Vancouver and this place did not disappoint! The salmon was perfect and the chips were extremely delicious too along with the sauces and salad. You can taste the freshness. For someone coming from the coastal part of South Africa we were greatly satisfied with the quality of the food. The customer service was excellent!

This place is a gem! It s a mom n pop shop that serves up classic fried seafood as well as soups and stews at affordable prices without compromising on quantity or quality. I loved the calamari - flavourful, lightly battered and appropriately tender and the oyster stew included three large oysters. It s humble and simple, yet thoughtfully and tastefully decorated, dining space is welcoming and comfortable!

Really glad I came here for lunch. The oysters were so fresh and juicy, good value at $15.99 for half dozen. The fish (cod) and chips were amazing as well. The lunch set with the chowder is great value. Do add another piece (or two) of fish and you will have one super satisfying meal. Recommended!!

This was a great find - we seemed to be the last people to get straight in to a table, as there was a line waiting to get seated the while time we were eating, this little place is so popular! The seafood platter shared between us was fantastic, tasted great and cooked perfectly, not overcooked like some seafood places tend to do. Clam chowder was also really good, definitely homemade. Prices are also very reasonable and the staff friendly, very rushed but always with a smile.

Grabbed the lunch special available during 11:30am - 3pm. Which was breaded cod with tartar sauce also served with fries and cole slaw We also got the breaded oysters. Definitely recommend grabbing this. Service was warm and welcoming.

Just love this cozy little place. We ordered the lunch special which came with clam chowder. Mom and sister had the oysters. Original plans to go to the fish market next door but Im beyond my happy place that we came here instead. This is my happy place and this is my happy meal! Ill be back!!

We came upon this cafe by chance. Walked in soon after it was opened for lunch. We ordered the lunch special for my son and sampler plate for 2 for ourselves. Portions were generous. The lady who ran the place was friendly, efficient and made us feel welcome. Will definitely come again when we visit Granville Isalnd.
No nonsense fish and chips place. Good service, fresh sea food and malt vinegar for your chips. Recommended
The service was great! My son had the lunch special, one piece cod, fries, coleslaw and clam chowder. I had the mussels and they were big. The food was delicious! I would definitely come back.

Ordered the classic fish and chips, it s the best fish and chips i have ever had by far. The crispy skin has no taste of baking soda (or alkaline taste) like how the usual fish and chips would taste like. I d recommend their lunch special for sure because you would get the clam chowder too! It s so creamy <3

Resturant is not big and nothing fancy. Quite busy at lunch hour. Had the lunch special. Soup was great. The batter for the fish was done perfectly. Fries was crispy and not soggy. No stale flavour from oil they deep fry with. Everything was very very good. Suprised at how good this is! 100% Better fish & chips than next door.

I m an English person visiting Vancouver on a study abroad, and let me tell you the batter for the fired cod tastes like the ones in England! Come here, you won t regret it! It s amazing, friendly staff and great prices
Nice little  restaurant.  Great fresh tasting  seafood.  Phenomenal  service.  Will definitely  be back for the fries. Best so far in Vancouver

A small seafood place in Granville Island! Food is pretty tasty! It gets crowded around lunch or dinner time! Fortunately, we came here for an early dinner. When we left, people needed to wait for tables.
Cozy place with great food!

reviewer_name: Dini and Kasun - The Flavor Bender
review_text: Ordered fish and chips. It was delicious, fresh and good portions!  Its a small and cozy place! Fast and friendly service too!

First off, the staff was so friendly. It was super busy but the lady managed to get a table for us quickly, the food was delicious and tasted so fresh ! I ordered the salmon burger and it was incredible and filling. Definitely would try again.
response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating and feedback. Glad that you are enjoying your time at our cafe. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

review_text: Great fish and chips! Super quick service as well for a good price!

Stopped in today as another place closer to me was still not open, so glad I did. I was proptly greeted by a loveley young lady. was shown to a table and placed my order. The fish and chips special was fabulous, 1 peice of cod, chips ,coleslaw and a small bowl of chowder. Very tasty. this will be my granville island go-to place. perfect balance of quality, price and freindly service.
Hands down the best prawn cocktail I have ever had! Super nice staff, cocktail sauce is off the chain!! Prawns...clutch AF.
As a non-local I must say Id consider this a hidden gem on Granville Island. Everything was delicious and the service was fast and friendly! Must visit !
response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you so much for your rating and feedback. Glad that you enjoy our foods and the time in our cafe. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

review_text: Amazing food. Service was friendly and fast. It isnt a fancy spot but the food and service is what matters. Highly recommend
Has one of the best oyster burgers. Nice seafood menu. Beautiful spot to eat on Granville Island
Had the fish & chips and the oysters. Really good and filling!

Loved every part of this restuarant! I ordered fresh oysters, calamari, halibut fish and chips, and seafood special (best). The halibut fish and chips tasted alright still bit dry which isnt what I like but their cod is the best cod i have ever eaten! Not dry, the right type of moist and soft which didnt need much of tarter sauce because it was perfect just the way it was! I went there with my family and we shared every plate together so ordering the seafood special and oysters were the best and is easy to divide up! Best service! The waitresses and waiters were nice. The place seems to get really busy easily so be sure to sprint there to get a good spot (especially if you have a big group) and this is the best place for families to have a get together! Very family friendly place and comfy.

This little shop is a diamond in the rough. In amongst the thicket of tourist traps that is Granville Island, Tonys definitely stands out as being more local-oriented. What it lacks in luxury it makes up for with good ol fashioned hospitality - and plenty of it! The staff even talked with me using my name, which I had written down on the waiting list. That was certainly a welcomed surprise. And the food? Well youll just have to try it for yourself. But with how good youll feel by the time you get it, how could it possibly taste anything less than spectacular?
The food and atmosphere was greatly appreciated. It was fast and so tasty the fish & chips

After a long day of roaming around in Vancouver,  Tonys fish and chips literally brightened my day. We did had a little situation while waiting for food but the manager Terry was amazing enough to quickly jump on it and resolve within no time, being the sweetest and most caring Manager. His words  I just want you to enjoy  Thank you so much Terry. Its a must visit place when in Vancouver.
response_from_owner_text: Hello Mr. Ali, thank you for your rating and feedback. I m glad and happy to hear that you are enjoying our foods. I m also would like to say thank you for giving me a chance to try, resolve and overcome the situation that you having. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

review_text: Loved the fresh oysters here. Friendly service as well!!!

The food was delicious and there was quick service. Given the portions of the food, this was well worth the price. I got 2 pieces of Cod, chips, and the clam chowder soup. I ended up having to take some of it home with me!

Have to go early to avoid a queue during peak hours and weekends but the fish n chips are amazing!!! Would recommend the oysters too because they are so fresh! One of the best fish n chips Ive eaten although its a bit pricey but worth it :) the chips are slightly soggy but other than that, its a solid meal

The fish was excellent. Crispy and not too much batter.  It was a bit salty but Im not used to food having salt nowadays. The fries was really great and fresh. Only had a few pieces due to dietary requirement. The server gave me excellent service, she even asked me if I like ice in my water. Not too many servers asked me that lately.
Nice little family restaurant.   Clam chowder was very good plus the fish and chips were tasty!   Would definitely return!
Really good fish & chips. The fish was cooked perfectly and bigger than I expected. The staff was very friendly. Great service!
Loved the place! Very cozy and homely atmosphere, and great service! Food was also delicious! Thank you!!
Of all the places we have eaten fish and chips lately, this one is the best. The fish is a decent size and the batter is crispy and not overdone. Service is also fast and friendly.
Unassuming and small. Well worth it. Value priced compared to some of the other seafood on the island. Id go back.
Located in Grandville Island - Great fish and chips, very tasty and good customer service. Price $$ totally worth it.

EDIT August 17th, 2023 I never thought I would say this but the quality went down big time! the soup was so thick, the spoon could stay up - the batter was thick and the fries were cold - let us hope that it is because it is tourist season and they are too busy to cook properly -
response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your feedback and rating. Glad that you enjoying your time at our cafe. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

review_text: Great little find with simple decor. I had the mussels and they were delicious. The place was full but has a little counter which worked just fine for a solo traveler.

It was listed as a top ten place to eat in Vancouver in our guide book and we were not disappointed. Excellent, fresh seafood and fish in a cafe environment. Excellent service and they have beer on tap from the Granville Island Brewery across the road.

I don t have pictures of the food because we ate it so quickly but their 2 piece halibut and chips and the clam chowder were amazing! Super tiny no frills spot, we were seated and served quickly, and the food was standout. Absolutely coming back!
A unique, warm and cozy place. Had the lunch special. Plenty of food and was delicious.
Yummy   fish   and chips   I love the halibut! Nice and friendly staff
response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating and kind comments. Glad that you enjoy our foods & services. We looking forward to see you again soon. Stay safe & well :)

review_text: Amazing fish and chips. I even loved the coleslaw. Raw oysters were great and we had a banana fosters special for dessert. The service was outstanding and they were super nice to our kiddos. Will definitely go again.
Beautiful and tasty experience! The place its pretty warm to enjoy Food
Halibut fish is what you need to order! Fresh, HOT, delicious. We tried their calamari- it came out rubbery. We were not a fan. However their halibut fish was on point!
I tried many fish and chips in Vancouver and Richmond but this is the one I like the most. Fresh seafood, crispy batter, amazing slaw, and best yam fries ever!
Oh my this was an awesome choice for lunch!!! Large pieces of haddock that were not greasy and the batter was so light and crispy. Came with thick cut fries. Service was fast and friendly.

Another wonderful time at Tonys Fish & Oysters on Granville Island. This is my go to place when I visit Vancouver yearly. Food is always on point, the atmosphere quiet and homey, and the staff always experienced and kind. Food : 5/5
Everything is delicious, the attention of the staff is great, definitely I will come back

Decided to try this place because I didnt want to line up for food inside the public market.  I was afraid it would be one of those tourist trap kind of restaurants because of its convenient location right by the entrance to Granville Island. We ordered 2 piece cod with fries to-go (because of Covid restrictions). Ordering and service was fast. Fish was fresh and tender, batter was perfectly fried and not too oily.  Also really loved the fries!  Great value.. two of us shared this plate and were both full.  Will definitely come back and try the rest of the menu.
response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your feedback and rating. We are looking forward to see you again soon. Stay safe and well :)

review_text: Excellent fish and chips lunch! The only problem (which wasnt even a problem) was I ordered halibut and received salmon but immediately she came over and told me they will make me the halibut so they actually gave me the salmon for FREE!! The hand cut fries were so good! Very friendly staff (Hamasa was our waitress; this lady is the example of what customer service excellence should be) and very good prices. Small and cozy place. Will be definitely coming back again and telling everyone.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Susan McAusland, Thanks for taking the time to give us your feedback and we do apologize for the misunderstanding that had happened. We are glad to hear that you were happy with your experience with our staff. We can assure you that with your feedback our service will improve even better. Thanks for your time and we hope to see you soon.

review_text: Good food with reasonable price. Service was great. Id recommend a visit!
Best fish & chips since living in the UK. Small shop, inviting atmosphere, and great service. A perfect lunch stop for a day on Granville Island.
Really nice people, and the food is just as good! Definitely for those who like fish and chips! They even have dessert! Gives off a good hang out vibe.
Delicious seafood gem here Fresh crispy Friendly staff Nice street view
response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating & comments. Glad that you like our foods & services. Looking forward to see you again soon. Stay safe & well :)

review_text: Fantastic Fish & Chips! I really appreciate the atmosphere and simplicity of this restaurant
response_from_owner_text: Hello Mr. Matthew, thank you for your feedback and rating. Glad that you enjoy our foods and your time in the cafe. We are looking forward to see you soon :)
