review_text: Excellent calamari, excellent value, good quality fish and hand cut chips. Staff service excellent

I had been there for lunch special fish and chips for couple months, the service are great and the manager/waitresses lady is always really friendly! The food is fast and served hot. Overall good portion with good price, you cant go any wrong with it.

We waited almost 40 minutes to be seated... Im glad we did. The place is cozy seating 6 at a bar and, Im guessing, at most 24 more - max seating ~30. But do you care? Come a little early or past the peak and youll be fine. The clam chowder was among the best Ive had, fish and chips, and halibut - along with a native Granville brewed ale - it was just perfect. Such friendly staff - the lady who served us went above and beyond, voluntarily splitting a family style order to make it easy for us to enjoy! She has been with Tonys for 12 years over three ownerships - now that means a lot! On Granville Island - youve got to treat yourself to wholesome food and good old Canadian hospitality!

Excellent service! One of the places you could dine causally at a quite affordable price. We ordered fish n chips (Halibut), a pound of clams and breaded oysters. It was definitely tasty for the value. (Mind u this is a premium location. Please do not expect to dine cheap in Granville Island. I read some of the ridiculous comments here complaining its pricey.) It was a busy place but the waitresses were quick and personal without rushing us. And we have a baby and a toddler. We ll definitely go back next time.

This is the second time we ve eaten here and it is a delicious place to visit for lunch. The lunch special includes a cup of clam chowder and fish and chips. We also got some muscles and they were the best we ve ever eaten. The only downside is that it is a very small sitting room with only 3 tables open because of covid so come early! Will definitely be back for more!
response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating & feedback. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

review_text: If your in the Granville Island area and looking for great fish and chips, Tonys is an awesome choice. Foods great, service is fast and friendly. The restaurant is a tiny place. At times you can be shoulder to shoulder with other diners, but no one seems to be complaining. The food there is worth it.
response_from_owner_text: Hello, Thank you so much for your rating & feedback. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

review_text: Great experience in a touristy area.  Youll pay for the experience but the food is high quality.

If you find yourself looking for a good affordable place to get quality fish and chips around Granville, Tonys is for you. Small but comfortable.  I came during a quieter time, still pretty full, but no wait! I was debating between the cod or the salmon fish and chips.  Waitress said I could have both, great!  Wait time was not long, under 10 minutes.  Good looking, fair sized portions, ( I got the 2 piece ).  Salmon was good, Cod light and flakey, both battered to a light crisp perfection.  Fries were good, well done in house.  Delicious coleslaw, not too creamy which I found perfect.  Tartar is tasty, you can tell its made in house. All in all, good tasty eats that wont blow your mind, but are what you are hoping for from fish and chips.  Service was friendly and helpful.  Price was around $19.00 for the 2 piece fish and chips. Would come back if Im ever in the area again!
What a lovely quaint place. The service is fabulous and the food is delicious. There is a very limited menu, but the food is prepared and served very quickly! Cant wait to go back!
Had the breaded deep fried oysters and yam fries to go...great food..friendly service
response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating and feedback. We are looking forward to see you again. Stay safe :)

review_text: Service was quick and friendly. Food was fresh and delicious

I would like to commend the lady who waited on us. Im sorry I did not get your name. We were there Thursday Oct 18th @ 5pm. If I had a restaurant, Id hope my staff was as good as you. The service you provided was amiable. Food was probably on the average side coming from fish and chips in Australia but havent had better in Vancouver.
Really good place for a quick bite. The fosh and chips is really good!!
Ordered Raw Oysters, Fish&Chips (cod) and Mussels. You could taste they were freshly made, nice and quick service. We d come here again!

Living land locked, was looking forward to some excellent seafood while visiting Vancouver and Tonys was the place to go. The fish (of the fish and chips) has a great texture inside and out. The location in Granville is small and busy, but it is well worth the wait.
I had the halibut and my mom had the cod. Both were delicious. Crunchy outer layer and flaky, moist interior.
Have to wait yet definitely worth it. Oyster is good, cod is delicious. Would come again

Cafe is an odd pick for a name, as this is much more like a fish and chip shop with some upscale additions to the menu. They have the local Granville Island Ale/Lager on tap, no doubt from the brewery right across the street-- the ale was well-balanced: not too hoppy, not too malty, and a great complement to the fish and chips. If you get anything here, get the seafood platter, which is a little of everything plus some garlic butter sauce. I dont know if the chef went to the nearby culinary school, but if she did, it certainly shows. The food was fantastic: perfectly seasoned, neither over- nor under-done. It is a bit cramped, having 6 or 7 small tables plus a bar in a space where I would use 4 tables, but the food and excellent service are well worth it.
Delicious and reasonably priced food in Granville Island. Also a nice option to get non-breaded fish and chips, with great portions. Service is prompt and very friendly.
response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating and feedback l. Glad that you enjoy your time at Tony s. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

review_text: I definitely enjoyed the platter for two because it gives me more variety of deep fried seafood for me to eat. Squids? Check. Oysters? Check. Halibut? Check. Ideally, your date would enjoy a great greasy spoon load of fish and chips, and its definitely best to visit two hours before closing time if you want peace and quiet atmosphere

I came in for a quick bite before peak dinner hours. I ordered half a dozen raw oysters and they were good. Service was good and quick. The place isnt too big so get here early if you are really interested

A little pricey but great food and location. We came twice during our viit and had some local beers (great), chowder, fish & chips, salmon.and oysters, all good. Staff is really friendly and you get views toward the water. Id recommend.
Sandy was so nice and the fish and chips here is the best! Price is ok and the place is cozy too. Ill be back and bring my wife and kids.
Great  small little seafood place  on Granville island Good prices too. Food
I love their fish and chips! And the portions are huge!!
Friendly sever and the food come out very quickly.
response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating and feedback. Hope you enjoy our foods. Looking forward to see you again. Stay safe :)

review_text: Great fish and chips (we had the halibut). Friendly staff, especially Sandra. Excellent service. Good prices. If you prefer bigger portions, order the three piece.
This was a beautiful place right by the ocean, with a great view overlooking a gorgeous landscape, the food was a little expensive but wayy worth it.

Amazing! My first meal on my first visit to Vancouver and it was delicious. Had the seafood platter for one and it has a good mix of cod, fried oysters, buttered crab, mussels, clams and scallops. Small space but great atmosphere.

Wow. Amazing. Such a good deal for moist, crunchy, flavourful cod and crunchy chips. The coleslaw with the meal is also amazing. Tony really has a way around the mouth feels. Will be coming back here!
response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you so much for your rating & feedback. We are happy and glad that you like our foods. Looking forward to see you soon. Stay safe & well :)

review_text: Very delicious fish and chips! And clam chowder.
response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating & feedback. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

review_text: This place must appear in a travel guide, as there are usually tourists noshing here. It is not big, and not a great place for more than four people. There is a signup sheet for diners waiting for a table. They dont take reservations. Being on Granville Island, they have access a variety of very fresh fish.
Pretty great fish burger. The side of onion rings wasnt an afterthought. They were actually delicious. Fresh Granville Island on tap. What more could you ask for?

Teeny tiny place with a wonderful server who is passionate about the food. Delicious fried oysters and fish & chips. I had to sign up to get in for two people on a paper outside. We only waited about 10 to 15 minutes.
Very good and fresh. Quick service
response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you so much for your feedback and rating. Glad you enjoy our foods and time in our cafe. We are looking forward to see you again soon :)

review_text: Small restaurant with big flavour. Fresh fish, great choices, friendly staff. The 2pc fish and chips are worth splitting if you also order an appetizer.
response_from_owner_text: Hello, thank you for your rating & comment. We hope to see you soon. Stay safe :)

review_text: Awesome fish and chips! Do try the calamari as well. Owners and crew were very friendly and welcoming. Keep up the brilliant work and food!
response_from_owner_text: Hello, Thank you for your rating and encouraging feedback. We re looking forward to see you again soon :)

review_text: The food is always great there. The waitress is so nice and very welcomed customers. You will never feel a rushy or push even you can tell that this is a very busy store. Always a great choice.

A great fine and dine just in front of the English Bay beach. You got to the see the best sunset from the patio, at the hook! The food is tasty, and it will bring mouth watery flavours to you. A great sea food experience, the one you wont experience anywhere else. Food service at its best, servers are so welcoming, friendly and their recommendations are great. Beers, Lagers, Ale, wine, and speciality cocktails name it any, and they will have for you at the bar. The best oysters with the best standards. Perfectly shucked. Come and have a experience!

Fantastic experience from beginning to end! Everyone loved the food - the only comment the even resembled criticism was the angry pasta could have been angrier (spicier) but so many dishes had us talking about them days later: baked oysters, sliders, asparagus, Brussels sprouts, seafood mac and cheese, the mocktails, cookies & ice cream  it was the highlight meal on our trip! The staff was beyond accommodating and everyone we interacted with was genuine, cheerful, and each an absolute delight! We were a group of 8 with small children and we wandered in without reservations and we were treated to a fantastic meal. I can t recommend this place enough!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Shawna! Thanks so much for the great review.  We will pass on the feedback to our Chef.  We hope to see you again soon!

review_text: Great service here! I was here with a few friends on the fireworks festival. Although we were here kinda the last minute they still gladly arranged seats for us. We sat at the corner seat which is a gorgeous seat with a full view of the beach. The food here are also awesome, which although there aren t that many choice of food dishes, this is still a highly recommended restaurant.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Ian! Thank you so much for your review- very happy we were able to accommodate you :)

review_text: The best beach side restaurant in Vancouver! The vibes in there are awesome. The service is absolutely bang on. Jonah, Theo and Sham gave us such an unreal experience at Hook. From the stunning drinks to the unreal shucking, the staff there treat their guests like family. Making sure to ask for your names and give you a good experience. Their seafood and oysters are the freshest I ve ever had and the biggest oysters I ve ever eaten in my life! This is the restaurant to go to not only for the food but for the service. Our new fave spot in the West End!

One of the best restaurant experiences we ve had in Vancouver! We had an event there and everything was absolutely perfect. The chef there is incredible talented, the staff was so friendly and attentive, and the manager Axel made sure it all ran smoothly. We watched the sunset through through the windows while everything unfolded perfectly. Everyone kept raving about the service, food and atmosphere. I would give more stars if I could. Thanks again for one of the best nights!!!
response_from_owner_text: Amanda thank you so much! The event was so beautiful and we were thrilled to have the opportunity to host you! Thanks for the review!

review_text: I ve been to Hook a couple times now and it s always been great. On my last trip the server Bre was amazing with our group. We had a couple different people with a lot of different orders and she took great care of us. The burger is a classic and the Miraval Rose was amazing.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Yohan! Thank you so much for the review!

review_text: Amazing food quality!  Clams is highly recommended! Awesome view at English Bay. Servers are really friendly and so kind. Come and enjoy your meal with your friends!

Three of us had dinner 11/11. The food was amazing. Hot and fresh and delicious. And the service was absolutely top notch. They went above and beyond to get me a drink I wanted. We re from Regina and always love coming back to Hook. Highly recommend.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Gaynor, Glad you enjoyed your experience! Well see you on your next trip to Vancouver!

review_text: Tonight, ten of my friends and I went to this bar on the occasion of one of our friends birthday and ordered drinks and sides. What caught our attention the most was the very lovely waiter there.  He was (I think his name is Theo) very accommodating, friendly and thorough and we will definitely go there again
response_from_owner_text: Hi, Arash! Thanks for sharing your feedback and we are so happy to hear that our staff helped make your visit enjoyable.  We look forwared to seeing you again!

review_text: Our food was delicious! We settled on a few appetizers from the happy hour menu. The setting was nice. We watched the sunset over the water from our table. The service was great! I don t eat dairy and our server was very accommodating. He had the kitchen fix mussels and clams in a way that wasn t on the menu so that I could enjoy them. Dietary restrictions: I don t eat dairy and our server was very accommodating. He had the kitchen fix mussels and clams in a way that wasn t on the menu so that I could enjoy them.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the review, Janet! We are happy to hear that we could accomdate and that you enjoyed your meal.  We hope to see you again soon!

review_text: Great view, good seafood. Fantastic place to host a business lunch - 5 of us squeezed into a booth and it went well! Awesome servers. Would repeat
response_from_owner_text: Hi Earl - appreciate your review and thanks for helping us showcase our menu! Look forward to hosting your team anytime!

review_text: Three nights on English Beach.  Three different restaurants here.  This was the BEST!  Great service.  Fresh oysters were fabulous here best ever.  Salmon bowl was inventive and tasty.  Most importantly, their dirty martini with house vodka was the best I ve had in years!  The only negative is that the menu is quite limited. Our group of 6 found appealing choices, but a broader array of possibilities would help.  We loved this place!

Nice to hang out at English Bay. Came here for happy hour on a bright sunny day and it was very good. Tried a margarita, beer, prawns and home made chips with salsa and guacamole. Everything was good and would come back again. It was very busy so there might be a wait on those nice sunny days.
Hook on Denman in English Bay is a nice pub/restaurant. Usually there is a line up especially weekends. Nice place to hang out.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Farid! Please remember you can always book a table through OpenTable to skip the line!

review_text: Super chill place! staff were extremely helpful and kind, food was well worth the price especially with view of the beach and drinks were 10/10! Margaritas and their calamari were especially incredible, i would definitely come back here and recommend checking it out! (Also pictured is Fish&Chips, Chicken wings, Pulled pork Poutine and the Calamari)
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for your review. We are glad you had a great time. Hope to see you again soon.

review_text: My husband and I had a lovely lunch.  We accessed the restaurant through the adjacent bar as my husband is in a wheelchair. The staff were super helpful, particularly Mackenzie, the food was great and the views stunning. Fabulous end to our Canadian holiday.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for the great review, Beverly! We hope to see you again next time you visit Canada. Cheers!

review_text: Great seafood with a nice sea view. Nice service and fantastic food, with great happy hour choices
response_from_owner_text: Hey Fabio, thanks for the great review! See you soon

review_text: We had Theo as a server and it was the BEST experience ever. Would 10/10 recommend a visit and ask to be seated in Theo s section!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Emilia! We are so happy to hear you had a geat experience with us. See you again soon!

review_text: We really liked this place...nice view, awesome staff and great drinks. We came back a second time also. We tries the lobster roll and the tuna salad. The lobster was really good and enough to eat. The salad was amazing!!! The drinks were really well prepared...we were seated next to the bar. We tried 2 very different cocktails and were awesome. The staff wear masks and were paying attention to the customers.

I had the privilege of trying some of the new dishes to be added to the menu in July by Executive Chef Arif Khalid. From a very delicate Red Snapper Cerziche (paired with pinot gris) to a great burger or the steak (w merlot), everything was delicious!! Hook is a casual dining experience facing west overlooking English Bay. A wonderful view at sunset. Lots of craft beer. The ceiling could use some sound dampening material as the noise level is a bit bright.

Lovely restaurant in a good location. Great views and fantastic food at very reasonable prices for the quality. Would recommend! Had a great atmosphere - slight caveat is the noise. If youre hard of hearing it may be difficult to hold a conversation. But otherwise excellent!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Charlotte.  Thank you for the 5 star review! We appreciate your feedback and look forward to having you visit again soon.

review_text: We fell in love with Eva. Great server, lots of personality. Saw her work an entire room and made every table feel special. Food was a tad pricey.. but considering the location, it was justifiable. Proportions were not large, but had a lot of flavour. They seem to slant toward quality over quantity. Loved the $6 / 20oz pints (finally.. a ma fa&kin proper pint!). I d return.

In from Calgary, and happened to walk in for some afternoon drinks and food. Nicholas was our waiter, he was absolutely fantastic, have been to Vancouver many times and is a great representation of what Vancouver has to offer. He shared his knowledge of the city and even called ahead of our next reservation to make sure we were taken care of there. Great host!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Marc! That is wonderful to hear, thank you for sharing your review! Hope to see you soon.

review_text: I enjoyed my cocktail and oysters there. My bourbon sour was very balanced and the view is nice! I havent tried their food yet, but maybe I will get their burger at some point to test the waters.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much! Our Axelito Sour has been very popular so thank you!

review_text: 5 star all the way       !  Amazing vibes, friendly and efficient service and most importantly yummylicious food.  We had yam fries, fish tacos,  baja rice bowl and finally chocolate brownie cheese cake.  Everything was finger licking good, literally!  Would definitely go there again.

This is a great place for locals and tourists. Right at Beach and Denman you feel the city beach energy. Great views of the water and great people watching. Food is fresh and very good. Portions are generous too. The fish and chips are some of the best I ve had. The oysters come with several tasty condiments. Happy hour is a fabulous deal. My only disappointment is that the crab wasn t Dungeness.

Very good restaurant, the food is amazing, portions are generous and quality outstanding!!  Our server Nicholas made of our evening a fantastic experience. The owner was present and came to talk with us. We highly this place. You will be hooked ;-)
response_from_owner_text: Hi David!  Thanks so much for the great review.  We are so happy you enjoyed your time with Nicholas and the rest of the team.  See you again soon!

review_text: Love this place, such good seafood! I ordered the blackened cod, and it was soo good. Very tender flaky cod, seasoned perfectly, on a bed of asparagus and crushed whole mini potatoes. My wife ordered the vege burger, although it fell apart easily it was still delicious. Service was really good, seating was awesome and the view was awesome.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your kind words Saadiq. The way you describe our food makes me hungry!

review_text: Great seafood/bar in English bay area with a nice sunset view from their patio. Everything I have ordered from their menu has been amazing (And I have ordered pretty much everything on their menu at this point  ). Great vibes and great service too. Highly recommend

Absolutely lovely. They reserved my sister and I a window seat and we got am Absolutely STUNNING sunset while we ate/drank. I had the prawn roll and I loved it. Sister had the fish and chips and she loved it (though her portion size was humongous, so not all of it).
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the review Sam, we are very lucky to have such a beautiful sunset view!

review_text: What a great place for good food great views and the staff was amazing from Christen (hope I spelled that right)our waiter who never let us want for anything and super suggestions and full of great information about the area to Dustin the manager who greeted us both days we were there and made sure everything was satisfactory if we lived in Vancouver but we live in Pittsburgh PA we would be regulars.  Nice meeting you all keep it going

Food: The chicken sandwich is very salty, but juicy. The fries are just okay. The premium oyster are delicious. The lamp chops are amazing. Drinks: The local beers are pretty good. Ambience: Gorgeous view of the beach. Seating inside and outside. The chairs are all outdoor design. There is leather booths inside. Elegant designs for the area.

Great happy hour selection! We had the seared prawns that were to die for and their calamari was exciting to eat with the jalapeno, tomatoes and arugula. There s also a pool table that s free to play. During our visit we had caused some confusion as we left our table to go play pool. When we came back to our table, another guest was seated which led us to thinking that we had paid already. They had instead moved us to a table nearer to the pool table and we mistakenly left without paying. When we called back, after realizing a few hours later, to let them know of the situation and what we could do to transfer the missed payment, our waitress, Eva, had informed us that they had already taken care of it even though it was our fault. We will for sure come back to Hook to try out other things on their menu and to leave a generous tip!

They accommodated our group of six by moving us to a better table with a view. It was a friends birthday and they made sure it was special for her. The food arrived at random times, but each item was worth the wait.

The best Caesars Ive ever had in Vancouver. It was dressed w a jumbo prawn the size of a coaster, pepperoni, crab claw and fresh horse radish. Staff and service were bomb. Pretty sure we met everyone in the front crew, servers, bartenders, managers... they made us feel super welcome and spoiled us. Were definitely coming back w more cash!
Food was good..gorgeous spot! We watched the sunset at happy hour and had nice cocktails. Had lovely truffle fries and calamari.

Great food on the raw bar, fantastic happy hour specials, beer on tap, and an extremely helpful and kind staff! This was our first time here with a larger group of 6 people and we had a wonderful experience. Definitely a must stop when I m the area!

Prompt and friendly service with a unique menu. The food was great and the hand made tortilla chips were delicious. Great view of English Bay from both inside the restaurant and the patio. Bonus surprise, theres a pool table!

Highly recommend this restaurant   it is VIBE. We went there and ordered a bottle of wine which was so tasty ( Friend) also we had Burrata & Focaccia which was delicious with amazing seasonings. The staff are an amazing and so professional. Definitely I ll check it out soon

Hook is one of English Bay s gems. I love to go for the fantastic view on the patio, great service, and excellent beer selection. Shout out to Eva, who always provides amazing service and wine and beer recs.
response_from_owner_text: So kind Jasmine, thank you!

review_text: Beautiful setting, the food was great and fairly priced ! We all loved our meal and we will be back
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the review, Charlene! See you again soon. Cheers!

review_text: Came here after being treated like trash at Cactus Club across the street. Great service, food and drinks.Friendly staff. Way better option than Craptus Club. Highly recommended. Food
response_from_owner_text: It was wonderful to meet you both! Please come back and visit us soon!

review_text: Very good service, good food and good environment. Very nice, well trained and friendly staff. They give you many reasons to come back.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the great review, Hamidreza! We look forward to seeing you again!

review_text: Perfect place to go to thats pretty much on the water. The vibe is very relaxed and calming with the music and the staff are very polite and welcoming. Food and drinks were great, as well as the perfect view of the ocean. Would definitely recommend.

Not sure if it was the seafood tower or my server but it was almost like love at first sight! Eva was articulate and charming and the food she recommended was the best. My favourite dishes are the sablefish, the anchovy toast, shishito peppers and the beet salad
response_from_owner_text: Hi Justin! Thanks so much for the lovely review, much appreciated!

review_text: This is a fantastic place!!  Theo was the best server we have had in a long time!  Lots of fun and energy!  Thanks for a great time and best fish!!!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Stacey, thank you so much for your review. Have to agree, Theo is fantastic! See you soon :)

review_text: Been coming here for years now, mainly for the amazing service from the sweet employee, Eva. She never fails to brightens up my day. Your hospitality is amazing my friend, food is always great and your energy is unshakeable!!! So thank you
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Melissa!

review_text: Great food, affordable seafood dishes. Stop by for the happy hour deal for some drinks and snacks! Mango habanero sauce for oysters was absolutely amazing!
Wow! What a location, and what fantastic food! Try the fish and chips, you wont be sorry (I want the recipe for that coleslaw, its the best Ive ever had).

This is my favourite spot on English Bay in @YVR. @HookSeabar is located in a perfect spot with its oceanside view across. I really enjoy their tasty meals and great selection of menu items and drinks. I had several patio drinks here with a few groups of friends during our COVID summer. I will definitely be coming back for the salads. A good selection of small bites. During COVID, dine in or take out via Uber Eats. Support your local restaurants during these times.
Amazing salad with tuna :) Fantastic staff. As my son did not like much meatbolls cause they were too spicy, he got ice cream as a compensation :)
We had a really good time having dinner on a patio. Friendly service and good food, what else do you need?
had an awesome time. Great place to have dinner especially if you re looking for a chill place to have a drink and snack. Eva was an amazing server and made me feel right at home.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Ray - thank you for the review! Look forward to having you in again.

review_text: We had Bre as our server on the patio! She went above and beyond to make us feel looked after! She was so friendly and attentive and made sure to check in on what we needed whether it was a drink, a snack or the heaters! We watched the sunset on the patio and continued to order more rounds because of her!! Honestly such a rockstar server !! Will defs be back again because of Bre!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Lexy! Thank you so much for taking the time to share this lovely review - I will make sure to pass your compliments on to Bre!

review_text: Aug 10 Ive never been to The Hook , reading the reviews about the restaurant are all very good. It seems like a great place to work I pass by The Hook one time when I was on the bus .
Decent spot! Really wanted to leave a review for our server, Bre (like the cheese!) though. Sat on the patio and she made the evening perfect for us. 5.1/5 for sure!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you!

review_text: nice ambiance, good food, Eva was the best server we couldve had!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Jenna!

review_text: Great food in an awesome location. The patio on a sunny spring day was A+. My wife and I really enjoyed our brunch here. Worth every penny.
I always have the best time here! Especially on the patio, Eva and Breanna always make my friends and I feel so welcome! This is the best place for oysters by the beach!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Siobahn!

review_text: always amazing food especially come for margaritas. the service was great i had breanna she took such great care of us she was so attentive and made us feel so well looked after!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Jaden!

review_text: Fantastic service, everything was fast and food came out quickly. We had 12 oysters, $2 a shuck. The beat salad and brussel sprouts were delicious. Also the seafood pasta. Right on English Bay. Great affordable spot! No reso needed either :)

Walked in for dinner with no reservations and got a table right away with incredible views of English Bay right at the window. Ordered fish & chips, lobster prawn roll and oysters, everything was delicious. Great service as well.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Daniela - thank you so much for sharing your feedback!

review_text: Really nice view from the tables. Food was good and the table service great. Its only a few steps from the beach and it is not really expensive

Creative and delicious cocktails at this place. I had 2 different cocktails, both were strong and bursting with flavour. We were dining on the deck in the fall with a party of four; the service was fast and friendly, very accommodating and knowledgable when told that one of us was Celiac. Alterations were made to that persons entree to make it gluten free. Lobster guacamole, salmon and fish and chips, it was all very good. I would push next time for my salmon to be a little rarer throughout, but it wasnt over-cooked. Well be back!
Delicious food, nice sea view, good ambience Really enjoyed our evening at hook Food
response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for taking the time to connect with us and for the great review. Cheers, Caro!

review_text: VERY nice staff!! They are helpful when choosing the right beer and are extremely funny. We enjoyed the happy hour when the sun was shining. Great afternoon at this great place! Also try one of their bites, they are to die for. They are also part of the happy hour, so dont miss out
My server was Bre, her vibes were immaculate . Not only was she fast and efficient, she cracked great jokes, and made our experience even better. Great place, and a great worker
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Emma!

review_text: No clue why this place isn t packed. Ordered chorizo mussels and fish and chips. Both were banging.

This place is awesome. The food and service was on point and the atmosphere really felt cozy. All the food tasted fresh and they had a slew of options. I highly recommend this place and I will be going back. The server was knowledgeable and funny.
Great food and fantastic view of English bay. We had a very early dinner here and all 7 of us were very satisfied with our dishes.

Amazing is all I have to say about this restaurant. The food was absolutely delicious and our server, Bree was so friendly, attentive, informative and great with my kiddo. Best service Ive had in a long time. 11/10 recommended to dine here !!!
Great view of the beach, good beer but not cold enough, food is also quite good.
Great food and drinks. Amazing service. Jack our server was outstanding and friendly.
Awesome food, great view, nice service and fair price! I m definitely coming back. I really recommend the soft shell crab BLT sandwich and the ceviche!
A few beers overlooking the beach. Very nice and thanks to Andy for looking after us and making us drink just enough beer to make us feel a bit fuzzy A great place to chill and watch the world go by.

Great Place to watch the Sunset! Heaters were on for outside and they have blankets. Good service. Kalamari is non traditional. French fry size pieces cooked and battered to perfection. I dont even miss the tentacle parts which are usually my favorite. Friend had fish and chips and the fish was massive and thinly battered. Ceasar was great too, especially with the type of pickle they use for garnish. Will be back for sure!
Delicious sea food and gluten free options
We were there for a Sunday lunch. We tried mussel and clams, burger, fish tacos, and fish and chips which wete awesome.

Sunny evening, bustling restaurant. We took my mother-in-law for her birthday dinner. She loves fish and chips. Our waitress was delightful and very cheerful. She really made my mother-in-law s evening even bringing a special dessert. Thanks all it was a great evening. Oh, and the food was great!
We come here every summer and we had to get our happy hour fix and we love this place cause it s close to where we stay. Definitely recommended A+++++++

The best customer service I got in a while. And the best mezcal cocktail (those flavours will blow your mind - sweet, sour, bitter and smoky all in one). I don t remember the names, but a big shout out for a closing crew from yesterday (Hawaiian shirt and  just  5.0ft servers, you know who you are!). Funny, nice, willing to tolerate us. This is how serving should be done. Great job :)
Amazing view of english bay! Their food is good as well as their service.
Perfect spot to view the English Bay
Great seafood and local Beers with beautiful view at English Bay. We were there on wednesday, there was Nice live music and cheap pints of beer. Loved it
lovely experience here :) creole prawns were great, the decor and music here is nice! Eva helped us out and she was so fun, me and my friend adored her
Ambience, staff, and food were all 5 star however the wine list needs work.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Dianne, Thank you for your review! Would love to hear your suggestions on the wine list, please feel free to e-mail marisa@hookrestaurant.com. Cheers!

review_text: We had a large party at Hook and did their family style meal. Lots of great food choices and the food was really good. Service has been really great both times Ive been here. Limited wine choices but enough for any palate. Staff are amazing and helpful and friendly. This will be a regular stop me in Vancouver.

The fish and chips is excellent - you get a MASSIVE piece of fish, and its very tasty. Ask for extra tartar sauce though, because its also delicious and the little ramekin it comes with just isnt enough! The menu prices are also very reasonable - but if you factor in the location and the view of English Bay, theyre an absolute bargain. Definitely a lovely spot for a dinner at sunset.
Loved the crispy jumbo prawns & oysters. Epic spot for happy hour. Beautiful view of the ocean and service is awesome.

Amazing!!! To drink definitely try the pick me up so many wonderful flavors in one glass! And to eat Im in LOVE with their beet salad! I had the cutest server, she was so bubbly and on point. Fantastic experience and loved my ocean view from the patio
OMG. Fish and chip heaven. With a view of the ocean no less! And if you cant find parking there is a valet service in the back alley. Perfection!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for joining us Cindy! We are happy to share a piece of heaven with you. Come back soon and we will lift you off your feet with more tasty treats!

review_text: Fantastic sea food and drinks and the new manager Boston was a real gem

We had a really lovely happy hour here. Service was great and patio was super pleasant. The food - for Happy Hour- was terrific. Ceviche with lime and coconut milk, fried chicken a la Blind Sparrow, guacamole with house made chips, and an epic burger with the perfect light as air but stay together brioche bun. It s the kind of burger worthy of a top ten list. Brasserie L ecole or Veselkas type of good burger. Really good beer list as well. Really punched above its weight class. Look forward to coming by when on mainland.
The best place ever! Lovely & respectful staff, high quality food and services, pet lovers! Perfect view! Highly recommend
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your review Mr. Hashemian! We are very much pet lovers and welcome dogs on our patio anytime!

review_text: Great food and great service Bre was quick and very friendly, will be back when Im in the area
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Sam!

review_text: Delicious food. Outstanding service. Physical distancing not so great. My wife and I had a date night at Hook and absolutely loved the food. We had oysters, fish tacos, mussels and clams, roasted sprouts and corn. All were incredible. The two cocktails that we shared were out of this world.  Our server was really nice and helpful. Overall we had an excellent time. However, we thought the physical distancing could use some work, as they ve taken a pretty lax approach and their staff don t appear to be actively encouraging physical distancing.

Hands down might be the best service Ive received at a restaurant in Vancouver. Chelsea was exceptionally friendly, knowledgeable and made us all feel so welcomed. The food was fresh and yummy but the star of our experience was Chelsea. 10/10 will come back just because of her amazing service and genuine personality.

Our severs name was Josh and he was awesome. Playful and Knowledgeable and recommend drinks for each if us based on what we like, he hit the mark perfectly. We had the happy hour coconut ceviche and fried chicken. Both were delicious. 100% would go back.
This place is new so we decided to try it with friends. A little pricey, but the food and service made up for everything. Just ask to sit outside because it gets really loud inside.

Went here for the first time over the weekend and loved it. Staff were friendly and they had various social distancing measures in place. Most of all, my boyfriend and I were impressed with their cocktail menu. The Sparrow & Lady Stanley were delicious! We will definitely be coming back.

So delicious, with a calm, relaxed atmosphere. Every dish was delicious. We had a halibut special with risotto that was seasoned perfectly, and fish and chips that had a perfectly crisp batter and the octopus app was excellent. We had our young children with us and the staff was happy to accommodate. They dont have a kids menu, but made a small pasta dish with cheese sauce for the kids.

Came here during happy hour from 4-6pm and had a table on their patio. They have some really good prices for their food options especially the oysters! Fresh and delicious! Server was really hard to flag down though which was slightly disappointing. Would recommend paying a little more attention to the customers that are seated in the patio section as they tend to be forgotten about :)
Highest quality food and service.  Lovely venue too.  I had the Wild Pacific halibut ceviche and seared scallops from happy hour menu - so delish   .  Will come back to try the rest of the menu.

Another sure winner when dining in North Vancouver, the Fishworks is in a trendy neighborhood with ample parking nearby and a nice view down the street. Service is fast and very friendly, the menu if interesting and varied. Happy Hour oysters are 1.50 each, so we had a dozen. Fresh and delicious. My wife had the special, pan fried Halibut in a roasted red pepper sauce which was delicious, perfectly prepared. I had the Paella with prawns, mussels and clams, it was delicious. Atmosphere is cozy and warm, altogether a delightful experience. Would highly recommended.
This is a must do if you visit Vancouver and like seafood. The food, the service, and the atmosphere was 5 stars! We will definitely be returning next year!

To say that the food is superb is an understatement, dining at Fishworks is an experience. There is no other place that has a personal touch of the overall experience, starting from the on-the-house warm bread with a side of chickpea puree and even to the chocolate truffles,a complimentary treat at the end. Now to the real deal, you can literally taste the flavors of the ocean in your mouth. You can savour its freshness and a whole level of gastronomical expertise tossed in a plate. The Sockeye Salmon Wellington, the Fishworks Paella and the Scallop Risotto are my top 3 food in their menu! A must to recommend to my friends and family.

I celebrated my birthday in this place, the food was very good, the salmon wellington took the night away. The place was full despite being Monday, for a moment it is unpleasant that they are reminding you that you only have 2 hours because the next reservation arrives, this don t let you enjoy the dinner. Other than that, it was a very good experience. Fair prices, good portions, friendly staff. They should have something for birthday s celebration (complimentary cake or something)

My wife and I have been coming to Fishworks for a number of years now, the food and atmosphere have always been high quality and consistent. However, tonight we had one of THE best waitresses we have ever had (and we eat out fairly regularly). Maia served us on the patio and was thoroughly attentive, thoughtful, ultra pleasant, and genuinely gave us a can-do, my pleasure attitude. Such a rarity in todays service industry. A request to the owners of Fishworks, please do what you can to keep Maia on staff. We will most definitely be asking to be seated at her table for our future visits. Thank you Maia for a memorable evening!

Was visiting Vancouver & found this gem! The seafood tower was absolutely amazing & under priced for the amount of food & the quality. Special thanks to Tom the bartender. He was very knowledgeable & made us feel like we were regulars.

Absolutely fantastic!! My partner and I went for a romantic date, and totally plan on coming back. The service is phenomenal and so is the food! I have never shucked oysters so quickly before IN. MY. LIFE.
The food and the quality was amazing.The tiramisu and the fishworks seafood tower is a must try.
We were going to have a just quick happy hour, but we ended up paying $200. The food was so great and the servers were very friendly. I highly recommend this restaurant. The vibe is good.

Highly recommend, the food is incredible. Crab cakes were so good and tender. Little wings oysters were so fresh and delicate. Salmon carpaccio was amazing, accompanied with garlic chips, roasted capers and emoji mushrooms. Bouillabaisse was mouth watering, mussels and halibut in it were so fresh! Totally worth visiting again.

Delicious happy hour deals! My partner and I enjoyed the honey mussels, seared ahi tuna, salmon carpaccio, and a dozen oysters. Food was delicious and beautifully presented. The decore in the room was very nice as well. A great vibe for some good deals on seafood!
Great menu options that never disappoint. Really enjoyed the Salmon Wellington. The service is prompt and friendly. It can get a little loud inside at times, but overall an amazing experience!

Great location, awesome staff, and amazing food. We tried a few different items from the menu... the lobster bisque was delicious, the Salmon Wellington- the best! Lobster Mac n cheese- excellent and so much flavor... last but not least the Cod n chips, perfect! The portions are generous, the presentation is lovely,  and the price is right for the quality you get. The restaurant is beautiful and the patio seating was quaint and had a romantic feel to it... definitely a place to check out when visiting North Vancouver.
Excellent food, great value, and server Chloe was simply awesome. I had Sturgeon for the first time ever. Just wow! Food
Happy hour!!! We had oyster, crab cake, salmon carpaccio, and mussel. They are all excellent and went very well with their house wine. Also their desserts were all to die for.
Everything s great and Chloe was the best!

Really delicious. I has the free range chicken which was amazing and garlic white wine muscles for an appetizer and my fave dessert the creme brulee. I would definitely recommend this restaurant and go there again. the service was great and its a cozy yet chic space.

We absolutely love going to Fishworks! One of the best places to dine in Lonsdale. Quality food and ingredients served in style by a very friendly charming team. I would order anything on the menu with confidence that it will be delicious! Whether we re going out for a quick beer and oysters or a full meal, Fish works never disappoints. The food specials are always spectacular and well worth a try. The atmosphere is both upscale and cozy!

The oysters are so good and there is a happy hour from 4 to 6! We also tried the octopus and the clam pasta and both were also 10/10. Front of house was able to accommodate us even thought we were early to our reservation and the servers where super nice! Cant wait to visit again.
Attentive waitstaff and well seasoned, perfectly cooked food! We loved the halibut ceviche, seafood paella and seared scallops with squash tortellini

Lovely dinner out with my friends on a dark, rainy and dismal Tuesday evening .three of us shared salmon pate and we each ordered the dinner special: halibut topped with wild mushroom sauce, served with roasted potatoes, carrots, green beans and cauliflower!   Delicious.  Wonderful service and warm ambiance.

We have been here twice, and each time was wonderful. This most recent time around, we got the seafood tower. It had, hands down, the best lobster that I have ever tasted *and* the best baked oysters that I have ever tasted. They must magick their seafood down from some wonderful place on high where the fish are personally blessed by a great deity. Seriously, it was that good. The service was outstanding as well. When we went pre-pandemic, we didnt have reservations because we were just dropping in to check it out, and the service at the bar was superlative. This time, we reserved a table and it was again excellent. They were even nice enough to help me with a mask when Id lost mine after taking it off for dinner. Well be making the trip up again in a couple months to eat here, and Id imagine that as long as we live in the region, well make sure to come by at least two or three times a year if not more.

Highly recommended! We stopped at this stunning restaurant and made a quick reservation and to our surprise we got in. You must have proof of vaccination. Back to the food, we were absolutely blown away. We ordered two ceasers, baked oysters, Salmon wellington, and lobster Mac and cheese, everything was very pleasing to the palate . We will definitely be coming back
Had a amazing dinner here, had the Sockeye Salmon Wellington.

Great dinner out. Everyone in our group really liked their meal. We did make a rezo for 5:30 which was good as they were pretty busy with happy hour. Oysters, appies and drinks on special. Our server was delightful and calm through all the noise (babies crying etc) and busyness. We really liked the oysters, as well as the octopus and paella. Parking: Also right where a bus stop is, so if taking the bus its an easy location to get to.

Been coming to fishworks since 2016, recently came here with my girlfriend for our anniversary and had a wonderful meal. The prawn carbonara and the Hokkaido scollops were delicious. The service however is what stood out to me and my partner, our server Michael was very attentive and helpful with all of our requests and questions. My water was never empty and we felt very well taken care of.

One of my favorite seafood restaurants in Vancouver. For the quality, I think the prices are on the reasonable side given Metro Vancouver. The seafood is fresh, and Ill recommend the starter platter (the King crab is the only thing I think may be previously frozen). The paella is packed with seafood. The salmon Wellington is their signature, but I find it is on the dry side and really needs the pesto sauce to help it out. No fuss good food restaurant to enjoy with your friends and family.
A hidden gem in North Van!! The food was fresh and delicious, and all at a great price point. Will certainly be a go to place!

We live on Vancouver Island and had not been back to this restaurant in about 7 years. Would it still live up to our memories of fantastic food?  OH YES!!! We started with Crispy Squid and Prawns - sooooo good. My hubby had the same as last time - Wild Pacific Halibut Poutine with goat cheese gravy... as good as he remembered. I had the Hokkaido Scallops with home made squash tortellini,  sage burn butter sauce, toasted walnuts. The scallops were cooked to perfection and everything else on the plate was wonderful too. If I could have licked the plate clean, I would have. Also the wine recommendation was spot on. We had a California white called Lieu Dit from the Santa Maria Valley. We highly recommend this restaurant... the staff are professional and friendly. If you are staying in downtown Vancouver hop on the seabuss (route 1 to get there and route 2 to return) and walk to this neighbour gem in North Vancouver. It is soooo good! Thanks Fish Works for a memorable meal.
Just squeaked in before 6 and got a few Happy Hour appies. Seafood Tower was excellent. Friendly server and great service and tasty food. All you can ask for.
Dined a couple weeks ago and had a great experience! The salmon Wellington was superb. Maia was a kind and caring waitress. 10/10!

Came here with the intention of trying their dine out Vancouver 2022 menu but their a la carte menu captured our interest. The price is also very economical for a seafood restaurant. Scallops on the risotto was perfectly cooked and the amount of lobster meat on the lobster Mac and cheese was plentiful. The favourite of the night was the paella. Everything was fresh and delicious. Highly recommend!

What a great experience. I live on the North Shore but first time coming here. Wow I will be back. Very telling when the restaurant is packed and it is a few days after New Years. Service was exceptional and the decor and layout was very welcoming. The food was excellent. We shared the best salad which was huge and then I had the Salmon Wellington, so delicious. My partner had the Sablefish special which she really enjoyed. Suffice it to say we were very full after that dinner. Looking forward to going back.

Fishworks is an excellent seafood restaurant, and its only a matter of time until I go back.  It can get pretty busy. My friends, wife and I were lucky to get a seat at the bar as walk-ins after being turned away from 2 other restaurants.  Service was friendly.  The frontman behind the bar was a true gentleman.  Their wine selection is pretty good but I opted for a beer since we walked in at the end of happy hour. Shucked oysters at happy hour seem like good value for money, so we got some and were served by the frontman. Great way to start the evening. My wife got the lobster bisque. As others have reported, it is really friggin good.  Their salmon wellington is quite simply the best piece of seafood Ive ever had in North Van. Awesome experience.

I started going to fishworks on my visits to N. Vancouver and now, 3 years later I ve relocated here and I m still going and have never been let down with every dish I ve had. My favourite go-to. Service is excellent and staff is friendly, knowledgeable and on top of everything. Highly recommend!

Its one of my favorite seafood restaurants.   Amazing food and spectacular service.  Michal and Tom do a great job behind the bar and the serving folks are amazing.  Attentive Receptive and helpful!  Can not recommend this place enough
it was so delicious; my family enjoyed so much. Especially, the white wine was so good with food.
I had an amazing experience! The food and customer service was off the charts. I will definitely be back when I am in town. Also, Tom was amazing. Made me feel right at home :)
Nice food, tase is good, abbot on pricy side but the it should be ;) Soup is amazing, both of them as we shared as family. There is a Syria s at the end, happy end ;)

Great food! We got the salmon and poutine for dinner and their take on the poutine and salmon Wellington was mouth watering ! Not too pricey either for the food! The customer service was excellent as well.

Greatest place ever. Even my kids (ages 10-14) loved it! Best food at the Shipyard area hands down and worth the walk away from the water. Loved the additional dessert treat. Thank you. Kid-friendliness: Kid friendly for ages 10 and up

I don t know how this place doesn t have 5 stars! Superb food. Best service I ve ever had. So happy I stumbled into this place, best meal on my visit to Vancouver (and this was the only place I hadn t specifically researched trying to find some of the best food!)
I rarely dine in North Van and glad to have found this gem.  Every single dish was so tasty and fresh  nice atmosphere as well
I liked how they served us free sweets after dinner. Ganache tasted really good. Great customer service and delicious and well presented food!

Fishworks is a real CATCH! Never disappoints! The Halibut Poutine is my personal fave but the Salmon Wellington is a close second. Chef extraordinaire always cooks the fish to perfection! 100%!!! Great atmosphere for date night or hosting big parties. Absolutely my favourite place to bring out-of-town visitors to WOW! them. Located in the heart of Lower Lonsdale steps away from the Shipyards. My husband and I feel lucky to live nearby and are truly welcomed and remembered by staff every visit. Fantastic Happy Hour to boot! Best to reserve ahead especially on busy weekends. What a gem!

I love this restaurant and the waiter that helped me the day that I was there. I was really really enjoying my perfectly made BBQ prawn alla carbonara, then whithin a few seconds, the heatstroke hit me so bad that I almost fainted, the guy helped me with a cold towel and water, I left when I was a bit better, but didnt have a chance to tell them that I am so sorry   and thank you for your help   I will come back again for sure.

Excellent choice for a birthday dinner! Lively (a bit noisy) atmosphere, good service and delicious, well presented food.  Our table split a halibut ceviche to start and had Fishworks Paella, Sockeye Salmon Wellington and West Coast Lingcod as mains. All were served in generous portions. Finished off with Creme Brulee to share.  The salmon and creme brulee were the stars of the show. Hope to return soon. Parking: Tough to find parking in LoLo.  We parked at the IGA garage on Esplanade. Wheelchair accessibility: The  main seating area is up a set of 3 stairs. There is one table by the door that is wheelchair accessible.  I have a walker and staff assisted in storing it away from traffic.

Excellent service and perfect food every time we visit. Bought a bottle of wine and something didnt taste quite right, they swapped it out for another with no questions asked. Service is miles above the rest.

This is my favorite North Van restaurant! The food is always so fresh and delicious, and they have a great array of seafood dishes to suit whatever mood you are in. My personal favorites are the Salmon Wellington and the Fish and Chips. Definitely worth stopping by for dinner!
The farmed sturgeon was delicious. They offer a nice selection of dishes. We sat on the patio which was a little loud as it was beside the road. Overall we loved it.

The halibut poutine was delicious! It was my husband s birthday and they offered up chocolate truffles on a Happy Birthday plate - very  sweet. Lucy our server was pleasant, professional and very kind. We definitely will be back. Thank you Lucy!
Best food and coffee in the north shore. Everything is amazing check out the pics. Food

They seated us promptly and were attentive but not overbearing throughout our dinner. Great menu options with generous portion sizes and good prices for what you get. Servers were very friendly and atmosphere was cool. Definitely plan to go back!
Amazing service!  Thank you Chloe for being such an incredible server and making our birthday celebration extra  special. The food and beverages were delicious.

In town from the states (Atlanta, GA) and this place is really nice. Not an expert but I would say more upscale based on what s around it. My wife and I both choose the Halibut (two different versions) and our daughter had the clams and pasta. Also had the salmon carpaccio and the lobster bisque. Don t judge we were hungry. In any case really really good. We were slightly underdressed but didn t feel out of place. Come here, service and food were special!

Our waiter was so friendly and funny. We ordered the paella and the halibut poutine. The portions were more than enough for one person, especially the paella. Both dishes were absolutely delicious and so fresh. The waiter was also great at accommodating peanut/nut allergies.

Glad that we have such a nice seafood restaurant like this in NVan. Every single dish was delicious and oysters were very fresh. Indoor dining area was properly sanitized with proper the social distancing measures.
Popped in for a quick dinner and we were pleasantly surprised to find that Fishworks is excellent in every way. We will definitely be back.

Simply divine. A must try and repeat. The Halibut poutine will simply take you to a new level of poutine tasting that you wish to repeat and repeat. The Creme brulee reminded me my Grammy Easter special threat that I wished to tasted it slowly.
Great food even greater pasta.

Amazing experience. Food wad was more than spectacular and the atmosphere was amazing. The servers along with the rest of the front of house staff were incredibly accommodating. When you re in North Vancouver, THIS is the place to go.
Delicious! Seafood tower for two was perfectly proportioned and the baked oysters were the best. Lobster pasta was full of chunky lobster.
Amazing salmon & paella... quick fresh food with great service! Wouldve been a straight 5 stars if the AC worked. .
Food is great! Definitely one of our favourite restaurants now! Looking forward to try all their delicious food!
I would highly recommend it if you are looking for fresh foods and happy hour in North Vancouver, you will never go wrong with them, staff always friendly and sweet <3

Amazing seafood place and always one of my favourites! I had the Lingcod dish recently and it was very tasty and refreshing. The vegetable was crisp and the fish was cooked perfectly. The Paella and the Salmon Wellington are amazing too. I discovered that taking SeaBus from Waterfront Station is so much faster and easier. Its a must 10-12 minutes scenic ferry ride and you get to enjoy an amazing view of the mountains and Vancouver skyscrapers. The restaurant is only a block from the Quay Market.
Ate here the other night and the service was outstanding! My server, Savannah, made my experience. I couldn t recommend this place enough!
We went for the dine out menu. Everything is so delicious and service is excellent. We also ordered some drinks and oysters.
Excellent seafood very friendly and nice service. Prices are fair for the quality of food and location. Highly recommend. Parking: Public parking available near the location.

Hip atmosphere. Delicious food. I had the clam chowder, a caesar salad and a pint of locally brewed ginger beer - loved it all. Sat at the bar and conversed with a thoughtful Swiss architect - also out for dinner in his own. It was a lovely evening.
Great north van gem. The seafood paella was so good!!

Really impressed at how good the food was! Recently Ive been to two other fancy seafood restaurants on the north shore and fishworks was the best. The others werent bad but wishworks is just a step above with flavor and quality.

I visit Fishworks every time that Im in North Vancouver, more than once per year, because the food, ambiance and service is always excellent. For the first time I sat at the bar; what a wonderful experience! To note that Tom is just the man behind the bar or the barman totally misses the point. Tom is the maestro food & entertainment director, he greets as many as he can, brings you into his dining area while ensuring that the entire restaurant is running like the well oiled machine that it is. So whether its a quiet tete-a-tete, a boisterous gathering or simply oysters and a beer you must visit Fishworks and say hi to Tom to be entertained, fulfilled and satisfied.
Good oysters (2.5$ ea from vancouver island) huge and mild salty Pasta is steelhead garganelli - fresh creamy mildly sour nice flavours Wine Pinot Gris rich spicy and sweet paired well with the food
Delicious Dinner.  Good service, friendly, efficient. Very noisy. Vegetarian options: The only vegetarian item I saw on the menu was a green salad. No main course.
We had a fabulous dinner. We would definitely recommend the raw oysters, the lemongrass, coconut mussels and the squash ravioli with scallops, delicious! Cant wait to go back! Food
Some of best seafood/dinner menu and very well equipped staff. While it can be a bit cramped and hot on certain days, it is 100% overshadowed by the fantastic menu and staff.

***DROOL*** When looking into Fishworks before our arrival, there were so many posts about the Salmon Wellington that everyone at my table ended up ordering it. It was absolutely divine. The same can be said about the squid and prawn appetizer and the chocolate mousse dessert. Im looking forward to visiting again and trying more menu items--Im confident theyll be equally delicious.
We had a wonderful dinner! Delightful service and a fantastic meal to wrap up our getaway. Well definitely be back!
Amazing food, wonderful service. Definetely coming back!

Delicious dinner with swift service and super friendly staff. Our food tasted amazing and fresh - from clam chowder to salmon and halibut. Our kids really enjoyed lobster mac&cheese Even dessert cream brulee was mouthwatering

Absolutely fantastic atmosphere and food. Get a reservation cuz this place is popular. Happy hour oysters at the bar, muscles in a garlic broth, and an entertaining bartender shucking and making drinks. Give this place a go if that sounds like your thing.

Delicious food. We did the dine out vancouver menu. Everything was really delicious. Service was great. The only bad thing Id say is that some (or maybe just this one) of the entrees are very minimal and we didnt know that they didnt come with a side, we would have ordered a side had we known and then didnt want to wait for a side with the dinner already having been served - my husband left feeling a little hungry. Otherwise, everything was amazing. Would def recommend.
Food is consistently good. Prices are reasonable, and portions are filling.
Yummy!! Came here for fish and it was delicious Oysters, main mane and deserts (tiramisu)were great! Highly recommend
Excellent place to have a seafood dishes!! Appetizers, Mains, desserts, everything tasted wonderful!!
highly recommend this restaurant for a drink and appetizers. The staff are incredible even during busy hours.

I can t say enough about how perfect every element of my dining experience was. Food, wine, service, perfect. I have been here many times and it is consistently exceptional. This time sharing with my sister, just now cancer free and able to be out of the house for the first time in two years. Where to go?  No question, Fishworks, and it did not disappoint.  Thank you all of you.
Lovely evening, good food on Lonsdale.
Excellent food, presentation, service, ambiance. If you love seafood, you really have to visit - its our go to place, always reliable and delicious.
Back after a long break and glad we did. The good and service were great. Loved the crispy prawns and squid!

Tried dinner at Fishworks for Dineout Vancouver 2023. The staff was able to accommodate for a wheelchair and the service was excellent. That said, there was no warm-bread and we were seated right by the door. Table favourites were octopus, scallops, and the poached-pear dessert. Steamed whole fish and other fish dinner was also well-prepared, tasty, and worth a try. Reasonable pricing, good food, highlighted by superior service earned Fishworks this 5-star review. Parking: No parking in front, but side streets and lot parking available Wheelchair accessibility: Able to accommodate, call ahead to confirm!
Really good food. Was there for a private function and the wait staff performed their jobs very well.

Make a reservation so as not to be disappointed at the door - as Fishworks is a local fave and well worth it! Top notch service and perfectly prepared dishes. I had the crab cakes appie and it was delicious - not over cooked at all. Scallops are a personal favourite so I went with the risotto and it was perfection. Great selection of BC and international wines. A local gem!

The best seafood in North Vancouver hands down. Great bartender, oysters, crab and scallops. The Sablefish was amazing as well. This little hidden gem was packed and for good reason. Make reservations, you will need them!

Been here twice and had a lovely experience both times. We ve had the crab cakes, salmon Wellington and halibut poutine. We thought the menu included original options, our server was very friendly, and the food was very tasty. We had nice, pairing wines as well. Will definitely go back again!

Excellent food. Reasonable prices.  Street parking nearby.  Usually crowded even on weeknights.  Check out TheTower a sampler designed for two (or 3 on a diet). Great attentive staff.  They also serve great fish and chips.

I visited North Vancouver District the first time just to try the food here. Honestly, they are best fish and chips Ive ever had better others Ive had in Greater Vancouver! The in-house tartar sauce was sooo delicious as well (can squeeze out as much as I want); it had a fresh, tarty dill taste. The onion rings and oyster were good. And the tomato juice was tasty and refreshing. The mushy peas, however, were not my cup of tea (it, to me, is like a coarse base puree thats just salted). It was quite the satiating lunch; perfect for going to a hike trail afterward.  Moreover, I did not need to eat dinner. As for the service, its excellent. I liked the waitress personality; shes chill and accommodating.

A great quick service, clean, one of the best in Greater Vancouver Area for those fish lovers, eat as much as you can meal also comes with unlimited refill for Pepsi products, coleslaw is great, onion rings and sauces. Enjoy the fresh fish & chips!

$20 all you can eat fish and chips! The only way to go! The pieces of fish are similar in size to chicken fingers, so not huge. Not sure it would be worth it to get the one piece meal for $16 or $17, but with the all you can eat, its a no brainer. Also comes with bottomed bottomless soda if thats your thing.

I like to come here sometimes after hiking very hungry and tired. The All-you-can-it fish and chips + a sleeve of a delicious Okanagan Spring beer, is a really good deal. The delicious food, the great service, the cleaning and the nice environment make this place a fresh spot to stay. Thank you!
Always love to come here. The all you can eat is great mad they always make it fresh. It is very basic yet very tasty. Recommended dishes All-You-Can-Eat Fish and Chips

Nice light and crispy fish and chips. We used to go here for all you can eat which was a good deal. The food is fresh and the service is good. Recently with COVID we ordered the Takeout Special which includes 2 pounds of fish, a big load of chips, a 2 litre pop, and coleslaw. Was packaged nicely, ready when we arrived to pickup. Enough for two meals for our family of four with younger kids. Great deal.

Id say C-Lovers is one of the better fish and chips places in Vancouver. I would recommend getting the haddock over the cod as they are very similar in flavour, especially after being deep fried, but the haddock is a larger portion.
A very pleasant suprise! The batter on the fish was so light and flaky. Its one of the best fish and chip places Ive ever been to.
I love the deep fried dill pickles! and also the platter was so good
Very good fish and chips and simple but great coleslaw. They have Haddock which is what my wife likes. They serve beer and wine also. The service was great and prices pretty good too.
Great fish and chips!  Large tasty piece of fish perfectly battered and fried.  Fries are great! Customer service was awesome and I would highly recommend this place for a first date!
Love this place..I always get all you can eat...I have been going to this place for years now..best seafood on the northshore

The go to place for AYCE Fish & Chips with bottomless pop. Service is friendly... you dont have to have fish & chips refill, you can just choose fish for your refill. Great value & the fish is good. They used pollock, meat is firm. Batter is light & not greasy.

Everything excellent. The minute you walk in the door they take your name and ph# for contact tracing tables approprately spaced out plexiglass seperation sanitizer a must before being seated. Servers are friendly and aaaaaefficient!!!!. The all you can eat fish and chips, tarter sauce and coleslaw is the best i have had. Kennebec fries fresh hot and crispy fish without too much batter. They have a great team from the servers  cooks & dishwasher. I highly recommend this C-lovers. I give them a 5+++++
Not elaborate but well run. Good F&C at (still) reasonable prices. Excellent, friendly & helpful service.
One of the best fish and chips in Vancouver

Never really had real fish and chips until I found this gem. Everything here was freaking delicious.   The onion rings here are amazing! But not as amazing as the different types of fried fish here. Will definitely visit again when Im around the area! Didnt know there were multiple locations of this place around Vancouver.
I liked the cuisine, the service, and the ambiance. I like professionalism and customer care standards, which should remain to the top. Another visit is required here!
Excellent food, cute little place but the service should be more friendly in the dining area. Parking: Good
One of the best i ve ever tried!!
We placed a largish take out order, and they made everything ontime and hot and fresh.  Everyone was very happy! Parking: Lots of free parking.

The halibut burger is the best fish burger Ive ever had! The house made tartar sauce is unbeatable. I made a pickup order and they waited until I got there to give me a piece of fish fresh out of the fryer  . One of my favourite spots in the city.
Authentic fish and chips! Friendly staff, delicious seafood! Loved our experience there and came out with super happy bellies!
Cheerful, hard-working folks, Fish is prepared, perfectly fresh change of cooking oil, pleasant waitresses

Amazing place with an all you can eat fish and chips option. It is very good quality for the quantity as well, and the servers were always smiling. Nothing much more can be asked of a place. Do make sure to go here with a big appetite, I am sure you will enjoy the fish!
Not too expensive, good fish and good chips. Great place for inexpensive fish etc. Onion rings were great Parking: Lot of parking in lot near
Consistently great takeout.  Big portions, reasonable prices, quick service.  Great tartar sauce.  The premium fish options are worth it and the oysters are the best.

THIS IS LITTERALY THE BEST RESTERANT IN THE UNIVERSE. ALL OTHER RESTURANTS CAN EAT -- as a local guide, it would be irisponsible for me to finish this sentance :) -- I LOVE YOU SO MUCH THOUGH EVERY YEAR I COME HERE AND I GET MY BIG MAGICAL MEAL. I CAN LITTERALY NOT EXPRESS MY GRATITUDE FOR THIS PLACES EXISTANCE. MY GRANDMA WENT HERE, MY MUM WENT HERE, MY DAD WENT HERE, C-LOVERS MAKES THE FINEST FISH AND CHIPS IN THE GALAXY. GRAAAAAAAAAAAAAHHHHHHHHHHHHH SDZAKSDZAWK,SDKHJ,DSZKHJZSDJKDJHKMZDXSCJHMKXDCJMHKZXCDSJMHKCJKMHMH

The fish and chips were really good, but I think the customer service is outstanding! Props to our server Jayden for being so attentive and considerate. We had ordered all you can eat and bottomless drinks. Whenever our drink is almost finished, she appears out of nowhere with a new one ready! The atmosphere had all smiles too! It is the little things
SO tasty! I ve reviewed before and will continue reviewing it every time I have their fish and chips because it s the best one in Vancouver.
Reliable choice for great fish and chips. All you can eat is good value but at the expense of eating their premium fish which is worth spending a little more for. Great place for kids however.
The fish batter is just in the right amount, not greasy, but a bit sweet. Great fish and chips overall.

As a Brit we can confirm this is the closest thing you can get to british fish and chips in the lower Mainland. Love this place, get a bread roll with you meal so you can make a fish butty. Also the chicken is fab too.
Good food, good fast service. Best fish n chips in town - not greasy, just crispy & delicious. Yummy fresh coleslaw too. I always feel young when I come here since its usually full of seniors.

Went to C-lovers for their all you can eat fish and chips special and it was really good! The fish they use is polluck and the peices of fish are quite meaty and the batter wasnt too overpowering. I like that they start you off with 5 pieces of fish and a half plate of fries versus other places that basically give a full plate and two pieces. The servers were also super nice and very friendly which made the experience even better!
Great seafood and the staff are very friendly and take good care of you.

Gotta be a 5-star. Have been a few times lately and the food has always been great. Very good portions of perfectly cooked fish and chips with the batter done to perfection. Ive also had the C-dog and the chicken strips and those are great.

Can be quite a wait when they are busy, but thats a sign of a good restaurant with good quality food. When you order an All You Can Eat meal, make sure you put in your refill a bit earlier as it can take a while before you get it. Parking: Unfortunately a couple of businesses closed down in this area, but as a result, more parking spots are available!
Fast great fish. Best fish and chips in town
Great food and super service! Love it!
Waitress wasnt the greatest and its was super crowded but still one of my fams fav restaurants for all you can eat fish and chips!!
Enjoyed the one piece Haddock which was more than enough. Challenge yourself with the 17.99$ all you can eat. Super quick service and fully licensed. Great fish.
Very nice place for fish and chips at reasonable prices. I always get the all you can eat special and generally have quick and friendly service from their server Shou.

We ordered the cod and salmon 2-piece dinners and they were fantastic. I was both surprised and excited after noticing the fish was very lightly breaded with large pieces of fish. The ratio of fish to breading was perfect.  The coleslaw and fries were also delicious. Perfect fuel for after a Grouse Grind hike! :)

Awesome place! The all you can eat fish and chips with bottomless drink included is the best deal in town. The fish and chips are incredible and they have the tastiest tartar sauce they bring to the table by the bottle full. A True all you can eat experience and one of the best menus for what youre craving.
Food was pretty good, service was great. Overall excellent experience!

Best Fish and Chips in Town! They have all you can eat and have great value all round. Parking: Free parking lot right out front. Kid-friendliness: This is a family friendly restaurant. Wheelchair accessibility: it is on the main floor so it is wheelchair accessible.
A nice fish and chip shoppe with an all you can eat and pop option Kid-friendliness: Discounted kid s meals by age Food : 4/5 |
review_translated_text: Food

review_text: Delicious fish and chips ( halibut) nice atmosphere. friendly guys.

Always worth the trip. Even though the price went up by about 30%, the all-you-can-eat fish & chip meal (including bottomless pop) is still a very good deal. Everything was very fresh & tasty, and our server was very friendly & attentive.

I enjoy All You Can Eat menu of C-Lovers. Unlimited hot and well breaded fish with fries and bottomless pops. There is lots of free parking in front of this place. I appreciate Rose for warm welcome and service.
Went for the all you can eat and the portions were huge! Nice and crispy not too greasy, chips were good. Staff was super friendly and attentive! Would def eat here again when the cravings hit.

All you can eat cod fish n chips was the bomb. I had 6 pieces to myself and I was so satisfied. The halibut fingers were amazing too. The freshness of the fish really came through and the fries were heavenly. The onion rings were beautiful too and everything went well with that amazing tartar sauce. Coffee is free flow. Id recommend this place in a heartbeat.

Excellent Fish and Chips. I always go for the Halibut, and ask for extra lemon. The place closes early by restaurant standards but maybe it is because it caters to an older crowd.  The drink menu is quite limited so I dont choose to dine in. We always do takeout...and the food is always consistently good. The service is prompt and the staff pleasant. Its the best F&C on the North Shore!!
