Our go-to fish n chips on the north shore. Lovely fish, fries and Caesar salad.

Fantastic! A great place for fish and chips. They have a great takeout menu and a nice dine-in layout. We ordered takeout and were very satisfied with the portions, cost, and service. Will be ordering from them in the future.
Food was fantastic.  Our waitress and other staff were super friendly.  Prices were reasonable.  Will definitely come back!

Great place for fish n chips! Lovely lady at front of the house, awesome gentleman at the back and very friendly server. Strongly recommend at least to try cod. We all enjoyed every single chip and delicious cod.

All you can eat fish and chips. Tack on a bottomless pop, and its heaven. Too bad that Im older now, so the food gets a little bit greasy and heavy. However its me and not them. When you have the AYCE, you need to add salt and pepper to taste. They provide ketchup and tartar sauce.
Best fish and chips you can find Northshore. Very fresh fish and great service.  can be very busy at lunch time.
A great meal of all you can eat fish and chips with coleslaw salad. Also bottomless pop is included in the AYCE fish & chips. I really enjoyed the tasty meal.

Delicious! The taste and the portions are really good, they offer different types of combos or plates for sharing. The onion rings are amazing. The food is fresh, the service is fast, friendly staff, nice and quiet place. They have kids many. Recommendations for the place, you can have more types of dressings. (Mayo, something spicy).
All you can est is a lot, just choose 3-4 strips of fish and thats all.

Probably the best fish and chips Ive ever had. It was recommended to us by friends and ...wow! We had haddock and halibut.   I preferred the haddock and its less expensive  as well.  Id go there next time Im visiting in the area again.
Great staff, always friendly. Never a hassle getting take out. They are flawless with their fish, Ive never had a bad order from them. Ive probably ordered 12 times over the last year.

Great fish and chips.  This spot is thin on atmosphere but if you want a traditional fish and chips menu this is the place to come.  Fills early with a more senior crowd and very family friendly.  Take out is busy all the time.  Best in town.

Great place, great fish and great service!! Thanks for the good times C Lovers North Van! The waitress is very nice. Still trying to beat my first all you can eat record number of fish pieces, maybe next time :)
The halibut family size fish and chips were delicious and well worth the cost. The staff were very friendly too

Great fish and chips. The servers are friendly. They are considered ocean wise which is good. There menu is rather limited, but what do you expect from a restaurant named fish and chips? We went during a slow time and the food was still amazing.
Had the 2 PC halibut dinner. It came moist and perfectly battered and cooked .delicious! Chips were the same and great service. Reasonable price for the quality  . Ill be back!
Friendly welcoming and serving throughout the meal and most importantly the food was delicious! It was packed around 6-7pm on a weekend night. Will have more visits in the future!
Good family restaurant. Food was really good. The server was a bit flustered, as I think she was new. She did well though.

Generous portions, fresh and tasty. Casual, clean and excellent service. Family of 3 we ordered a haddock burger, cod meal and a large caesar salad for lunch. We wish we lived closer so we could visit more often.
Love their fish and chips deal for take out. Feeds a family of four and you can request their homemade tartar sauce. So delicious!
Yes it was very filling the 2 pic cod was awesome

Fish and chips is the soul food of the West Coast, there are times your soul just desires it. I order piece of fish and fries with a small gravy to go, along with nice amount of malt vinegar. They paper wrap the food, no plastic! ! No seasoning is needed, batter is near perfect in constancy, cannot wait to try the AYCE option they have when Covid is over.

Happy New Year     To All my Friends & Relations. I grew up near Steveston BC.  Ive tried alot of different deep fried fish    C- Lovers  is on the Top of my list. Delicious, Consistent ,They Always get it right ! I enjoy 1 PC. cod ( for me huge portion ) & 6 PC. Jumbo shrimp   dinner with fries ,gravy ,always ask for condiments & extra accessories., They always give Very Generous ,Fast!  Worth the Drive .
Great food, generous portions of fish. The all-you-can-eat fish-n-chips is great value if you have a big appetite. Clean and cosy restaurant. Wheel chair accessible. However parking is very limited.
Loved the Cod fish and chips here!!!!!!! Best place in Vancouver but in north van lol

Absolute best fish and chips and if youre not into fish then they have the best chicken fingers youll ever have. Theyve spoiled me. Now no other chicken measures up to theirs. Hey, they even make a hot dog (corn dog) with the same scrumptious batter they put on their fish or chicken. Its a bit hidden behind the bushes behind the Shell service station at Pemberton and Marine. Reasonably priced, its become our go to weekly dinner out.

I have been going to this restaurant for over a decade and the quality has been consistently great. Their all you can eat is still a good deal, but these days I settle for a 1 piece cod meal which is enough to satisfy my fish and chips craving.

The first I had fish and chips in C-Lovers was back in 2004 since then I go there very often. Love the food, their great customer service and the peaceful environment. I highly recommend C-lovers to all seafood lovers

Good to see the north shore location persevered through the last couple years.  Staff are always hustling and working hard!  Great fish & chips!  Busy busy...always a good sign of a good spot to dine!
Im impressed and surprised. Never knew about this place until a few days ago. The staff did a great job. The food was excellent! Thanks and see you soon!
First time customers. Will definitely return. We got the take away special. It was a ridiculous amount of food, all of which was delicious.  Friendly, quick service. Happy new customers!

I go here with my family occasionally;  They have never, EVER dissapointed us.  The fish tastes super fresh, their foods are barely greasy, the crisp is amazing, and if youre going there, I recommend the All you can eat meal.  Endless tasty fish! What more could you want!  Call me greedy, but everytime I go there, we all see who can eat the most.  Usually, no more than 5 pieces, since they fill you up, but boy are they delicious. Plus, they have such great staff!  I recommend going here when you can! Best possible way to spend 15$. p.s Get the onion rings too!  Theyre great!

C-Lovers is by far the best fish and chips in North Vancouver. I highly recommend the Halibut although it is a bit pricy. Still it is absolutely delicious and since going to C-Lovers its become impossible for me to enjoy random fish and chips at a pub or some other restaurant. I also love that they wrap their Togo orders in paper + newspaper, a real throwback to the old days. No matter what kind of fish you get C-Lovers is the place to go in North Van. Just be warned, it may ruin everything else for you like it did for me!
response_from_owner_text: Wow! Thanks so much for the awesome review! We hope to see you again!

review_text: The BEST fries, cole slaw, home made tartar sauce, fries (did I say fries twice? Yes! Theyre that good!) and of course.....the beautifully battered fish, especially love the halibut but their cod and haddock are fantastic too. Chicken strips! Dont forget to try their moist, delicious chicken strips. Very large portions too! And a good tip for left over fries.....take them home! Yes! Pop them in the freezer wrapped in newspaper then a few days later, bake them like theyre McCain frozen fries. Nom!!
Favorite place on the North Shore for some great fish n chips. Never disappoints for me or my dining guest(s).  Have always returned and left satisfied - Cheers!

Excellent food, no waiting to be seated.  Very friendly staff. The plaxe is spacious and clean. If there was a restaurant like this on Marpole it would be my favorite. Too bad this pkace is too far from home.

2011 July update. Just as excellent as ever. The best haddock and chips Ive had in a long time. Thick, juicy and full of flavour. Next time Ill ask for only a half order of chips. Great lightly battered fish accompanied with hand cut chips...plus very friendly staff...$13.99 AYCE Cod and Chips & Pop

The best fish and chips Ive ever had. Consider ordering the ALL YOU CAN EAT fish and chips...you will not regret it. Will definitely come back to this restaurant on mu next visit to North Vancouver...

Very affordable ayce fish and chips. Im quite sad their downtown location closed down as this north Van establishment is very far from my home. Try not to over eat! Five stars because I feel like I get more than what I paid for. Also the service is very nice!

Great food! Fast service and a wonderful cashier. Better than fish and chips at a fancy restaurant. If you want something tastey and fast this is the spot!!!!! Even wrapped in newspaper its the best!!!!

Whenever I take my Grandma out for lunch I take her to C-Lovers. For some reason old people just love this place. Everything here is reasonable priced. Just remember to arrive early before lunch, because thats when all the seniors come for their fish and chips.
Had a lovely meal here on a Friday night. Mushy peas and coleslaw were excellent!
If you love halibut n chips, or cod n chips, then this place should be your goto place like it is mine. A little pricy but the quality out ways the price! The atmosphere is always spot one.
Great value for money. Really good fish n chips considering its an all you can eat joint. I was definitely surprised. Highly recommended

Their Take-Out Special is worth it! Youll get surprised how much youd get with what you pay. I like very good deals. : ) You can search on their website and order ahead by calling on the contact# by location.
Fast service, good quantity, great taste

We had the chicken waffles and steak sandwich, both are very delicious and servings were generous! The chicken was crispy and juicy. The steak sandwich was very tender and well seasoned. No accessibility for wheelchair or strollers but the staff were very friendly and they helped us get our stroller up the few flights of stairs. Thank you!

I had a great experience here! We came here for happy hour for oysters. $2 for regular oysters and $3 for premium. We got 2 dozens of oysters, the poutine and calamari. The service was also great! Highly recommend.

Incredible happy hour joint. Had drinks and some oysters & beers. Extremely warm service and vibes in general. Will be back for sure. Edit: My brother dropped his phone through the deck. We met the owner who went above and beyond to help us to retrieve the phone.  We even ended up staying for dinner which was incredible.  Jambalaya, mussels and carfish which were all excellent. Kid-friendliness: Good for kids
We came for oysters during happy hours but the deep fried food (i.e. calamari, chicken wings) is also good. I love their craft beers too.

Awesome happy hour in a relaxed cozy environment with friendly staff that will make you feel at home.  The happy hour offers were limited but good!  The calamari was tender and delicious!  Service was solid!
I had a great experience there. Everything was excellent. The oysters were delicious a good place to stop in and enjoy the food and atmosphere.
Small portion sizes but the quality of the food is top tier (Calamari and local oysters)! Tremendous local BC dry cider as well that Im extremely impressed with! Food

We hosted my daughters first birthday at their Kits location and it was amazing!!  The staff are super friendly.  This is a restaurant owned by a lovely husband and wife  (Jamie and Mel) who I had the pleasure of coordinating this event with Mel also offers decor/ ballon arch packages that you can coordinate with her for special events. The attention to detail Mel provided was incredible. I would highly recommend either one of the chewies locations for your next special event.
Came here for Dine Out 2023 and the menu was fantastic! Each course we got was very delicious.
After having the oysters and their fried spicy broccoli I think you cant go wrong with anything on their menu. Just exceptional.

The oysters here are so fresh! The fried broccoli, calamari, and jambalaya were all excellent too. The service was impeccable and friendly. Would highly recommend Chewies to anyone visiting Vancouver. I ve read some of the negative reviews and they are way off. This place completely turned my outlook on oysters around. 11/10 would recommend.

Had an amazing experience at Chewies. They accommodated a table of 20+ people on short notice on a sunny Saturday evening. Staff were awesome and the owner even came out to offer us some complimentary tequila. Food and drinks were delicious, 100% would recommend and I will be back. Oysters were awesome with a great selection as well.

I love this place! Perfect location, relatively easy to park, and medium-priced menu. There are two patios on both sides of the bar and one is heated. Waiters and waitresses are cool and approachable. I visited this bar about 3 times and once my friend ordered fries with her food, and she got tiny, tiny little fries, like half inch pieces, that was super weird and also difficult to eat. When I asked the waiter why they were so tiny, he said that the size does not matter. Yes, man, it DOES! ...Especially when we talk about fries.

Amazing happy hour menu! $1.75-$2.50 oysters and they were so plump and fresh! Happy hour food: hot wings, calamari and spicy broccoli. The calamari was melt in your mouth tender and the broccoli was actually a nice tasty surprise!

I had such a lovely time here! Corey who was shucking oysters was super helpful and nice and fun. The whole staff were killer and the drinks were well balanced and fairly priced. When I come back to Vancouver Ill be back for sure :)

Really missed the one on Hastings but Donavin and Jim were there and it felt like home again! Loved their service, the food and the grad and baby pics of the staff had. This Chewies has been around for me since I first worked at kits in 2017, though I worked in DT now I ll make the run back for the great fresh oysters and friendly service
Went one day and had the special (tuna ceviche) and it was amazing, definitely you have the best hazy IPA beer in city, great service and staff, always feel very welcomed at this place.

Family met up for Saturday brunch. Incidently, its recently that they offer brunch. The menu is very creative to say the least. I had the grab bennie that was so artfully presented that we had to take pictures with our phones. All other items ordered were equally visually appealing.  The food was wonderful. The service was great too. All in all a great experience that will have be duplicated in the futue.

Excellent establishment right next to the beach, incredible choice of oysters as well as plenty of interesting drinks to try. I will definitely be visiting every time I come to kits Beach and recommend you do the same. Ask for Rich, hell definitely sort you out.

We decided to eat here for Dine Out Vancouver and were not disappointed. Our mains were Chicken & Grits and Jambalaya - they were *chefs kiss*. My partner had the oysters and he says theyre the best hes ever had. Big portions, reasonably priced, fun and friendly atmosphere. The staff were outstanding from the time we booked our reservation until the time we left. Food came out as soon as it was ready, empty plates picked up quickly and our glasses were always full....and this is on a busy Friday night. Fantastic job following COVID protocols. Would give 100 stars if I could.
Get the cornbread. It was so good!!! Mussels were tasty and jambalaya had a unique twist to to, drier than traditional ones but still very flavourful. It s a neat resto near the beach.
The food is delicious and the portions are VERY generous. We had the Chicken and Grits, Jambalaya, and the poutine. AMAZING. Service was awesome too
First time at this location. Oysters are good loved the kushti. Cajun fries are tasty as well!
Wonderful place walking distance from Kitsilano beach. Great selection of fresh shucked oysters. Servers and very personable and knowledgeable. A very pleasant dining experience.

Everything here was amazing and delicious. The mac and cheese we ordered twice because we loved it so much the first time. The pecan pie was fantastic. I dont even love pecan pie that much lol. The service was spectacular too. Must check out here.

Me and my partner looove chewies!!!! Menu can be pricy if ur not there at happy hour but it always feels worth it for the great time that we have there. And its honestly it s standard price for Vancouver so I really don t have anything to complain about. Love the staff. Food is bomb. Happy hour is great. This is our top spot in Vancouver. Always looking forward to next time. Thanks for everything guys. So much love to you

Update: Jamie, the owner, called me directly to hear my feedback. He handled the situation well and I certainly appreciated his call and his willingness to hear my feedback. I ve changed my rating from 3 stars to 5 stars. Original Review: I ve been coming to Chewies for years, mostly on Sundays. I ve recently been back after COVID. Our  experience was less than optimal. The food was great all around, however the service was not great in the slightest. It took close to ten minutes for someone to come over. Once they did, we placed our order, but from there, we constantly had to ask for obvious things. More water, another drink, new fork, the bill, etc. Our entire time was spent trying to flag down the server to either order additional items or ask for common things. Not intuitive or on top of it at all. We also came at a time in which there were limited tables in the restaurant. The server probably had one or two tables to look out for. Disappointing. Chewies has always been a favourite destination, especially in Kits, because, you can head for a walk down the beach after your meal.
response_from_owner_text: Hello Nicholas, I apologize for the delay in getting back to you. First and foremost I would like to extend my appreciation for the support for Chewies over the past. My name is Jamie and I am the owner. Very rarely do I reply to the comments, but this one I felt it necessary. A post like this is obviously a double edged sword. I appreciate the fact that you have been a long time supporter, and the food was great, but the issue with the service is concerning. As I have always tried to stress to our service staff, service first, anything else second. It has been a very trying time since things have reopened. There is a definite lack of staff both FOH, and BOH which has made things even more complicated. By no means am I trying to make any excuses, and I would like to know exactly what time and when it happened (assuming it was on the Sunday, Aug 2nd). But just wanted to clarify. I/we take pride in our service and to have this happen is concerning. I would like to offer you a GC on us as a thank you for bringing this up, but more so an apology for your experience. Please let me know your thoughts. Thank you again for your support! Have a great day!

review_text: AMAZING service, oysters, fried chicken and grits, and fish and chips! Will definitely be going back to try more. 10/10 would recommend
GREAT oysters in many varieties, good and fresh. Good drinks and exceptional staff! Absolutely recommend
We ordered oysters, mussels and the sea food salad, it was really fresh, well dressed and tasty. The waiter was also really nice. I recommend it. Food

I was having a really bad night....but then Angus made it way better. Great server, great attitude, he gave my dog some sausage and water, just a great guy!!! We will be back for more oysters and maybe some sausage for Doug!

I can t say enough about the food, the people and the service at Chewies. Hands down the best calamari in the city! It s fresh, delicious, and a great appetizer before their famous fried chicken. We are fans
I would highly recommend. Amazing place to get your southern fried chicken and oysters. Staff are amazing, friendly, and accommodating.

Theres a lot to like about this hidden gem in kits beach area. The staff are down to earth and friendly. Service was always very attentive even when the restaurant was full and our server somehow managed to get our entire tables orders correct and bill everyone correctly which is amazing given he never wrote anything down! . We didnt get enough time to try out all the choices but we will go back. The Cajun Creole style mussels with sausage were delicious and my partners burger was apparently awesome, and he is quite the picky burger connoisseur. The price point was also in the affordable, not break the bank range. So combine all those things and its defineately worth 5 stars.
Delicious! Great service and great food. All reasonably priced too.
New Orleans is one of my fav cities for cuisine and Chewies does a great job with it in Kitsilano. Staff are great and long timers. Ask for a glass of wine and see their meniscus pours!!
10/10 experience at the best restaurant in Kits. New brunch menu is also FIRE! Highly recommend.
Loved this restaurant! Really great service and the food was awesome - good variety and had local seafood options. Would definitely go back!
Situated in the middle of the Kits residential neighborhood, its a nice location with a chill atmosphere. The food is good but pricing is on the higher side.
Best service because its genuine, and god the food is simple but executed to a mouth watering symphony. DO NOT Overlook the chicken and grit. To die for.
We came here for oysters and it did not disappoint. Super fresh and tasty. Great service and staff.

I love Chewies! It s our great neighborhood spot in Kits where you re always welcome to drop in for a drink and maybe a dozen oysters.  Oysters are premium quality, good selection of local craft beer and BC wine.  And if you re hungry, the fried chicken can t be beat.  Service A++.

The menu is focused on a southern seafood experience. While initially, I felt the menu a little small, I can appreciate them focusing on what theyre good at. Deets: The seafood chowder was the best if had in years: generous recognizable content. Soooo many tender scallops! The BBQ oysters were perfectly el dante. The tasty breaded chicken was so crispy but the protein moist. Overall: great brass band music played while friendly outgoing staff checked in regularly. Casual and fun.

I brought my mom to Chewies for the first time. She loved the food and the atmosphere. The Oysters, seafood salad, and their traditional fried chicken were on point as usual! The service was great. The food runner went above and beyond. Im glad to see you guys still have the magic touch. See you again soon!
Love everything about this place. The staff, the food, the drinks and especially the ambiance. I have such great appreciation for what this company has given to their beloved community and city.

One of the best for fresh oysters and our hostess Scarlett was so sweet and so helpful and the manager Corey was awesome too he helped us with an issue we had with our table and went above and beyond to make sure my husband and I had a great experience and Scarlett was so helpful and attentive as well we will be coming back thank you !

Finding this place seriously made our day. We stumbled across the restaurant while looking for a nice patio to sit on in the sun. Not only was the patio perfect but the food was out of this world. Service staff were friendly and accommodating. Will definitely go back next time I m in Kitz.
Honestly we did have the best seat in the house which helps. Besides that their ribs were some of the best ribs Ive ever had. I would also go back for their Fried Chicken.
The platter was SO good, especially the collard greens and chicken. Mac n cheese was a bit bland but everything else made up for it. Be sure the get into the honey butter with the chicken!!
Arrived early for the oysters! Excellent! Quick service
Great bar, expansive menu and excellent food. Service was slightly slow but they made up for it with how nice they were.
Unbelievable food and service, will definitely come back!
Only place I can find deep fried chicken skins and its the best!!! Staff also nice.
Love the oysters, the way they pour wine & the brussel sprouts!!! & more mmm
Wonderful oysters and wonderful service (the kind that makes you want to tip)
Nice relaxed ambiance, chill but attentive servers, decent food, and really great happy hour! Also great location for heading to the beach before or after
I wished for a bigger variety of cajun food, but what they served was excellent!
Food a drinks were great killer place to go to on a Friday night after the beach

1 year later. Good food and good service May 2017 5 stars. Good food, the oysters were as fresh as could be possible. Service was excellent, and the server had a great understanding of the menu, and how some of their dishes were different from the typical presentation. Good food, indifferent service. Aug 2016 3 stars Our server really didnt care about us. The place was busy, but he was more interested in socializing with one of the women sitting at the bar than remembering to bring our order. He didnt tell us about the happy hour price for oysters (it started 20 minutes after we arrived). He also sold us a bottle of wine that was available to $20 less at happy hour. The only good service we had was when we paid the bill. The server seemed quite happy that we were leaving. The food was good, but not worth putting up with the service. We noticed that the tables on either side of us also seemed to be getting poor service.

I went here with a group of friends a few weeks ago for the first time and will definitely be going back! The happy hour runs from 3-6pm on Saturday and Sunday which was great for us because we were hungry after shopping on 4th! I would highly recommend ordering the broccoli and poutine. Patio was also heated and open when we were there. Go check it out!
Loved this place. Super friendly staff and fast service. The fish and chips was well cooked and I definitely will be back for it.

When you dont know Chewies in Kits you tell yourself youre going for the food... Well I keep going there weekly, now. Because not only the food is superb, but the staff is the reason I go there. Theyre great and thoughtful... and they wear shorts. Definitely one of the best Canadian dining experience!!

Absolutely love this place. Theres so much great food here. Though it might be slow at times that is to be expected due to the large amounts of people who come. Oysters are a must here. There is not many spots so make sure to figure that out by calling ahead to check. Enjoyable and one of the better oyster spots in the city for sure
Best happy hour in town. Tasty locally sourced oysters on happy hour menu. Good variety of pints for the lads

This place was amazing! My girlfriend and I came here after a sunny day at Kitsilano Beach/Pool, the staff was very friendly, accommodating and had us a table on the patio inside ten minutes. The food was the best part: Deep-fried Cauliflower (easily the best thing on the platter), Fried Brussel Sprouts with Gorgonzola Cheese, Cajun Fries and Cajun Fried Chicken. Beer selection was pretty good and the wine selection seemed even better. Even after my beers, her wine and the platter of food the bill was around $120.00 for the both of us - well deserved in my opinion.

Love this place! It is by far one of my favourite places to dine on the weekend with my wife/family or have a nice ice cold beer after work. Their Breakfast is to die for and I highly recommend you come try it on the weekends before your stroll down the street to Kits beach. They also have an amazing selection of oysters and very knowledgeable shuckers. I have had some of the best oysters of my life at Chewies. Location, food, drinks, ambiance, and staff are all 10/10. When ever I have someone visiting town this is a place I always take them to. The room and staff really make you feel at home and thats a big reason why I always come back. My wife and I are there at least once a week and this is a Kitsilano/Vancouver staple. Family owned and operated I will definitely continue to be a loyal patron. Thanks crew de chew you never disappoint!

Very delicious and wonderful atmosphere. Oysters are varied and delicious and the 4 house sauces they serve with them elevate the experience to the next level. Definitely worth trying to catch happy hour! Great place to kill a couple beers and chat with friends.

We went during happy hour on a Tuesday and it was absolutely incredible. Oysters were so fresh, and only a buck each. Half priced appetizers, and the entrees were awesome. The calamari was perfect. Also excellent service. I would go back in a heartbeat!
Had a phenomenal time back in December with my softball team. Food was amazing, staff was fantastic, and this place lived up to the hype. Bravo!

Great place! Was only able to try the chicken skins which was so good and well priced too! The drinks are quite pricey but its a cool place. Fun to sit at the bar and feel sorry for the guy who has to shuck oysters all night! They have a happy hour so make the most of it!

The absolute best place to grab a bite, have a drink, and hangout. Their oysters are wicked good. Love all their sauces. Huge fan of the jambalaya. Fried chicken and waffles for brunch. Amazing. Oh and dont forget the brussel sprouts. Service there is top notch and theyll always make you feel like youve been there a million times, everytime. Favorite spot in Kits for sure

Went for  dinner last night with a few friends.. Exceptional service Great happy hour offerings Delicious calamari and tuna ceviche Oysters top notch as always Our group had burgers ( they said the best they have ever had ) prawn wrap - delicious ! Would highly recommend Chewies in Kits!
Amazing service, fantastic food! My partner has a dairy allergy and the staff let us know immediately what had dairy in it! 10/10 I do recommend!

A cozy neighborhood restaurant with an incredibly strong staff that definitely have been expertly staffed to facilitate an incredibly unique oyster and barbeque fusion experience. With nods to a creole style of exploration of tastes with locally and coast to coast availability for oysters, tucked on the corner of an incredibly lively Kitsilano street steps away from the coveted Kits beach. Reservations are recommended.

This trendy, casual space was perfect for our date night. The single wide booths by the upper bar were an ideal spot to sit, chat, drink, eat and relax. The attentive wait-staff guides us to ideal beer, cocktail and food selections. All in all our best stop yet in Kitsilano. Bonus points: West coast oysters were perfectly shucked and presented, with top notch horseradish to boot.
Most friendliest bunch of staff ever. Amazing oysters and brilliant service. Highly recommended.

The serving staff of this restaurant (particularly Tony our server) provided some of the best service I have ever seen in a restaurant. I have celiac and the chef (Mauricio) knew that I was not able to order their typical menu items and came over to specifically provide customized options that I was able to choose from. All amazing! I will absolutely come back here and you should go here too.
Great happy hour, friendly and approachable service from the boys. Best brunch in the city, on God. Good vibes!

Great experience from start to finish. Friendly staff on arrival, hilarious servers and super tasty food and oysters.  Coming back to try the chicken and waffles for brunch next. Definitely a kits hot spot!

Big fan, fried chicken was awesome, the buttermilk mashed potatoes were incredible and my wife also had an amazing gumbo. We are planning to try brunch one of these days, as the checked and waffles look great. Great southern style food!

Alright, so the meal was fantastic. The oysters were fresh and delicious, the mussels and fried chicken were out of this world! But as great as the food was, my main man Corey was the server and that dude was next level. Easily the most entertaining server Ive ever had, if youre going to want to share a beer or teo with a server at a restaurant, thats the dude. Keep it up Corey!

Came in on a busy Saturday and we had a great time. The food was amazing, 2 of us had the fried green tomato poboy, 1 plate of jambalaya and 1 fish and grits. Everything was great. All the food was recommended by our waiter Tim who was a hilarious, nice guy. I highly Recommend the restaurant for everything, drinks, food and good company.

we had the portabella burger w/ fries, the UNREAL jalapeno grits and oysters. Andy gave us unreal table service start to finish. Answered all our questions about the different types of oysters we received, highlighting the best attributes of each. The oysters were fresh and succulent. The fries were well seasoned but not too salty. The portable burger could ve had a bit more structured it definitely slips out one end, my recommendation is to make a bed of the fries for the burger to spill over onto. Fantastic service start to finish, experiences like this are why I go out for meals and why I will be definitely coming back to Chewies Kits for date night and beyond. 10/10 would recommend to a friend.

Great food, great people! Atmosphere is laid back and welcoming. Drink menu is amazing and the fried chicken is to die for! I bring all my friends visiting Vancouver here and they talk about it for months after! 10/10 must go!

Absolutely incredible! Best fried chicken you will ever eat whether its at dinner with the amazing mashed potatoes or at brunch with the best waffle Ive ever eaten! Ive also had the Beef Brisket: AMAZING! Anything you eat there is the best! And of course.... THE OYSTERS! The home made sauces they have there to go with their massive section of raw oysters is divine. My wife and I usually get the Oyters Rockefeller. Its so good we cant stop ordering it every time we go. The drinks are also top notch. Best Cesar Ive ever had and their wine is filled to the brim. Youve got to try Chewies or youre just missing out and hell... youre just not living! :-)

The BEST fried chicken. So crispy and tasty. My favourite is their fried chicken main that comes with mash and a gorgeous honey butter glaze. Delicious. The chicken and waffles is also very good. My one issue with this spot is it is a bit on the pricey side.
For good reasons one of the most well known happy hour places in the area.
One of the best happy hours place.

Great service, got the buck a shuck happy hour oysters and jambalaya, and my companion got the halibut. Both dishes were excellent. Im upset I didnt get the fried chicken and finding parking can be a bit annoying so give yourself extra time.

Staff and oysters were the highlight of this great little oyster bar! We had the happy hour oysters and they were so fresh and delicious! Loved the cucumber vinaigrette the best! Thanks for a lovely experience:)

I know one of the owners, Chewi. Great man! And the few times Ive been, Ive never left unhappy. Great atmosphere and service :) Too bad Im allergic to oysters. I hear theyre really amazing! Ill have to come by again sometime soon :)
We go there often for the oysters and happy hour, never been disappointed
Best oyster bar in all categories: fresh and delicious, friendly people, and cozy interior. Aside from the oysters, we love their calamari!

We love Chewies for Happy Hour - great service from all the staff every time we are there. The calamari is probably the best we ve ever had! We have made it our local. Thanks Jim, Corey and the rest of the gang!
Oysters were amazing and not too expensive

Fantastic Oyster Bar with great food, great service, and a very fun atmosphere. One of the best watering holes for the Kitsilano neighbourhood. Love going here. Highly recommend to everybody and anybody
Friendly service and a good vibe. Although its an oyster bar their fried chicken and grits is phenomenal.

Awesome for oysters. When I was there place was very busy and they had very good choices of oysters from BC and Washington including my favorite - Kusshi. I would like to see better choice of sauces served with raw oysters.

Chewies are situated in the heart of Kits. I usually go here for my Saturday or Sunday brunch. With lots of 2hr parking in the area, this location feels natural amd easy to get to. They serve some really good oysters and a great variety too! My 2 favourite items on the menu is the Spicy Ceasar (seriously amazing) and the Chicken & Waffles.

Came for the happy hour and stayed for dinner. Great food choices and wide selection of drinks. Fast friendly staff that made the experience wonderful. Recommended for casual get together with friends or family.

Aquariums West is an aquatic paradise right in the heart of Vancouver. I was immediately captivated by the sheer variety of plants available - from lush greens to vibrant reds, they had a wide selection that were visually stunning. The knowledge and guidance provided by the staff made it easy to select the perfect plants for my aquarium. One of the most delightful discoveries during my visit was the adorable cherry shrimp. These little creatures added an unexpected charm to the store. The staff s expertise in caring for these small invertebrates was evident, and their health and vivacity were a testament to the store s commitment to quality and care for all its inhabitants. The store itself is a treasure trove for any aquatic enthusiast. Beyond the vibrant flora and charming shrimp, Aquariums West boasts an impressive array of supplies and fish species. The attention to detail in maintaining the tanks and the quality of the aquatic life on offer truly sets this place apart. Whether you re a seasoned aquarist or a newcomer to the hobby, Aquariums West is an absolute must-visit. The diversity, quality, and expert guidance make it a top destination for all things aquatic. I left not just with new additions for my tank but also with a wealth of knowledge. Kudos to Aquariums West for providing such a wonderful experience.

First time ordering with you guys and ya have some of the nicest plants I ve seen in a long time. Very accurate fullness like the photos. I ordered 4 different Anubias types. Many had multiple plants too.  Great prices for what I received. Packaged well. Super pumped and definitely need more so I look forward to it!

Honestly this is the best (and only?) good Aquarium store in the city. Always super knowledgeable & helpful staff regarding reptiles and fish. Aquarium equipment and supplies. A Great selection of water plants. They also sell rodents, guinea pigs and chinchillas too! Pretty much bought everything for our tank from this store over the past 15 years. Except our actual tank which was from the 80s. Just a heads up side note; It can be a little uptight with the on-going covid restrictions and how you enter and leave the store can be a bit uncomfortable and off-putting. You have to leave your backpack behind the counter and wait behind a rope before being allowed entry. This is understandable in our city of Vancouver where shoplifting & addiction is rampant unfortunately. This store is way too nice to let any scumbags in. I get it.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Nicole, Thanks for being a happy and loyal customer for 15 years.  It is unfortunate that we have had to implement security measures at the stores entrance and exit.  It is all meant to keep staff and customers safe.  The stories we could tell....

review_text: I didn t buy anything but my god did I have fun here for an hour or so. They carry such a large variety of fish. There s also reptiles, amphibians, spiders, and a set of guinea pigs looking for a home!! When I have the time and space for fish I will be coming back here to get them and all the supplies
response_from_owner_text: Hi Avery, We hope that you do come back if/when you decide to get into fish, plants or exotic reptiles.  Hopefully, you have been inspired.

review_text: Beautiful, beautiful aquariums and friendly employees. You may find interesting fish now and then, as they frequently import fish from Asia. Check their website to find out what they currently stock!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Jocelyne, The staff will love your review. Thanks for recognizing that the aquariums are beautiful and the employees are friendly.

review_text: Ive finally made it to this place after a long desire to come here.  The lack of parking and location make it hard to visit. The store is clean and tidy.  However I am thrilled about how clean their tanks are.  Also they seem to specialize in planted tanks.  Fish are also quite unique. We were asked if we needed help twice so we were looked after well.  The prices are decent and we noticed other stores upping the cost of basic fish like neon tetras.  I wont complain about the cost here because everything costs more in this day in age..  Plus rental space downtown is not cheap.
response_from_owner_text: Hi P Cho, Thanks for leaving such a detailed review and noticing the clean aquariums.  Parking downtown is difficult if you dont know where to go. Lucky for us we are super close to Costco where there are tons of parking spots all the time.

review_text: This is my go-to pet shop, despite living out int he Tricities. Super amazing staff who are friendly, knowledgeable, empathetic. Prices are good and if you have any specialty reptiles, I trust the people at Aquariums West as having the final word. Theyve made entering the exotic pet hobby welcoming and easy for a newbie
response_from_owner_text: Hi Cassandra, We are so happy that you make the trip from the Tricities to Yaletown to shop in our store.  The fact that you trust us as having the final word with regards to reptile care is fantastic and says volumes about the staff.  They will be so happy to read this review.

review_text: Amazing selection of high grade equipment, unique breeds, and the best aquascaping supplies I ve ever seen. If aquariums are a hobby you enjoy or want to get into, I highly recommend a visit. It s also a gorgeous store to just take a look in, the staff clearly put a lot of love and care into the stunning ecosystems they create.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Ashley, What a fabulous review.  Thank you so much for recommending Aquariums West!  We have an amazing staff that are passionate about what they do.

review_text: Fantastic specialty place with everything anyone would need to start or maintain a fish tank or terrarium. Great stock both in hardscape, live plants and both freshwater and saltwater fish. The staff is very knowledgeable and will be able to help you with any problem you might have. I couldnt recommend them more if I tried.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Michael, Thanks for taking the time to leave such a great review and letting people know that we have everything anyone would need to start or maintain a fish tank or terrarium.  We are so happy that your experience was a good one.

review_text: Great customer service - I bought an aquarium kit as an impulse. When I got home searching for accessories etc I found out that another local store was selling what I just bought for 40% less than what I paid for it. I was disappointed in myself for not checking before hand but I let the owner Jeannie know and she accepted the discrepancy and refunded me the difference even though I said I would prefer supporting small businesses and happily take store credit - she insisted I take the refund. We don t see these kind of store owners these days  thank you Jeannie
response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for the kind words Ivor! Jeannie will be happy to hear you had a good experience with us. We always try to make things work with our customers. Being a small business and competing with larger chains can be tough, and we appreciate you supporting us!

review_text: My first time here was great! I m new to the fishkeeping hobby and aquascaping - the staff were answering my questions without me feeling annoying and gave me some helpful tips. The store was stocked with so many cool natural decors, equipment, and beautiful livestock. Thanks guys!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Alex, We appreciate you taking the time to leave us a fabulous review.  Glad you got some helpful tips from the staff.  We receive new fish, plants and decorations almost every week so you will have new products to see next time you come to the store.

review_text: Happened to wall by on our way to lunch and of course had to go in, even if fish store shopping when you cant buy fish is torture. Beautiful store, well organized, whoever is planting their tanks is AN ARTIST, they are absolutely stunning. Fish all seemed well loved, but the care and attention paid to their bettas made me so happy. Lots of space, fresh clean water, happy clear eyed brightly coloured fish. The same love and attention paid to their reptiles and amphibians. Your store was a pleasure to shop in and we are so happy we are going home from our vacation with some new decor for our own tanks.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Allyson, Thanks for the great review.  Glad that you made a trip to visit Aquariums West during your vacation.  The staff work very hard at their presentations and are so happy when they are recognized as artists!

review_text: Good service Friendly employees Cool animals Store is overall clean and organized would find everything you need for your fish tanks or reptiles 10/10  recommended checking is place out
response_from_owner_text: Hi Enrique, Thanks for the 10/10 review!

review_text: I ve been to Aquarium West several times and I ve only ever had nice experiences. The one time I purchased a large tank, they helped me carry it to my car and when I had questions about the plants and livestock their staff was very knowledgeable and would help me find exactly what I was looking for. The girl that works there is honestly the best! There was one time where she helped me brainstorm a plan for re-aquascaping my tank. Overall, I highly recommend it here :)
response_from_owner_text: Hi Queenie, We are very happy that you have had nice experiences shopping in the store. And yes, Jenn is the best!

review_text: Went on a morning visit over to Aquariums West the other day! Had an alright time purchasing aquatic plants and a few fish, staff there are super friendly and knowledgeable! Thanks again friends :) Will for sure be back soon!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Noah, Thanks for taking the time to leave a 5 star review.  The staff will be happy to see that you think they are friendly and knowledgeable.

review_text: Fantastic aquarium shop with a great selection! Knowledgeable and friendly staff, well-maintained tanks, and a wide range of products. I especially love their terrariums and paludarium displays. Highly recommended!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Med, Happy that you enjoy the terrarium and paludarium displays.  They are meant to inspire and enjoy. Always nice to hear that the staff are friendly and knowledgeable.

review_text: JAW DROPPING BEAUTIFUL STORE Trust me, go here instead of ANY other fish store in Van!!! When I walked in my mouth dropped until an employee said hello lol. I have problems with every fish store I ve ever been to because of quality, disease/parasites, bad employees, etc, but NOT THIS PLACE I came in for some stuff for my betta because I did a fish in cycle (tank was barren), and left with 4 beautiful and cute red cherry shrimp (cheapest I ve found in Van and great quality), a couple bundles of moss, and two long grass like plants. No sign of disease, high quality supplies/fish, friendly and knowledgeable staff, and the care of the tanks were immaculate! Lots of the tanks had GORGEOUS aquascapes (good for inspiration), and I was met at the door by a pond of goldfish (lovely touch, a little overstocked but they take such good care of the tanks/water it s not a problem). I also saw a cute turtle, and lots of saltwater supplies/fish, all in great condition. I also saw a few enclosures for reptiles I assume, and they looked very natural and well put together (I know nothing about reptiles, but the enclosures looked very nice). I have to give these guys a full 5 stars because I ve NEVER seen such a well kept fish store in my life (I used to breed fish and I ve kept fish for almost my whole life). I could go on forever about how amazing this place is, everyone who has fish NEEDS to go here sometime!!!! I couldn t find a single fish that looked sick, all plants were high quality, a few discounts around the store for bulk buying, all in all they ACED what a pet store should strive to be. Jaw dropping impressive and stunning, I wish I could give 10 stars   I ll never go to another place from now on for fish. Fantastic job to everyone who works there and whoever owns the place
response_from_owner_text: Hi Meadow, Wow! what a fabulous review.  We are so happy that you had a really good look at everything and recognize all the hard work it takes to have healthy fish and beautiful aquariums.  The staff appreciate the fact that as an aquarist and fish breeder yourself, you really know what it takes.

review_text: Great selection of supplies needed for any sort of fish tank, very helpful staff and always a pleasant experience when i visit
response_from_owner_text: Hi Blaithin, Thanks for your 5 star review and posting such great pictures!

review_text: My son wanted to start his very first terrarium for his very first pet and everyone I knew said this was the place to go.  The store is super clean, well organized and stocked. Doug was extremely helpful.  Even though he was the  fish guy  he was so knowledgeable and patient and took so much time going through everything with my son and I.  Everyone in the store was very helpful and obliging to my sons questions and comments.  I highly recommend this shop, not only for their amazing selection of products and beautiful setup but their service and knowledge is top notch. Ty Doug and AW!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Mayumi, Wow!  Thanks for taking the time to leave a great review.  Doug will be so happy that you recognized his patience and knowledge. How exciting for your son to learn all about looking after a living creature!  I am assuming he got a lizard, which makes for a fabulous first pet.  Have a ton of fun with your son and his new responsibility.

review_text: Great collection of healthy fish. After buying my fish from here and taking care of it for more than a year now, i agree that its not possible to teach a customer everything there is to know. The staff was actually very helpful when I came in at a slower day.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Aryaman, Thank you for updating your review! We love helping people see the joy in fish keeping, and its always fun to see how our customers improve and continue to be excited about this amazing hobby!

review_text: Ive been in a bunch of different aquarium shops. This one stands head & shoulders above anything else around the lower mainland. Great selection and super helpful staff.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Bob, Wow!  Thanks for the great review.  The staff will love that you recognized them.

review_text: Fun to have a look even if you re not buying a pet (though you might be really tempted to after seeing all the marvellous creatures here) Such a huge collection of animals they have at Aquariums West. Mostly fish but you ll also see plenty of other neat specimens like snakes, lizards, turtles, frogs and even huge spiders and scorpions. Check out the biggest spider you ll ever see in real life: the Bird-Eating Spider

Best pet store in the area for nonstandard pets. Clean, knowledge, and kind. Have all I need for reptile supplies. Absolutely worth the extra commute time for me to go there instead of the dirty and grungy pet store down the street. ^^ The above is my original review from 11months ago, and I stand by it. I got my beloved bearded dragon here. My lizard is a delight. The shopkeepers here care for the animals well, and get them acclimated to people calmly and compassionately. Dropping in, Id often see them with a chameleon or a chinchilla on their shoulder, getting the animal used to chilling with them. I have since moved away, so I cant go here anymore for my pet supplies. But I found myself needing a letter from them verifying that my lizard was captive bred and that they sold it to me - they responded to my email immediately and professionally with a letter stating as much. I wish this shop all the best, and highly recommend them.
response_from_owner_text: Hi there, Thanks for the 5 star review and choosing Aquariums West over a dirty and grungy store.  Yahoo!  All the cleaning has paid off!

review_text: Thank you Aquarium west! Great customer service and super helpful to a newbie trying to raise neocaridina s. They were super patient with all my questions and helped me along the way. Best experience ever!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Wendy, Thanks so much for leaving such a great review.  Raising shrimp is so much fun.  Maybe one day when you master breeding shrimp, you can supply us with some of your babies!  Good luck!

review_text: Best fish store in Vancouver   I could live in it. Super helpful staff, shout out to Jen, lol. The stores located downstairs & a bit hard to find at first. But totally worth it. Excellent prices too. Wish I had more tanks.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Youngmin, Thanks for the great review and Jen will be pleased that you have appreciated her help.

review_text: Nice selection of all things fish and reptiles. They have great display set ups of reptile terrariums and vivariums! All the staff were very friendly and helpful too!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Aman, Thanks for taking the time to recognize our great displays and helpful, friendly staff.

review_text: Coming here is an addiction at this point! They have everything you could possibly need and more. Number 1 indicator that an aquarium store is high quality and knows what they are doing to me, is how they keep their bettas Not a single miserable cup in sight! Each fish has its own little tank and they are all healthy and happy looking! Staff is helpful and friendly without being overbearing (think constantly asking about assistance and following you around) which is nice when just browsing the shelves and planning what to get! Highly recommend this store
response_from_owner_text: Hello Anna, What a great review. Thank you for taking the time to share your thoughts.Over the years we have changed how we keep our Bettas, and are always looking to improve.It can be a challenge when we get new orders of over 100 or more, but we always try to give them a comfortable holding area until they go to their larger, enriched, forever homes. Thanks again and hope to see you soon.

review_text: Lots of aquatic pets here, some reptiles and guinea pigs as well. Cool place
response_from_owner_text: Hi D B, Thanks for noticing that we have a cool place!

review_text: Very knowledgeable staff and wonderful selection of aquatic supplies and live stock
response_from_owner_text: Hi Nurse Nina, Thanks for leaving us a stellar review.

review_text: Very friendly staff even if you dont buy anything and just go around looking like me :)))). Nice place.

Great! Always have a good range of freshwater and saltwater fish, as well as a moderately-sized reptile section. I come here mostly for frozen food for my ball python, which they have in many sizes for decent price.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Alison, Thanks for taking the time to leave us a 5 star review.  We really appreciate that you have noticed our selection of fresh and saltwater fish and purchase food for your ball python.

review_text: Lowest prices at any fish store we ve been to in the lower mainland. Will be back!

This place is awesome! Amazing staff! They re extremely knowledgeable and will take the extra time to make sure any kind of set up you are building for your animal friends is safe, clean and well put together. Also makes for a great place to stop by and see some awesome critters and learn more about what youre getting into before you make any big decisions. I would recommend this as a top spot for all aquarium needs
response_from_owner_text: Hi Heather, Thanks for the detailed 5 star review and recognizing the knowledgeable and amazing staff!

review_text: Great place with good selection of fish and everything. People working in there are always nice and knowledgeable. Definitely recommend
response_from_owner_text: Hi Manny, We so appreciate you leaving a 5 star review and noticing the knowledgeable staff.

review_text: Its a unique petshop where things are way more organised and clean.. there is variety of different pets in containers like fishtanks and setups you can choose from as per your needs.. and interests.. very friendly, knowledgeable and helpful staff..
Best local  aquarium store in the lower mainland

I love this place. Its like a very relaxing place for me. The website is updated daily with live animals and goods, different shipments coming from different parts of the world. The Staff were very knowledgeable and friendly. I like the gothic cool chic, she is great and knows it all. Also, the cute tall guy with aviator hat, hes very approachable, nice. The other guys as well and cashiers were on top of things. I highly recommend this place for beginners, advanced and pet enthusiasts.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Cris, Thanks for loving and recommending Aquariums West!  We really appreciate you noticing the fabulous and knowledgeable staff that work here.

review_text: Probably the nicest aquarium on the mainland! Every tank in here is a masterpiece - huge props to the staff for the creativity and skill it takes to create and maintain them. Lots of plants and fish for sale, as well as niche things that are hard to find elsewhere.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Sar, Thank you for leaving us such a great review.  It is so nice that you recognize the staffs hard work.

review_text: The more you go the more you like it, the longer you stay in there the more you find the hidden gems. They help you test your tank water and you can call them for stock availability. You can even call them to have your items ready in a bag to pick up. They listen to your instructions carefully and they have your items ready right on time. Before buying, if you ask about the fish, if it has been medicated and quarantined, they are always able to tell you. If your fish is sick they are willing to talk to you and provide advice. The plants are on the expensive side but they do not have algae. I especially like their low iron glass aquascape tanks. You can watch them for days. The Asian staff I think his name is Douglas is super enthusiastic and funny. The manager seems kinda quiet and yeah that is kinda true and you may be scared to approach him at first but he is actually super chill dude. Please do your research on the animal before purchasing.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Harran, Wow!  Thanks for leaving such a detailed review.  So happy that you have had your questions answered and been given good advice. Doug will be very happy to read this.  And...the rest of the staff too.

review_text: Went to Aquariums West for the first time today. Ive been keeping fish for decades and this is hands down the best aquarium store Ive ever seen. The COVID protocols are good, the staff are friendly. If you want help, they help you, if you want to be left alone, they leave you alone. They are knowledgeable and share information without being condescending. The selection is amazing. The tanks are beautifully kept. Its just a really fantastic store.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Caroline, Thank you so much for taking the time to leave such a stellar review.  The staff will be very happy to read this.

review_text: Love this store. Great selection of equipment, hardscape and livestock. Prices reflect the convenient location.

Always come here to buy my Amphibians and Nano fish! They always have a great rotating selection of Reptiles, Amphibians, and Fish. Staff are always welcoming and helpful. I highly recommend them for all your Exotic Pet needs!
response_from_owner_text: Hello Hayden, Thank you for the great review! Hope to see you again soon.

review_text: Aquariums West is absolutely the best Lower Mainland store for aquarium and terrarium needs. Ive shopped there many times and have always found the staff to be very professional and knowledgeable. Jenn in particular has been a life-saver numerous times when Ive needed amphibian advice. Highly recommend!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Trevor, Thanks for leaving such a great review and recognizing Jenn for her knowledge and professionalism.

review_text: Great selection of aquarium supplies, fish, and plants.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Bijan for taking the time to leave a review.Great pictures !

review_text: Another zoo we visit on the way home from school, but this is downtown. Great, family owned pet store.

Amazing place with super knowledgeable and helpful staff. I dont get my fish/other tank animals anywhere else. It is clear that all the staff truly care about their jobs. Yes their prices run on the higher side, but in this hobby you should already be at peace with having to spend a little money for quality products. If youre not ok with spending money, maybe this isnt the right hobby for you (you are taking care of live animals after all). I could honestly spend hours in there looking at all the cool species. 10/10 would recommend.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Jack, Thank you so much for taking the time to give us such a stellar review.  We appreciate your business so much.

review_text: Aquariums West is a great pet store. The staff is knowledgeable and they take very good care of their varied living creatures. This provides those acquiring a new pet a much needed good start towards furthering the health and well being of a new animal friend.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Brad, Thanks for taking the time to leave us a 5 star review.

review_text: This is a great pet store, they provide good service, healthy fish and accurate advice. Ive never bought a fish and had outbreaks in my tank. I have had problems in the past with my tank and they were able to help me. Regardless of the limited occupancy due to COVID restriction, the staff gave me the time I needed to make the right purchase.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Kolyn Gay-Gray, Thanks so much for your review.  We are happy that you were able to get the help you needed for your purchase and advice when things didnt go quite right.  Everyone is trying their best.

review_text: Came in looking for a fairly uncommon reptile and they were so much help. Glad I went in. Although the entrance and exit are a little odd, I ended up having to help a woman in a wheelchair in because no one heard her knocking on the door
response_from_owner_text: Hello Yosuf, Thanks for taking the time to leave us a review. Glad we were able to help with your reptile needs. Being in a basement does have its challenges for sure. We do have doorbells and an intercom for building entry for those coming down the elevator, which work most of the time. We are always a phone call away to come let folks in if there are issues with the door. Thanks for your help and have a great day.

review_text: Fantastic store. They actually seem to care about their fish and customers. For a medium sized store they carry a lot of products and livestock. Definitely with coming here from out-of-town.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Firstt3nor, Thanks for visiting from out of town and leaving us a 5 star review.

review_text: Decided to buy some plants online as I dont have a car and transit would take me about an hour.  Plants got here the day after they shipped in perfect condition.  They even refunded some of the shipping cost since it wasnt calculated properly in the online checkout.  A great experience and looking forward to visiting the store one day.  I actually work about 5 minutes away but have been working from home for the last year!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Terry, Thank you so much for taking the time to leave a review.  I hope you do come by and visit the store but now you know how easy it is to buy plants online!

review_text: Aquariums West is my go-to shop for fish and reptile supplies. I have an assortment of pets at home, and its so convenient to get all of my shopping done in one place. The staff is very friendly, knowledgeable, helpful, and gives advice to work within your budget. The animals husbandry standards and care are superb. I have seen them give great advice to first-time pet owners, and they are equally able to help me answer more advanced questions about my animal care. If a staff member on duty doesnt have insight into a specific issue, they have great teamwork to source the correct information for their customers. The only downside is that their hours conflict with my (admittedly unusual) work schedule, so I really have to prioritize scheduling my trips! Highly recommend for all exotic pet and reptile needs!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Aliyah, WOW! Thanks for leaving such a detailed review.  We really appreciate you taking the time to do that.  If you ever need anything sent to you by Canada Post (so you dont have to leave work) that isnt listed on the website, just let us know and we would be happy to mail it to you.

review_text: Awesome store its so cool. The staff where super nice and gave me a awesome deal on a plant I liked. They have everything at a good price and fully stocked. Huge selection of shrimp and fish. This is the only place Ive see hillstream loaches. Also the red tail shark near the entrance is huge! 100% a must go for fish keepers. I ment Ive never seen hillstreams In my life :) it was my first time there dont mean to miss lead
response_from_owner_text: Hi Clayton, Thank you for leaving such a great 5 star review.  The staff will love it! We order in Hillstream Loaches every time we see them on our suppliers availability list.

review_text: Great store! Despite being swamped with Covid, theyve been handling the demands pretty well and doing the best they can managing crowds. Worth the wait! Knowledgeable staff that are honest about what your pet will need and do their best to prepare you for giving the animal youre purchasing the best life possible. Definitely recommend - great staff, clean store and great atmosphere!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Skye, Thanks for the great review.  It is a very challenging time and we really appreciate your acknowledgement of the demands that the staff face every day.  You are obviously a patient and kind person to let others know that it is worth the wait.  Thank you so much!

review_text: Absolutely amazing aquascaping and fish store! Would highly recommend! They are super helpful and can help you no matter where you are at in skill level. They have been instrumental in helping me get my first aquarium set up and stocked with great plants and decor.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Vlad, Thanks so much for posting such a great review.  We really appreciate you recognizing that the store is for both beginners and experienced aquascapers.

review_text: Experienced, knowledgeable, professional, and fun staff. They can help with any questions from beginners getting into the hobby and for those a little more experienced. Great selection of shrimp and fresh water fish. Lots of great live plant selection. The overall environment of the store is welcoming.

The nicest and cleanest fish store that I have been. The fish and other stiff are not expensive too. Nice staff too. I bought a guppy here. And the next day the guppy that I bought from them died ( so I thought it was my fault ) the following day I went to this store again. Checkinh i they still have the same guppy that I bought. To my surprise the lady told me they all died too. So I told her the one that I bought died too. And then she told me that I could choose a guppy again and shell gonna give it free.
Great selection of fish, shrimps, aquatic plants, accessories and equipment. Very knowledgeable and helpful staff.
Great selection of freshwater fish
response_from_owner_text: Hi Jessica, Thanks for leaving a 5 star review and some great photos!

review_text: Great Store. I bought some Marine Shrimp there that I am very happy with! They are healthy and were well cared for inside the store. I was helped by two very knowledgeable employees Jen & CJ who were more then happy to spend all the time with me that I needed to have all my questions answered, and the Shrimp were bagged as I selected them. That visit was great experience overall and I will for sure be returning to the shop!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Grumpy Walrus, Thanks so much for leaving a detailed 5 star review.  Jen and CJ will be really happy to see this!  Seems to me you are a Happy Walrus instead of a grumpy one.

review_text: Aquariums West is a great aquarium store! They have a wide selection and helpful staff. Weve bought all of our fish, shrimp, snails, and plants here.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Matthew, Thanks so much for taking the time to leave us a 5 star review.

review_text: line ups were long. Waited 45 min to get in so I recommend planning your trip around a 45 min wait so you are prepared. Staff was really helpful and kind.( Really sexy guys that work there , so, ladies that was a plus +++ tattooed guy was very sexy ;) made my wait worth my while LOL ). But really, very beautiful layout and very good prices. I recommend this store to anyone in the lower mainland  who is in the hobby of starting out, you  must go here.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Alexia, Thanks so much for your very positive review and so sorry about the wait, not too much we can do about that.  Glad you liked the eye candy!!  The tattooed guy will love this review!

review_text: The staff here are fantastic and helpful.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Fraser, Thanks for your 5 star review.  Your review gives such a boost to the staff!

review_text: Lovely aquarium and pet store just outside BC Place in Vancouver. Its located in the basement, but the store is well stocked and the staff were super helpful and willing to help educate. Focused more on aquatic life and pets, but theres a small section for other pets as well.  The tanks are all very clean and were happy with the fish recommended and purchase there. Parking is on the street and a bit of a challenge, be prepared to walk a block or two.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Adrian for your lovely review and it is so nice to acknowledge the staff.

review_text: Aquariums West is pretty outstanding. My experience with them is limited to buying live stock and asking for advice, a lot of advice. I cant count the number of times Ive been in the store where... well, really every person working (esp. Alex) is willing to take the time to listen and help you. The coolest part though, and why I truly give them 5 stars is when I call. Often, I have a simple question, other times I have a pretty complex one dealing with a specific fish. No matter the case, they have taken the time to talk and listen, and then lead me in the right direction. I really am thankful that stores like this exist and how passionate they are. (Yes, Google helps too but often its conflicting info and its nice to have someone help you sort all that out.)

Ordered some living plants online and very satisfied. Those living plants arrived on time, healthy, and were well wrapped and protected inside a box. Also the shipping cost was partially refunded (automatically) to reflect the real cost. Definitely will order more.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Kevin,  We really appreciate you leaving us a 5 star review.  Thanks for the synopsis of your experience.

review_text: Aquariums West is always my go to place whenever Im downtown. They have everything you could ever need for Aquarium hobbyists and terrarium critters alike. The service is excellent and the prices are reasonable. Their displays are stunning and very well kept. Love you guys!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Rowan, Thanks so much for leaving such a nice review.  We really appreciate you noticing our stunning (as you put it) displays!

review_text: My first visit, stopped in quickly to buy a betta. There were lots of options, and the staff person was super helpful and knowledgeable. Good covid safety measures in place as well. Would definitely visit again for any aquarium/fish needs!

Have been buying all my tropical fish and a majority of the food & accessories from this store for 20 + years. They are always helpful and found them very knowledgeable about supplies and fish. Have followed them around to three different locations. I know travel from Surrey to Vancouver for my aquarium needs.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Glenn, Wow!  Thanks for being a customer for 20+ years and following us to our different locations.

review_text: Just started keeping cherry shrimp and I noticed that they were dying off at a fast rate. The person who gave me the shrimp told me to go to this store and I did. I was helped by three different staff members, all of whom were super friendly and laid back, not to mention able to answer all of my questions. They tested a sample of my aquariums water that I brought in and told me what I needed to address the water issues without  being insistent or pushy. Prices are what youd expect for a specialty store, but to me its definitely worth it for the service and expertise I get here.

This is our go-to fish store. The staff working at this location is friendly, kind and knowledgeable. You can call them and ask about their fish inventory before visiting the store to make sure they have the fish you are looking for. Wide range of fish food and plants are also available at this location.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Shivani for recognizing the friendly staff.  We appreciate you taking the time to review the store.

review_text: I have been shopping at Aquariums West for years now, and they are my go to store. I have always found the employees to be friendly, and accommodating and will do everything they can to help. I have never had a bad experience at this store, I will continue shopping there for my aquarium and reptile needs. I also appreciate that they have taken COVID seriously and keep capacity down, and require masks, one of the best retailers I have been to in regards to their COVID protocols.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Justin, Thanks for taking the time to post a great review and your mention of our Covid protocols.  We appreciate your appreciation!

review_text: Great staff, very friendly and knowledgeable! My wife is really into fish tanks and this place has been amazing at helping her find the right stuff to get started. They take covid protocols very seriously which is something I really appreciate. I drive all the way out from Maple Ridge to shop here, thats how good they are!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Dan, We really appreciate you appreciating our Covid protocols. I hope you too are getting into fish tanks along with your wife.  Thanks so much for the 5 star review.

review_text: Pricey (it is downtown after all), but very elegant displays, and great and healthy livestock. The have a new up and running saltwater fish and coral section which is looking really good as well. Good stock of dry goods, tanks, equipment, etc. Staff are friendly and knowledgeable, especially when it comes to freshwater fish. They stock a few reptiles as well, like frogs, geckos, snakes. All look to be in good condition!
The place was a little hard to find but once I did the staff was super helpful. Very friendly and accommodating. They had some beautiful fish in there and some nice reptile set ups.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Amber, So glad that you found us!  Thanks for leaving a 5 star review!

review_text: Have been coming here for years ever since I started keeping planted tanks---staff are all very friendly and have never done me wrong with advice that doesnt hold up.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Eli, So happy we havent done you wrong with our advice.  We appreciate you taking the time to leave us 5 stars!

review_text: I love coming here! Great experience, friendly and knowledgeable staff that offer help but also give you space to look around. I love my cherry shrimps and guppy fish! Go during the week if you are able to when it is not as busy and no lineups :)
response_from_owner_text: Hi Fantsy Pants, We really appreciate you taking the time to give us a 5 star review.

review_text: Super helpful staff. Vancouvers best local fish store. I regularly shop at different fish stores online and brick/mortar and the cleanliness of the livestock at Aquariums West is next to none. Ive never had a single pest on any of the dozens of fish / coral Ive purchased. All my livestock go through strict quarantine procedures and I document as much as I can to help other people in the hobby.

Picked up 3 rats here, staff were accommodating and very helpful and knowledgeable. Because of my situation I needed to pick out the rats one day and pick them up the next day, no other store was able to accommodate this but they had no problem with it. The animals all look well cared for here

I wish I lived in Vancouver because I went here yesterday and felt sad that I wouldnt be able to come here often. Very beautiful tanks. The guppy and mollies looked really good. Might consider a road trip to pick up some plants and fish
response_from_owner_text: Hi Dana, Thanks for leaving us a 5 star review.  We do ship live Tropica plants and dry goods all across Canada.  You can check out the website www.aquariumswest.com New plants arrive every Tuesday afternoon.

review_text: I was so impressed by this store - the animals are in great setups, well taken care of, and appropriately fed. Youll be hard pressed to find healthier amphibians/reptiles/fish at another store! I would recommend Aquariums West to anyone looking for healthy plants, animals, or equipment. The staff are also extremely personable, friendly, and knowledgeable. There isnt a bad thing I have to say about this place.
Huge space Especially being located in a downtown Freshwater and saltwater is available here. Huge selection of filter, tanks and others. The fish looks pretty and healthy I bought swordtails here.
response_from_owner_text: Hello JC, Thank you for your review. We try to get new livestock every week to make it interesting. Hope your swordtails are doing well.

review_text: The place is great, they have a good variety of products and theyre very friendly, I have to clarify that the only thing is that some stuff are a bit over priced, maybe the location     besides that is a good place to find anything you need for your pets!
response_from_owner_text: Hello Leopoldo, Thanks for taking the time to leave us a review. We are always looking at our prices to stay competitive, even when our prices are changing weekly from our suppliers. Hope to see you again soon!
