Great food, excellent service. Highly recommended :)
Live seafood. If you like seafood you will love this place in downtown

Love the food, great taste and beautiful presentation!! It is a bit too noisy for us but we can tell it is a very popular place for a good reason. My husband usually doesn t have dessert. I ordered the olive oil cake, he shared half of it, it was so good!! We will definitely be back for more!

So happy we found this restaurant! Large selection of vegetarian dishes and sea food, delicious food! Especially loved the halibut and the vegetarian pasta. Also the fries are delicious. Service was friendly and attentive. Only note is it s REALLY loud inside, we couldn t hear each other speaking (even the young ones;). I recommend sitting outside. Overall great experience
Amazing food, everything I tried was delicious. Cant even pick a favorite item. Oysters, mussels, sable fish, salmon tasted all very fresh and prepared excellently.
The portions were pretty small but the food was good. The burrata was SO GOOD. If you like a more lively atmosphere sit inside, we chose the patio because it was more intimate.

Fresh ingredients but portions are bit small. Came here for our first dinner during our visit in Vancouver on a Friday night. The place was fully booked the only place available for us was in the heated patio area. The patio areas had plenty of heat lamps and the place was fully closed off so you won t need to worry about rain or snow (we were here during March and it actually snowed during our dinner!) The food was pretty good, we ordered tiger shrimp cocktails, grilled oysters, assorted sashimi platter, seared scallops and a bowl of clams. Our favourite was the seared scallops hands down. We also orders some vegetable dish and they were amazing too! The beets with avocado and warm goat cheese was out of this world! The portion was kind of small so consider yourself warned. But the quality was certainly worthy of the price tag. Would come back again!

I did have a hand in building this place, and I do know the owners and chefs..... but that doesnt influence my review of this amazing local tapas restaurant. Quite a varied selection and fresh sheet that is updated so frequently, dare I say daily?!  I recently returned here for the first time since covid with my parents who are exceptionally picky eaters.  We ordered about six to seven plates between the three of us and we were stuffed with the lightest freshest and tastiest foods that their spanish cuisine has to offer. (All with the West coast flare). Oh, and there is an outdoor (but enclosed) patio that makes it feel like a bistro in California. 9/10 would highly recommend, and it could be your new favorite regular place! **Reservations can be very difficult

Oddfish was quite the experience. I had one of the best meals I think Ill ever have. I went with a party of four and we were all able to share, it was wonderful. I need to express how fresh and creative their menu is - especially when you realize it is all based on what comes in from that days catch. The octopus carpaccio, seared scallops, and the sole were divine. I can recommend all of those plus the mussels, though I have a feeling whatever you order here will end up being good. The one negative I would have is the price point if not for the fact I think the experience was well worth it. We ended up spending around $100 per person this meal.

Not many places like this around. Everything from the water to espresso and dessert was excellent. Best olives, oysters, and fries I ve ever had. The raw fish platter was amazing and the deserts were satisfying. Presentation and timing were perfect. Scott was a charming, competent, and helpful server who made the experience whole for us. The serving sizes are not especially large but the flavor is worth the prices. El Popo cocktail was a unique spin on a margarita that was excellently balanced. Couldn t recommend more.
Seafood lover s paradise. The muscles and fries were some of the best I ve ever had. Our server helped with some recommendations and answered any questions we had about the menu in depth.

Gonna go with 4.5 here... Oddfish is a super unique place based on the fact its completely pescatarian. Situated in a quaint little neighborhood, Oddfish has a lot of character and its not the atmosphere that lends to it, its the food! We had a selection of delicious dishes: scallops, a sole picatta, an amazing burrata, and we had to throw some fries in there as well. We were hesitant about the Picatta but its a best seller and was very flavorful. Scallops again are exceptionally delicious but a smaller serving as was the burratta. Understand that the portions arent the largest at Oddfish, but they make up for it in taste. Service was good. Not too overbearing and knowledgeable with respect to the menu. Our guy made a few excellent suggestions that we appreciated. If youre interested in a menu centered entirely on seafood and fish, there arent many places better than Oddfish in Vancouver

One of my favorite casual share plate restaurants in Vancouver. The food is always amazing, and its a great selection of fresh seafood and vegetable dishes. The drinks were a tad pricey, but I feel the food was very reasonably priced considering the quality and creativity of the dishes. The service is also amazing. The last time we were there the server for our section was super slammed but never let stress show. The manager(I presume) jumped in occasionally and the two made a great tag team. I always have a great experience whenever I come here!

This place is getting on my top-3 eat-out spots list in Vancouver. Everything was on a pretty high level, Richard, our waiter did his job brilliantly, he was very attentive and his sense of humor made our evening a bit brighter. The restaurants chef is also on the right spot, dishes look like a masterpiece and taste delicious, thank you for that pleasure. Smoked salmon toast and the oysters were my absolute favorites that evening. There were a couple of things that could be improved though: the water glasses look is not really nice, they look old like with scratches and salty traces from a dishwasher. We don t drink alcohol so we had to use those glasses whole evening. I really liked the smoked salmon toast and asked for another one, but second time the toast itself was badly burnt. But Richard made things right by saying that he was sorry and we won t be charged for this one, he also offered to bring some bread so we could trade it with burnt toast, thanks! But putting the toast like that on the plate in the first place is not really nice. Overall it s a really nice spot and we definitely coming back! Thanks Oddfish!

The servers were prompt and very comfortably professional. Even though it was a super busy evening, our server, Ashley, took time to get to know us and talk to us about their menu. Their vongole & prawn diavolo spaghetti dishes were amazing, and I like the overall vibe of the restaurant, energetic & vibrant. Strongly recommend for a nice dine out place in Kits area. It would be about $50/person for a shared appy, dish & drink.

This was an incredible restaurant with fresh and flavorful seafood!  I really appreciated the small portions... Much better to have small amounts of delicious food than a large amount of mediocre food that I would feel obligated to finish. Everything we ordered was mouthwatering; the highlight was the mixed ceviche.  I ordered potato wrapped halibut and my wife ordered the branzino. Both dishes were very good.  Cocktails were well made, even when I requested something not on the menu.  Service was awesome, staff was attentive but not excessive.  Didnt rush us at all.  This is a place well definitely be returning to!

We had a great time exploring the dishes here. The sashimi tasting plate was was very good. The scallop we had was too salty in the first place, but they fixed it for us. The beats salad is also tasty.

Cozy ambiance inside and perfect patio for nice days. Baked oysters, crudo and burrata were favorites, but everything was excellent. Nice Sancerre wine paring recommendation. Highly recommended if youre in Vancouver.

The pan seared scallops were fantastic. Perfect crust on both sides, and cooked perfectly. Brussel sprouts were also very tasty, with a nice mild spicy kick while being loaded with a mountain of parmesan, slightly warmed and stretchy from being shaved right on top of the parmesan.

Probably the best meal Ive had Im some time. Absolutely loved Oddfish for the food, atmosphere and service. The ceviche was sublime, burrata was amazing and the fish mains and sides were all excellent. Yum!

I ve never felt the need to write a restaurant review before, but this place deserves one. I honestly can t believe it doesn t have more rave reviews. Every dish was delicious - our favourite dish was probably the perch. Our server walked us through the menu and was also super attentive. Just keep in mind everything is a pretty small, so make every bite count!

Always amazing. Since theyve opened we have been here 6-7 times already. Ruby trout is so juicy and perfectly cooked, oysters are always perfect, fresh, crisp, and clean. The citrus salad is refreshing and simple. Whole seabass is wonderful too.

Had the whole sea bass, mussels, octopus special, and spring onions. They were all fresh, delicious, and clean flavors. The staff are fantastic. Don t skip on the dessert. The pot di creme and this Meyer lemon mousse something rather were both amazing!

I wish we could have ordered one of every dish but will just have to come back! They were incredibly accommodating for dietary restrictions, and while the menu may not specifically state gluten free options, the choices were abundant. We will absolutely be back.

Excellent restaurant, I would highly recommend it. If youre prepared to spend a bit more than your usual meal out, this place is awesome. The food was on top and the staff was great. So many good options from the menu. Its a good idea to share the food so that you can taste more plates. The atmosphere is dynamic and slightly noisy with people chatting but if you dont mind it, it all actually works out to a great atmosphere. Deserts on top too, I would give you a recommendation but I think that youre safe if you just trust the waitress

I have never wanted to lick a plate so desperately in my life I had the salmon feature and from the artful presentation to the mouthwatering flavours- I was smitten It was quite literally the best salmon that I have ever tasted. It was succulent, moist, flavourful & melted in my mouth. They further maximized the flavour with a crispy skin finish that gave a hightened texture and finish that was utterly swoon worthy The service is ALWAYS top notch and you ll often find the owners there, nimbly sliding in to bus tables (ahem - Brad  ) and have a friendly word The wine selection is also top notch and if you re not sure what you want, Kyle is there to assist in marrying a vino to your palate with exquisite accuracy 5 Stars all the way

Excellent Celiac Safe meal at Oddfish!  Really impressed with the attentiveness of the wait staff, the care taken when dealing with a medically needed diet and the nice outdoor atmosphere!  It is better to sit outside as inside is very loud.  Outside is still loud but traffic dependant. Vegetarian options: The menu is heavy plant / vegetarian / seafood oriented.  Despite not being a vegetarian the food was outstanding for flavour! Dietary restrictions: Celiac Disease / Gluten free diet - very accommodating and understood ins and outs of diet needs (such as sweet potato chips fried in oil in pan instead of fryer) and cross contamination.  Another Celiac dining at next table.  Chocolate mousse desert was outstanding! Wheelchair accessibility: One floor.  Did not check washrooms.  We sat outside and let them know that I needed an accessible table and a very suitable one was provided.  The tables are pretty tight together so it was good to warn them.

Food is absolutely delactable. Highlights for me were the fungi linguini and lemon posit. Although for the linguini we opted no wine due to the kids as they dont like the taste, olive oil replacement was just as amazing. Service is warm and friendly. Environment is noisy once it fills up as quite a few tables tend to carry very animated conversations so not for folks who enjoy a serene dining experience.

This is a new seafood restaurant that just opened in the Kitsilano neighbourhood. The seafood is incredibly fresh and delicious. My suggestion is to come to this restaurant and share the dishes family style between 3 to 4 people. This gives you an opportunity to try a bit of everything on the menu. Our favourite dishes were the fresh burrata, grilled octopus with spicy romanesco puree and the pasta with chanterelle mushrooms. So insanely good. The wine selection was also very reasonable with a mix of local and international wines. Definitely worth trying out if you are in the mood for great seafood.
So glad we were able to get a table here - the food was incredible and the service was very friendly. A must try!
Both fish were perfectly cooked along with the pasta being perfectly Al dente. The pesto pasta was especially delicious.
I found the food really good. Fresh ingredients and skillful preparation. Drinks were really good too. The waiters were lovely too, however they forgot to bring the 2nd drink I ordered :D.

We had not just an incredible dinner here, but also a magnificent dining experience. The restaurant has an ever-changing specials menu based on what s fresh from the sea. Two of us ordered the blood orange octopus carpaccio and it was to die for. Mains were delicious too- thai mussels, scallops and piccata. The ambiance here is fantastic- and the service was amazing. Our server and sommelier really knew the menu & had excellent pairing suggestions. We will 1000% be back. What a fantastic evening
Best spot for seafood! Oysters and mussels were delicious. Staff was very helpful and friendly. Definitely will be coming back!

I ve been here many times before but only a few times by myself. This time as a solo diner I was sat at the table by the kitchen. My server was so amazing, she didn t make me feel rushed cause I was solo dining. The food was amazing. Wanted to thank the chefs personally but they were so busy. I ll definitely be back for solo dining and with friends. The watermelon salad was amazing

Absolutely phenomenal! My better half and I celebrated a new chapter last Thursday and we couldnt be happier with this dining experience. We started with some oysters that were both fresh and delicious. Our server, Lisa, was exceptional at describing specials and welcoming us into her section. Although it was her section, the entire team worked beautifully together at making sure eveey guests was attended to. We selected our meals from the feature menu and highly recommend it. Our appie was the Burrata, and it was spectacular. Paired with our white wine, on their heated patio was heavenly. We shared the Branzino feature and it was light, soft and cooked to perfection. We wanted to ensure a compliment to the cook was sent as it blew our minds. Well done Jonah. If youve got room for dessert, do it. Everything this Odd Fish does is remarkable.

Great food and service was excellent. Staff was always there to fill your water and take away the dirty dishes. Our server offered us more toasted bread to soak up the broth from the mussels. Its thoughtful gestures like that, that is often missing from restaurants these days. . Dishes are shareable and theres a good variety. The menu is more than what is on their webpage as they have a seasonal menu with quite a few dishes in addition to there regular menu. The inside seating sounded noisy so we chose to sit outside.Outdoor patio is enclosed and heated.
The best Branzino I have ever had! I highly recommend Oddfish for anyone looking for delectable fresh seafood raw or cooked to perfection.
Great seafood, veggie restaurant. Server really helpful with menu and wine list. Bit out of downtown where we were staying, but well worth the $10 Uber.

A must-try restaurant for any seafood lover! They ve got all the classics as well as great tapas style dishes that will make your mouth water just by reading them up on the menu. It s definitely on the pricey side so this is not your everyday go-to restaurant (unless you re in the 1%, in which case please have dinner there every night!) but rather saved for special occasions.

Simply delicious and fresh. Burrata with romesco sauce and olives served with toasted bread. Whets the appetite. The bread had a nice bite that complemented the cheese. Seared scallops with cauliflower puree. That cauliflower was so smooth! Clams served with toasted bread. Flavourful garlic and chilis wine broth was perfect. Olive oil cake. Light lemon flavour and the right amount of sweetness served with creme fraiche and macerated blueberries. It was a lovely dinner with wonderful food and great customer service. Will certainly be back.
Everything was excellent! We had 2 oysters each, fanny bay, they were delicious. Same goes for their mussels and fries. Well save a bit of appetite to order their desserts next time.
Easily my favourite restaurant in the city. Fresh sheet always offers something new to try, along with regular menu staples that hit the spot every time. Awesome staff!
Another strong recommendation would like seafood and you are in Vancouver. This place is fabulous seafood dishes. Highly recommend it!

I have travelled to many countries and sampled many restaurants. I have to say that the Oddfish experience was simply divine..food was incredible..server (anthony) an absolute gem. It was an moment that allowed us..the 7 of us to stop/reflect and come to the same conclusion..that was a materpiece of a meal..i feel honoured and privilged to say that i have dined in vancouvers finest seafood restaurant..it will always be a fond memory back in galway, ireland.
A fantastic seafood restaurant with expert staff and delicious food. Our server helped us craft a tapas menu that was a delicious culinary experience. Thank you!
The oysters were so delicious, they tasted fresh out of the ocean! I appreciate that they serve non-alcoholic cocktails too.

Delicious! The food is absolutely awesome here. We loved the Hot Mess dish and the pistachio crusted sturgeon! The salted caramel desert was also superb. You ll be impressed with mostly anything you order here. Waiters are very friendly and knowledgable. Listen to them and their suggestions. A little on the expensive side but worth the indulgence.
Hands down some of the best food weve had in a very long time. Highly recommend!
This is amazing restaurant. Some of the finest seafood dishes I have ever had. The service was great too.
Wow... Order family style. Food is a little pricey, smaller portions but its fantastic. This was worth the splurge!
Fantastic service, drinks and above all, fantastic food!

Odd fish restaurant takes pride in what they do! Love this place. Fresh and tasty seafood dishes with excellent service. We ordered the fresh oysters, mussels and fries and then the potato crusted halibut as well as the sole piccata. They were all so good that now it s stuck in my head and palate for such great foods. Our server was also outstanding. Totally recommend.

Amazing seafood! Hands down the freshest mussels I ve ever had. The fish entree was also fabulous with crispy skin. The prawn ceviche was quite acidic but still delicious. Oysters were juicy and fresh. I only wish the waiter was more warm and welcoming.
Great seafood and fantastic service! Get the Seafood Hot Mess - its perfection on a plate. Also awesome, a place in Vancouver that serves dry sherry by the glass.
Service was amazing and food was incredible. If you like seafood, this is the place for it.
Awesome menu. I personally recommend the burratta. You can ask for some changes in the plates. Very nice waitress.

The service was great. The Google reviews are right! The light that comes in from the big windows and decor of the place is realy nice even though we were there on a rainy evening. The patio was covered and still open which was surprising! Good to know for next time. We had the spaghetti with tomatoes and basil on special and it was so good. You could tell the pasta was fresh and made in house as they say. It was also very al dente which is what I like a lot about fresh pasta! We also ordered the squid the whole seabass with the harissa sauce. I personally didnt think too much of the seabass as I think I just prefer harissa with more heat but thats just me. The other highlight of our meal was the parsley salad that came with the whole fish. It was SO Good. Like literally a light fresh tangy surprise in your mouth thats like the best contrast after taking a couple bites of the fish. So refreshing. So yum! Id come back for the pasta and am looking forward to trying nook. Our awesome server told us their sister restaurant nook does the daily fresh meat pastas while oddfish does the seafood ones. So excited, I hope they have some parsley salad over there too lol
I am glad we found this restaurant! Fresh and delicious food, excellent service, warm atmosphere. Super!
Food and service were both great! Been here a few times now. :) Would recommend

The staff are friendly and never steer you wrong with suggestions. The food is delicious and the wine selections are well curated. If seated in the dining room, as is always a packed house, tends to be a little loud.
Great Food and Ambiance. The service by Tony was exceptional as well.

Oddfish was a great experience overall! Excellent food with lots of different dishes to try, fantastic service that was genuinely helpful, and a lively atmosphere. We shared about 6 different dishes and liked all of them! Awesome spot for a special occasion, youll have to make a reservation.
Delicious seafood, Friendly Staff, Great Ambiance and Punchy Cocktails!

Server coped with our frequent changes of numbers easily. Food was excellent especially main dish of sole recommended by the server. Lovely location on the patio. Second time we ve eaten here and will reserve every time we visit Vancouver.
This is by far one of the best in the city. The food is delicious and the service is friendly. A neighborhood fav. I highly recommend it for a nice  evening out. Food
Love odd fish. Great food, great service & a vibey place

10/10 would recommend Weve been here on multiple occasions and always leave impressed and completely satisfied with the quality of the food and the service. The menu continuously changes but it is always great includes GF, DF options. Great for sharing with a group of people or for a business dinner. Love the heated outdoor patio for the summer/ winter.

Three varieties of oysters on the half shell. Great beet salad, truffle sole was excellent, crudo delicious, very nice Thai mussels. Wonderful house marinated olives. Great service. Half eggplant was unevenly cooked, the mixed texture combined with the simple BBQ sauce was underwhelming. We will be back worth a visit. Thanks

Nice cozy place on the corner and was quitr busy on a Saturday evening. Good that a booking was made so I could sit on a table. If not, would have been on the bar counter.. Amazing variety of sea food and I LOVED almost everything. Despite living in a hoise close to beach on a tropical country, I thoroughly enjoyed the dishes and the variety. Price was on the high side but good value for money..

Just wow!  Our server was amazing.  She was very attentive and knew what our needs were before we had to ask for anything. She was very prepared as she knew the specials and menu items intimately and communicated it perfectly to us.  I should have taken a picture of the daily specials as we ordered some from that menu and they were amazing.  The regular menu items were also really good.   We we definitely go back and try more of everything there!  Next time I will do a better job capturing the details of what we had.

Really nice restaurant and menu if you like fish, with fully vegetarian options too. If the chef is reading: I would personally use something finer and softer as the crunchy element in the Leches de Tigre Ceviche. But really nice and agreeable, certainly to be experienced.

Have dined here 3 times in the last couple years and each time is fantastic. I didn t even notice until last night that they don t even have meat on the menu. No one including my meat loving husband missed it though! The burrata as a starter is a must have. I ve had both the honey pistachio and the seasonal pea mint one. Perfect. I didn t even like burrata before this. The fresh pasta makes a nice side dish with a veggie side too. We shared the halibut but I could have eaten it all! For dessert we had the salted caramel bowl of heaven (not actual name). The only other dessert I ve had elsewhere that is better than this is the date pudding at Rim Rock Cafe. Beyond the food, the servers are all very friendly and attentive. The vibe is  as casual or as dressy as you want .  Very Vancouver. I d you make a reso for the patio know that most of it is covered/enclosed from rain and there are heaters, I was warmer out there than I often feel indoors!

Great seafood spot in Vancouver. We especially lived the Halibut Crudo and the Mussels. Everything was excellent. Nothing too fancy or novel but everything was very fresh and tasty. Nice ambience too.
Grilled oysters are to die for, great vibe and excellent service.
Some of the best seafood i ve had in some time. Scott was a fabulous server, and my wife and thoroughly enjoyed the mussels and tuna tataki that he recommended. We ll definitely be back!
The best seafood I eaten in the west coast over the last 7 years. Really fresh, cooked to perfection.
Great recommendation from a lady on the street, we had a great time and really enjoy the food

Food: Food was great. The mushroom gravy with baguette was fantastic, and they brought out extra baguettes upon our request. We also had their 2 daily specials market fish, sea bass and ocean perch which were both very nice. We also had their fresh dozen oysters and vongole pasta for 3 people. Their portion size is not that big, so we ordered a bunch and shared everything. Service: All staffs are attentive and polite. Our waitress went over the daily specials for us with as much detail as possible (herbs, sauce, whether the fish has bones or not, flavours). They seated us out in the patio despite walking in without any reservations. Despite going off on the menu + wine, our will came out to be less than what we expected. (I guess we overestimated the market price).

Super flavorful. Good amount of food. Absolutely delicious. We got 6 oysters, two apps, and two mains...that was too much food for us but it was hard to stop because of how good it was! Highly recommend
Amazing service and hands down one of the best seafood restaurants in kits.

Very good selection of seasonal seafood thats cooked to perfection. The drinks are wonderful as well. Their open kitchen concept is really  fascinating and fun to watch, especially watching all the prep work. Overall ambiance of the restaurant  is great and weve always had friendly staff. Really recommend getting the oysters.
Wasn t a fan of pasta before until I had Mushroom Linguine  bonus-it has some spice perfectly to my taste. For sure will go back and order few to go
A+ great meal, fresh fish, impeccable service. Kinda pricey cocktails but food is spot (praw)on.
We had dinner there for the first time and it was amazing , the food was great , staff were friendly , for sure will go back

Went here before going to Bard on the Beach.  Great restaurant easily within walking distance to the event. Wonderful outside seating area with complimentary blankets if you get cold. great fish selection and everything that came out of the kitchen looked and tasted superb. not cheap but I would highly recommend it to anyone looking for a good meal.  My only complaint was a lackluster filet job on the sea bass we ordered (dodging bones is never fun) but the flavors of everything were fantastic.

My meat-loving fiance and I enjoyed an incredible early Valentines Date this week. We shared 3 dishes including the mouth watering scallops and perfectly balanced pasta - to ensure we saved room for their salted caramel dessert... highly recommend! Relaxed, comfortable service and delicious cocktails made the night one to remember. We can t wait to go back!

Five star service and food here! Unique menu and interesting dishes. Make sure you try their drinks -- best Ive ever had. Everything tastes like heaven here. Staff are so friendly, thoughtful, above and beyond. They treat you like a rockstar that you wish you could stay forever. The service totally completes the dining experience here. Good for both groups and dating. Highly recommended and make sure you mark them down on your to go list when you are in Kits.
Amazing food, best seafood and freshest oysters in town! Great atmosphere and friendly service. The kitchen bar is the best seats to get a view of the action!

The is where to go for great, fresh fish. If fish is not your thing, then this is the wrong spot for you. We had the Hot Mess, a medley of different seafood, all of it excellent. We shared appies, one of prawns and one of squash. Both were delicious. We should have added some side dishes with the Hot Mess to round out the meal but it was still really good. Friendly, informative service. Good wine list and a very nice modern space.
The Hey Sailor and delicious potato wrapped halibut were incredible. Thank you!
Absolutely fantastic food. I highly recommend it.

I have a bunch of food allergies, so its tough for me to eat out sometimes. These folks were *so fantastic,* the head chef even came out to chat with me, and let me know that the dressing on one of the salads was mayo-based, and collaborate on how to make it differently delicious. The food was *so incredible.* Peak-fresh veggies and fish, beautifully prepared, and perfectly cooked. I highly recommend Oddfish.
Food was delicious! Would come back here next time! Kid-friendliness: Yes. Very nice and kind to kids Food : 5/5 |
review_translated_text: Food

review_text: A night to remember. Was my birthday and all the specialty items were to die for. Our server was one of a kind and very personable. Very attentive to making sure we had drinks full and bellys full. Thank you for an amazing experience.

Favourite restaurant in Vancouver! My top recommendation for sharing several plates with a few friends! Thats just the way to go at oddfish because you will want everything on the menu plus a few of the many features!! I have absolutely loved everything I have ever eaten here. Creativity prepared fresh seasonal veggies, and seafood! I always feel blown away by something seemingly simple but prepared so deliciously with flavours I wouldn t expect! I love that there are always new tasty features, always expect seafood prepared a little different. The burrata is also perfection. Great oysters and pastas too! The staff and management are so kind, always accommodating, recognize us and give excellent service. Not too fancy but doesn t feel weird to dress up for. Thank you Oddfish!

Great service from an experienced team that all work together to ensure you are well cared for. Everything is freshly prepared and the flavours compliment the fish very nicely. Wine selection is succinct and the servers are knowledgeable in pointing you towards the right pairing. A great experience all around!

Every single aspect of this meal was 5 star; dinner, apps, wine, server,  ambiance.  Yellowfin crudo melts in your mouth. Chicken Sauce roasted snapper was full of flavour. Best meal weve had in a while.

What a great spot. Innovative menue that was absolutely delightful and tasty. We had mussels in spicy lemongrass coconut milk. Excellent. Roasted cauliflower was perfect. Shared a pasta in pesto dried tomatoe sauce. A touch dry but again very tasty. Casual but busy location nice wine choices and cocktails. Will be back.

A hidden gem in Kitsilano. Amazing seafood, drinks and service. They also totally nailed the dining experience despite the pandemic restrictions. Nice work! Just a tip, if you want to have your selection of everything on the menu, go early - they have sold out of items all three times that I ve been there.

Went here prior to a Bard on the Beach performance and absolutely loved it. The grilled octopus was the best we have ever had, and the mussels in coconut broth were also excellent. Highly recommend this place to anyone looking for high quality seafood dishes showcasing the best of the west coast.

Hamachi and ceviche dishes really stood out. The sea bass was also great, you can really taste the grill flavour. I did not care for the octopus dish as I found the flavours were not to my liking but some may like it. Great French fries and bread. Top service

Came here for the Alaskan King Crab dinner with my family this week and it was amazing and super reasonably priced. They pre-order the crab once you confirm your reservation and show you the crab before bringing it into the kitchen to cook (it was alive and flailing). The crab was perfectly cooked into 4 dishes. The legs and claws were steamed with garlic, the body fried with salt/pepper/shallot/garlic, seafood fried rice was baked into the shell, and residual meat/juice was used to poach some yuchoy. Everything was perfectly cooked and tasted fresh and delicious. Service was amazing too. You have to drive through some shady areas of Vancouver, but definitely work the trip. Highly recommend and would go back in a heartbeat.

review_text: Prepare yourself for a wild ride because Pelican Restaurant in East Hastings is not your average dining establishment. If youre an adventurous foodie seeking new taste experiences, this place is a hidden gem that deserves your attention. However, if youre looking for a visually stunning, Instagram-worthy ambiance, well, lets just say you wont find it here. Upon entering Pelican Restaurant, you may be underwhelmed by its lackluster decor. But remember, its the taste that matters, right? And boy, oh boy, did Pelican deliver in that department. Every dish we devoured was an explosion of flavors that made our taste buds dance happily. We decided to visit Pelican for brunch, and it turned out to be an epic choice. Who needs pancakes and eggs benedict when you can have a unique culinary experience like no other? We knew we were in for something extraordinary when they opened their doors at 10 am. The menu at Pelican is a delightful mishmash of creative concoctions that will challenge your preconceived notions of what a brunch should be. Expect the unexpected as you peruse through their intriguing selection. From out-of-this-world flavor combinations to random ingredients, Pelican dares to push the boundaries of culinary norms. As we devoured each plate, we couldnt help but appreciate the boldness and creativity that went into the dishes. Pelican Restaurant is a playground for innovative flavors and unexpected pairings. Sure, the decor might not be Insta-worthy, and the ambiance lacks pizzazz, but who needs that when the food is this extraordinary? Pelican is a haven for true food enthusiasts who are willing to step outside their comfort zones and embrace the weird and wonderful. So, if youre a true gastronomic adventurer seeking a new experience of taste, make your way to Pelican Restaurant in East Hastings. Come with an open mind, and an empty stomach, and prepare to have your taste buds blown away. Trust me, its a brunch you wont soon forget.

Great for dinner and large parties. Ordered lots of food and all came out fast one after another. Flavor was a bit in the salted side but thats most Cantonese Chinese food. The duck and chicken came out with crispy skin so that was bomb. Tea was strong and dark too, tieguanyin tea. TIP: If you come with large party, call ahead and order ahead so you dont have to wait for them to cook in the back.

Prawns with Rice. I ordered late and it was Delivered right away. Generous Portions. Rice is Dashed with Egg and Light Vegies. I was going to give a 4 star review. Because I couldnt believe there was no Soy Sauce or Napkins or Chop Sticks etc. with the Delivery. I just thought that goes unsaid. But Im Blaming myself, soo... 5 star Review. I cant eat much rice without soy sauce or Something. Fast and Friendly Service. Donny
Giant portions of dim sum. Best value for sure. Nice asian minority Hangout.

Great place for large parties - It s always best to make reservations so you can secure your spot! Highly recommend Pelican!

review_text: Still my familys go-to place. Weve had dim sum regularly, simple dinners to a $1000 dinner here. It is consistently good food Chinese food. Dim sum is simple here, not too many creative/different dishes, just the good old favorites. Serving size isnt Western-Lake-size (also really enjoy that restaurant) but quite fair for the price. Service is good, tea is filled timely, never felt rushed to eat. I dont understand complaints about sequential food delivery; when the kitchen finishes the dish, the servers get it out ASAP. Would you really rather have a dish sit under a heat lamp while waiting for another dish to be completed? Ambience is just a typical Chinese restaurant. Chairs show wear and washroom needs a renovation but its not the worst...
We thoroughly enjoyed our dining experience at this establishment. Excellent and authentic cuisine!

review_text: Used to go here all the time for dim sum.  Always knew it was good because my  chinese grandma goes to ALL the chinese places and weeds out the bad quality/deal places before taking me somewhere and this is a place wed always come back to if in the area.  Now that the pandemic is full bore and there is no in person dining I went and ordered dinner food for the first time and it was SO GOOD.  I dont even like sweet and sour pork but everyone said it was the best they ever had.  Everything was incredibly tasty and well done. The place doesnt look like much from the outside but those who know, know that this is one of the best places for chinese in Van.
Delicious late night eats! Open until 12 am, actually.

I booked my birthday at Pelican a few times in the past years. Both times were really great. Always loved the food and quality of seafood here. I recommend Pelican to those who love Chinese food in the Hastings area. Thanks to the manager who always took care of my bookings - he was awesome! I must come back soon.. maybe for dim sum this time

We go to this restaurant often and the food is always very good. They have a change table for children in the washroom which is huge! Not very many traditional Chinese food and dim sum restaurants offer washrooms with a change table and this has always been unfortunate for this parent who loves going out for dim sum or traditional Chinese food. Love it!

I ve been going for dim sum here since I was a little girl with my family and dinners for almost every birthday. Fresh, delicious food with great service. Dim sum is always a good price while dinner is more on the pricey side but it is well worth it!
Food is so satisfying! Make sure you sit near the back to get the full experience of all Santana music videos all the time.

review_text: I come here with my in-laws and husbands grandparents for Dim Sum because they are regular customers. We get VIP treatment, they know what we like to order and always get some of our dishes started before we get seated. Service is great! Staff is friendly and attentive. Highly recommend their cha sui bao and beef parsley congee.

Best Chinese food ever!! The waiters speak very little english. But they are still very accommodating. Based on food alone, this is the best place for chinese food. So tender, tasty, and perfect. I orderes the house special chow mein which was filled with big split prawns and white crab meat and large scallops. As well as the sweet and sour pork which was done perfectly and not chewy. As well as veggie mix that had my two year old asking for more broccoli. Absolutely love this place and definitely going back.

Pelican Seafood Restaurant has pretty good dim sum. It was my second or third time and the portions are big. Compared to San Francisco you would expect small bite size but here the hau gau and siumai are at least double the size. Everything tasted great and I would highly recommend it.
Awesome restaurant to be at for my dim sum! Serves the stuff I love all time of the day and the fish maw soup all day also!

The best part is getting to know the servers on an individual level, they are all so friendly and unique.....the OUTSTANDING SEAFOOD and ambience of a bustling beachside neighborhood is a bonus. The food is ABSOLUTELY worth coming here for.. BELIEVE ME....the oysters and everything else on the menu are 2DIE4...but its the service and waitstaff that makes this place truly unique and special. This place is definitely my go to spot for fresh seafood and oysters. Youll have a heck of a good time at Papis guaranteed!!!.

review_text: I recently visited Papi s Restaurant and can t say enough about our experience. We were fortunate to be seated on the patio for Happy Hour and the view was spectacular! We tried a selection of Oysters, the Prawn Arancini and Crab Cakes to start. Hands down some of the best crab cakes I ve eaten in Vancouver. We then shared a fish and chips for the main course. Wow! I m Australian and haven t found a place that makes fish and chips like the motherland until now. The batter was cooked to perfection, not too heavy and I really loved that they had two fish to select from. Huge shout out to the General Manager Dan for making our date night so special. I was surprised that a GM would personally serve our table but that is the vibe Papi s provides. It s not too big. You don t feel like a number. The service is so friendly and you won t leave disappointed. Highly recommend for a trip to the West End! Thanks Papi s!!

This place is fantastic. First of all, location is amazing. View of the water, view of the bustling city and vibrant life and many more. More than that,  the food are exceptional. We had their lobster roll, fried fish (can t remember the name, haha. Long ones for apples), fries, oysters and their seafood curry. It is to die for. If you like rich, exotic and full of flavour. This is a must! Have it with pasta or dip it in bread or eat it as is. Delisioso. The staff were on the younger demographic but they great. Very polite and easy to talk to. Would recommend this place to anyone looking for a place to lounge and drink or to have a feast. Will come again!

review_text: After doing just take outs and deliveries for almost a year, we finally decided to try dining in at Papis Seafood and Oyster Bar! Turned out to be a perfect restaurant to start the culinary experience at Vancouver.  The restaurant was perfect ambience with sunset views from the patio and amazing seafood.   I tried the fish tacos which were light and had light tangy flavour and then for the first time ever I tried a lobster roll.  I was not disappointed. The creamy buttery lobster with their secret sauce was finger licking good and went great with their cocktails, specially mezcal based drink called smoke and mirrors! Our server were friendly and patient.  Pro-actively checked on us and made sure we were enjoying our meal. Would definitely recommend this to everyone!

I headed straight to The Lobster Man for lunch upon reaching Granville island market. My wife and I ordered Signature and Connecticut lobster roll. I preferred the former while my wife preferred the latter. Both were so good. It s not a restaurant but more of a takeout place with some outdoor seating. I love it as it serves great lobster rolls without much fanfare and sitting outdoors in a casual environment is such an enjoyment. We visited the live seafood next door where we were keen to try the sea urchins. However, they don t cut the sea urchins for you so I decided it was too much hassle to cut it myself. It didn t look as delicious as ones I had in Hokkaido so am ok to give it a pass. Don t miss out on the lobster rolls though.

Live lobster, crab, and oysters are often considered some of the best options for seafood enthusiasts for several reasons: 1. Freshness: Live seafood is the epitome of freshness. When you order live lobster, crab, or oysters, you can be confident that youre getting seafood at its peak quality and flavor. 2. Flavor: Live seafood tends to have a more delicate and succulent flavor compared to seafood that has been frozen or stored for an extended period. The natural sweetness of these creatures is best preserved when they are alive until just before cooking. 3. Texture: The texture of live lobster and crab is exceptional. When cooked properly, the meat is tender, juicy, and full of natural juices, making it a delightful dining experience. Oysters, on the other hand, are prized for their unique texture and briny, oceanic taste. 4. Interactive Dining: Theres an interactive aspect to dining on live seafood. Preparing and cracking open a lobster or crab can be a fun and engaging experience, perfect for social gatherings and special occasions. It s really fun dining experience here in lobster man. Especially thank staff Sean. He provided exceptional service. He was attentive, friendly, and knowledgeable. Sean went above and beyond to ensure our dining experience was enjoyable. We appreciated his recommendations and the way he made us feel well taken care of throughout the meal. Thank you, Sean, for making our visit special!

I do have a shellfish allergy so I bet you are wondering why am I even reviewing this place? Well, if you walk past the sit-down restaurant, you come across fresh seafood; oysters, crabs, lobsters and mussels. Heck theyll even cook the lobster and crab for you! As you know, I love oysters and they are reasonably priced almost, a hidden gem. If you live in the area want, fresh seafood or  hosting a party this is the spot for you!

Can t speak much for their actual menu, but I ve ordered live lobsters from this place a couple times now and they have always been great. Their online ordering system works very smoothly, the lobsters are fresh and are always packed so securely that we were able to come via motorcycle to pickup our order (which we carried home in a backpack with no mess!) and the lobsters were still alive by the time we arrived home to steam them.

The lobster rolls here were too too good. The meat was so fresh that you could feel the softness in it. They could do better with their fries though, super oily and I somehow did not enjoy them. But a 5* for their rolls.

Cheap place to enjoy lobster! The seating is limited, but dont worry, as customers eat quickly and move on. If youre in the mood for oysters, theres a neighboring vendor; however, they dont offer dine-in options.

Great place to buy fresh seafood.  Went next door for the lobster roll.   Price has gone up since earlier this year.   Now it s $23 plus taxes, which is expensive it still very good.  Small outdoor patio. Great to bike to as you can have your bike close by.
If you love lobster, don t walk - run to Granville Island. We crave these lobster rolls on regular basis. They are SO FRESH and delicious. Make sure to get there before last call at 5:30pm!

The seafood here is so cheap! I brought back a bunch of clams and oysters for my family. I just called them the same day and they had everything ready for the airplane. My flight was delayed by many hours. But the seafood was still fresh and alive when I arrived back home. Everything was packed securely and appropriately. I had no issues bringing it. The seafood prices were really competitive.

We got the classic lobster roll and Manhattan clam chowder. They were both amazing! There s not a lot of seating but the meal isn t a large portion so by the time you ordered and got your food, a spot cleared up!

Nice lobster place at Granville Island! I got this simple, yet tasty lobster sandwich and went to eat it at the square near the Granville market. That little sit down with the lobster, the music and the sunshine made my entire day.

Lobster man, what a man. You can taste special creamy, fresh sandwiches with cruncky fries. Waiting line is long (maybe 20 minutes) but this is so worth it. Highly recommend when you go to Granville Island.
If you re craving a good lobster roll that this is the place to come in please order the Connecticut roll because it s truly the best!!

Lobster rolls were divine - both the signature (miso mayo) & connecticut (melted butter) were great. Dungeness crab roll had a bit too much sauce that the sweetness of the flesh couldnt stand out on its own. Manhattan clam chowder was yummy but very tiny portion. Get the live lobster/crab cooked on the spot if you can - absolutely worth it. Theyll even crack everything for you if you ask nicely. Pity oysters cant be shucked by them.

What a great meal! Prices are reasonable considering how much meat they put into the rolls. We got both the lobster and crab rolls. It s nicely toasted and dressed, compliments the sweetness of the meat. Love the outdoor seating but not a fan of it being so close to other businesses where they smoke cigarettes nearby. Parking available near the ferry docks and walking over.
If you visit Granville Island you have to try this lobster roll - it is famous for a reason! Great service and delightful food.

Im super happy that lobster man is finally selling  grab and go food!      We havent been to Granville Island for at least a year and we were so surprise to see the retail store was opened. Needless to say, the SUBs were goooooooood!!! Very delicious, and its super FRESH!  Juicy, tender, well seasoned, you name it! Clam chowder is good too, and we will definitely come back to try everything on your menu. Lol. Thats how good they are!

By far one of the best lobster roll in Vancouver! A must go if you re visiting Granville Island. The lobsters are sourced from the east coast as the meat is very tender and sweet! The Dungeness crab is quite good and savour

Got the Dungeness Crab Bun ($23). Very fresh and lots of real crab meat for the size of the bun. Super delicious, and the dill/celery combination compliments very well. Only con is it s a bit on the small side for the price.
These lobster rolls are Maritimer-approved. The brioche buns are VERY fresh and very good.
Had the Connecticut roll. It was delicious! Good amount of lobster and the flavor was very nice. The brioche bun was so yummy. Recommend this spot!
Each bite is a delectable blend of richness and freshness, making this sandwich a gourmet delight!

My go to place for lunch when visiting Granville Island. I love my seafood and this hits the spot when I want a lobster roll. Great place to visit with friendly staff. The price is reasonable and one order is quite filling. Highly recommended!

Visited Granville and had to try the lobster roll. Got the Connecticut lobster roll. Which was $25, which was a bit pricey. But the brioche bun, and butter lobster was worth it. It came with ruffle potato fries. Not much for seating so get it to go and find one of the many near locations to sit and enjoy. Also make sure to grab plenty of napkins, you will need them.

Enjoyed a dairy free lobster brioche roll. Mayo, lettuce, celery and good chunks of lobster! Outdoor seating next to the shellfish shop makes the experience even better. Crab and shrimp rolls also available.

Lobster Man is a must when in Granville island! We got some oysters and a steamed lobster. We brought our own corn and baby potatoes to eat with it. The staff are super kind and willing to help. Lobster gets steamed quickly and free of charge. Lemon and butter is available for pretty cheap as well.

First time at The Lobster Man and tried there specialty lobster roll and Connecticut lobster roll! AND BOTH were delicious! Would definitely come back for more and recommend anyone going to Granville Island to try it ! Chips were paired greatly with the rolls!
Good price and fresh oyster and lobster ! They dont open for oyster but you can buy oyster knife and easy to open it up. They do cook for lobster and cutting. Thx for perfect dinner :)

Stumbled upon this place while exploring Granville island and I got to say their lobster roll really hit the spot. Great use of fresh and delicious ingredients all mounted on a brioche bun served with a side of crisps which helps with finishing off the pieces of lobster that fall off while eating. 100% recommend

I got the signature lobster roll. I saw the staff pack 2 giant scoops to the rim in the bun...I was smiling ear to ear :D Nice, fresh, creamy with a few crunchy bite of celery in it yum yum yum yum yummy
Fresh lobster rolls which are excellently seasoned.  For the oyster lovers you can also purchase a variety of oysters which you can eat there for a fraction of the restaurant price.

The key part of this fabulous dinner meal was arriving at Granville Island, parking just in front of the entrance to The Lobster Man where live shellfish are readily available..this store has been a part of Granville Island community of businesses since 1977 and we have been longtime advocates of their focus on quality and sustainable..the staff are exceptionally helpful and very open to answer any questions..So purchasing our oysters was the first step, now we arrive home for a fabulous meal with warm French bread and fresh asparagus...the entire day was a great success...

Ignore the Haters, this place is great! Had the Manhattan clam chowder and the Signature Lobster Roll... Both were delicious! Ive made lobster rolls before and its a lotta work. The rolls are generous in portion and other than the miso Mayo (which I didnt really taste) they got the classic just right. Looking forward to trying the Dungy crab roll next time. The reviewer complaining about chives on the roll and foreign ownership... stay home, please. Soup was good too, just wished their cup was a little bigger. Small streetside patio which is great to enjoy when the weather is cooperative.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Tri, Thanks so much for your positive review! We appreciate your kind comments and were glad to see that you enjoyed the soup and our lobster roll. We look forward to seeing you again next time :)

review_text: I come here to buy their fresh oyster only. The quality has always been great and prices are reasonable. Royal miyagis are currently at $1.35 per piece if you buy a dozen and the oysters are sizeable. Parking is a pain at Granville Island but unless you are here for some walk, you can probably just park near the store and quickly buy some to go without paying.
wow, the cheap price with the most fresh lobster. They can cook for you if need. A wonderful place at Granville Island

Great place for lobster, crab, shrimp, oysters, clams and mussels. Tough to go wrong with $9.95 for a dozen oysters. The annual lobster boil is worth showing up for as well. If you are ever in a pinch you can pick up a freshly boiled container of lobster for a quick salad.
Great place to get oysters and other fresh seafood. My husband and I have been coming here for years to buy raw oysters and they are always fresh and delicious.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the great review! We appreciate your loyalty over the years and hope to see you again soon!

review_text: My whole trip was pretty much me saying, if only I lived in Vancouver. I would be at Lobster Man weekly. Go here, experience the Oysters and by golly take some home for me! I wish I could have! It was one of the coolest little crustacean markets Ive ever been to. Pro-tip: THEY DO NOT shuck oysters for you, so bring your own knife or purchase one at the store (I think it was $9).
Super expensive signature lobster roll... Worth every penny! Grab one of these and go sit by the water to enjoy it.
We ordered Signature lobster roll and Octopus salad, both of them are delicious!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Jean, thank you for sharing your positive feedback! Were so glad you gave us a try and hope to see you again soon.

review_text: Great quality lobster, generous serving, warm fresh brioche and balanced flavour!
Meal with the chips was very very tasty and didn t have to wait long at all! The server was really kind as well. This restaurant deserves the hype coming from tourist tiktok
response_from_owner_text: Hi Lean, we are so glad to hear that you enjoyed our food and had a great experience. We appreciate you sharing your feedback and hope to see you again soon!

review_text: The market next door is amazing for your fresh shellfish needs
This is a great place to buy some lobster, mussels and oysters Super nice and helpful stuff
If you want a variety of fresh clams, oysters, other seafoods, look no further. You wont regret. Highly recommend.
They cooked and cracked the crab for us as well. The amount of crab meat is incredible! I will definitely visit again!

Lobster rolls are ubiquitous on the east coast with varying price ranges depending mostly on location & presentation, sometimes upwards of thirty US dollars. The Lobster Man offers two distinct rolls, the Signature & the Connecticut, that offer significant value for flavour & presentation. Sure, theres some shredded lobster in the mayo, but its topped with generous chunks that almost require the use of the included fork. I ate mine without the fork & it was challenging & satisfying. The brioche bun is mildly sweet, soft, & fluffy. The included lemon & chips in the box make for easy take away. A moist towelette is included because this is hands-on comfort food! (update: prices have increased +30% in 2022)
I got the lobster roll for the first time, and it really blew me away. So delicious and its absolutely to die for!

I took a group of friends here for lunch as I hadn t seen them for quite some time. There were 10 of us and we all agreed that these were the best lobster rolls we had ever experienced. We also had the shrimp cocktail, that was incredible. Fresh beyond belief!  The service was so friendly and they couldn t do enough for you. I will definitely be back and so will the other 9. This place gets 10 out of 10 in all categories.

Id like to say a big thank you for being so friendly and welcoming. Theres plenty of places in Vancouver that are not but at Lobster Man, the ladies here we very kind and welcoming the moment I walked through the door and were happy to take my order. Thank you for that, its very refreshing. Dont ever lose that. As for the food, its amazing and so delicious. The Connecticut roll had me enjoying every last bite. I wish I could eat a whole bowl of that delicious lobster
The Connecticut lobster roll was so delicious! Seasoned and buttery, the perfect combo with chips!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Reema, thanks so much for the great review! We appreciate the feedback and hope to see you again soon.

review_text: Amazing service the food presentation was great and the taste OMG was to die for,  definitely we are going back thank you guys for the great job
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much Liliana! We really appreciate your feedback and am so happy you enjoyed it. We look forward to seeing you again soon!

review_text: Wonderful Connecticut lobster roll and crab roll. Both had a fair and reasonable amount of meat in them, and I appreciated the fresh brioche - the sweetness pairs well with the seafood. I prefer a bit less bread, so I just sliced off part of the roll lengthwise, leaving me with my ideal ratio of bread to meat. I also topped off both rolls with a bit more melted butter, but again, personal preference.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Jeff, Thank you for the positive review! We are glad you enjoyed your overall experience and have taken your feedback about the bread to meat ratio to heart. We hope to see you again soon!

review_text: Great selection of oysters. Lighthouse oysters were little bit hard to shuck, but my friends loved them.

Fresh, good prices and a wonderful selection. Staff are extremely helpful and polite. Parking and location easy. These folks are consistently pumping out some incredible products. Today in particular was an extremely delicious day where they had savory clams and some new oysters. Hats off Lobster Man for putting restaurants to shame and letting people enjoy high quality oysters at a great and reasonable price.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Tigran for the 5-star review and kind words. We really appreciate your support and hope to see you again soon!

review_text: You will find great fresh seafood here! Large variety of oysters!
Their lobster is always very fresh and delicious. I recommend this place..
freshest lobster sub! fresh from the ocean :)

Great spot to buy a great variety of oysters, clams and mussels. Lobster and crab galore which they will cook for you for take home. Next door they have tasty takeouts. We have never been disappointed by the quality of their seafood.
Excellent service ! We made the crab cook and we went to eat it at the Stanley park !
Fresh seafood, a lot different osyter to choose.  Friendly staff with good knowledge of their products. And sandwich is killer.

Easy online ordering process for pickup.  Pick your preferred crab weight.  Pick date and time of pickup.  Done! Plenty of free parking on Granville island.  Even on busy weekends.  Who knows how long the free parking will last? The prices are pretty good.  I m happy with the price.  Definitely cheaper than ordering a whole crab in a restaurant. It was handed to me in a plastic bag with a bag of ice but I live nearby so it wasn t a problem.  If you have to travel far, maybe ask about other packaging methods.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Michael, thank you for the detailed feedback! We re glad to hear that you enjoyed your overall experience. We also do have travel packaging options if you are ever travelling far. We hope to see you again soon and thanks for sharing some great pictures on social media!

review_text: Fresh seafood at very reasonable prices in the heart of Granville island.

Incredible experience at the Lobster Man today! New retail manager Shelly (I think that was her name) was so lovely, patiently helping me examine the sea urchin and finally handpicking some paradise oysters for me. Seeing as the seafood vendors inside the public market itself are marking everything up, this is the place to go to instead for all your shellfish needs! Super fresh and well priced, and top service. Ill be back as soon as I can!
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the feedback and positive review Iris! We re glad Shelley could help you and look forward to seeing you next time.

review_text: They boil lobsters and crabs for you if you want. Absolutely delicious and a great view eating outside!

We went into the new part of Lobsterman where they have lobster rolls, ready to eat shrimp cocktail and large assortment of frozen seafood. The lobster rolls are served in a brioche bun with some crispy potato chips on the side. Full of lobster meat, delicately seasoned so that you could taste the freshness of the lobster - it should be on everyone s list of things to eat while on Granville Island. There is a small outdoor area where you can sit to smell the ocean breezes while enjoying lobster rolls. The frozen seafood had a wide assortment of seafood and individual portions of frozen mahi mahi, salmon, black cod .  One would expect higher prices with the outstanding quality of the seafood here , but they are lower or at par as any grocery store. Will definitely be back!

The food is good and one of the employees there were sooooo friendly and nice! She had brownish reddish hair? My only regret is not giving her more tips anyways this place is goooood + [Edited] I went again to see her cause my friend was interested in her but apparently she quit    so sad  he wanted to get her number next time we come but he never did

Purchased a cooked and cracked Atlantic lobster through their online website. It was ready for pickup at the requested time (literally just boxed) and I was able to prepay for it online. The quality was amazing and the cracking was impeccable (I didnt need any tools to dig right into it!). I would definitely order from here again. Painless and hassle-free!
Small little shop, simple uncomplicated food with high quality ingredients

This place is HEAVEN for seafood lovers! They have spot prawns, lobster, crabs, scallop, oysters, etc. Fresh and reasonably priced, best of all, steaming service for free! Planning on an memorable picnic or potluck near Granville Island or the seawall? Come pick a lobster or crab and have them help you cook before you go! Highly recommend!
The crab roll was delicious and the staff pleasant and customer focussed.
Truly fresh swimming Lived Canadian Lobsters indeed
Fresh and delicious. I always buy a lobster and let the store crack and cook for me to take home.

I can trust the quality because I can choose by myself. If you want to get steamed lobster, you need to go before 4:30. ( Strongly recommended! Its very convenient, and even its free ) That service will be provided for crab and lobster but shellfish are not.
One of the best lobster rolls I have ever had!

Had a great lunch of 24 oysters today. Sure I had to buy an oyster knife and learn how to shuck them myself but I had a great time and made some memories. Yes i had to pay for the knife I needed but I still got a great deal, 24 oysters and a souvenir for about C$30 is a bargain
Had awesome scallops (frozen) and fresh oysters from here!
Really Enjoyed the Lobster Roll
Good selections of West coast and east coast oysters for descent price. Cheaper if buy in dozens. Also have live crabs and lobsters which they can cook on site for free.  Friendly staffs.
Fresh boiled lobster with good price and kind staff
Tried their live oyster, bought a dozen back for $18 and shuck it myself, super fresh and cheap. Not to be missed if you are there

Went there on Canada Day for Lobster. Had to wait in line but totally worthy it. Oh my, the best. Fresh with great price. Just need to prepare to get dirty with your hands. I took the shell home to make soup.
We loved it!
The Lobster Man is always a 1st priority goto when we visit Vancouver. Always order the Connecticut Lobster roll....PERFECTION !
I always bought fresh oyster and scaloops here everytime I visit Granville island .And also the signature lobster roll its awesome
Fresh seafood, be patient with the staff, theyll give you great service if you just be more clear on what you want.
We picked up the most delicious oysters yesterday for $1.25 each. If you want oysters at home this is the place to pick them up!
Valuable abd fresh oyster
Best lobster I ve tried so far, ingredients are fresh and well served. Totally recommended

review_text: The Lobster Man was Delicious!
Always have fresh shellfish.. I also love how you can order love pre boiled lobster. Best picnic idea
Delicious lobster rolls, one of the best place in Vancouver

Aprils Aquarium has become a mecca for the planted Aquarium hobby. I cant  say enough good things. They regularly order unique and interesting fish. Their team is surprisingly knowledgeable. The experience has improved since the two locations merged. Having all the live stock in one location is convenient. Ive been very happy with aquarium coop products, and the wide selection of hardscape. They stand by their product warranties. Lastly, Aprils aquarium treats their fish with great care. They score big points on quality. The fish they sell are well fed and healthier than Im used too. I havent had any issues with diseases. They are the only store I know of that quarantines all of their fish before selling it.

review_text: This is an incredible aquarium store, highly recommend! Over the last few months Ive been building a 55 gallon aquarium for my 21-year old Red Eared Slider. Every employee there is really knowledgeable about aquarium care. Although I wasnt there to buy fish, the principles are all pretty much the same for my turtle, and I was able to get all the necessary decorations, chemicals, and materials to make the perfect home for my turtle. I also ordered my aquarium stand from them at a great price compared to other stores, and they hand-delivered it to me within the week! I felt particularly grateful for that, because I did not have the strength to carry that item myself, and I was already a bit stressed about that. They took the worry right out of my hands. Not to mention...it was free! I also had one of the employees teach me about improving the flora in my aquarium, and advised me on some good decorations that would not just be pretty, but support the health of the tank. Since Ive done the recommendations, my tank is healthier than it has ever been, and it requires less maintenance compared to before. Every time I go into the store I learn a bunch of new things! I always enjoy going to Aprils Aquarium. Not just because its fun to look at the fishes and browse the goods, but because the service is truly top notch. I highly recommend it for all your aquarium needs! Thank you!

Even further back, they have beautifully aquascaped display tanks designed by Aquarium Co-op (they have partnership with them). These tanks are works of art! The times I ve been there, they ve had calming piano music playing. The atmosphere in the store is peaceful, kind, and friendly, and all the staff I ve spoken with so far seem like true fish nerds and are very knowledgeable. Highly recommended checking this place out if you haven t yet!

review_text: I recently had the pleasure of visiting Aprils, a hidden gem nestled in metro Vancouver. This aquatic emporium is a true haven for aficionados of the aquatic realm, offering a mesmerizing array of tropical fish, shrimp, snails, and aquatic flora that left me utterly captivated. From the moment I stepped foot into Aprils, I was struck by the vivacious hues that danced through the tanks like an aquatic symphony. The kaleidoscopic variety of species showcased was a testament to the meticulous curation undertaken by the stores proprietors. Their dedication to sourcing exotic species from distant aquatic domains is evident, as evidenced by the unique assortment of freshwater creatures on display. What truly sets Aprils apart is their dedicated staff, whose expertise and passion in matters of aquatic husbandry are second to none. They tailor their advice to my specific tanks needs, ensuring a harmonious cohabitation of my newfound aquatic companions. Their sagely insights into the intricacies of maintaining a thriving aquatic ecosystem were both illuminating and indispensable. Moreover, the ambiance within Aprils is a delightful departure from the commonplace. The aquatic tableau is complemented by an ethereal soundscape, evoking the tranquil cadence of waves lapping against distant shores. The interplay of chromatic gradients and the rhythmic gurgle of well-maintained filtration systems coalesce to create an immersive aquatic sanctum. As a connoisseur of the rare and exceptional, I was thrilled to discover Aprils unparalleled selection of aquascaping merchandise. Their inventory extends beyond the ordinary, featuring a plethora of artifacts that range from the arcane to the avant-garde. These treasures enabled me to cultivate an aquatic ecosystem that is both visually pleasing and ecologically harmonious. In summary, my journey to Aprils was an experience tantamount to traversing an aquatic wonderland. Their peerless assortment of tropical fish, combined with their well informed staff and serene ambiance, renders this establishment an unmissable destination for both new aquarists and seasoned enthusiasts alike. The piscine wonders that await within Aprils are a testament to the stores dedication to providing an extraordinary aquatic experience that is, quite simply, unparalleled. Best selection, best prices, best fish store in Vancouver.
