review_text: Great shop! The tissues cultures I ordered shipped fast and are in great condition. Will be shopping here again :)
response_from_owner_text: Maia, Thank-you very much for making the time to provide a top notch review of our services. We really do value your business and support and of course we hope to hear from you again very soon @yourlocalfishstore

review_text: Great online service.  They have good prices and they went above and beyond to make sure my order arrived promptly and correct.  I will definitely be ordering from here again  : )
response_from_owner_text: Thank-you sir for the very kind and rewarding review we do appreciate it very much. Please visit us again soon online or even better in person , if you are ever in Vancouver pop by and say hi we are very close to the Airport. Thanks for all your support, cheers  yourlocalfishstore

review_text: Good customer service and knowledge. Its an added comfort to know that staff are knowledgeable with the livestock they offer. Ive only been in the hobby for a few months and very likely Ill be doing more business here.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Ron, Thank-you for your excellent review and your kind words. We hope of course to see you again very soon @yourlocalfishstore

review_text: Recently ordered plants. Healthy and happy. Have placed orders in the past, and look forward to many future orders.
response_from_owner_text: Lisa, thank-you so much for the 5 stars and your support. We are delighted you are happy with our services and of course we hope to hear from you again soon @yourlocalfishstore

review_text: Amazing store with a lot of options for nano aquariums.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Jessica for the fantastic review we do try our best and we are delighted with your valued comments . Thanks for all your support and hope to see you again very soon @yourlocalfishstore cheers

review_text: Purchased some plants, shrimp and substrate as apart of the delivery order to west Kelowna! Everything is absolutely amazing and the whole process was very smooth and saved me having to drive farther (40+) minutes or even to Aprils Aquarium which is a 3hr drive from me! I only had to drive about 5 minutes which is always nice to have this option and all the items they carry in a more local setting. Attached is a picture of all the plants, shrimp and substrate that was purchased!
response_from_owner_text: Kaitlyn - we are delighted you are happy with the service and quality of our livestock it s what we drive for and your very positive review just enforces that. Hope to see you again on our next road trip. If your ever in Vancouver we are near YVR so pop in say hello. Cheers and thanks again .

review_text: Fantastic experience, availability of products hard to find here in Canada (aquarium co-op products particularly), super fast shipping and good prices.  Ill definitely shop here again!
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Derrick for the fantastic review sir. Yes we are the sole retail partner in Canada for Aquarium Co-Op Premium Products, so no problems now on availability for you.  We pride ourselves in customer service and that includes fast shipping / fair pricing and of course  any issues or concerns we have you covered. Thanks for all your supprt and of course we hope to hear from you again very soon @yourlocalfishstore

review_text: My first experience buying fish online. I visited the old Burnaby location under previous management and had mixed reviews. I am a dedicated loach keeper (since 2013) and saw dwarf chain loaches available in Vancouver. Incredibly good communication.Ordered online and couldnt sign in.  And then a Scottish man showed up at my house asking if I had a snail problem. So much more polite than asking if I have a loach problem.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Shessa, Thank-you so much for the glowing review. We do try our best and glad you are happy about  our overall offering. Yes on the snail problem :-) of course chainloaches are infamous for eating ramshorn snails etc. so thought that was why you were buying them having a loach problem is also good you know were we are :-) Thanks for all your support and hope to hear from you soon @yourlocalfishstore. cheers

review_text: Fantastic establishment with great customer service! Darrin was so friendly and super helpful and patient with all my questions. They have a great selection of products and I was able to get all the supplies I needed and it was shipped to me in Edmonton so quickly, which I greatly appreciated! I ll definitely make sure to come back for any of my aquarium needs. :)
response_from_owner_text: Thanh, fantastic, great ,super helpful, patient , great, quickly . Wow so many positive adjectives we just love it , thank you so much for the fantastic review and of course your valuable business. Hope to hear from you again soon Thanh @yourlocalfishstore   cheers

review_text: Tried one of each of the 8 different oysters that were available. They were all so good although I was gravitating towards the briny ones. Sean executed them well on the plate by placing them in the order as the menu so we d know which variety we were eating. The fresh prawn cocktail were huge and meaty and the fried oyster were so crunchy and delicious. Fries were perfectly crunchy. I love the cozy environment and the window seat is great for eating and people watching. I will definitely be back.  Highly recommend.
Such a great little spot. The staff is super friendly and knowledgeable and the oysters are super fresh. Always a great selection and the space is a great vibe!

Came here for the oysters and it didnt disappoint. We had the special oyster of the day which was discounted to $2.50 each. It came with the full complement of different toppings to accompany the oysters. Needless to say we couldnt stop at only 1 dozen..
Delicious & fresh oysters. Lovely little shop that specializes in oysters and does it so well. Knowledgeable and sweet staff. The small space aids in the charm so I recommend making a rezo.

Coziest little oyster bar ever! I dont know if it seats more than a dozen people, but I am glad I was one of them last week. Top class fresh oysters, usually 6-7 varieties to choose from. The raw shucked are outstanding - the shucker is a master. We had 2 dozen raw and each was a work of shucking art - each oyster perfectly separated from its shell, undamaged in any way. And with the liquor intact. That is some skill. Hats off! Oh, and the homemade chili-vodka condiment? Inspired! The fried oysters were big meaty west coasters, perfectly crispy, juicy. I want to go back with a bigger group, so we can try them all. Big thanks to the owners - such nice people

Always love visiting here. Has such quiet charm and the oysters are always delicious. On my visit they were offering 5 different types of Oyster. My favorite was the Sannich Bay Oyster. But all were tasty.

If youre in Chinatown and crave oysters THIS IS THE PLACE TO GO. Ive been here a number of times over the last 5 years and havent been disappointed. The oysters are fresh and service is genuine. They usually have a handful of different types and can describe them to you. Fresh shucked in the restaurant. Plated on a bed of ice with grated horseradish. Cocktail sauce, Mignonette sauce, chili water served along side. They have happy hour!!
The oysters were so fresh, tasty and smell of the sea. All the food we ordered was excellent and enjoyed by all. Small menu means the quality is excellent.

Fresh & delicious oysters!! Can t compare with other oyster restaurants for this quality and service! Oyster shucking skill is one of the best I ever seen at the restaurant - clean & not damaging oyster meat. Highly recommend!
Wonderful! Came for a quick hh before dinner and had the hh oysters. No frills spot (think dive bar) with great service and delicious fresh ones.

A hidden gem! Great option for a spur-of-the-moment, very casual dining experience. The pair that runs it are great: theyre personable & enthusiastic about oysters. Everything is always fresh & portion sizes are good. Fairly simple menu but I mainly go for the oysters anyways! Always tempted to stop by when Im in the neighborhood or passing by :)

DAMMM!!!! I finally came here and love the happy hour!  I got two dozen fresh oysters, fries, and I especially love the deep fried oysters!!!   Cool place to chill and have a alcoholic beverage, or a 100!!!

Their oysters are always so fresh and plump! Love the $1.50 happy hour deal pre-covid, now post-covid dine-in at $2. Had nanoose bay and pink pearl today. The pink pearls were HUGE - fresh, plump, sweet, and a great deal even outside the daily happy hour price. The staff is knowledgeable and they rotate the daily oysters so you get to try different kinds on different days. Their sides are also yummy, especially yam fries. They pair so well with oysters. My go-to spot for oysters in Vancouver 10/10!
The best place for oysters... The seafood Argentinian shrimps are amazing, the best chicken wings my favorite its delicious  .... Fine dining Best service I highly recommend come

Weve been coming to Oyster Express for over 10 years. It is by far my favorite place for oysters - other establishments cannot compare to Oyster Expresss freshness and selection, not to mention the care the owners put into their craft. The restaurant is small and intimate and is run by a really lovely couple (Shawn and Soran). They always provide stellar service and are very genuine for the support their customers provide them. Weve always had a great time! Continue the great work!

5 . Five ! Five stars ! What a delightful little not so hole in the wall on the wrong side of town place. On the edge of china town which would seem like the middle of no where, then you walk in  woot woot woot oyster heaven , served up by a duo shucker and server, fried oysters were crispy and yet so juicy and the half shell selection was delightful fresh and came with the expected accoutrements. For a little hole in the wall Oyster bar on the edge of town. Chinatown. I didn t want to leave. Fresh beer and an interesting take on the bubbly. Love this place.
This is an extraordinary little  place full of energy and good vibe. A nice variety of oysters in the heart of China town. The staff is so friendly. It is a nice stop in the area

Oysters were very fresh and clean with comfortable environment! Good place to talk with your bestie. Me and my friend went there yesterday and each of us ate approximately 20! We ordered white wine as well, perfect match! They also offered few sauces for your own table that you can choose. Price is reasonable and good service! I left my key on Sunday and unfortunately they closed on Monday. I was so frustrated the whole night. I tried to massaged them through google map which I won t expect to receive prompt responses. However, The owner (I think he is the owner) replied my massaged the next day morning, and he was so nice and helpful, he went back to the restaurant to pass me the key on the day suppose to be closed. It was a great experience, so I bought two drinks for him and his wife as a gift for doing all this. Hahahahahha highly recommend that you to go there! Try the fresh and affordable fresh oyster!

Take out only for now. Extremely well packed, fresh and delicious oysters, reasonable prices (around $2-4 per), highly recommend! They pack their oysters in a plastic take out container, already shucked. Top of the oyster shell still there to cover the oyster for freshness. Oysters sat on top of a pack of ice in Ziploc bag. Condiments and lemons included as well. Must try if you like oysters and youre in the Chinatown area!!
Amazing spot! Oyster Varieties galore! Best prawn cocktail and a great room.
Freshest and cleanest oysters Ive had     Warm and attentive service    Was able to fit our baby stroller during down time. Highly recommend this hidden gem!
Amazing, we ordered 3 dozen oysters shucked to go.. and he politely obliged.. took great care of us and then we went down to beach and ate them all. Thank you so much! Love the Effinghams!!
Loved this place. Great service down to how well the oysters are shucked. Great happy hour specials.

Love the raspberry oysters so much. The house made vodka with pickled chilli sauce match great with the oysters yet wont cover the original salty and ocean flavour of the oysters. Wild catch prawns cocktails was amazing too. Mild sweetness which stay for a long time in your month. Also the bouncy and soft texture is different from the others prawns I had.
Delicious and fresh oysters, shucked to order. Small bar with a relaxing atmosphere.
Easially the most lit oyster experience you can ask for. They have an assortment of lit oysters, the sauces are on fire. The flavors are memorable.
Family owned oyster bar . The place is small in chinatoen . The couple has run the business for 10 years , a lovely couple . The oysters are very fresh , will definitely recommend friends here .
Great place run by a couple who are clearly passionate about their restaurant. The menu is small but thats almost a good thing, because everything on it is excellent. Highly recommended!
Great little oyster spot. Chef really knows how to shuck. $1.50 special is a great deal. Usually a very good selection of oysters from both coasts. A gem. One of my Vancouver favorites.
Great oysters and value during their happy hour. Love the location and the feel inside. Good selection and good at what they do. Always a great place to start before dinner out.
Fresh oysters, good varieties and service. We came for happy hour this time and have 30 oysters for 2 people.  $1.5 each medium size Pink Pearl Oyster ~ totally satisfied!!
super fresh delicious oysters.  we had Kussui  oysters and Gorge Inlet oysters.  Both kinds of oysters are great to eat.  Come and enjoy the oysters.

Cozy little place but what else do you need in a oyster bar.  Aside from the specials which are quite satisfactory nonetheless, I do recommend trying some oysters from other places since they are usually not available elsewhere.
Friendly service, fresh oysters with variety source locally and from east coast. Note they mainly serve oysters and not much else but beer and some pub food.
Very cute place with a lot of choices for oysters. The service was great and food was amazing as well
Fresh oysters, shuck to order, friendly staff, different menu for oysters. IMO, West coast oysters are tastier. Go during happy hour 5-7pm
Amazing place with incredible owners. If you want the best oysters in Vancouver this is the place to be. Master shucker !! Drool worthy hot food especially the wings.
Phenomenal oysters and great vibes, will be back again soon!

Enjoyed 2 dozen oysters of 4 varieties, all were fresh and expertly shucked. The white wines were amazing, I sampled 3 varieties and all were excellent choices that would please many pallets. For those not into raw oysters, the fried oysters, soy chicken wings and fries were all hot, crispy and well seasoned! Already planning a trip back with girlfriends :)

We love this little hidden gem in Chinatown, near Science World. The fried oysters are to die for, and the mussels are great too! We were going quite regularly before Covid and have been doing takeout since. The quality of the food is always amazing, and the owner is super friendly and welcoming. Definitely one of my go-tos in the city and a must-try!
Excellent fresh oysters and welcoming service. Well done.

Best Oyster place in BC. -The best condiments (the flavored vodka is amazing) -The best service, its only a 2 people business, husband & wife, and you can tell they are so passionate about everything they are doing. -Prices are amazing, lower than other oyster places and most other restaurants, oysters or not. -Small memu, but EVERYTHING is absolutely delicious If you love oysters in any way, do yourself a favor and come here. PS: Excellent spot to bring your date, haha.

Friendly and intimate place for tasty and fresh oysters! Happy hour(s) a must. My wife and I tried both raw and fried and were thoroughly impressed. The yam fries also went down well. I really can t fault this place!
Amazing hidden gem. One of the few spots in town for top tier oysters shucked perfectly. May have had my favourite oyster of all time
Omg, I ended up ordering 40+ pieces of oysters. I have to save up some to come here, can t resist their amazing oysters. Sand dune was amazing!!!! Oh, don t forget to try fried oysters too!!
Friendly staff, nice place with a wholesome environment. The oysters are also quite good. Food
Great server, very fresh and properly shucked oysters. Hot pepper infused vodka on the table! Wow.
Fresh plump oyster! Highly recommend.
Great service and most of all super fresh oysters. We will definitely be back again and again- if only we live in Vancouver! This place is a gem.

Oyster expert. In the time I was here I watched three groups sit down, look at the menu, and say they were hoping for more options. They re missing the point. This place is giving you exactly what they promise: amazing oysters.
This is my go to for fresh delicious oysters for many years. The quality shows as the owner handpicked each one  ... excellent service and we like its cozy ambient too.

Cozy and delicious.  The menu is not very expansive, but what they do, they do well.  They serve great Asian style chicken wings and a fabulous grilled cheese for those who are not oyster lovers.  Friendly, knowledgeable staff.  I am not a fan of oysters, yet I eat there at least once a month.  Well worth a visit.

My fiancee and I went there last night for the first time and had a great time! We like oysters but dont really know too much about them so we were really in their hands. Shawn and his team definitely had us covered. They took their time with us, really explaining the differences and recommending oyster pairings. The wealth of knowledge that they have and share is incredible. It really feels like youre getting a tailor made made experience in a warm, cozy and friendly place. The selection of oysters is great too, with lots of varieties to choose from from both the east and west coast. The cherry on top...they played Al Green in the background. We will definitely be going back and would highly recommend this place to anyone, whether youre an oyster officianardo or novice.

WOOT! Cheap oysters, beer and close to Downtown? I am totally in! Came here after work with a close friend and had a beer with fresh oysters. The place used to be a Chinese Bookstore, and sold random Asian junk from time to time and it was a DVD store after that. The place has been renovated into a brand new restaurant with new wood inside, keeping it simple and a great layout. The oysters that are served here change daily, from what I heard. We ordered 4 dozen of daily oysters and finished it all in an hour. The shucking skills of the chef are amazing, because I didnt find a chipped shell in my oysters. The waiter that was serving us is a cutie too. He was easy on the eyes and had a British accent. He was attentive and very kind to us. Enjoyed his companion for a while :)
One word Oyster! Fresh, good, price good, small friendly restaurant.
Great quality and nice selection of oysters on the half shell, friendly efficient service, warm atmosphere: I would certainly recommend.
Delicious fresh oysters. We came for happy hour and got a great deal on oysters of the day at 1.95 a piece. Maybe the best oysters Ive ever had. Quaint, and friendly service. Cant wait to come back!

Im very new to the oyster world, so a friend took me here to sample some different varieties. The waiter described the origin and flavour of a few oysters and made some recommendations. They also had daily specials, which were quite reasonable. Theyre fully licensed as well - we had a couple beers Parking can be a challenge. The area is fairly dense and its mostly metered parking, or some pay lots nearer to Main St.

We ordered 12 of the pink pearl and the 12 of the raspberry and the quality was excellent.  We ordered for take out and it came in two take out containers with separate containers for horse radish, seafood sauce, and vinegar (I believe).  This final price was a little pricy $69.30 but overall it was worth it.
This place is amazing!! So worth the wait. The oysters taste fresh and amazing. The happy hour of the best Ive ever gone too. Definitely have to check it out!

Only been here once but the wait staff was great, helpful in decoding the oyster selection, service was good. The oysters were super tasty. And I guess the only review that matters when reviewing an oyster bar is, no one got sick... We had no problem finding a seat during happy hour and they oyster special was our favourite.
Wonderful staff, delicious oysters, amazing ambience. The $1.50 happy hour is a great deal, but the other oysters are well worth trying as well. Plan on becoming a regular.
Fresh oysters at a decent price. Lots of selections and friendly staff.  One daily special each day.  Nice cozy atmosphere. Good place to hangout and bring guests from out of town.

Chinatowns best kept secret. This little hole in the wall offers the best, most fresh oysters in the city. Friendly to those who are not very knowledgeable of oysters - staff has all the info you need. Also, menu ever-changes, so be sure to look at the board for pointers.
Delicious mix of oysters served by a fun team
This place has the best oysters in town with great service. Expect some wait during happy hours if you like to order in small batches but otherwise this is the oyster shack you want to eat at.

Best fresh oysters in town with great selection and shucking skills! Love raw oysters?! This is the place to go!!!  Great service! Fresh! Yummy!!! My favourite oyster bar!! Clam chowder is soooo Good!!! Must order!!!
Love this place. Best oyster selection and shucking in the city. Hands down. Great price, great quality.  Also the wine list is phenomenal. Staff is great too!  Hidden gem.

Yes yes yes! Amazing prices for delicious oysters! Im abit of an oyster connoisseur,  eaten them all over the world and this is a great valueand fun for friends. Dont worry about the location,  its a must visit.
Amazing jewel oyster restaurant in the middle of Chinatown. Well worth the visit especially during happy hour. Fresh high quality oysters, good selection of draft beers, well trained stuff.
Very good, fresh oysters! knowledgeable waitress! Went for their happy hours! Quality and price so much better then Yaletown Rodney oysters!
My favourite spot for oysters. Great food, good price and friendly staff. Oysters are always fresh. I really like their chicken wings.
Fantastic oyster house! Super fresh and awesome value! hard working  owner and the staff are extremely nice. One of my favourites in Vancouver. a definite Gem!
Great food and service as usual! Fresh, perfectly prepared oysters and succulent chicken wings. Paired with a nice white wine.

I first came here was in 2014, recently I came back to Canada living and I cant believe the oyster bar is still here, food, quality, friendly and everything is  awesome, I will keep to support this bar.

My favourite place for raw oysters in Vancouver.  The owner is very passionate about oysters and maintains a large and constantly varying selection.  Great place to hang out, drink, and slurp back very fresh oysters.
Great oysters without the pretentious vibe (hard to find in Vancouver). Great happy hour. Super friendly and accommodating.
The quality of the oysters was fantastic!

Tucked away at an inconspicuous corner at the edge of Chinatown, this homely little haunt is an oyster aficionados heaven. When we visited, the board boasted 10 types of oysters, featuring a wide selection of oysters harvested locally, on the east coast ( from Prince Edward Island) to even overseas. The oysters are lovingly served with a side of fresh horseradish, lemon and an assortment of homemade and bottled sauces. Star of the night were the Kaipara flown in overnight from New Zealand, simply sublime. The steamed muscles were sizeable, steeped in a rich creamy broth complemented by fresh onions that added some crunch to the taste. Perhaps the only disappointment was the freshly shuckled live sea scallop from Qualicum, BC. At $7 a pop I was expecting fireworks, but the taste was slightly underwhelming.
Nice service, no fragments or silt in the oysters at all, fresh, delicious, and fairly priced. Well worth it to come here!
I m obsessed!!
Hands down my favourite oyster joint. Hole in the wall with SO MUCH GOODNESS. Great service, solid music, quality oysters and great prices!
If you love fresh oysters this place never disappoints.
Lots of oyster options! Happy hour is worth it!!! Good service! Love the raw oyster, steamed mussels and prawn cocktails!!!!
Fresh and delicious oysters came prepared to eat. Great experience ordering on the phone and reliable delivery.
I was so happy to eat oyster here. So fresh and sweet. We couldnt help but slurped down a dozen in just a few minute!! Well be back for sure!
My favourite food place as of 2 weeks ago. Can t believe I ve never been there before. Really good fresh oysters and more.
One of my fav spots in Chinatown area !! Oysters are great deal and tasty.  Wonderful staff, delicious oysters, amazing ambience.
Gorgeous little spot. Great happy-hour specials. Wonderfully friendly and patient staff. Happy hour gets packed, so, avoid it or be early. Stay for a few hours, its cozy.
The best oysters in Vancouver by far! Great selection of oysters, awesome local beers, and the best happy hour around (5-7PM daily)!
Incredible experience. I highly recommend Oyster Express if you just want the good stuff. Oysters, drinks, and an amazing setting.
Great variety of fresh tasty oysters, knowledgeable pleasant staff.
If you want great oysters without little pieces of shell in them like most other places, this is it!
Delicious oysters during happy hour. Cocktail sauce is the best. Will definitely come back!
Fantastic oysters. Great service. You really cant ask for more in a place. Cozy and welcoming.
Oyster Express is where I take visiting friends and myself when I need a treat. Perfect oysters! Attentive and knowledgeable servers.
Really great oysters, wings and chowder. Highly recommend. Will order again soon!
Small little place, great oysters :) Friendly service and good wine selection.
Excellent quality oysters and service alike. Area may be a little sketchy for some people though.
Amazing place, great service well priced oysters and friendly staff. Great Value!!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Update: price has gone up at least 25-35% last month. Still reasonable I think Delicious!! Fish batter was thin, light and crunchy. Everything so fresh. 1 piece combo includes fries and soup for $7. $5.5 if you don t need soup. 2 pieces combo for $10 Cash only I believe
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much. Yes, the price is absolutely legendary. Please come back soon for more. Youve seen the small boss. God knows how much longer she can last doing it day in day out at her old age!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: This place is amazing. Great prices and tasty fish and chips. The batter is light, crispy and sticks to the fish. Every bite of fish had a bite of crispy batter. The batter didn t fall off the fish like many places. Not to mention the fish was super moist. Chips were good and slaw was nice and tangy. What a nice meal to end the week !
response_from_owner_text: Wow! Fantastic review, thank you so much

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Hidden gem for fish and chips. Great deal on high quality halibut. The fish is fresh, thick, moist inside with a crispy layer outside. House cut fries and homemade tartar sauce were amazing! Best part, they value providing high quality food such as using Canadian made vegetable oil as opposed to canola oil, which greatly impacted the flavour and didnt make the texture overly greasy. Friendly, respectful and kind service at this family run restaurant.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the awesome review!! Come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: A great unassuming fish and chips place that my husband and I happened to come across. The interior is pretty basic and nothing to write home about, but the food was delicious and service quick. I got the halibut which was fried to perfection - crisp on the outside, juicy on the inside. The fries and coleslaw were also fantastic though I would ve liked a bit more slaw because it was so good. Husband got the regular fish (we re assuming cod) which was also delicious and cheaper than halibut. He got the chowder with his combo which lacked salt but was an easy fix and would be good for those trying to be mindful of their salt intake. We were the only customers for a while on a Tuesday at lunch so you wouldn t have to wait long if you re in a rush. We will definitely be back!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much, Mindy! Fantastic. Please come back for more soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: I was super impressed by this place and almost cried for the quality and price. How can this be so cheap but tasty?? The combo is less than $7 and it includes fish, chips, seafood chowder soup, coleslaw, mayo sauce, ketchup. And one of the staff approached to me and asked how the food is. I can see that they are so caring of customers. Everything was great, but the greatest one was seafood soup. I was really craving for a cream soup, and I was fully satisfied with this soup. The French fries were ordinary though. The black coffee was instant one but it was only $1.5, so I liked it. I will visit again for sure !!!
response_from_owner_text: Hello Vero Vero, thank you so much for your honest and heartfelt review. We are very humbled. We have been frying fish and chips the old way for almost three decades. Same price, same quality and same heart. Thank you and please come back soon. We are getting old and dont know how long we will last. One dish and one day at a time we go.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: This place is not at all fancy, but it has the best fish and chips Ive found in Vancouver. The crust was beautiful and crispy, while the fish was perfectly cooked on the inside. Not at all over-cooked and dry. It was perfect.
response_from_owner_text: You are the best. Thank you, sir!!!!!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Stunned by the hospitality of the aged owner from Hong Kong, reminds me of those family-own chippy in London, UK (always forget there s London in Canada). The hand cut chips are sooo great and sadly no fresh halibut until summer. Batter is thin and just right. And they have malt vinegar! If there s HP sauce I would be more than delighted. Will definitely come back and chat with them.
response_from_owner_text: Yes, sir, please come back soon for more!! You review is awesome!!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Cash only. Greeted at the door. A nice friendly family run restaurant. Double sided menu. Good sized portions. Great prices. Good location with parking lot. Fish is lightly battered, non oily or greasy. Back of the menu, I had 2 pieces of fish and chips. It came with a glass of water, individual dish of tartar sauce. The front of the menu 2 pieces of fish and chips with soup of the day or can of pop and coleslaw.
response_from_owner_text: Great that you enjoyed your meal. Thank you.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Visited this place for the very first time last week( despite living in the neighborhood)and Ill have to agree this is the right place for me to enjoy a good lunch with friends or even all by myself ...fish is so crispy and only lightly battered... generous portion of french fries....plus the cole slaw is excellent also...Oh it comes with a bowl of clam chowder too ....all for a reasonable price of $14.95. For sure will come back more often!
response_from_owner_text: Fantastic! Come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Exceedingly reason pieces, like a flash back to 15 years ago. Excellent quality of fish and shockingly fresh (I watched them bread and fry it infront of me). Go spend your money here!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for your appreciation. Awesome pics, too!!!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Excellent quality fish for far cheaper than anywhere else. I got the fish burger. On its own, it was rather plain, but I added a little dill ranch dressing and it was fantastic. Also, the fries needed salt, but just add salt yourself. The cokeslaw was better than pretty much everywhere I have gone. Where else are you going to get a good quality fish burger and fries for $8.50? Most places that I know are twice that price.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for the awesome review!!!!! Come back for more soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: A great low key small local restaurant for my craving for fish and chips. Haha. They only take cash, but the amount and quality of food is phenomenal. One order of 2-piece fish and chips is only about $8. We had a full table of food for only $39. Lovely Cantonese speaking ladies always smile and say thanks. Will definitely come back.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much! Please come back soon.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: My neighbour recommended this restaurant. Price is excellent, fish was juicy. Fries, clam chowder and coleslaw were also good.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much. Please come back for more soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Truly a hidden gem of a small fish and chips diner on Kingsway...Water, menu, condiments and ordering of the food were ready and available within minutes. The lunch combo fish was lightly battered and cooked to perfection! And to my delight, the senior woman owner came to greet us at the table and to ask in her Cantonese if everything was to our liking. Fortunately with my minimal Canadian Chinese, I said yes and thanked her as I would like to do the same in this review. To Seahouse Fish and Chips, thank you       for your service and the YUMMY fish combo.  Will definitely return and share this review with other diners. Kid-friendliness: Both younger and senior women owners are so hospitable that they will go out of their way to make their restaurant like your home. Wheelchair accessibility: Tables and chairs are flexible and light to move around in the large dining space.
response_from_owner_text: Wow! Thank you for such a wonderful and thoughtful review. Come back soon, please!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: The portions are small but so is the price, good value for the money. Very friendly and good, fast service. My wife and I got clam chowder and the 2 piece halibut and chips and coke to drink. I will go back again for sure. Parking: Parking lot is very small but there is free parking.
response_from_owner_text: Fantastic! So happy you like the food. Come back for more soon.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Great fish and chips and well priced. They use basa and its soft and juicy. Family run with quick and friendly service. Wish I discovered this place earlier! Cash only Food
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much. Awesome!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Yummy fish and chips! The coleslaw is good too. The fried fish is fresh and lightly coated. We ordered the family set tonight and very delighted. Exceptional value when everything so expensive these days. Thank you for providing such yummy food with great value.
response_from_owner_text: Fantastic! Glad your family enjoyed the meal. Come back for more soon!!!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Family run fish and chips shop.  Owner was nice and she prepared the order right after the order.  Ordered halibut and chips. The portion was decent size and quality was good.
response_from_owner_text: Wow, cool! Thank you so much

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Food was great. Not the commercial style fish and chips restaurant. Very home made which is wonderful.
response_from_owner_text: Fantastic! Thank you very much

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: We decided to check out this place today as they got good reviews. I cannot imagine how I have never tried it before. We used to live about 4 blocks away and have never tried it. Anyway, they deserve the 5 stars for the food and of course the price. They only had the basa fish that day but it tasted really good. The batter was light and it was cooked well and not oily. The place is homey and looks like it is family owned. We will certainly come back and would like other folks to try their fish and chips as well. Parking: Enough parking spaces
response_from_owner_text: Yes, same family owned and operated for more than two decades! Come back for more soon! But price has to be adjusted soon because everything has gone up way too much!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Probably the best restaurant in Vancouver. Simple, no-frills and value. $5.50 for a hamburger with fries, cheapest in the city. You can t even get a quarter pounder at McDonalds for that price. The burger s patty is real beef, unlike McDonald s. The fish and fries are freshly fried right in front of you, and the batter is perfectly crispy and fresh is tender. The fries aren t salted, so make sure to salt them at home. I would love to try the halibut, but they ve been out the 3 times I ve been there. ~$30 for 10 pieces of fish + 3 fries, coleslaw, and gravy is such a good deal! Customer service is great, two or three Cantonese speaking aunties work there, they ve been running for 20-30 years. They tried to talk to my friend and I with our limited Cantonese/Mandarin skills. So nice!!! This place is a Vancouver hidden gem, standing strong in the face of inflation. I will be so sad if this place closes.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for your detailed review and recommendations. We really appreciate that. Unfortunately, due the high prices of everything we need to purchase to make our food nowadays, we have no choice but to increase our extremely low prices to a more moderate price point for all our menu items. Hope you come back again for more!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Stopped in for lunch today, they didnt have any halibut, so opted for the regular fish and chips. Fish was nice and thick, cooked perfectly with the proper amount of breading. Fries were a bit starchy, but the fish more than made up for it. Tartar sauce was quite tasty. The price is fantastic and the service was quite friendly. Will definitely be back. Parking: Parking is out front of the store.
response_from_owner_text: Sorry, no halibut from Haida Gwaii for a while. Thank you for the fantastic review. Come back soon!!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: My go to Fish and Chip place. Why? Still have 2 tables for dine in. They have really great lunch specials before 2 pm. Fantastic cod and halibut. A fish sandwich thats superb. Even great   burgers. The staff are super friendly, make sure your water   is always full.
response_from_owner_text: So nice to hear. Come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: For the price this is unbeatable. Fish, fries and clam chowder soup for only $10!! The fish was just awesome to bite into and the chowder was great as well. Fries were only okay though but at this price you cant complain.
response_from_owner_text: You are right. What a deal! Come back soon for more!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: The best and most affordable fish and chips in Vancouver. The fish portions are huge and always crispy. Love going here for a quick lunch.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much. Please come back soon!!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Fish is  well seasoned and fried to perfection, tartar sauce is tangy and balances out the fish. Although prices have increased slightly, the quality is still the same, and I will continue to be a loyal customer! Thank you!!
response_from_owner_text: Awesome! Thank you! Yes, please keep coming back!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: I was craving fish and chips for a week, but I refused to get it from any place other than this one. No other has compared to this one. The way they batter and fry their fish is perfection. The batter isnt too thick but still boasts such a good flavor with a perfect crisp and their fish is juicy! The portions and price are perfect as well. They take cash only, so I assume thats why there isnt a skipthedishes/ubereats/doordash option for delivery. If there were, Id be ordering here a lot more. Its a Hole-In-The-Wall/Mom-and-pops place that seems pretty off the radar. People are really really missing out.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for the awesome review! Come back for more soon!!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Fresh and flaky battered fish at extremely reasonable prices. Fries were not overly oily, but perhaps were from an older batch (as they were not super crispy). Note to owner: signage on the street lost a number - I believe it says $_.50 should you wish to make the quick fix.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your comments! Please come back soon!!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Staff are friendly, the fish b chips I ate were cooked to perfection.  Very delish and great prices
response_from_owner_text: Yes, great price indeed! Thank you

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Home made style fish and chips. Simple settings, simple menu, tasty food, and friendly service. 2 slices of fish plus chips is $8.75. It keeps the same price as it opened the door over 20 years ago. Great family!  Lovely food!   Call ahead before you go. Parking: Have parking in front of the restaurant Kid-friendliness: My son loves here.  We enjoy simply conversation with the Cantonese speaking owners.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much! Come back for more soon!!!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Unbeatable fish and chips! Been eating here for years and fish is always crispy on the outside, moist and juicy inside (never dry); the portion size is always super generous. Also, the aunties running the place are total sweethearts, and while its a simple little place, you can really feel the friendly and warm atmosphere. Highly recommend!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much! Come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Amazing price with decent food. Fried fish is so tender. Will definitely come back again.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much! Come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: The halibut was tender and juicy, nice thick cut. Will definitely recommend and be back. High quality fish!!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much! Please come back soon for more!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Amazing fish and chips, the best in Vancouver! The service here is amazing, you are all very kind    . Great atmosphere.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much. Please come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Great cheap place for fish and chips! The fish is free and the chips are crunchy and soft on the inside. The ladies who run it are super friendly. Food arrives quite fast.
response_from_owner_text: Awesome, love to hear your experience. Thank you.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: This is not a fancy place to sit but the two old ladies who work here are respectful. We ordered Halibut and chips and they make the food as they get the order. So, thats a nice thing and the fish too is fresh which you can see as you eat. Most Honest eatery on Kingsway!!!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much! Come back for more soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: its vancouvers hidden gem!  price is good  service is good and most importantly, the food is really really good
response_from_owner_text: Wow, thank you so much for your kind words!! Come back for more soon!!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Got the dinner special. Truly good value as it comes with good clam chowder, fish was juicy and lightly battered and unsalted fries and coleslaw. Love the chowder as its not crazy salty like other places and I like how the fries are unsalted. Downside is, I wish they put in their menu specifically type of fish it was (Basa). And wish the fries were homemade. Overall, would go back again because their fish was indeed done very well and price is great value. Doesnt seem like they reuse the oil so much that makes the food taste bitter, so well done. Would go back and try the halibut instead
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much. The fries are homemade everyday right at the back of the kitchen!!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: What a hidden gem! I first came here a few years ago when i was on a really tight budget. I cannot believe how high the quality of food is for the price that they charge, and it s REALLY tasty! You cannot get this quality and value anywhere! I had the honour of chatting with one of the owners.  She shared her story for why she started the restaurant and why she continues to run it. It is such a heart-warming story. I will be so sad if this place ever closes. Thank you so, so much!!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the fantastic review. Much appreciated. You are right. The boss likes no fuss, no frills, just good value! Come back for more soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: The fish and chips were absolutely perfect along with the service and atmosphere. Highly recommended
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much. Please come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Nice, no frills place for reasonably priced fish and chips.
response_from_owner_text: You are right! Come back for more soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: The batter on the fish is light and not greasy like other restaurants, and I could actually taste the fish.
response_from_owner_text: You are absolutely right! We like the batter light and crisp

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Awesome family ran business, good crispy fish and prawns! Support local and come give it a try! Good prices also ! :)
response_from_owner_text: Fantastic! Please come back for more fish & prawns soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: I and my shadow went to Sea house Fish and Chips in early May 2022 The fish is so fresh and the price is also very reasonable. This 3 pcs of big fish and homemade fried cost only $ 11.95  This price is hard to come by in this inflation situation. We plan to come monthly because we dont live in Vancouver. They accept cash only. Thats why they can offer just a low price. The point of sale systems will make the cost of food rise. I admire mother of store owner she is 90 years old and she cooks fish for us perfectly done. She is inspired me. Definitely we will be their regular customers
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much! Please come once a month for our great deals!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: I have driven past this place so many times and only recently brought myself to try it. Ngl it looks pretty dead from the outside but it s truly a hidden gem! It s a family owned business too. Service wasn t amazing but the taste and value makes up for it. 2 piece fish Special Value Meals $9.95 Comes with coleslaw and choice of soup or pop. The chowder surprisingly was decent with lots of clam pieces. The fish pieces were on the smaller side but the meat was juicy and the batter was thin and not too oily, very solid. Fries and coleslaw were standard. 10/10 have to get again!
response_from_owner_text: Wow, thank you so much! Please come back for more soon

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Great crispy battered fish. Sauces and coleslaw were really good. Service was good and the restaurant was very clean. It was empty when I attended, so I hope theyre doing good business. They deserve to make a good living. Because they are doing an excellent job.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for such a thoughtful review and your good wishes. Come back soon for more.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Been looking for a nice fish and chips joint and this one is pretty good. Nice owners, tasty food, and quiet place. Come here to eat!
response_from_owner_text: Awesome and thank you!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Hidden gem. Great value and taste super good. Quiet most of the time though. Hope it stays in business as long as it can.
response_from_owner_text: Hey Bobby, we misssed this review. Thank you so much. 6 years later, the old lady boss is still kicking and frying. Please come back again for more!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Fish is delightfully crispy! (with both pieces devoured within 2 minutes) Although some may prefer that extra crunch, the batter is light & thumbs up for me.  The fries are decent & not as crispy, being in the supporting role, but quite filling with all that potato.  Even with the increase in price, which is very fair, solid deal on the dinner for two! (of course I was hoping for the family pack, not being too heavy on clam chowder, but the other half had eyes on that) To maintain that freshness, make sure you get home FAST! (drive or walk safely of course) We will be back, & whatever it is we order.. itll pair nicely with beers. Cheers!  #supportlocal
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much! Great combo with beer!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Fish was great and the portions were good for a price of 9.99 fish and chips. Cash only. Friendly folks there.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you! Come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Good fish for really cheap.  Decor hasnt been updated in a while.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you, sir!! Come back for more soon!!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: My friends and I came over for a lunch. The portions were very good. Fish was juicy and crisp on the outside (we had halibut). Nice portion of fries aa well. Good quiet environment. My friends and I enjoyed the meal.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much! Please come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Food was great: Cheap, fast and filling. And Im not kidding on cheap; most affordable chip shop Ive found so far in Vancouver and Ive been around. I highly recommend this place if your ever driving by Kingsway and want something light on the wallet and filling on the stomach. Its also nice to see that the flavor hasnt changed since I was a kid and the prices are very affordable.
response_from_owner_text: This sounds awesome: light on the wallet and filling on the stomach. Thank you.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: We have driven by countless times unimpressed with the outward appearance and location. But this is a lesson in don t judge with eyes alone. For a very reasonable price, you will enjoy a decent 2 piece fiah and chips without much to complain about. We were impressed that the fish was lightly battered, and not greasy or thick with dough. For this price, I was afraid that it was going to be a treasure hunt searching for the fish in the batter. In fact ours was not even  pre-battered . I saw with my eyes   four fresh fillets being coated and dropped into the fryer! The fries were good too. We forgot to grab some salt, but still good enough to munch down every crumb. There is little to be impressed by visual distractions, but I feel this is a secret for some of the best cheap eats in West Coast dinner food, and if you take a momment to chat to the owners, it is made up in delightful character.
response_from_owner_text: Wow, thank you very much. Come back for more soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: $7 1 pc fish and chips includes a drink!  3/4 size portion but is healthier anyway.  Fish moist inside, Korean crispy outside, super hot from the fryer.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much! Come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Awesome fish n chips sandwiches. They make them piping hot fresh when served. The chowder is fantastic. You can also see them make your food within view. Plus a great affordable price to come back to.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you! Come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: I just ordered a take out special for two. I did not expect a whole lot beforehand, but it turned out to be a nice surprise!! Especially the fish, they are perfectly fried. The batter is thin and crunchy but not hard. This is definitely a hidden gem!!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you. Glad that you enjoyed it. Come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Comfort food! Very nice staff! Will definitely be back for more! I ordered the dinner for 2. The soup is absolutely amazing and if you dump the coleslaw in it, it gets even better! No time for pictures haha Fish and chips was great too. The amount of food is perfect for 2 hungry people
response_from_owner_text: Wow, never tried that before. Good idea!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Ive been eating at this place since before Google reviews and its without a doubt the best place in the lower mainland for fish and chips I still cant believe that for 20 years they have kept the quality the same delicious
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your support for so many years!! Awesome!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: My family has been coming here for years, both eat in and take-out. We enjoy their fish & chip combo, its affordable and filling for the price! Their coleslaw is delicious (not overly dressed, which I prefer), but my favourite item is the clam chowder. Fragrant flavour, and I love the homemade taste with the vegetables (celery, carrots). Its more of a hole in the wall eatery but its definitely worth stopping in to check out.
response_from_owner_text: Awesome. Thank you!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: This is a great little mom-n-pop fish and chips eatery. The batter is very light and very crispy, which is a surprise, considering all the local fish and chips places that claim to be authentic and British, yet have soggy, oil-soaked batter. GREAT value, great service, clean restaurant, quiet atmosphere. Its a great little neighbourhood gem to support!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much. Come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: The owners are really friendly, and super nice to kids. The fish is crispy and the deals are great. Its a wonderful family restaurant. 10 pieces of cod, 3 orders of chips, 2 coleslaw, and 1 gravy for only $24.10. (After tax) the coleslaw and tartar sauce are homemade, too. Cash only.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Incredible flavour. Crisp, fresh, and delicious fish and chips. Highly recommend. Try the fish burger with the bacon add-on. Lunch special like no where else in the city.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you, please come back for more soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: They have the most juicy fish here and very good pricing! A hidden gem.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Its rare to find a restaurant with good quality food at a good price. For most fish and chips place, they coat their fish with heaping amount of batter so that the customer get more flour and fish. This place do it just right: Thin coat that makes the fish crunchy but not get in the way of fish. Also we did not eat in the restaurant and have it as a takeout. The fact that the food is still nice and crunchy after the drive back gives you an idea of the quality (Ive seen many fried foods turned soggy after even a short drive) The owner is generous in servings: 10 piece cod, 2 coleslaw, 3 fries and gravy for $24!! Thats quite unheard of!! This is a mom and pop shop that I would recommend to anyone

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: A quaint, inconspicuous fish and chippery along Kingsway. This shop has a varied menu revolving around the British meal at incredible prices. The restaurant is owned by an Asian family (which is as authentic as it comes, as the best F&C shops in Britain are also similarly operated). The fish batter is perfectly thin and crispy and the chips are crunchy and hot - overall fantastic. The service is great and the ladies are attentive. So glad we popped in here.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: The takeout family pack is INSANELY good value!  Its 10 pieces of cod, slaw, gravy, and a mound of fries and is just over $20. Highly recommend the cod.  Coating on the fish is very very crisp, and not at all bready, which I prefer over the more traditional.  This is so far my favorite fish and chip place. Staff is very nice.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: You need to go there to believe it.  First impression, the place was spotless.  Not only does the owner wipe the table after each diner, she also wipes down the ketchup bottle, salt and pepper and all condiments on the table.  Wife went for the two piece fish and chips. Comes with clam chowder and cold slaw for $7.95.  Chowder is commercial chowder but thick and tasty.  Two pieces of fish done to perfection.  I had the combo with battered shrimp.  Tasty and well done.  Not your upscale fish and chip restaurant but great value for the dollar.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: This place is a hidden gem, the prices were awesome, excellent value, i had the prawns and fish and chips, amazing value and so tasty prawns and fish nice and fresh, my wife had the one piece of halibut and chips $8.95 and again outstanding, we will definitely be back!
response_from_owner_text: You are right, Michell. Super Value is the core of this hidden gem. They adjusted the price once in the past 15 years in January 2022 due to pandemic rises in food costs. And I was so surprised that they only increased a dollar twenty-five here and 75 cents there! I asked the boss why not increased the price to at least match the competitors because the new prices are still 20% to 30% below market. She says, l want to make sure all our meals are affordable for the neighbours and long-term customers; I just need to break even, I dont need the extra cash!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: First visit ever, Very nice people, decent food and incredible prices. Not salty food at all, especially for those sensitive to salty food.  Id never thought to go here because the place always looked closed (security bars across windows, dark inside) when in fact it was opened all the time.   Theres also a park down the road so well be stopping by with the kids this summer and taking the fish and chips down to the park for a picnic lunch in the sun. Update: tried a hamburger with cheese on a second visit. Recommend! The patty covers the entire bun, condiments all fresh. The seahouse patty isnt chewy like a McDonalds patty and a lot bigger (except quarter pounder). The seas house patty doesnt have MSG like an A&W patty (wont leave you thirsty!).  Its just a good ole homemade burger, with fries, and it came to 5.80. Cheap good and fast! (how is it possible for any restaurant to get all three?!, rules for cheap, good, fast, pick two but leave one out, but sea house has all three, cheap, good AND fast).
response_from_owner_text: Hi Matt, Thank you so much for your comments. Come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: What a wonderful discovery! This is a classic greasy spoon fish and chip spot. And I mean that in the best possible way. Spacious seating and open, fast and efficient service (I had my water glass refilled at least thrice, a rarity in Vancouver), food was prepared quickly and properly, good sized portions and all at a super reasonable price! Vancouver used to have lots of places like this ages ago but I havent been to one in about two decades. I definitely recommend if youre looking for an inexpensive meal from memory lane.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: 2 pc fish and chips for $7. Was very tasty, good comfort food and perfect if youre looking for a greasy, fatty meal ^-^ 10/10, will come back and recommend to my friends. Definitely fixed my craving
response_from_owner_text: Awesome! Thank you so much. Glad that you like it. Come back soon.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Great value for money! Where else can you get some tasty, crispy, fresh out of the frier fish, and fresh chips for $4.99? Amazing. They dont use cod anymore, so your choices are halibut, salmon, and fish. Probably tilapia, but its pretty good. The other standout bargain on the menu is the family pack. It has to be ordered as take out, and it comes with 10 pieces of fish, 3 orders of chips, 2 coleslaws, 2 gravies, tartar sauce, and lemon wedges--for $23 including tax. It easily feeds my family of four, and the kids love it. This place is an East Van gem, and a great place if you miss the Vancouver of yesteryear. Old school vibe, delicious, no-frills food, and the old school prices to match.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much! Our prices and menu still havent changed much. Come back soon.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Lovely lady who took my order patiently as I wasn t sure which way to order my halibut and chips was the most economical.  I had a take away and it was nicely wrapped up in papers so even when i got home the food was not soggy and was still warm (30min after).  I had my baby stroller with me.. and the lady was so kind to open the door for me even without me asking for help... really appreciate this :)
response_from_owner_text: Sounds great. Please come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: I rarely give 5 stars. And yes, technically we can talk about  quality over value . Yet I do believe this place deserves a full score. Strongly recommended! You made my day The Sea House. We ll visit you again soon!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much. Come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: The favorite fish and chip in town! Good deal with reasonable price and best taste! Food
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: This place is awesome! It`s a tucked away and hidden little gem of a restaurant, quiet and clean. The owners are super friendly, I got the burgers and fries lunch special, less than 6 bucks for a huge freshly brewed coffee with cream and sugar, a heaping serving of fries, and...quite possibly one of the best homemade burgers I`ve ever had, and I`m not over-exaggerating. The burger is perfect, juicy in all the right places, crispy and saucy in all the other places. I recommend this place to anyone and everyone!!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
reviewer_name: Karla with a k ok Brophy
review_text: This restaurant has been around for a long time, 15+years an I absolutely love the food, prices an the very nice warm family who make all of this wonderful food happen. For that I rate them all the stars   possible. Note food is always made to order an never sitting around- always hot an fresh.yummy.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Karla. So happy you love our food. Come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: This mom and pop restaurant offers decent fish and chips.  My son loves their hamburger.  Will come back for sure.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much. Please come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Excellent value meals. Ordered the two piece fish and chips meal, hot and fresh out of the fryer, clam chowder was tasty.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much. Come back soon.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: I order hailbut* And calamari. Taste all really good and they made it right when I order it. Hope is doing well with COVID. Clean place and a cute hipster aunties. Only downside is cash only.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your comments. Sorry about the cash only policy, our prices have not change for 15 years to keep costs down. Come back soon....

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Excellent quality fish and chips.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much. Come back for more soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Cozy feeling place, good fish good price
response_from_owner_text: You are absolutely correct. Thank you.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Such great value with generous portions and delicious fish! The ladies are always kind :)  please support this little business, it s a hidden gem!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much. Come back for more soon.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Best fish and chips Ive ever had, and super nice staff. 6/5 would go back.
response_from_owner_text: Awesome! Come back very soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: This is pretty much the only place I have fish and chips anymore. Always good always consistent. Batter is crispy and not doughy/bready like other places. Amazing prices.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: This place is amazing! Perfect fish n chips and Wow the price is so inexpensive. I love the halibut n chips!!! Been coming here for years.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: The food was really good, price value for the money. I was impressed by quality of fish
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much. Please come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Excellent F&C and the lunch special is always satisfying. You have a choice of soft-drink or chowder and I highly recommend the chowder; very nice.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much! So nice to hear that.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Honestly some of the best fish and chips I ve had. This place has the best value for food and the staff is very wholesome, would definitely recommend!
response_from_owner_text: Awesome. Glad that you like it. Come back soon.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: The best fish and chips in town!  The batter is nice and light, and the fries are crispy.  The coleslaw is our favourite.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Food is great and totally worth the price. I ordered the colesaw and loved it. Take out was nicely packed, so it tasted great when I got home.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much. Come back soon!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Had my doubts as a passerby... and was quickly proven wrong on many levels. Service, quality, and value - all there. Dont miss out!
response_from_owner_text: Awesome! Come back for more son!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: It was good fish for a very reasonable price. Dont let the store front fool. Go in and enjoy good food. CASH ONLY!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: My favorite fish & chips place in Vancouver~~~ Get the family pack with 2 friends (maybe 3 if yall aint that hungry), best bang for the buck. Shout outs to big ddy Kelvin Low and Josh Amato.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Lovely people, good fish, mushy peas, you wont find a better value, parking lot, all the dressings. Maybe 3 mains on the menu.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much. You are right! Unbelievable value. Come back for more soon.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Excellent place for fish n chips! The halibut was so fresh and tasty & you cant beat the price
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for the comment and come back soon!!

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Cash only, take out portions are large, ,batter nicely flavoured and thin and very crispy. Made to order.  Great food.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: Its a great place with fresh and tasty food and great service. The  people were very nice. Great value aswell. Come and check it out, you wont be disappointed.

place_name: The Sea House Fish and Chips
review_text: The fish is great, I had the halibut. Staff were humble and friendly.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much! Please come back for more soon!

review_text: I ordered Cod with fries and tartar sauce tonight and it caused me around 25 dollars or so. To be honest it s a little bit expensive to me as a student, but the food and its taste is definitely worth the price. The fish is fresh and tartar sauce is delicious and flavorful I m so into it after the first taste.  I will probably pay Fish Cafe a second visit.
response_from_owner_text: Hi thank you for your very kind words and for visiting us, next time you come in come and say hello, I ll make sure to give you a better deal

review_text: Was running errand in the area. We actually waited over 30 minutes for them to open, it was well worth it! We got 3pcs snapper fish&chips! Good portion! The batter was crispy, fish was moist, perfectly seasoned! It was soooooo good, really hit the spot! Tartar sauce was light and refreshing, not heavy at all. I craved this again 3-4 times that same day, I m still thinking about it today! We also got the scallop, grilled, over rice, with garlic butter! Scallop was also perfectly cooked! Sweet and juicy! I enjoyed dipping the scallop in the butter and adding tartar sauce to the rice for the perfect bite! Food was a little slow but we went right when they open so it was understandable. I appreciate that the chef take his time to prepare the food properly instead of rushing them out. Service was friendly and casual, very warm and welcoming! We enjoyed our conversation with them and our time there. This was also the first time we took our puppy to a restaurant, we were glad it was a pleasant experience. Their supplies came late that day and we couldn t order what we originally wanted, but we would definitely be back for other dishes. What we ended up ordering turn out great though, so no complain there! But next time we want to try cod fish& chips, grilled calamari, and clam chowder. :) We wish they have deep fried oysters too, I think it will be amazing!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much, please come and run some errands in our area so we can spoil you again soon

review_text: Local restaurant with world class food. Chef Marcus is personable and goes out of his way to make sure you are taken care of. The fish grilled or blackened is always delicious. However, the calamari appetizer will always remain my favorite.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for this, but we cannot forget the  team  behind this servers, dishwashers etc

review_text: OMG! The food was amazing! We got the halibut sandwich, fish soup, snapper with fries - yum! Definitely coming back! Food
response_from_owner_text: WOW !! Thanks a lot

review_text: This is the little hole in the wall people drive for great distances to enjoy. The Snapper Fish and Chips is a whole body and brain experience. It awakens pleasure centres deep in my brain. The staff creates a happy vibe from the ground up and I really enjoyed dining outside on their tiny terrace.
response_from_owner_text: WOW!!! Thank you so much for your very kind words, and thanks for recognizing what an important role our servers played in your overall experience.

review_text: Great neighborhood restaurant.  I like the blackened fish with lemon butter sauce on the side. The fries are worth the calories here. If you re craving fish and chips make sure you eat here. They offer take out here.  Parking meters on 41st Ave is usually very easy.

It was an incredible experience dining here. Food was great, we had fish n chips and caesar salad. Chef and both waitresses were so kind and welcoming. It was a lovely experience. I just moved to Vancouver and this restaurant has definitely become my goto place.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your kind words, welcome to Vancouver.

review_text: Fish Cafe was great! Im from Toronto and my cousin mentioned BC has great seafood, its fresh. We started with the grilled calamari with garlic butter which was a great combo. I had a Greek salad with 1pc fish and chips. He had the grilled salmon on rice. For dessert we tried their chocolate cake (they didnt have anymore carrot cake). Its understandable that some menu items wouldnt be available due to the freshness of the food so we didnt get a chance to try their crab cakes or clam chowder. I would highly recommend the fish and chips, the snapper was very light and battered perfectly. Overall Im happy we visited and I would definitely go back if I visit BC again :) Parking: You may find free street parking if youre willing to park around the corner. Otherwise there is paid parking right in front of the restaurant.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for coming in tonight, I really pleased you guys enjoyed yourselves, thank you for taking the time to leave your thoughts here.

review_text: I absolutely love this place. This is the type of place you see in movies where the small local fish restaurant has one chef and two waitresses who know the local patrons by name and their usual orders. My favorite dish on the menu is their fish burger. If you re a fan of blackened fish or focaccia bread this menu item is for you. I ve had both the salmon and red snapper options and I ve been impressed every time. The fish is always cooked to perfection and the focaccia bread *chef kiss* The fries are also always crispy and fresh which just competes the dish. Make sure to get some of their tarter sauce on side because it s the perfect blend of creamy and tart. I will note that the typical wait time for your food to be served feels a bit longer than most restaurants but when you re served amazing food, the wait time doesn t matter. Order a drink and enjoy the company around you.
response_from_owner_text: WOW thank you so much, yeah that extra bit of tartare sauce is so good.

review_text: I really like the ambiance of this small cafe- casual and no nonsense. My partner and I prefer places like this where there is a limited menu with all the dishes executed very well. Its also an added bonus to be able to choose how your fish will be prepared (grilled, blackened or fried), and of course the fish is fresh & prepared to perfection.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for taking the time write this, glad you both enjoyed yourselves.

review_text: Definitely the best fish and chips that I had in town. Marcus is a great chef making the food amazing and the staff is so friendly. Definitely I would visit again.
response_from_owner_text: Hi, thanks for coming in and eating at Fish Cafe, appreciate the review, thanks

review_text: I was driving around looking for something to eat and saw this place...I stopped in and was warmly greeted by the young lady serving tables. It was toward the end of the night, so the fish options were limited, but it worked to my favor. I ordered the steelhead with my seafood platter, which I would not usually go for. Well, it was amazing! Blackened with that garlic butter...just simply awesome. The grilled calamari, scallops, and prawns were equally fresh and delicious and those fries were among the best I have had. I would recommend the fries over the rice, only because they are so good! All in all, it was an amazing meal and I am glad I stumbled upon this place. I will be back next time I am in Vancouver...
response_from_owner_text: Hi Brian thanks for  stumbling in  and for choosing Fish Cafe  , stumble in again soon. Take care

review_text: We routinely do takeout from this amazing fish place. Have had countless great family dinners while enjoying the fish and chips.
Came here on the recommendation of a local friend while visiting from out of town. Perfectly cooked steelhead   probably the best fish I ve ever had at a restaurant
response_from_owner_text: WOW!!! Thank you so much and for coming in to eat. The steelhead has been particularly nice in the last few months.

review_text: Absolutely love this place. Food is outstanding and the service is incredible. Have eaten here for a long time and will continue to do so!

Incredible meal...Just walked in the door from this place....Mrs had Arctic Char and a house salad...I had fish soup, Grilled Scallops with Rice....Service was fantastic, and for a 1 man kitchen very efficient and quick...my ONLY complaint is that there wasnt MORE scallops on my plate. If I lived in Vancouver, this place would be a regular stop!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you, and a special thank you for mentioning your server, they are a very important part of our business.

review_text: Service was slow but food was worth the wait. The last call was 7:30pm and we got our food around 7:40pm. But definitely worth the visit, food is amazing tons of fish options
response_from_owner_text: Thank you.

review_text: My partner and I had a SPECTACULAR experience here! I had the blackened cod with garlic butter (divine), they had fish and chips (unreal), and we split a house salad with the vinaigrette (why was a salad so delicious??). Our server was fantastic, and the place was packed. It s a small dining room, so we were happy to have a reservation. 10/10 recommend! Can t wait to go back and try more of the catches and sauces!
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for coming in tonight and for your kind words

review_text: The single best piece of fish I have ever had in my life. The waitress was personable and friendly. I will definitely be coming back here and recommending it to all of my friends!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for the very kind words, and for acknowledging your server in such a positive manner, it s refreshing to get this feedback, usually people only write and complain about service.

review_text: Fish cafe is the only and best fish chip place in kerrisdale.  The fish is always freshly cooked and served.  Because only one chef works, the waiting could be long on weekends.  Not a place for a quick bite
response_from_owner_text: Hi thank you so much, yep I agree I do get a little overwhelmed sometimes when it gets busy, part of the issue is I try and put out the best I can each time.

review_text: The best seafood is here. The fish so fresh, blackened yet so juicy and almost milky. The deep fried calamari is tender and flavorful. The scallops are so soft, savor the taste and it melts in the mouth. The fries, rice and greek salad are so satisfying. The serving is just right, the servers are pleasant and attentive.
