review_text: The Fish Cafe serves the best cooked fish in Vancouver, bar none.  Always fresh; if its not available that day, it comes off the menu.  Weve been coming here on at least a weekly basis for years and the quality has never dipped once.  The fish soup is sublime, with large chunks of fish every time.  My mother loves their fish and chips using cod; the fish is always moist and the batter is crunchy and light.  Even the fries are amazing.  Its worth pointing out that the fish and chips is cheaper here than at the White Spot and clearly on a completely different level.  I love the grilled trout and its never overcooked or dry, despite being such a thin, delicate piece of fish.  Portion sizes are always generous.  This is a comfortable neighbourhood spot, with really friendly and professional service.  Thanks to Marcus, his family and the staff for always making us feel welcome and VERY well fed.
response_from_owner_text: Such kind words, thank you. I look forward every week to seeing you guys for lunch on Saturdays

Fresh Ideas Start Here sells fresh and frozen sustainably caught seafood and the majority of their products are locally sourced. They have seafood that is raw and ready to cook as well as foods that have already been assembled and may just need a bit of time in the oven or on the stove before its ready to eat. (eg. Crab Cakes,Truffle Spot Prawn Mac n Cheese) To celebrate the launch of their fall seasonal menu, Fresh Ideas Start Here was offering a small bowl of complimentary seafood congee to the first 50 customers who came into their store and mentioned the word halibut. Wed never tried this seafood congee before, but apparently its a cult favourite so we went to the store right when it opened and managed to bring home some of this famed seafood congee. Oh wow! This seafood congee exceeded my expectations. I totally understand now why its a cult favourite. It was packed with seafood. They dont skimp on ingredients at this place. According to the stickers stuck onto our containers, a small congee is normally $6 and a large congee is normally $8. I would absolutely go back and pay to have this seafood congee again! Im so happy that its Fall now. With hot summer days leaving, and cooler weather arriving, we should definitely have a reason to go back for the seafood congee! Service: Good Parking: Plentiful and free Location: 7515 Market Crossing #180, Burnaby
Chris is always friendly and the seafood is super fresh and their prices are great. I grab stuff to make dinner and ceviche and stuff all the time! Highly recommend

The employees are very kind and explains in detail if you have any questions. I visited because I wanted to get sea urchin(uni) and spotted prawn, but it was not the season yet, so I bought frozen sea urchin and defrosted it. Also I m very satisfied with the poke that the staff makes on the spot and it was delicious. I m going to visit here again.
I come here to buy uni. The staff here is amazing. Very knowledgeable and always cheerful. You leave with a smile on your face. I recommend that you also try their smoke salmon and cod.
Popped in today and all we got was ready made food--onigiri, inari, and a poke bowl. All were very fresh and tasty and the staff were very good to us :) Will be back!

If youre in the area or not.  Craving for some fresh poke!!  Look no further!  You can purchase the onigiri here as well to go with your poke bowl.  Its jam packed full of fresh poke and ingredients.  Need some super fresh seafood as well!   They have all that as well.  Cant be any fresher then them processing it in the store.  They do have some frozen products as well, but mainly fresh.  You wont be disappointed

Best Poke bowl I have ever tried. My sister and I both got the Bara Chirashi and it was delicious! They ran out of octopus so we picked more ahi tuna. I may decide to do the same substitute in future since the tuna was great!

Ive had this place on my radar for months, finally got a chance to order online and pick up! Their seafood congee was A++ and was apparently on special ($8, regular $10). It was packed full of seafood and so comforting! There were a few shells/bones throughout, but it was so delicious and bountiful with ingredients, we didnt mind. Just checked their site and doesnt look like its offered anymore, which would be shame, would have definitely come back for the congee alone! Also had 3 customized regular poke bowls, no complaints. The fish was so fresh and we enjoyed some of their more unique toppings, like the ginger-y squid salad. Great sauces to compliment the fish! I snagged a couple of their onigiri left from the grab-and-go section, also fair in size with a mildly spicy cooked tuna flavour. Perfect for a snack or lunch/dinner accompaniment. I picked up some frozen soup that Im excited to try, and cant wait to be back for more poke!

Poke bar is fresh and tasty. Delivery is a great option too. We just tried the Valentines Day platter (medium) and it was fantastic! The crab dip and crab cakes are amazing too! Ive been going to F.I.S.H. for years and they dont disappoint.
This little store has a great selection of seafood. Super friendly staff and I especially enjoy their salmon jerky - depending on flavour and fish, the jerkies range from $6 - $12 per 100g.
I go here every year for spot prawn season! Always fresh and live. They do pre-orders online too and sell a bunch of other amazing seafood in-store (check out the uni or uni pasta).

Great quality seafood products, very good service. Especially their manager Jordan, he is very knowledgeable, helpful,  shares tips and recipes. He goes above and beyond to accommodate special requests.
Great place to grab UNI. They are around the same price as T&T but more fresh (as writing this review). Will come back for Seafood.
Fresh uni! Friendly staff.
Bought frozen Hokkaido Scallops and sashimi grade salmon and tuna. It was amazing! The store was clean and the employees were super friendly! Thanks guys, so glad you re my local go to for good fish!
Ordered the caviar set - Great value and price! Staff are super friendly and helpful. We also starting purchasing fresh seafood here.
A hidden gem for seafood lovers. Their congee is so nice and filled so much seafood. The owners and workers are amazingly friendly, always giving extras for free.

They are so knowledgeable, so friendly, and patient. I really appreciate his they take the time to sort out my mussels and clams to make sure theyre fresh. I asked many questions, they helped me choose what I needed to impress my mother in law. I always order online through them. I like the different methods of payment available online. Honestly its always a positive experience coming here. I also look forward to their freezer sales.

Very friendly staff, I would highly recommend coming here if you want something fresh to go. Prices vary but I feel like its definitely worth it! They also have a poke bar, the rice isn t the greatest imo and I personally probably would ve went with a salad base if I knew but the toppings were great regardless! Easy to access area, located in market crossing. Lots of parking space, lots of things on display as well.

My daughter always requests poke bowls from here. Always fresh. Great service with a smile. They pack the food into the bowls so you feel you are getting great value. I love how you can add ikura or uni to your order because you feel like splurging. Great little gem in Burnaby.
best value and quality poke. the fish is always so fresh because it is also a fish market. our favorite poke place.
Delicious prepped meals, fresh seafood, and friendly service.

I love going to shop at this place for all of my seafood needs. They always have a good selection of fish that is local and very well priced. I always get the crab and artichoke dip and the taste of it is very good.  Overall very and helpful staff, good seafood at great prices and the taste of everything is great. Highly recommend to all

So my wife and I came here a few times to get fresh seafood, and yeah its a great place to get seafood.  One time, when we were shopping here, we tried their seafood congee.  Holy $#!% was it good!  We got two orders the next time we went back.  Now every time we pass the market crossing area, we stop at FISH and get their congee and happen to get some fresh seafood. But the main objective now is the congee. Order large.

Best price for fresh sea urchin in lower mainland. Great service. N for the Chinese style cold cooked crab, just have to give them a 1 to 2 day advanced order for that. Instead of going 80km out of my way from surrey to deep cove thru horrible traffic for the alternative

I love this place. Poke and congee bar in the back with great quality seafood, naturally. Excellent prices- $11 poke bowl I think. Nice selection of fish, great scallops, oysters, and their assorted fish cakes are always good. Lots of interesting bits in the freezer - DIY chirashi sets, soups, lox trim, sashimi, spot prawns. My go to seafood place and absolutely the only place in the area worth discussing.

I was referred to this place by a friend. I was pleasantly surprised by their products. The poke bar is situated at the end of the store. Generous portions. Great menu selection. Delicious and very affordable. Very nice and friendly staff. Truly this place is very underrated.

BEST FISHMONGER! I may not live in Burnaby but I come out here for consistently good quality seafood.  The staff are friendly and helpful.  There will always be local choices whether they be fresh or frozen.  Ive had fresh and frozen and it is both good.  Especially the sashimi grade selection and shell fish.
Great local product / selections, always fresh with knowledgeable staff. Forgot my wallet there today, they secured it and held until I could pick it up. Trustworthy, good people.

Love F.I.S.H.!!! Its my go-to place for fresh seafood. They are always super friendly and helpful; answering any questions I may have. Their seafood is top notch and pricing is super fair. Keep an eye out for their biannual freezer stock-up sales!! They always have seasonal items too (like spot prawns, local BC uni). Wouldnt consider going elsewhere for seafood and is the only place I trust for fresh seafood!

Just bought some fresh green uni trays from here and will be returning for more! The quality of all their products are top notch and so is their service. Highly recommend for anyone who loves their seafood.
Lots of options for seafood. Crab cakes, fresh scallops, mussels, live crab...They even had the Japanese Kewpie mayo.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you!

review_text: I almost dont want to write a review for this business because it is SO GOOD...but more people are finding out about it (when I go in sometimes there are lined ups) - so here goes. I love seafood. LOVE IT. Love it so much I l drive down to Stevenston and buy fresh of the boat. BUT, I dont have the time to do that so often. However, I do go into Fresh Ideas Start Here  at least once a week to pick up something fresh. Last week it was fresh, wild pink salmon and it was amazing. They were super busy for Valentines Day but very prepared. I could not believe the amount of people coming in to pick up live lobsters and crabs. And the prices were WAY BETTER than what you would find going into a box box store - dont even want to imagine the quality of those! The sushi is good, anything salmon is top of the line.

Havent been here for a while, returned recently for their poke. YUM! got the regular $12, for 2 proteins (tuna and salmon). As we couldnt decide which tuna to get, we got half of the 2 tuna varieties. And we got the crab imitation, octopus salad (YUM), and seaweed salad.  Also got the large $8 seafood congee which is PACKED with various seafood, halibut, scallop, octopus, shrimps. All so tender, perfectly cooked, and HUGE chunks!  Brilliant dish.  Better than chinese congee i have to say!!

One of my favourite fish markets. I miss getting the newsletters, but pointless now that I live in Calgary. Always good service and the salmon is always great value. I also like how they prep the halibut and their sushi is always on point. Every time Im back in BC I make a point of going here.
Seafood extremely fresh. Love that you can pre-order spot prawns and pickup.

There are a lot of seafood options for you to select. The most surprising thing for me is they have poke! Tried it and love it. So fresh and large portion. The rice a bit soggy to me but overall is pretty good. Definitely recommend

Fresh, and clean. One would think that their price is higher, but i do find it reasonable. If you are getting shellfish like clams, or mussels, they would only pick the live ones, and remove all the dead/ or looks like dead ones for you.

The fish is very good but what is different are the sushi bowls with rice or salad tuna, salmon etc. They are amazing and at a great price. Its something that I havent seen before at a fish store. If I feel like a healthy meal I pop in and take one away.

A wide variety of fresh fish and surprisingly POKE bowls! Expert staff.  Frozen fish locker.  Sushi chef creates small amounts of sushi each day.  NEW to this shop is the addition of POKE bowls prepared fresh for you from a great selection of options.

Had the Halibut cheeks last night. To die for !! Will definately be back to buy more. The jumbo shrimp and fresh halibut I bought last time, fresh and good prices. Wish I could post a photo dinner was so good.
response_from_owner_text: This is so awesome to hear Barbara - thanks so much for stopping by!

review_text: My wife and I go here for great oysters that we shuck at home. Delicious and we like the smaller ones. Their Dungeness crab cakes are yummy too.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you!

review_text: An absolutely wonderful place to shop. A large selection of fresh, previously frozen and frozen seafood. The staff is courteous and helpful with explaining any off their products. They welcome everyone with a smile and are ready to help you.
I live close to Steveston and the docks.  I still prefer to drive to F.I.S.H   even though its 25 minutes away   everything is great staff are helpful and the poke bar is excellent
Best place in town to get the freshest seafood! Poke bowls are amazing too. always great friendly service too. Highly recommended!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you!

review_text: Convenient location for fresh local seafood. The sashimi grade wild sockeye salmon is delish. The staff are always really friendly!
Amazing service and delicious poke bowls! Will definitely be coming back here again!
Great seafood selection: fresh, prepared, frozen. Excellent sushi to go, especially inari pockets filled with a mix of fish, avocado, mayo that tastes like a great Symphony sounds
The owner is the best! High energy happy proud of his store and excited for customers to enjoy the quality products he offers!
Great small shop overall, only shocked when i see the tips option when paying with credit card. It is a fish shop isn t it, not a restaurant.  I am confused.
response_from_owner_text: Hi there! Thanks for taking time to review our business. We pride ourselves in providing excellent customer service, and many happy  customers have requested to have an option to allow them to tip! As we take all our customers feedback seriously, we have added this option as well as a No Tip option. We are happy to hear that you enjoyed your visit and we hope to see you again soon!

review_text: Freshest fish in town and friendly, knowledgable staff. The sablefish is delicious. Marinate in their sake miso sauce and grill. Yum!
I m so glad they have a fish bar here now! Fresh sustainable poke in South Burnaby is now a reality! The staff are friendly and knowledgeable and the food is always prepared fresh! Love it!
Sent them a message on IG with online order issues at 9pm n got a reply within several minutes. Picked up in store and the staff were friendly. Great unique products!
Amazing quality of seafood and they now have a Poke Bowl station where they make the most amazing Poke Bowls. Lots of ingredients and fresh, fresh, fresh!
Anyways great service and a good selection of fresh and frozen seafood. We really enjoy their poke bowls as well!!!
There s a poke bar at the back and it s a hidden gem
Consistently fresh seafood from sustainable sources at fair prices.  Love this place!  Favorites include live sea urchin, smoked sablefish, salmon candy, and the halibut fish cakes.  Yum!
Fresh large and delicious alive oysters
Best onigiri ever! Today was better than before.
The Indian candy is absolutely amazing, as well as the fresh crab. This place is expensive but you get what you pay for, its incredible something so specialized is in such an area!
The hike is not too hard.
Picked up some beautiful mussels for a linguini dish tonight. Also got some nice roll mops, great fish monger selling excellent seafood.
Great selection, fresh and frozen. Excellent customer service
Always something new and yummy. Great service. More then just your average fish monger!
Always a great selection of fresh seafood. Staff are very courteous and helpful.
This is the best seafood store i have ever been to. Great selection of fresh fish and friendly helpful staff.
Went there for the poke bowl. Delicious and large portions. Its just takeout though. No where to sit.
Its my go to poke spot in Vancouver. The fish is so fresh!
Freshest seafood and best poke bowls! Check them out! Its a must!

Discovered the great poke bowls and the cute employee too late on my last day working in the area.
You can get a wide variety of fresh fishes here, reasonable prices. Only problem is public accessibility
My go-to seafood shop. Good service, quality, pricing. Two thumbs up.
very tasty crabs and good service, I would recommend

Thank you K & H Seafood  we look forward to eating at your Restaurant the next time we are in Vancouver
Friendly staff. Yummy food. Big portion. Deep fried chicken is a must try and it comes with shrimp chips too!!
This has always been my goto place for Chinese food.   They always hit the spot, good prices and I have never had a bad experience from here.
Great deal and delicious Deep Fried Squab (ask for uncut to keep juicy and warm if takeout). Dont miss this item.

If you are looking for an old school Cantonese restaurant with great food and big portions this is the place. Came here once on a family members recommendation and now I am a regular.
Excellent food with a reasonable price. I discovered it during cocoa do Ive only had takeout so far but its been consistently great.
This is always my to go restaurant. Price is economic and portion is decent. It might not be the finest, but it always fill my belly well.
Food is excellent and portion size remains unchanged big, restaurant itself didnt have any renovation for a long time, otherwise nothing can complain to the food itself
Good price and portion. The steam fish that goes with the meal is so fresh it is hard to believe its a bonus item.
Take out combination dinners are 12 bucks and fill your belly...delicious...i wouldnt go anywhere else for that price.

Rose Garden on Kingsway Vancouver has great food. The shrimp is fresh and nice portions too.
Solid late night food. Been coming here for years and they are very friendly. Great seafood too!
My local chinese joint. Order from here monthly. Just not a fan of the wonton soup.
Consistently great food.  The aroma in the restaurant and packed house testifies to their great food.
Great food for a great price!  Friendly staff!

The restaurant has a traditional Chinese vibe. The food is great We ordered lobster ($35/lb), cod fillet with corn cream (~$23), spicy Chinese eggplant, and two other dishes that I forgot the names. But these ones that I named were great. There were some options for group of 10 people for a good price too. There are some parking spots in the street beside as well as at the back of building if you can t park in Kingsway right in front of the restaurant. Parking: There are some spots in the street beside as well as at the back of building if you can t park in Kingsway right in front of the restaurant.
Great pricing for food and quality is usually on point. Could use some renovation work and service is good.

One of local go-to restaurants when were looking for some classic Chinese dishes. We often used to visit when they were called Rose Garden back in the day. The owners changed (I think) but the name on the menu still bears the old Rose Garden name. Not so much of a hidden gem as this place was busy when we visited. Nice that they have live seafood available. The lobster in ginger and green onion sauce on noodles was really good. The interior decor isnt fussy. Good option for take-out too.
Excellent cuisine. Large servings. Fair prices. Parking could be busy during mealtimes.
Decent Chinese restaurant, but looks like you need to be a local to know what they are good at.  Busy place with lots of returned customers.
Very good tradition Cantonese food! The interior was a bit tired but the food was good and service was prompt. Would definitely return!

Our family always goes here because its a convenient location, fast service and fair prices. They pretty much make all of the Chinese and Asian cuisine favourites, and you cant go wrong with anybody them
Good Chinese food, reasonable prices, and large dishes. Staff were also very nice.

Visited this restaurant this week.  Formerly known as Rose Garden.  Food was fantastic, despite being packed with customers our dishes came out in a timely manner.  Seafood (fish and crab) tasted fresh, other dishes were very tasty.  To boost my rating to a 5star they really needed an extra server to serve drinks and maybe to clean up a bit better. We got everything we asked for but getting the attention of a server was difficult at times. Price was more than fair compared to other Chinese restaurants in the area. Must try
Good country style food. Reasonably priced.

Cozy simply place with no fancy deco. Took our friends there (15 of us around one table!) and had an amazing experience. Servers do not talk much but they are actually very nice friendly people. Their BBQ pigeon is our favorite dish, highly recommend!!
Rose Garden changed name to K&H due to copyright infringement.   Same restaurant, same management.  Place looks like a hole in the wall but food is decent and worth going to.

Good fresh food ... and fast.  Ive been ordering from here for years.  Love the BBQ pork fried rice.  And the wonton soup has a heavenly broth.  Good clean, fresh food.  (Rarely greasy.)  Remember to ask for the free pop that comes with your order.

Ordered vegetable tofu pot.  It was tasty consider it was requested to be cooked without both msg and sugar.  The service was on point. The price was a little over my expectation, $15.70 including gst. I would recommend this place.
Its not a good looking place but foods are not bad people are friendly prices its fair street parking only thought.

While I was in the area, I would only order chinese take out from this place. the portions are great,t he quality is fantastic, some of the best rice and noodles I have ever had (get the BBQ pork fried rice and chao mien, the chicken and broccoli with black bean sauce is to die for!) you even get 10% off if you pic up your food from the restaurant! when I had to move from the area I was supper bummed that I couldnt walk here to get my orders despite this I still try to order from here when ever I have the craving for Chinese food
This place closes late. Good food and beer. Not very appropriate for wheelchair. Maybe one if there is space by the entrance. Decent prices. Park on the street. Not a fancy place but comfortable.
Best price for deep fried pigeon 15$ each (most Chinese delicacies) set dinner was good 6 dishes youll get a free life crab
Opens late till midnight. Great spot when hungry. Food is delicious. Recommended the pork chops in apricot sauce. Priced reasonable.
Classic HK style family diner. Good seafood and prices to boot. go with a large group and enjoy this place family style including lobster three ways.

Great place for a cheap dinner for a group. Even better for Chinese late night snack called Dai Lan. If you are not Chinese, ask for the Dai Lan menu after 930-10pm it consist of smaller dishes and if you order enough you get free congee.
Fabulous cuisine, innovative dishes, reasonable prices. Decoration could use some upgrade. However not much to complain value for money.
This is a great little well known fact that this is one of the best Chinese restaurants in town the food is fresh and of good quality, I have been coming back this restaurant for close to 25years !!
so cheap. 8 dishes cost only 125CAD and have a big free can of rice. However, service is not good enough
Great place for a late night congee.
Good foods with good prices. Only not so goods are: street parking and slow service from staff.
Food taste great at a reasonable price but can use some updating.
First time here for dinner. A lot of special dishes that are not generally available in other Chinese restaurants. Food is good. Service is not bad. May repeat again for some other special dishes.

Went there with few other friends for dinner. The service was good and the food even better. The server recommended whats fresh and some dishes as there were so many to choose from. We all enjoyed the good immensely. We all said that we would be back again with others. Food was too good and I forgot to take pictures!
Great food at a super affordable price compared to other similar Chinese restaurants. A must order is the flaming crab with sticky rice. Just ask for that and the server will know which one

We had an outstanding experience at New Fishport Seafood Bistro on Marine Drive.  There is sufficient parking in front, but its quite packed during dinner hours.  The restaurant is clean, bright and has a good and welcoming atmosphere.  The service was friendly and helpful.  The food was exceptional.  Fresh ingredients and well balanced flavours.  We were particularly impressed with the fried rice (lots of crab meat).  Highly recommended.

The owner and waiter/waitress are friendly and welcoming. They are not pushy to ask you to order foods and expensive items. We were thinking to order four dishes but the lady told us unless we wanted to take left over home.  Otherwise, three dishes are enough for 3 of us.  She gave us complimentary soup. We ordered 1) Lingcod 2 courses ( Stir-fried Lingcod with Choy Sum and Steamed Lingcod with Special Sauce) and 2) House Special Soy Sauce Chicken. Dessert we had 3) Double Milk Custard and complimentary Vanilla Ice Cream. This is our first visit and 100% will return again soon.  I recommend to call ahead to make reservations as it was full house on Tuesday night.
Staff were nice. Food was great. Generous serving that we had to Take Home some food. To Go packaging was great; handled perfectly. Definitely, going back and next time, well invite our friends
Delicious food and excellent services
Seafood is always fresh and well prepared here! Dishes are creative and cannot be found in other Chinese restaurants. Highly recommended!
Lots of special and delicious dishes.  Some dishes need to pre-order. Make sure to book the table before you go.
Very flavourful, perfect seasoning, signature prawns were phenomenal. Definitely coming back!!!
Very tasty and reasonable price. One of the best Chinese restaurants Ive had in Vancouver and Ive tried many.

Very high quality Cantonese restaurant, normal environment but high quality food with high price, but definitely worth a try, I would say best Cantonese seafood restaurant in Vancouver, I really want to try the chef s selection but since 200-300 per person it is not in my budget, I would say maybe later lol( give me a special discount if owner see this post)
Came in busy, but they managed to seat us for 2. Food came very quickly, and the waiter is very observant to our needs.

Our new favorite Chinese food place in South Vancouver! The owner is nice and server are well trained to take care of your dining experience. Another bonus is that whatever you order, it comes with Free soup of the day, served on a medium size pot, for up to 4 people. They also have daily special menus which you can ordered 2 days in advance. Food portion and price are good and competitive. We ordered 2 dishes for 2 of us: fried rice and chicken cashew nuts. And it can last us for 2 meals!
Yummy food. Friendly staff. Happy customers!
Food is good and staff are friendly.  Prices are a bit higher but it reflects in the food.  There are several items that you need to order a day in advance.  Will return to try them.
This is my favourite place for the typhoon crab, no other place is as tasty. Their other dishes are very good as well and we always get good service.
One of the best Chinese restaurants I have tasted so far in Vancouver.
Delicious food, fair prices, and lovable service! Suggestion: dont go by yourself, all the dishes are group size, otherwise,  you will have food to-go!
Very nice food. Suitable for all types of gathering. Price is a bit on the higher side though.
Excellent food and service. I just had a great meal here which featured King crab served in so many delicious ways. Service was top notch and all the food was authentic and very tasty.
Excellent food and services. Thanks so much for Chief Leungs creative dishes and warm welcome from the owner Wendy.  We never disappointed
Great hospitality, owner came over and chat to make sure food is good, got complimentary soup, just like moms cooking in hk. Feeling the love.
Nice food and very friendly service. If you would like to try something different, here is the right place.
Excellent food options in the menu! Their seafood are the best
Price is relative high but the size portion is big and tasty, very good services. Highly recommended
Love the dishes here, very prompt and courteous service with excellent cooking. Cant thank the chef enough.

In particular, the bee fire meat crab is not only delicious, but the mandarin duck glutinous rice inside is also a must-have. The butterfly bone must not be missed. Will definitely dine here again if I have the chance.

highly recommended: Their chicken is very tender and ranks among the best in Vancouver. The seafood is also very fresh. The owner was very enthusiastic and gave us soup. The price is a bit expensive, $40-50 per person who doesn t eat seafood.

review_text: Delicious, worthy of the ceiling

Reasonable prices and fresh food.
A real gourmet canteen

I stopped in to check out the smoked salmon offerings. Top quality product and a variety of options available. I decided to have fish and chips while I was there. I had a piece of halibut. It was everything I want a piece of battered fish to be. Crispy batter, tender, flaky fish. Excellent fries and tartar sauce. The coleslaw was adequate, but not a show stopper. Its worth a trip, for sure!

Great store with more than just seafood items. In a pinch, you could come in and pick up dry pasta, fresh fruits and veg , and of course seafood. I normally come here in the summer for salmon and when the time is right spot prawns and they dont disappoint. A lot of traffic (as you can see from the other posts) are mostly commenting on fish and chips and their other cooked food. Again, its just a portion of what they do. The fish and chips are solid and the batter is not too thick. Got takeout and ate it 20 minutes later and was still crispy. Recommend calling the order in , especially if its getting close to lunch time as there is a high school close by and it can get crowded. People talk about the fries and they are good. For value and quantity, it definitely hits the spot. Also tried the curries eggplant halibut wrap. It was good. Maybe a bit mild for my tastes but for those wanting that light curry flavour with their fish, this would work for you. Parking in the complex , with the highschool crowd etc...can be a bit of a slog depending on the time. Though I find the best and easiest place to park is on the street.

After visiting their Victoria location last year, I was keen to go the Vancouver Location in Arbutus for having fish and chips. The fish was delicious, crispy and fresh as expected. We tried sockeye salmon fish, with potato fries, coleslaw salad. We also had the yummy bisque for the first time (a thick seafood fish soup ) with some garlic bread. The prices were very reasonable. Great portion size. The fish and chips dinner is enough for teo people. I will visit this place again for trying the other fish cuisines.
Halibut and chips. Enough said. Always fresh seafood. Friendly staff.

Definitely amazing! Ordered all kinds of deep fried fish and literally everything tastes fresh and amazing. Just a note that there is already tartar sauce in there so you don t really need to order more lol

Customer service was great in helping me decided what I wanted to purchase! Took the time to answer questions and find the right item for me. Food was also amazing, best fish & chips I ve had in a long time! A must check out when you re in the area.
Excellent fish and chips. Never have been disappointed and Ive had the halibut, ling cod, and salmon. Generous portion of fries!

My local take-away chippie serves up fresh helpings of Cod, Sablefish, Salmon, & Halibut. I find the portions to be generous & reasonable. Eat it while its hot otherwise it can lose its crunchy texture. The yam fries are a great option.

The best place in town for fish & chips (oh yes and basically any other seafood need you may have). While the fish & chips made from Halibut, Lingcod, and other fresh fish, and their freshly made chowders are really why I usually go here, Finest At Sea really is a seafood market in the first place. Always fresh, always well presented, always friendly.

The fish and chips are so good!!!! Theyll fry up cod, salmon, halibut, or sablefish, all of which taste amazing and are served with a hearty portions of fresh fries that are always feel slightly overcooked but still great. They also have other dishes, but I cant try them because that would mean forgoing the fish and chips.

I had the just fish option and considering the flavor, portion size, and price point I can say its well worth the experience. It was cod and they clearly season their batter which stays crunchy throughout the meal unlike other places where it gets soggy after a while. Also their tartar sauce is delicious. Will be trying more items from here.
Great selection of seafood, and pickled/smoked products. Large condiment section including fresh bread. Small bistro type area. Good prices. Good parking. Friendly helpful staff.
Great grilled halibut and chips. Excellent tartar sauce to go with it. This is definitely a family favourite when in Victoria.
Very good fresh fish. Would go again when in Vancouver
The fries were the best in town m! yurm chipotle mayo to die for
Great seafood boutique store. Food is awesome too!
Always enjoy dining and shopping at this shop. The seafood are really fresh and tasty. However its getting a bit pricey since last year .

I ordered takeout from here twice and both times I was very pleased with the quality of their fish and chips and the portion size. The fish has a great batter-to-fish ratio, tasted fresh (not frozen) and was very crispy as well as their fries. I no longer live in the area but if I were to visit kitsilano again I would love to dine-in and check out their market/ other goods.

Their shrimp sandwich is AMAZING! They also had these crab paste one time that were unforgettable as well! I usually come here for lunch but have also bought their marinated fish to go as well! Also very delicious!

Weve always been fans of Victorias FAS, so it made perfect sense, we continue the tradition in Vancouver, now that we have moved to the North Shore. FAS did not disappoint! We stocked up on FAS sockeye and rockfish filets, then added one healthy cold smoke tuna side as well. The front-of-house staff took time to get us the correct portions, then vacuum seal an extra lot for our freezer. I suspect it wont be long, until were back at Arbutus to stock up again. A special thanks to the team back in Victoria, (Rose, Dee-Lynn, and Aaron) for taking care of us for many years, and to the plant staff and fishermen/women for the hard work, and long hours bringing it to the shop. I highly recommend a stop at the FAS stores, and food truck, if youre visiting!
So good.  Is both deli and little cafe counter.  The fish is so fresh.  Comes with a TON of fries - would consider buying a 2-piece fish+chips with another person since youd still have lots to eat!

I cannot believe that after all these years I have not yet tried this hidden gem located minutes away from where I live. This place by far has one of the best fish and chips that Ive ever had in the city, including Steveston Richmond. If you live in Vancouver, come check out this place. Its a seafood shop, selling everything from fresh seafood, to salads and clam chowder. Theres an area to the side where you can order hot food like fish and chips and seafood sandwiches. I ordered for the first time today the lingcod fish and chips with a side of fries. It included a nice portion of creamy coleslaw and chunky creamy tartar sauce with dill slices in it. The beer battered fish was light and crispy, while fried to golden perfection. I will definitely be returning with my partner and friends.

Excellent seafood shop. Beautiful filets, fresh shellfish and smoked fish (try the candied sablefish), with a nice variety house prepared salads, and other ready made sides. Also various choices to craft a seacuterie plate with artisanal canned and jarred provisions. Off their made to order menu their lingcod fish and chips, shrimp roll and seafood bisque are great.

I love this place but keep in mind it is expensive. If you live in the area(Closer to North Van, Alot of homes in the area cost well over 2 Million) then you probably earn enough to not have to worry as much about your budget. But thats besides my point I live in Surrey. I go here when Im in the area I have work close by. They have a fresh selection of seafood, and a healthy selection of fine ingredients along the lines of white truffle olive oil(to me this is Fancy stuff as truffles are hard to grow and Even harder to store plus I hear chefs gush about these.) When I look at the assortment of oils and the limited but fresh selection peppers and cheeses. Im not joking my mouth starts to water. Im no chef but I love food then again who doesnt. Also I have been incarcerated which isnt something I like to say but it does give you a different perspective on food once you realize just how bad the food can be then you go to Fancy rich restaurants where the comparison or the spectrum is so vast and far apart is not even fair to call it a comparison. Its like trying to compare McDonalds to an Italian restaurant that serves fresh homemade pasta. You cant compare the two. Finest at Sea. Has it all in the name. They sell the finest and if you talk to the guys and gals here they will tell you exactly what your getting and when is the best time to buy certain fishes. They also have what they call a bistro Im not actually sure what that means. But you can order things like fish n chips. An amazing shrimp sandwich that just mmmm to die for. One Thing that isnt as good as it used to be and it was literally the reason I started coming here is sadly the clam chowder. They used to have a chef here and I call him a chef not because he cooked but because after he left you realized what a chef is. It isnt someone that can cook, its someone that truly takes pride when you come to tell him I came here just to spend money for your cooking. I came here because I think this is the best and nothing else has even come close to this soup. And when he left, sadly the clam chowder has never been the same. I dont know if he used a different method and never left the full recipe or if he would use a few different ingredients from a recipe that was already there but in my eyes I realized he was truly a chef because he elevated that dish to new heights. I hear a lot of people and also cooking shows say that but when you witness it firsthand you realize what that truly means. And its like taking a burger or a recipe from McDonalds and turning it into the burger nobody knows where it came from but everyone knows they want more of and they want to know who made it so that they could say thank you. And you know the sadest (dont know if thats a word but now I say it is) thing is... I never got his name because at the time I took if for granted I was younger and didnt appreciate life as much. Now that I go back and order the clam chowder it isnt as rich. There was a certain thickness to it that just isnt there anymore. And thats not to say it isnt good. Its just not as great as it used to be. And I hate to say that because maybe they try there best there and one of those cooks there see this and think you know F you I try to make it the best I could. But when you see the ingredients surrounding them and then you see the clam chowder barely has any clams or potatoes it feels more like just a plain watered down mushroom soup how can I say its the best when I have had better. But the shrimp Sandwich is still excellent and I love the fish n chips from here I really do. Im just giving my two cents here. I love the seafood salad and the Avocados Shrimp and Lime salad I think its called. My mom loves the orzo salad when they have it. But the one thing I can never leave without is the Salmon Pate. Mmmm it is the best I have had or found and trust me I am picky as all hell when it comes to calling something the best. In Short Finest at the Sea has the Finest you can find(Except that dam clam chowder IM SORRY It isnt.)

Possibly the best if not one of the best clam chowders I ve ever had... The soup is not overly rich or creamy and it is very heart, just perfect. A must try if you enjoy clam chowder. They have pre made refrigerated soups, perfect if you want to take home and heat up for your family!
best selection of fish and marinades in Vancouver

1st time in your Wonderful store .You have so much selection & giftie items for the Foodie too ! We pre-ordered your West Coast SEAFOOD BOIL Bucket  & picked it up yesterday to Celebrate in Whistler Canada Day ,All good keeping it maximum FRESH .Thanks for the ice . A sturdy reusable bucket came stuffed with pre-seasoned Summer garden veggies & Shellfish  we personally LOVE like  frozen Spot Prawns ,Crab and the list went on ...it came easy to transport & so so *Made to ORDER* What a Fabulous PARTY idea Thanks for the wax presentation paper & French bread .extras ..see you again ! Thank YOU      Finest At Sea

Great options for take-out meals and in-house shopping! Finest offers a wonderful selection of salads, jarred items- both local and imported, and their specialty-- the best quality seafood in Vancouver! Bon appetit!

Awesome spot for local seafood and other culinary products, premium pricing though. You can find spot prawns, stripe prawns, halibut, and all other kinds of fish here. They also have fresh bread, as well as herbs, spices, oils and lemons for your seafood. I really like this place, but its pretty expensive.
Pricey but great quality fresh seafood. We ordered their lobster boil bucket and were extremely impressed with it. Very friendly staff at the store as well.

Visited Victoria this past sunny week. Had halibut twice, OMG so  fresh. Felt very spoiled to be eating and cooking this ourselves, the best. No idea there was a store in Vancouver. Will be visiting that on a regular basis now we know it s there. Thank you Finest at Sea. You are the BEST.
Food here was fresh and delicious, curried halibut and eggplant wrap was the bomb. Prices werent too bad either, just dont go around 11:30-12:00 gets really busy due to the highschool nearby.
Fresh fish tacos and lots of outdoor seating. Panko oysters are for true oyster lovers. Giant 2 piece halibut and chips and freshest halibut.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: Newer restaurant that replaced Peaceful restaurant that was there prior. The GOOD: place was busy for a Sat night at 8pm so thats a good sign. Didnt wait long for a table for 2. Pleasantly surprised at the preset 2x combo meats + main + soup + 2 bowls of white rice for $56. So we ordered BBQ duck + pork, main was green beans w minced pork & soup of the day. The MEH: menu should have spelled out that the combo soup is the soup of the day; no choosing. We asked for hot n sour, but the server brought the daily soup instead. When asked why, she then said the combo soup has to be daily soup. I found the BBQ pork and duck very tasty and not too oily. The green beans w minced pork were perfectly crispy but not too deep-fried. Again, very tasty. Didnt care for the daily soup, as its just a thin broth w few veggies + few pieces of meat. Would have preferred the hot n sour Final bill w tax was just under $60.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: Great Chinese restaurant with very good BBQ items. We went here and got one of their set dinners that came with soup, lobster fried rice and 3 side dishes. We also got a set that came with Peking duck. The portions here were enormous and you will likely have leftovers if you dont go with many people. Overall I would come here again for their set dinners. Service was pretty good too considering how busy the storefront was.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: Really good, fresh legit Chinese food   good for Hong Konger taste buds. The servers are fast and friendly. Would come back!

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: On a busy evening, we got a table and the boss guy treated us very well.  There were a lot of customers eating but he came by to see how we were doing; a very nice and personable guy. The bbq Meats are great. Tables are a bit close to each - that would be  my only complaint

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: Amazing new Chinese BBQ restaurant. I came to dine-in with my family and got their 5 signature dishes menu which included: - House Special BBQ Platter (Roast Pork, BBQ Duck, Char Siu and Soy Sauce Chicken) - White Pepper Pork Tripe Soup - Lobster with Sticky Rice - Baked Codfish in Yuzu Mustard Sauce - Baked Beef Rib Their BBQ is all done very authentically. Roast pork is super crispy with a good mix of fat and meat. The skin on the BBQ duck is crisp and flavourful as well. If youve had their BBQ meat from the same restaurant in Richmond then you will know what to expect here, very high quality and delicious meats. Being a Chinese seafood restaurant as well, you can expect to order your traditional Chinese cuisine from here. What they also have sprinkled in are some slight fusion dishes that you will not find commonly elsewhere such as the baked codfish with yuzu mustard sauce and the baked beef rib. Their seafood is very fresh (both the lobster and codfish) and the beef rib is so amazingly tender. Definitely would recommend both those dishes. Overall very happy a new BBQ restaurant of this quality opened up in the neighbourhood. Service is very fast and friendly as well. Even though its their first days of opening, they already have line-ups for take-out BBQ. Will definitely come back more often and recommend this place to all who are in the area to check it out.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: Really authentic Hong Kong style BBQ shop. We had lunch there, ordered a 3 BBQs on rice and steam veggies. Good service and they gave us free daily soup. The roasted pork was the best.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: Love this place! Clean and good staff service. The bbq pork and roasted pork is so so good. Recommend you to try it!

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: Popped by to pick up some last minute dinner meat. Been meaning to check out, finally tried out. The half day and half skinny Char Siu ( aka BBQ PORK) cut was hands down the best Ive had in a long time. Better than Chinatown dollar meats,  TnT, and Richmond Master Hung. Id for back to try other items. The pic below shows Half of our 1lb $12.95/lb. The lady who served had an attitude/arrogance but the BBQ master was nice.

review_text: Excellent food at good price. Really large portion and very Hong Kong style BBQ. Service is good for a Hong Kong restaurant.

review_text: Nice little shop with a good lunch selection.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: The roast pork is always crispy. The best around Burnaby and East Van, of all the places I tried. Prices of most dishes are good. The only thing is that like many small BBQ stores, they only have the belly part of the roast pork, not the whole pig. This makes it less authentic in my opinion, and you cant choose different cuts, such as the butt area where the meat is lean, albeit tougher.

review_text: The bbq is very well priced and delicious!  Wish there was a better line up process but overall the food is delicious!

review_text: Good food, BBQ duck and pork especially recommended

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: Food here is legit. They have great service. And phenomenal BBQ duck and Roasted Pork. Affordable pricing and it s good af.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: My wife and I decided to try here since it took over Peaceful Restaurant. She was not impressed with the fact that we were the only couple (only staff was there). I told her to just enjoy the fact that all the attention will be towards us. The food brought back memories of the cooking that my mom cooked for me when I was a child. The salted duck egg with minced pork was almost as good (they should have mixed the egg into the pork) as what my mom made The BBQ hanging on the racks at the front has me wanting to go over and buy and take home in the near future. Im told that these guys were from the HK BBQ Master from Richmond and started their own business instead.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: Do yourself a favor and visit this Chinese restaurant. The service is great, the food is great and the portion sizes are amazing. Absolutely the best meal we had while in. There are lots of Asian restaurants in Vancouver however this has got to be one of the top. BBQ is always a good option when going out to eat and this is not exception. The BBQ pork is so tender and flavourful and the roast pork is so crispy. Highly recommend!

review_text: Its what you call Asian Fast Food.  Very fast and efficient.  Great bang for your money these days when eating out.  Portion size is plenty compared to other places.  As always some dishes were definitely better than others.  Stick to what they are known for and you cant go wrong.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: Cantonese BBQ Seafood opened up in the former Peaceful location on Kingsway. The little mini mall has a busy parking lot but you can usually find street parking (both free and paid). Weve been here a few times to grab a quick bbq lunch combo. But we finally visited for dine-in recently. In addition to their bbq service, they have a full Chinese seafood menu offering. We ordered the 3 item bbq combo (you pick and choose which bbq items you want but we opted for the roast pork, bbq, and soya sauce chicken). While the bbq price is higher than the lunch combos, you get more meat. Not a bad price when you consider how much the price of bbq duck has gone up lately. The duck was good... meaty and juicy. Roast pork has nice crispy skin. A welcome addition to the area for bbq. Pea tips were good too. And I like that we received complimentary soup to start and green bean soup for dessert. Really want to come back here and try some of their seafood combos. Update: We did return in October to try a dinner combo with a 2lb lobster sticky rice with 2 bbq items plus 1 other dish for $118 (we picked the sole fillets with veggies). We also added the Taiwanese cauliflower with lap cheung and bacon. Again, you get complimentary soup and dessert. Bbq items were as good as before.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: The food quality is above average. The price is reasonable. Variety could have been better though. I would recommend this place if you want to try some typical and authentic Cantonese food.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: Visited 2 weeks ago on a weekday, not very busy, not quiet, just easy to get a table for 2. Ordered 2 entries and it comes with soup of the day and dessert for free. Good quality food for the money! Definitely come back again and try something else on the menu Parking: Lots of parking behind the restaurant from London Drugs lot, free.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: One of the few places that offered a BBQ meats counter. Pretty decent and will definitely go back to try other dishes.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: Newly opened Cantonese BBQ restaurant on Kingsway busy Joyce area. Limited parkings. Busy and central location. Food was good. Came out quickly and hot. BBQ pork was very tasty and juicy. Yet very crunchy skin. We ordered double items plate. Half duck half BBQ pork. Duck was good too. Deep fried squid wasnt as crunchy as it should be. Beef green beans was heavily sauced and load of black beans. Over powering the whole dish.  Lastly, eggplant tofu scallops. Good amount of scallops and tasted fresh. Tofu was freshly deep fried before cooking into pot. Very few eggplant.  Tasted a bit too sweet than savory.  Overall a little bit too salty. I will ask for less salt next visit. Service was good and fast. They were very busy. Yet they were able to take care of the basic needs. Polite and friendly. Overall, it is a great addition for this area for Cantonese cuisine. We have enough hot pot or skewers restaurants in this area.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: Really solid spot for Cantonese eats! Portions are huge. Appreciated the free soup during lunch. We got the bbq duck and roasted pork with noodles for lunch, as well as a beef chow fun noodles. Prices were reasonable too.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: Although the restaurant appeared to be small and not fancy decorated, the barbecue food is famous at this place, and dishes is good size to fill your stomach. my best choice of food is barbecue ribs, barbecue pork with crunch skin and half fat CharSiu, tender meats and honey sauce that is so delicious. Parking at the back large parking lot but full all the time.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: Found this little gem just across from one of our go to spots on Kingsway. We ordered bbq roast pork, deep fried tofu, fried rice and a side of Chinese broccoli. The table menu, take out counter menu and the delicious crunchy roast pork was very similar to HK BBQ Master in Richmond. As it turns out, it is owned by the same person, mentioned by our server. So if you don t want to line up and wait for a table or do take out at HK BBQ Master this the place for you.

place_name: Cantonese BBQ Seafood Restaurant Authentic Cantonese Food (Order from our website & SAVE MORE!)
review_text: The roasted meat platter is amazing. The roasted pork was juicy and the skin was so crispy - like a fresh bag of Lays! Portions are big - good value for money. Food

review_text: Super busy, often long line up.  So popular, they ran out of most BBQ meats by 7pm.  Understandably, the roast bbq pork was the best. There are vegetarian options, limited but also very tasty. Downside: packed, long wait for food and service.  Hard to find parking.

review_text: I ve been here a few times now. BBQ duck, chicken and pork is solid. The tea on the table is great. Service is pleasant and atmosphere is cozy. I ve had a few dishes off the menu and they have come out way too salty, over cooked, flavours are drowned out and slow to arrive at the table. I guess it s just a matter of what you order and who is cheffing it up in the back? I give it a 4 star because I want people coming in and keeping the place busy.

review_text: I came in and bought 2 lbs of fresh prawns($63). The man at the counter was helpful and polite. The prawns were absolutely delicious! If you ever need some good seafood to impress people at a party, this is the place to buy from.

review_text: My girlfriend and I recently made the decision to eat more quality food so we decided to buy a range of seafood options from Daily Catch. We were blown away by the customer service and knowledge of the staff. We ended up getting steak fillets, halibut, tuna and shrimp. Everything was fantastic! My brother owns a seafood restaurant so I am very particular when it comes to seafood and the quality. After the seafood de thawed it had a sweet smell with no  fishyness . I was able to make raw poke with the tuna and it was divine. Would 100% recommend Daily catch and now we place bi weekly orders so daily catch has been crucial towards us leading a healthier lifestyle with amazing seafood! Thank you Daily Catch!

I recently had the opportunity to visit Daily Catch, a retail seafood shop that I had heard great things about. From the moment I walked in, I was impressed with the friendly and attentive customer service I received from the staff. They were more than happy to answer any questions I had about the products and make recommendations based on my preferences. The seafood at Daily Catch is absolutely top-notch. The freshness and quality of the seafood they sell is outstanding. They had variety of species to choose from and were all expertly handled and packaged. I especially enjoyed the local oysters and the fresh sashimi-grade tuna. The prices were very reasonable, and they had good deals on the specials of the day. I also appreciated the shops commitment to sourcing sustainable seafood. Its always good to know that the seafood Im purchasing is not only delicious but also responsibly sourced. Overall, I had an excellent experience at Daily Catch and I would highly recommend it to anyone looking for high-quality and sustainable seafood. The customer service is top-notch and the seafood is outstanding. I will definitely be back!
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the Amazing review Chad we can t wait to see you again!

review_text: Everyone is friendly and helpful. A great selection of fresh seafood. The lobsters, the smoked salmon treats, the freezer stocked with goodies, and other tasty offerings make this place a must when shopping on the Drive. We like to buy a whole salmon and have it filleted and wrapped for our freezer. Yesterday, live Spot Prawns were available. Excellent seafood market!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the outstanding review John! we work really hard and a hearing this from customers make it all worth while! Look forward to serving you again in the near future! cheers!

review_text: I am so thrilled to have discovered this little market on the drive. They have incredibly high standards, which means that we get only the best seafood out there. This store is kept so clean and free of clutter, that you just want to spend a lot of time looking around. They have everything from fresh cut fillets, fresh oysters, clams and mussels, to frozen and vacuum packed items done in store. They also have a variety of smoked products that are either frozen or ready to eat. What ever you a looking for, they got it! There are so many things I love about this store, and I hope that more people take a trip down to the Drive to experience what the Daily Catch has to offer.

review_text: Just great! I called because of the 100% Sustainable part, and Ill be back because theyre awesome. I know nothing about seafood, and when I called about picking up something on Valentines, the person I spoke to was super helpful, and listed many great options with friendly enthusiasm. They answered all my questions, and encouraged me to come in to see things for myself. So I did, Valentines after work, when I thought they would be slammed/fried/out of everything. Instead, I met Matt, who took time to recommend me his go-to (steelhead), as well as how to cook it -- he added his favourite marinade, gave me the time/temperature/technique, and what touches he likes to add for best flavour. He could not have been nicer or more helpful. It turned out great, was totally delicious, and helped me look good in front of the girl I like...! These guys are great -- Matt for sure. I appreciate them being sustainable, and being so awesome about it. I will be back, I recommend them to everyone, and most of all -- thank them for being great! Theyre awesome -- huge props to Matt -- thank you!
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Jesse! Look forward to seeing you again!

review_text: We enjoyed a delicious Wild Salmon Burger on Kits Day 2023 ~ appreciated that there was a Table & Chairs outside the store where you could sit to eat and enjoy. A small favour ~ It would be nice to have the option of different types of Buns, besides a White Bun ~ thank you!

Were thrilled to hear that you enjoyed our Wild Salmon Burger on Kits Day 2023 and that it was a hit with your group, even converting a self-proclaimed non-salmon lover! Your feedback regarding the bun options is greatly appreciated, and well definitely take it into consideration for future events. Thank you again for your kind words and support.

I need to go back and pick up some frozen shrimp. Love the selection in the frozen section. Keep up the great work!

review_text: This year we were late for canning Sockeye salmon.  After phoning several places and not having any success we stumbled on to 7 seas. Spoke with Stevie who said yes they had Sockeye. They have many other varieties of fresh and frozen fish and sea food.  And sauces and spices. I also talked with Cato, the store manager and knowledgeable about their products. They are oceanwise. Highly recommend this place.

review_text: What a great store. Their staff are Uber helpful - they provide lots of information on different fish choices and are will to explain patiently to someone I would be tempted to slap (that being me  ) Seriously good job team.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the honest review Peter! We appreciate you!!

review_text: First time at this store, heard about their specials for BCspot prawns and copper river salmon. It is a little out of the way for us but so glad we came. All the staff was so friendly and the young owner that was helping us is so knowledgeable and helpful. Everything looked clean and fresh. Nice to hear the same family had been in this business since the 80s. Another staff member highly recommended the salmon pate which is excellent :) we will be returning for sure.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for stopping by Jacqueline! (and for the kind words!!) We look forward to seeing you soon.  Check out our new Ceviche and up and coming Hawaiian Poke = )

review_text: The team is wonderful at this little seafood market. Tons to choose from, and the poke is amazing. They are sticklers for freshness and will cut what you need on the spot. You will find a large selection of frozen products like, octopus, Dungeness crab, and even bone broth and soups. Love this little store. Pop in while you re in the area.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Melissa. See you again soon!

review_text: Candied salmon is so good, especially the maple one, and employees are soo friendly! I went to buy some candied salmon as a souvenir before flying home and the employee was so considerate to even wrap it up securely before my flight and recommending the best way to transport it. Ill definitely be back next time Im out there.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Olga! We look forward to seeing you again!!  Safe travels :-)

review_text: Got some smoked salmon for our Eggs Benedict. Delicious and available in smaller portions. Owner is very knowledgeable and happy to share best practices when it comes to fish preparation and recipes. Excellent fresh fish selection.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Christian! We appreciate you.

review_text: Holy moly! Was their poke ever good!!! I was a bit skeptical at first but was SO pleasantly surprised! It was FULL AND PACKED with flavour! This is definitely my new go-to poke place!! Also, can t forget about the phenomenal customer service!
response_from_owner_text: Jenn - thank you so much , and Im so happy our bowl hit your high standards!  It was a pleasure to meet you. We hope to see you soon!

review_text: Man I love this place! The people here are so genuinely nice and always have great recommendations. The frozen crab stuffed salmon pinwheels are to die for. They even let me taste test an oyster while I was waiting. Really made my day today :)
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Alex, youre the man!  Try to eat an oyster a day for your daily recommended dose of zinc!  Its vital to good health!   Take care and see you soon :-)

review_text: Great family run.  Service was awesome and so was the fish
response_from_owner_text: Thanks George! So happy you had a great experience all around!

review_text: You can get lobster, oyster, fish at this fish market.

review_text: I shop at this 7 seas located on 4th regulary for the past 8 months as I am a private chef working closeby this location. 7 seas offer a wide variety of fresh fish and seafood. I usually go there to get shrimps, mussels, and a couple of different fish. The staff are always friendly and helpful. I have worked with James a couple  years back when I was working in the restaurant industry, and he is very knowledgable, friendly and always tries his best to meet the customers requests to make them happy! Last week, he had recommended to me their Arctic Turbot. I had tried it for my client and personally for myself, and we were impressed by how beautiful, succelent and buttery Arctic Turbot fish was. Now I have to say that Arctic Turbot is my top favourite fish. I am looking forward to try upcoming new fish/seafood they will be bringing in the store.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your kind review Kat!

review_text: Great family owned and operated business! A staple in Kitsilano

review_text: Your chowder is the absolute best I ve ever had, tying one that I had at Bodega Bay, CA, about 35 years ago. Been looking all this time for it s equal. I added a little milk and a sauteed spot prawn left over from last night. Btw your spot prawns are always excellent too!!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Bill!  We really appreciate your kind words and patronage!  We will see you soon, Im sure! = )

review_text: Amazing fresh seafood. The oysters, housemade tartar sauce, and clam chowder are the best!

Just bought some fresh cod fillets, and the fish was amazing! Employees were very friendly. The display is looking a lot better, and the fish is excellent. Highly recommend 7Seas and their products, especially the salmon candy dip!

review_text: Helpful, knowledgeable & cheery staff ready to showcase the beautiful selection of seafood they have! Love coming here. Easy 5 stars

review_text: Only ever had great service here. The mussels are amazing. Very fresh. Very cheap. They discard the ones that are no good. They explain to you how they are a living creature..... I would never buy vacuum sealed ones at Costco! Great store,  friendly service.

Love this store. I live in Kitts and shop locally and 7seas is my seafood shop. I really enjoy the crab and salmon cakes as well as the wonderful customer service. Its has a wonderful section of fresh seafood and I really like the fact that they are part of the ocean wise program.  Ive have recommended this store to many of my friends   Thanks 7seas

review_text: Store was only interested in taking orders but failed to fulfil them. Email announcements were inconsistent with the actual situation and wasted a 30 minute drive all the way to Kits and back home empty handed. Update: James (sorry!), the manager,  reached out and extended his apologies. Mechanical breakdowns do exist, so I just hope that there is clearer communicate for next time.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Jeffrey, Im sorry our boat hit a log and didnt allow us to fulfill your order for fresh BC spot prawns yesterday.  We did our best and are fulfilling orders today (1 day late) if you still want your spot prawns, feel free to come get them!  Wild fishing is not as consistent as farmed fish or other farmed proteins, and that makes it hard to predict outcomes.  Our humble apologies as we tried our hardest and we hope you give us another shot to fulfill your needs in the future.  Thanks for your time and the opportunity - James (not Steve)

review_text: Decent variety of fresh and frozen fish and friendly staff. They also offer a good rewards program for regular customers.

response_from_owner_text: Hello itsme ovrdar, Most fresh fish goes out of season during the autumn and winter months. Looks forward to our almost fully fresh seafood case in the summer months!  If you came recently, you should have found fresh options for:  cod, halibut, char, salmon, steelhead, rockfish, sole, along with live mussels, clams, oysters, and many more!  Im sorry you didnt see those in the display case.

review_text: Came here to grab some squid for paella, I am not sure how old it was but it basically disintegrated into mush in the paella. It smelled ok, but who knows.  This place is expensive and questionable quality.
Dont think leaving 40 bones in a 1lb  piece of salmon is acceptable. The explanation is its processed in Richmond plant now so its ok. Dont think so
response_from_owner_text: Hi Donna, this was a miscommuncation. Im sorry for your poor experience. Please be sure to ask for fish that is pin boned removed at any fish monger as fin fish almost always contains bones (excepting shark and sturgeon which has cartilage instead). Usually bones are all removed but admittedly, sometimes they are not based on manpower or coordination of inventory and supply options.

review_text: Bought supposedly fresh spring salmon here yesterday. When we got home the fish rather than being firm was mush with an  off  smell. This place should be AVOIDED. There are so many good place for fish in Vancouver. No reason they should be in business.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Stanley, Im sorry about your terrible experience back in 2020. Come try us again and speak to the new manager. Hell be happy to make sure you get the best seafood for your needs!

review_text: paid an arm and a leg for BC spot prawns here assured enthusiastically by the gentleman behind the counter that they were fresh and amazing. got them home to find half of them mushy and bordering on inedible.  not okay and I wont be back.  with so many fresh fish shops in Vancouver this kind of inconsistency is not appreciated.
response_from_owner_text: Hi J P, Im so sorry to hear about your experience 2 years ago. Spot prawns are definitely a fickle creature. Hopefully youll give us another shot to earn back your trust!

review_text: Their seafood is gross. Super intense  fishy  smell. Went back to the store about my experience and brushed off. Definitely won t return.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Lars, Im so sorry to hear that. I do apologize for your negative experience and thank you for your honest feedback. That you should feel to leave a 1 star review and negative commentary , we really must have done something wrong.  I am so sorry about this. I would love to know more about your experience so I can work to make it better in the future. Sometimes these things happen though it is not okay!  We typically have a very strong rotation on our fresh options and perhaps something slipped through the cracks. Please feel free to call me (James) at the shop (604-732-8608, so we may discuss and for a chance to make things right. Kindest Regards, James

review_text: AWFUL. After many years of buying fish here, just pulled Black Cod out of the oven to find it was liquified - most likely spoiled from having got wet. Disgusting experience, having to do dinner triage on protein. Thanks Seven Seas for ruining our dinner and our evening. We wont be back.
I was there today at 6:15 and they turned me away saying they were closed. Just a heads up that they close earlier than 6:30.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Margaret, Im sorry for the confusion. I dont know what the hours were like before. We are currently open from 9:30am-6pm DAILY!

review_text: Wth! Too expensive

response_from_owner_text: Hi V, Im sorry to see a 1 star review - what can we do to make your visit with a 5 star?

review_text: We ve been patrons of this excellent fishery for nearly a decade. Lots of really fresh seafood of many descriptions. Brian and Ray run an outstanding enterprise, quality is a prime factor. The barbecued salmon is to die for. Amongst many other seafood stuffs, too numerous to mention. Professional and friendly advice too.

I would like to take this opportunity to thank Brian and his crew for all there effort and bringing in quality product which has absolutely enhanced my culinary experience . Definitely recommend. Thanks again Cam

Fresh fish haven ! Started my day with fresh uni and wasabi tobiko. Gave them an extra star for the service . A young man who goes by the name , Happy , served us with a smile and went the extra mile . Located in Granville public market in Vancouver.
Very nice indoor farmers market to visit when in Granville Island.

My family was visiting Vancouver from Montreal last week, and was introduced by our friend to Seafood City because it sells fresh fish straight from Japan.  We were looking for sashimi grade fish, particularly Hamachi.  They don t have it at the time, but they introduced Shima Aji, which was pretty close to what we were looking for, and we were glad to follow their recommendation.  We also purchased  Bluefin tuna, and of course the toro was very fresh.  We were very happy with the quality of sashimi grade fish we got there, and will definitely visit the place again the next time we go to Vancouver.  Thank you Seafood City.
Found sashimi grade fresh fish from Japan !!! They detailed clean and filet deboned it !!! Great place for some unique seafood ingredients !!

I had a pleasant experience there even though I just wanted to buy so little sea urchin. After knowing that I wanted to try sea urchin for the first time, the guy there offered to sell me a section of the tray, which he needs to cut the portion off of the tray. He prepared a little bowl along with a fork and knife and condiments for me.
Always great selection of whole fresh fish

I trust Seafood City for its premium fresh live Dungeness crab. Friendly and helpful staff in a clean working environment, they ll package that healthy, happy, juicy meaty crab for ya. Around $20/lb in late July 2021. Paid parking outside I think was around $1.40 for 30 minutes. Thanks guys the family LOVED the crab I steamed up for dinner.
Came by Seafood city to get sashimi grade fish. The quality is really good, and the price too. I plan on coming back to try their other fish :)

Seafood City is our go to place for fresh fish. They have great variety and friendly service. We can also use our own containers. Saturday mornings are usually best to get fish for sushi (usually we get hamachi, chutoro, hotate and ikura).

These guys helped me out for years, finding unique fare for both my labs (I am quirky Bio teacher) and for family meals. They dilligently call if your on a specific list, they care about their product. I am a very happy patron, and plan to be for years. Seafood City is a great business that deserves your business and patronage.
Customer service was excellent! Then man helping was super friendly. The BBQ salmon and maple nuggets were a fave! Went there twice in one day.

Great selection of West-coast  and international seafood, very friendly service, many of the products they carry you cannot find in other fish shops, they are busy in Granville Island so you know the product is very fresh. Ive been shopping there for over 15 years and have always been happy with the quality and freshness of their products.

The seafood is always fresh. The people know what theyre talking about and tell what is good that day. A bit pricy but you definitely get what you pay for. A consistently excellent place to buy seafood.
Been to this store twice. The same nice lady loaded me up with a variety of ready-to-eat salmon treats, and then with sockeye salmon sashimi.

This is by far the better place to shop in GI for seafood. Owner is passionate and clearly teaches staff well. I always ask them for tips about preparing new fresh items and theyre always super knowledgeable!
Simply the best! Crab cakes over there are absolutely insane! Big ups to Brian! 100% recommend it.
Great service and fresh seafood!
Bryan and crew have some of the best available seafood in the city. Great service and an evolving selection of local and imported products.
Omg amazing. I love fresh seafood and they have delivered. Service was great. Highly recommended!
Very helpful and great quality fish. They even offered to fillet the sushi grade snapper for free.
Great place for all your seafood needs -- scallops, seabass, prawns. Thank you Brian for procuring the white anchovies especially!!
best place to get seafood in Van.  quality and service is top notch.
Fresh fish. Lobster.
Been going here for years! Always top Quality friendly best selection in the city. Family run go support them!
Excellent service, very responsive & they delivered some great langoustines for me
Lively fresh fish. Bought salmon here to make gravlax and it was delicious.
Great fresh seafood for sale there. Will be back to buy more.
Always great seafood and the staff super attentive
Great smoked salmon straw candy

review_text: Awesome customer service and products, very professional crew!
Really friendly and helpful staff! Helped me a bunch and saved me money!
Great place for fresh fish..
fresh fish! thx

Fresh seafood
Good assortment. Everything is fresh.
