Visitor area.  Good place to have a walk.
There are a variety of fish, meat and food. You can find raw oysters and sell high-quality steaks by cut and production region.
This is a place where you can buy and eat raw fish. They also sell a variety of seafood.
You want to buy good food and cook at home? This is the place to go. Expensive, but good. You just want to eat and drink? Forget it. The usuall disgusting junk food - only more expensive.

This place is horrendous. I had been going there for weeks and each time I asked about whether the fish I was purchasing was oceanwise. I was always told it was. One time though, I purchased some prawns and I just thought these cant be oceanwise based on the type and location of prawn. I was also suspicious because the owner said oh yes, theyre wild when I asked if they were oceanwise, and when I told him that had nothing to do with being oceanwise, he then just said oh yeah, they are oceanwise too. I looked it up and sure enough, not sustainable caught AT ALL. I then realized that this place is not even listed as an oceanwise retailer! Also, the prawns were inedible. They tasted like chlorine and we gagged on them. I will never shop here again and encourage anyone who cares about buying products that are actually sustainable to avoid this place as well. Lobsterman (also at GI) does have oceanwise products as do lots of other places in the city.
This entire place is for tourists only. Expensive and not many choices. Parking is very bad. Don t go this place. Totally trap.

Delicious, fresh, local seafood - what more can you ask for! These guys are great. Ive picked up at their Fishermans Wharf location and one of their North Shore spots - both easy and high quality. They have an easy to use online platform, and a great selection.  I never buy seafood anywhere else!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for this review Anna, and we appreciate your ongoing support as a member! We are so happy to hear you love our wild and sustainable caught Canadian seafood selection!

review_text: We have ordered from Skipper Otto for 3 seasons now and absolutely love their products. We get our orders shipped to Ontario and have never had an issue, we love the quality, freshness, and value. We would definitely recommend Shipper Otto to all fish lovers out there. Keep up the great work guys! John & Virginia
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much John and Virginia! We so appreciate your support as members and so happy to hear you love our seafood!

review_text: Great location to buy fresh seafood, especially the spot prawns in May & June! They are not cheaper compared to the ones at the supermarkets, but you definitely get the freshest seafood of all! If you live in Vancouver, I recommend this place, why bother go all the way down to Steveston?
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for the review Youngsung!

review_text: Excellent initiative. The staff are friendly and will do their best to accommodate requests.  Bought some fresh sustainably caught sockeye salmon and it tasted great!

Our family has been members of Skipper Otto for the last few years. The quality of the fish is amazing, it s convenient to order and pick up and the benefit to community and supporting small, local independent fishing families aligns with our values. Thanks for doing what you do!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much Saul for this lovely review. We appreciate your support as a member and so happy to hear you are enjoying the seafood we provide directly from local independent fishing families in Canada.

review_text: Ive been a Skipper Ottos member for over 5 years. Love the ease of ordering online, and so many pickup locations for frozen items. Great selection of seafood too- scallops in the shell, albacore tuna, sablefish, lingcod cheeks, smoked salmon... A picture of the Fisherman who caught your seafood is on the package so you know exactly where it came from and can say a little thanks before eating. Fresh items is a Thursday evening pickup at Fishermans wharf- think spot prawns, mussels or live crab. Great business that I will continue to support.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much Sheri for this review! We are so lucky to have you as a long time member, and so happy to hear you love our products and to know exactly how and when your seafood was caught by Canadian fishing families. Thank you for your continued support!

review_text: We have been members of Skipper Otto for several years.  The quality of the products are outstanding. Its easy to order online.  Its easy to do pick-ups at Fishermans Wharf and at community partners (e.g., Choices).  We believe in the way they do business: supporting local fishing families who catch seafood using sustainable methods.  Every time weve chatted with Skipper Otto staff, weve come away enriched by the conversation and full of admiration for their commitment to our oceans.

Ive been a member since their second year as a Community Supported Fishery. They have made many changes over the years to add more selection and make it easier to order/pick up. Every thing is delicious! But the best part is all the effort they put into educating their members about the fishing industry and the lives of the fishing families. I love the videos from the boats, the emails telling what to expect from the season, and updates when a salmon run doesnt open as expected.

Great quality, good feeling after supporting local and the staff is just beyond every expectation! Everything about Skipper Otto is great. Have been with them for two years and without hesitation I will sign up fro the next one... and hopefully many more to come! Thank you Skipper Otto! And  hoping you just keep introducing lesser known products - I am always in for that.

Been a member for a few years now. Its a great way to always have enough great tasting seafood on hand. Theres always staples (salmon, ling cod etc) available and then certain catches that are only around for a short while. Ideal sizes for 2 and 4 servings. Super easy to order and pick-up. Even better how it supports the fishermen/women directly.

This place is the BOMB. Sustainably caught seafood at a price that equitably covers the small business fishermen s wages. Their canned albacore tuna is a whole new experience of canned tuna - not tinny and fantastic real tuna taste! Sign up for the delicious seafood but stay for the recipe ideas, service and collective greater good

Love having access to fresh local fish all year round. The Fishermens Wharf is an easy place to pick up and to see what else is on the menu.  Skipper Ottos has an easy to use online platform.  Support your local fisherperson and join the Skipper Ottos community.
Sustainable, quality seafood and great support for the local fishing community. Ive never bought fish anywhere else since having Skipper Otto recommended to me. Plus, a great site!
Delicious fish caught by reputable fishermen. Great communication. Easy pick up at a store nearby. Whats not to like!
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Shirley! Were so glad youve enjoyed being a member:)

review_text: I am very fortunate to know and be part of Skipper Otto! One regret is, I wish I could have known this amazing company like ten years ago! Love the quality of food, excellent customer service and reasonable price. Highly recommend.
Delicious, carefully prepared, sustainable seafood from fisher families - by purchasing from Skipper Otto, you re supporting small, family-owned businesses. Plus they have sushi-grade salmon!

Quality, selection and peace of mind for support local fishers is the best combination for putting nutritious and fresh food on my familys table.  Thank you Skipper Otto, you have never let us down!  :)
Community supported fisheries Sign up now to get in for next year!
If you are going to Granville island .. drop by the wharf
Skipper Otto is a place after my heart: local folk catching local seafood and serving local folk.  This is what fishing is all about.  This is what enjoying local is about.
Get your membership and join this great business. Regular prices but you have the guarantee youre getting sustainably obtained fresh fish, all while supporting a local, family business.
We love the fresh community supported seafood program.

I always like to support local business but not at my own expense. We went to buy 2lbs of spot prawns today. The gentlemen fished them out from the tank using this yellow crate. He then proceed to weigh the prawns inside this plastic crate (hence including the weight of the crate along with the prawns). All the while there is no scale display facing the customer so nobody knows what the actual weight of it is. Came home and weighed the prawns on my kitchen scale 1.7lb. I might be nitpicking here, and honestly I don t care about the money, it s just shaddy business practices. Whatever. The prawns are still delicious. Edit: I response to the owner, that s great that you guys do that. May I suggest 1) letting your customers know this before hand. 2) getting a scale that has a display that faces the customer.
response_from_owner_text: Hi J X, Thank you for your feedback.  I want to assure you that our scale is certified and set at -1.1lb as that is the tare weight of the yellow basket. The spot prawns do retain some water once they are taken from the tank and our staff typically adds 0.1 - 0.2lbs worth of spot prawns to the basket to make up for water retention. I can not speak for your exact experience however we do typically shake the basket once it is filled with prawns to remove excess water and this step may have been missed.  I do apologize that you were shorted weight and we would be happy to make it up to you the next time you are in the neighborhood. Best Regards, Coldfish Management

I build a fluval panoramic aquarium...looks great.. Thanks Sam!

A great stock in aquarium supplies and high quality fish. My main interest is discus and I find that the quality of these types of fish are to a higher standard that some other stores Ive been to. Very apparent that Sam knows his stuff as he is very knowledgeable and can take the time to explain if you are uncertain about certain areas of the hobby.

When I had walked into the store, the first thing that tranced into my mind first, was the glimpse of the neatness of the product ailses. Everything  in the compartment of wares were decently organized, so you could really scroll through the store with ease. The pricing was reasonable, sometimes the products were cheaper by a couple of bucks and some other products that were very expensive, for instance, seachem paraguard-250 ml being priced at a whoping $30. The fish tanks had a excessively a average price on them, so nothing special about that, although some of the tanks were more on the expensive side. So pricing was pretty standard for an average store like this. There was a lot of selection on meds, fish foods filter medias at a pretty cheap price, so this was one of the few things that stood out from this store. Now, the fish selection. The pricing was fairly reasonable and there exceedingly lots of fish to choose from. Some of the fish were very appealing, their colors gleaming across the glass, for instance, the cardinal tetras and rummy nose tetras. They were a standout for me, because the quality and the looks of the cardinal tetras were some of the most colourful ones I had ever seen in my 15 years of pain, compared to aquariums west, which looked like the terrified faces of the people dying at Travis Scotts Astroworld concert. Most of the fish were healthy, however I had spotted a couple of dead or dying fish in the tanks, and several of the tanks were very cloudy and filthy, for instance, the goldfish tank, so that is one thing to improve on in this store, is to have a daily check on the fish, and quarantine sick fish and dispose dead fish. One thing I was dissapointed in, was the bettas in cups. They were unfiltered, and was very cramped, so next time try to make a filtered betta set up and try to upgrade the cups to small acrylic tanks. Finally, the customer service needs a bit of improvement, because the owner looks like he experienced vietnam flashbacks. When I did some communication with him, he didnt show much enthusiasm and  replied to me in a monotonous manner. Also when I was try to pick a schooling fish for my 32.5 gallon aquarium, he did what the call the asian death stare(my dad does this a lot) so it was a bit uncomfortable, felt like I was the victim of the John F Kennedy assasination, but eventually I got a bit used to it. Henceforth, this is a pretty good, average fish store with a couple of quirks, and I reccomend this store to anyone who doesnt care too much about customer service, but wants some high quality schooling or centerpiece fish including a good selection of fish supplies.

Very sneaky and not honest store. Be aware.! I went to buy spot prawn today  $24.99/lbs.. bought 6lbs, was told to pay $170 . Just wondering $25*6=$160.. Asked cashier why $170 instead of $160. Staffs on the floor tried to fool me around.blah blah blah. Finally they said they charged extra $10 as tips. R u kidding? I suspected they recently changed their owner. I used to be a loyal client for over 5years. Recenlty notice all old staffs disappeared...all new faces. Will not go back and suggest whoever view this comment not going there.

This is a very unfriendly and bad customer service place. During my one week visit to Vancouver, I found this place on Google and decided to drop by for some fresh seafood. Upon entering the store, my family and I already received an unwelcome look (not sure if it was just precaution approach because the store is located in a rundown part of Vancouver). Then when I ask for the price for lobster and crabs, they told in, a bad tone, me the price much more than the posted price then what it s written on the sign. So we just walked out and will never plan to come back. Google rating for this place is not realistic. Not recommended!
Dont come here if you actually want seafood thats fresh. You can smell the rotten seafood from miles away.

I would give this place a -2000 rating. It was a shock going in there. They do not practice humane treatment of the cruststions. They are piled in tiney buckets without oxygen bubbles. The crabs and lobsters are dying slowly by suffocation. Its disgusting! One crab it seemed was desperately trying to get out. I did not expect to see such cruelty. The fish are stuffed into small tanks. I will never go there again!!

There is no doubt that it is a black shop. WeChat group sells it called Haida Fresh. The fish/shrimp delivered are too lazy to even put ice on them. They are delivered downstairs at night and the meat is so rotten. When buying salmon, you must make it clear that you don t want the fish head. The head is 3.99 and the body is 6.99. Then they will sell it to you for 6.99. Dont just yell and say you didnt make it clear.
This shop is a black shop. The shop floor is wet and there is no parking space. The service attitude is bad. The boss speaks badly to the customers. Opinions are met with bad words, VIPs be careful.

Local, multigenerational family run business. Longliner Seafoods never disappoints. I ve been coming here for a few years now for my seafood, and could never go anywhere else - it is always super fresh, and super delicious. Their organic spring salmon is some of the best I ve ever had (highly recommend), and their smoked salmon selection is fantastic. I always go for the peppered nuggets (super moist and flavourful), the double smoked, and the cold smoked spring - they re the only people I ve seen who cold smoke spring salmon! The service is always wonderful and they often go above and beyond. It s a bit pricey, however it s expected for the quality and location. I have and will continue recommending this place!
Even if it looks busy, get in there and buy the Candied maple salmon. They do get to people pretty quickly. The salmon was still tender and the flavor was perfect with beer.
Super tasty smoked salmon. They are a bit pricy but it was worth it. We tried garlic and honey salmon. I prefer the honey salmon but others in my party are split 50 50.

Amazing salmon in all different tastes and flavors! Definitely one of the stand out stalls for me at the market. I only ordered a few pieces of smoked salmon since I didn t have anywhere to store the food, but I wish I did because this fish is super well done! The maple glazed salmon nuggets are the best. The staff here was also really helpful in providing us recommendations and answering questions so kudos to the team.

Bought wild King salmon and seafoods is very fresh. Caroline & Mangi provided great customer service. They are the best! The owner Dave is friendly and helpful too. I would highly recommend buying their seafoods.

They have a good selection of seafood and more reasonable prices compared to Longliner on the other side of Granville Public Market. Their products are all very similar in quality. They also sell foil packaged salmon that does not need to be refrigerated. Good idea for any gifts to bring back home.
The candied salmon from this counter service fish spot in the Granville Market is amazing. By amazing, think: Its like crack. Yeah. Its that good. Really, really good.
If I could add more stars, I  would. Amazing Pepper Salmon Nuggets..done the right way.  Moist and delicious. Best ever!
I got a little bit of all the smoked fish. The double smoked salmon sticks are some of the best smoked salmon Ive had. Service was also great.
Seafood was looking good small nice seafood place inside food market at Granville Island
The maple syrup candied salmon is worth the hype. Not overly sweet. It s yummy!
The smoked salmon is totally worth the drive and the parking hassle of Granville island. A must try!
Nice place. Great customer service. Salmon was super delicious and very fresh.

Im celiac and have not had crab cakes for over a decade. We went there on Sunday and found out their crab cakes were gluten free. Oh my goodness they were so tasty!!! We are going to be buying crab cakes from there for the rest of my life!!

Great candied salmon and amazing service! We were helped and when we told him we would buy 3 small pieces to try first, he gave us those pieces for free to try. We really appreciated that. After trying them, we bought a box of them!

In Granville Island market. Parking a real pain in butt sometimes. This is an excellent fishmonger, lots of specialty items like caviar and king crab. Lots of different smoked fish. Good prices. Fast attentive counter staff.
Best place in Vancouver to buy candied and smoked salmon! On top of that, the staff are absolutely lovely and I always leave with a smile. Highly recommend this gem on the island!
Bought the sealed smoked salmon to take back to Ontario. Ate it 3 weeks later and it was very good with capers, cream cheese, and red onion.

Stopped by to pick up a small bowl of maple syrup glazed candy salmon and smoked peppered salmon. You can do a half and half 100g bowl so you can try a little bit of both. The smoked peppered salmon was a bit dry and the maple syrup salmon wasnt as sweet as I was expecting. Overall it made for a small, tasty treat. The staff were very nice and quick with service.

Definitely one of the busier joints in the Granville Market and had a big line on Saturday at lunch time. Came back later and no wait. Lots of smoked fish selections and of course a ton of salmon varieties. Solid flavors.

Going for a healthier snack option, got my ready-to-eat seafood fix from Longliner Seafoods.  Smoked Mackerel for savoury and Maple Syrup Glazed Salmon Nuggets for sweet craving.  Both fish are of good quality, texture and flavour are on point, one can tell great care has been poured over these creations by tasting them.  The seafood selection is vast, the fish is stacked neatly, the display looks clean and pleasant.  This shop is a great stop for quality seafoods at Granville Market.

Hi.........normally I would rate you *5* without a second thought but today I have to drop that to a 3 because yesterday my husband picked up some Dungeness Crab for $34.19  0.222kg and it left an awful lot to be desired.  We have had your crab so very many times previous to yesterday and it has been marvellous!! but yesterdays was not good.  It was mushy and had a fishy smell that we have never detected before.  I ate it but I have to say, I kind of buried it in cocktail sauce so I might not notice the mushy texture;  my husband didnt eat all of his portion which is a complete rarity for him - hes like Mikie - he eat anything.  I just wanted to let you know we are disappointed but want to continue buying from you but we may just think twice first.   I am sorry to be negative because weve never been disappointed before.  thanks for reading..... Rose Jorgenson-Mills
Their customer service needs improvement. I tried a variety of their ready-to-eat salmon treats. They were just alright.

Charge premium prices for fish but quality is questionable. I have on more than one occasion seen worms crawling on the fish in the case (flicked off by the staff and served anyway). Today I bought a piece of cod ($25/lb) with a sign that said fresh and local only to get it home and find a big parasitic worm next to it. From what I can tell online, this only happens when the fresh fish is not filleted right away but is kept whole, giving the worm a chance to borrow through from the fishs intestine out of the fish. Sure, its probably fine when cooked thoroughly. I did cook it but could not enjoy it and threw half of it away. Found another cooked worm on my dinner plate and just couldnt finish it.
Fish out front looked great, but bought a pack to take home and was nowhere near as nice.

I bought a red spring salmon fillet on Saturday. Had it for dinner the same day. I was given ice to pack with it. I brought it home immediately to the refrigerator. The fish had a very fishy smell to it. That indicates to me its not too fresh. Ive had salmon from other grocers to compare & no other places had fishy smell to my salmon. Very fresh & high quality fish is supposed to be scent less & not fishy. I wonder if its because not too many people were buying the spring salmon fillets & they were there for a while. Im kind of disappointed in this place seeing it is supposedly a high end seafood store in a high end location. I doubt Ill be back to do business again.
I paid for two packages of smoked salmon and the cashier only wrapped up 1 not happy with this place make sure you check your packages after you buy them

Pretty disappointed with my experience. I bought the candied salmon and paid with my credit card, they called me back to say their internet was down so they would have to use the old school method of swiping my card with the imprinter - they broke the chip on my credit card with the imprinter so now Im in Vancouver for 2 days with no way of paying for items on my card. When I called to tell them what happened they offered nothing in compensation (not that I expect much) and basically said sorry, thats too bad. I wont be back. The candied salmon wasnt worth the experience in terms of quality or customer service.
Terribly ran, thought I d give them a shot and I will not be returning. Wasted a large sum of money here and all the fish were filled with worm like parasites. The staff were also extremely rude.

Im tired of vendors who think their personal mission to enforce mandates are more important than relating graciously with their customers. Longliner is one of those. Im unimpressed, get your priorities straight.

review_text: My favourite fish shop in the Greater Vancouver Area! They always have an amazing variety of the best seafood. Very friendly and helpful staff!

place_name: Village Fish & Oyster Market Inc The
review_text: Amazing selection of fresh and wild caught fish. I tried their Halibut (local), Spring Salmon (local), Branzino and steelhead Trout. Lovely staff as well. 100% would recommend if youre looking for high quality, fresh, wild caught fish.

place_name: Village Fish & Oyster Market Inc The
review_text: Cannot say enough great things about this place. Delicious fresh food of the best quality, served by courteous staff. My favourite place to shop. Dont EVER get rid of the old screen door! Wonderfully old school in every way. FIVE STARS...excellent!!!

place_name: Village Fish & Oyster Market Inc The
review_text: Cute store and fresh food! Tried the Fish of the Day Taco Bowl for $15. Good sized portion, it s filling and you don t feel gross after. Definitely a hidden gem in West Vancouver.

review_text: This is the only place I buy my fish now, the staff is always so friendly, the fish is always so fresh and the price is hard to beat. They have a new lunch menu with soups and sandwiches which is very delicious. Ask for Nell, she is always so helpful and friendly!

review_text: Best Fish Market On The North Shore:  I used to live in W Van, shopped  here a lot. We live near Deep Cove now, but VFM is worth the drive to W Van. Always, fresh + excellent selection. Haddock & spot prawns are two of my faves. I only have one small complaint & that is that at times they sort of oversell us more than we need. It would be nice if they sold restaurant size portions like they do @ Granville Island.

review_text: Extremely dissapointed with the service. I called in 3 weeks ago letting them know what I needed to pick up. I gave them early notice because I knew not all of the items would be regular stock. I was assured that everything would be there and ready. I showed up to find out that they had no record of my order, and only had 1 of the 4 items I needed. I put my faith in their ability to stay organized and was let down. Definitely will never support this business again.

review_text: Great service. Price reasonable. Cash only
Fresh Seafood. Lots of selection at a fair price!
Lots of selections

Great great seafood. The razor clams were so fresh and plump. All live and kicken in the bunch.  Crabs looked huge and fresh.  Only thing that doesn t make it a 5 star experience. It s cash only and the service is typical old school chinese abrupt and gruff.
Long line up for live spot prawns...
Fresh and affordable!
Not as cheap as super market in Richmond. Fresh fish and good service
Fresh seafood supply. Unfortunately it is closed. Not sure for renovation or permanently.
Seafood was fresh

Let me start by saying that honestly, the seafood here is great and fresh, and you can find stuff you dont find elsewhere and prices are reasonable, BUT dont expect anything else. They only do Cash which is very very annoying as you have to run bring cash and come back, they dont speak a single word in English so its very very hard to communicate with them we had to translate through Google and show them what we needed at some point.  The lady that works here is very sweet, and she tries, but the males are very rude, and they yell a lot. My friend went to bring cash before we knew the total price so we were short of 50$ and said we will go bring more hold on but the guy started screaming in Chinese and just dropped some of the stuff we brought back to the tanks and kept only the food we had the cash for at the moment (our order was 200$, for this amount i expect a better treatment at least! Plus, we were about to go bring more cash!!) But they didnt understand us. We didnt understand them its just a mess! I was annoyed that i couldnt get the rest of the stuff i wanted, and after that , I was not willing to go bring more money and spend it here! Also, if a Chinese customer comes even after you, they get to pass you and pay first even if youre standing there first, so just expect that.
We called for the price of their fresh crabs. The guy answered the phone was so rude and with super bad attitude.  We ended up going somewhere else . They dont deserve a penny of our money .
Called them to ask if they sold the fish I wanted, before I could finish my question the guy said he was really busy and put the phone down on me. Poor customer service and will never get my business

It made me extremely sad seeing in the window all these huge fish crammed into one tank all touching each other, not able to swim but stand still flapping their fins. Now I m not a crazy peta supporter at any stretch but this was definitely animal cruelty and I think it s disgusting :(

Staff seems to be bullying towards seniors by making them count all their loose changes( instead of paper bills), in addition to keeping a portion of the chopped    tilapia from the consumer, short-changing the transaction, literally.
Do not support this store. Their customer service is terrible.

I bought a few pounds of shrimp, but when I weighed them at home, I found that they were 10% less in weight than what I purchased. The store used a nine-ounce scale. I am disappointed with the lack of integrity. I bought a few kilograms of shrimp, but when I got home and weighed it, I found that the weight was 10% less than when I bought it. The store uses a nine-liang scale. I am very disappointed in their lack of integrity.

There is no service attitude to speak of. The cashier and the crab boss were all black-faced the whole time. You were not allowed to choose blue crabs. He would choose the smallest and dying ones for you and wouldn t change them. I misheard and made an extra package. I tried to force the sale to the customer but was rejected. Later, he shirks the responsibility and blames the customer for thinking that it is troublesome to change the price. I have never seen such a store clerk. If he had not made an appointment with a friend to eat blue crabs, another one is far away and will be closed now. I will never buy here. If I have the choice, I will Give zero stars

As I work close in the area this was a convenient stop for me to grab some Spot Prawns for the coveted Spot Prawn season here in Vancouver. It was after work, so I was lucky enough to catch Calvin the owner unloading a van full of Spot Prawns that were massive and still kicking. We did he prawns sashimi style and a quick boil. These were some of the best prawns Ive had even better than what Ive had at sushi restaurants. Debating if I need to go for round 2 of prawns tonight.

Be brave. Go in, let the fish monger at the front door make a suggestion. Ask whats the special. On our day it was $1.99/lb Ling cod heads. Great for soup! We also picked up some salmon heads! Prices are written, so you wont get tourist charged.
Fresh seafood, nice people, good prices. We always enjoy driving down to China town and we always stop in at Hung Win Seafood.
Great prices. Freshest seafood in Vancouver. Been customer here for over 10 years
Great service and great people. Always enjoy my time at Hung Win.
Proper
Good people, good seafood!
Very good
Fish is quite nice.
Not sure if they pass health and safety standards as there are dead fish sitting in buckets with no ice.

My mom bought a fish in the afternoon and when she came back she discovered the fish was exchanged to a bad one and weighted less than the price she paid. This kinda attitude and behavior is unacceptable, and she is disgusted , and will never go back again!

As we are European people we are not used with Vancouver marketplace. Just come back  today before 5pm from this store, 585 Gore Av. Vancouver. We bought a little crab at 16.90$ per pound. Had to pay 35$ in cash !! I was very surprised and didnt ask for explantions. I paid, nothing more. No ticket, no invoice. When back home we weighted it for less than one pound. The good price was less than 17$. This behaviour is unacceptable !

Been here multiple times and the fish they have in stock is always very fresh and affordable. They do a good job at cleaning the fish for you after you select the one you would like. Definitely would recommend frequenting this mom and pop store over the grocery conglomerates

They have a variety of seafood and prices are reasonable. Staff here are friendly and always welcoming. They will cut the fish however you like and will ask if you want to keep the bones. The black cod that I get from them is always fresh and typically at a good price. The prices do fluctuate but compared to other places, I find theyre the most reasonable.

I dont shop here bc Im vegan but I support small Chinatown businesses since I grew up in Chinatown. It saddens me to see it in this state. However, Im happy to see that non-Chinese shoppers patronize places like this. TYVM! I even heard one of the workers speak in fairly good English to the White Euro looking shoppers. These shoppers seem satisfied with their purchases. Please keep Chinatown businesses going by choosing to shop here than in T&T or in other places. Come explore Chinatown, experiment with products that you can buy here n with all of our help, hopefully Chinatown businesses will come back to their former glory . Id love that

Favourite Seafood Shop in British Columbia. Lots of fresh fish and seafood options and you can choose which fish or crab you would like to buy. The prices for the seafood is a lot cheaper than if you were to go to TNT and the quality and freshness of the seafood is incomparable. The quality is amazing and Im surprised by how juicy my lobster and black cod was. Highly recommend!
Great Fresh fish and other seafood. Always a good price. Lobsters, crabs, clams, and also you have various fish like ling cod, salmom or other fish that you get from Asian supermarkets.
Their sashimi grade salmon is great. The oysters and shrimp here were amazing too!! And price was cheap!

Perfect place to buy spot prawns. No need to line up at Steveston to buy prawns. Fresh swimming prawns are sold here as well as a bunch of other high quality fish, crabs and lobsters. Will be coming back for more seafood!
Best rockfish fishmonger in the city no cap. Also one of the fewer fishmongers that sells green uni when theyre in season.
This place is a hidden gem!  Seafood is sooooo fresh.
Love it here.  Crab clams fish all fresh and fair prices.
Got 1 crab 1 lobster. Crab was huge and fresh. Lobster was not. Lady was super sweet. Price was decent, worth it for the crab but not lobster.

My familys favorite seafood store in Vancouver Chinatown. We would stop by here to buy fish whenever we are in Chinatown.  I know there are plenty of other seafood stores in Metro Vancouver.  Their prices are very competitive and you can select the live fish you want to buy.  Other fish stores doesnt allow you to select the fish you want.  The smell of fish doesnt please everyone nor is the sight as well.  This seafood store have a variety of seafood such as fresh fish, live fish, dungeness crab  , Atlantic lobsters, fresh clams and oysters.
Great seafood. Closed on Mondays- hope they update it on google soon.
One of the few Chinese operations left in Chinatown, they cater to some royal customers.
Mr. Yip is very professional. Definitely will come back for another purchase of oysters and clams!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you.

review_text: I dropped in on them today and bought a couple of salmon fish heads.  They were 99c a pound.  Thats all I really needed.  What surprises me was they took the time to chop them up and cleaned and washed them REALLY WELL!   Needless to say, such customer service deserve to be rated 5 stars!
Great seafood place. Owners are really good people and the seafood is some of the best in Vancouver. Would recommend 10/10.
Good service, live or very fresh seafood
Very fresh seafood, highly recommended!
One of the Best service in market
Friendly staff member and was patient with all our questions
Fresh seafood
We bought a Sockey Salmon today from the Captain. He gave us a really nice fish for a Great price. It is Delicious, it melts in your mouth.! Thanks Captain, See ya soon for some Ling Cod.! Rob

Hands down freshest and cheapest fresh fish!/seafood you can find in town.! And not like big box stores, you are actually supporting local fisherman! Its funny to read the other reviews, people reviewing his parking and complaining how fish market stinks! LOL, ever been to a real fish market?
This fishmonger always has fresh fish daily. The facility he has is very smelly due to no drain and water.

This market stinks and takes up the side walk, always people in the way and carts blocking your ability to pass. Plus today I caught him parking in the handicap spot just up the street and going into the bank, great respect there buddy!
Ignorance and disrepect is no way to run a business. One of this companys trucks chose to take up two disabled parking spots when they dont have a disabled parking permit. Disgraceful.

These lobster rolls are spectacular everytime I get one, they are especially delicious when made by that one asian guy with glasses i think his names justin? He definitely need the head chef position.
Lobster roll was made to absolute perfection! Whoever made this deserves a raise 100%. GO CANUCKS!
Lobster Roll sandwich was absolutely top shelf.

I attended my first game of the season Dec 10th.  The Canucks played and lost to the Minnesota Wild.  The lobster roll was honestly my favorite thing about attending Canucks  games.  The lobster roll tasted good.  The lobster meat was cooked well and the texture perfect.  I admit it s been a few years since I had season tickets.  I renewed this year and told everyone the lobster roll was a can t miss.  The lobster roll held it s own but the new kettle chips are a miss.   Bring back Ms Vickies!  The kettle chips were hard and tasteless.
The lobster roll is pretty decent with good flavour. The downside was that the bread was on the drier and staler side. Comes with kettle chips or coleslaw.
I think these might have been the best spot prawns Ive ever had! Super friendly service too. Thanks again.
Best salmon jerky Ive had! Looking forward to getting some more soon!
Great place for fresh fish - great service and helpful hints to cook   we all need a little help now and again.
